Al - Kashshaaf ' an Haqa'iq at - Tanzil , popularly known as Al - Kashshaaf ( `` the Revealer '' , al - Kashāf , Arabic : الكشاف‎ ) is a seminal tafsir ( commentary on the Qur'an ) by Al - Zamakhshari written in the 12th century .
The Saga of Shadows is a planned trilogy of space opera novels written by Kevin J. Anderson .
Marius the Epicurean : his sensations and ideas is a historical and philosophical novel by Walter Pater ( his only completed full - length fiction ) , written between 1881 and 1884 , published in 1885 and set in 161 - 177 AD , in the Rome of the Antonines .
How Much Is Your Iron ? ( German : Was kostet das Eisen ? ) is a short play by German modernist playwright Bertolt Brecht .
The Cuckoo 's Calling is a 2013 crime fiction novel by J. K. Rowling , published under the pseudonym Robert Galbraith .
The Future of Socialism by Anthony Crosland , published in 1956 , is regarded as one of the most influential books in post - war British Labour Party thinking and the seminal work of the ' revisionist ' school of Labour politics .
Things That Are is a young - adult book by Andrew Clements .
The Mirror of Love is an epic poem by Alan Moore , written in the form of a romantic letter .
`` A Little Fable '' ( German : Kleine Fabel ) is a short story written by Franz Kafka between 1917 and 1923 , likely in 1920 .
The Gandalara Cycle is a series of seven Fantasy / Science Fiction paperback books created and written by authors Randall Garrett and Vicki Ann Heydron beginning in 1981 .
Set in 1962 and 1963 , the show chronicled the trials and tribulations of the 11-to-12-year - old Oliver Beene ( played by Grant Rosenmeyer ) , in first person perspective .
The Mistress of the World ( German : Die Herrin der Welt ) is an eight - part 1919 silent film made in the Weimar Republic starring Mia May in the lead role .
Night Convoy ( German : Nachtkolonne ) is a 1932 German drama film directed by James Bauer and starring Vladimir Gajdarov , Olga Tschechowa and Oskar Homolka .
The Right of the Weakest ( French : La Raison du plus faible ) is a 2006 Belgian drama film directed by Lucas Belvaux .
Treehouse Hostage is a 1999 family film directed by Sean McNamara and starring Jim Varney and Joey Zimmerman .
Adayalam is a 1991 Malayalam film by K. Madhu starring Mammootty , Rekha , Shobana and Murali .
Madras Cafe is a 2013 Indian political espionage thriller film directed by Shoojit Sircar and starring John Abraham , Nargis Fakhri , Rashi Khanna and Leena Paul in lead roles .

John Howard Kitching ( July 16 , 1838 -- January 10 or 11 , 1865 ) , often referred to as J. Howard Kitching , was an officer in the Union Army during the American Civil War .

Gary Evans Foster ( November 6 , 1894 -- July 22 , 1951 ) was a S.C. National Guard Soldier serving in the United States Army during World War I who received the Medal of Honor for bravery .

Lieutenant General Sir Harold Redman , KCB , CBE ( 1899 - -1986 ) was an officer in the British Army during World War I , World War II and the post - war era .
Asim Vokshi ( 1909 - 1937 ) was a staff officer of the `` Garibaldi Battalion '' in the International Brigades during the Spanish Civil War .
Admiral Hugh Rodman KCB ( 6 January 1859 -- 7 June 1940 ) was an officer in the United States Navy who served during the Spanish-- American War and World War I , later serving as the Commander - in - Chief , U.S. Pacific Fleet from 1919 to 1921 .
Edward Ringold ( 1827 - 14 October 1874 ) was a United States Navy coxswain and a Medal of Honor recipient for his actions in the American Civil War .

General Sir Thomas Blomefield , 1st Baronet ( February 1774 -- 24 August 1822 ) of Attleborough , Norfolk , was colonel - commandant royal artillery , to whose untiring labours as inspector of artillery and superintendent of the royal foundries that the progress of the British artillery during the Napoleonic Wars was largely due .
Oberleutnant Frank Linke - Crawford ( 18 August 1893 -- 30 July 1918 ) , was the fourth - ranking ace of the Austro - Hungarian empire during World War I , with 27 victories .

Irene Morales Infante ( 1 April 1865 -- 25 August 1890 ) was a Chilean soldier who served in the War of the Pacific .
Paul - Werner Hozzel ( 16 October 1910 -- 7 January 1997 ) was a German World War II Luftwaffe Stuka pilot and the first pilot of that type of plane to be awarded with the coveted Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross .

John Yates Beall ( January 1 , 1835 -- February 24 , 1865 ) was a Confederate privateer in the American Civil War who was arrested as a spy in New York and executed at Fort Columbus , Governors Island , New York .
William Heath ( March 7 , 1737 -- January 24 , 1814 ) was an American farmer , soldier , and political leader from Massachusetts who served as a major general in the Continental Army during the American Revolutionary War .
Simon Weston CBE ( born 8 August 1961 ) is a veteran of the British Army who has become well known throughout the United Kingdom for his recovery and charity work after suffering severe burn injuries during the Falklands War .
Pierre François Joseph Durutte ( 13 July 1767 -- 18 April 1827 ) joined the French army at the beginning of the French Revolutionary Wars .
Joseph Stewart Temple Fall DSC & 2 Bars AFC ( 17 November 1895 -- 1 December 1988 ) was a Canadian World War I flying ace with 36 credited victories .
Max Hermann Kloß ( usually referred to as Max Kloß ) was a German Wehrmacht officer of World War II and recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross , awarded to recognize successful military leadership or extreme battlefield bravery .
Harold Van Heuvelen ( born March 30 , 1919 ) is an American composer and musician known principally for his Symphony No . 1 ( opus 7 ) , which was composed during World War II and which premiered 67 years later in 2012 .
William Stewart Walker , usually known as Stewart Walker ( October 6 , 1914 -- February 6 , 1999 ) , was a lieutenant colonel from Winnfield , Louisiana who , during World War II as a United States Army major , rescued 380 of his fellow soldiers from behind enemy lines in Belgium in December 1944 .
Nathaniel Lyon ( July 14 , 1818 -- August 10 , 1861 ) was the first Union general to be killed in the American Civil War and is noted for his actions in the state of Missouri at the beginning of the conflict .
Lieutenant Colonel John A. Ellet ( 1838 - -1892 ) was an officer in the United States Army during the American Civil War .
Abdelhafid Boussouf ( 1926 , Mila , Algeria - 1980 ) was an Algerian nationalist and a leader of the Front de libération nationale ( FLN ) during the Algerian War of Independence ( 1954 - -62 ) .
Willi Rosenstein ( 28 January 1892 -- May 1949 ) , Iron Cross , was a German Flying Ace in World War I , credited with 9 victories .
Joseph Piston ( 1754 - -1831 ) , baron of the Empire , was a French general who served during the French Revolutionary Wars and Napoleonic Wars .
John Kizirian ( Armenian : Ժան Գիզիրեան ) ( April 2 , 1928 - February 26 , 2006 ) was a highly decorated member of the United States Armed Forces for over three decades and served during World War II , the Korean War , and the Vietnam War .
Heli Rolando de Tella y Cantos ( September 14 , 1888 -- October 10 , 1967 ) was a decorated Spanish soldier and military officer who served in the Moroccan War and the Spanish Civil War , siding with Franco 's Nationalists .
Wing Commander Allan Hepburn , DFC , ( 11 October 1896 -- 21 July 1975 ) was an Australian World War I flying ace , who was born in Melbourne , Victoria .
Hans Seidemann ( 18 January 1901 -- 21 December 1967 ) was a World War II Luftwaffe general .
Aaron R. Fisher was a Lieutenant in the United States Army in World War I , and a recipient of the Distinguished Service Cross .
Gustav Forstmann ( 10 June 1908 -- 2 February 1985 ) was a Fregattenkapitän with the Kriegsmarine during World War II and a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross ( German : Ritterkreuz des Eisernen Kreuzes ) .
Lieutenant William T. Fitzsimons ( 1889 - -1917 ) was a United States Army officer in World War I , and is considered the first American officer killed in the war .
Neal Creighton , Sr . ( born 1930 ) is a retired Major General of the US Army that led the 3rd Squadron , 11th Armored Cavalry Regiment during the 1968 Tet Offensive in the Vietnam War .
Hans Michaelis ( 10 September 1910 -- 26 May 2000 ) was a highly decorated Oberst in the Wehrmacht during World War II and an Oberst der Reserve in the Bundeswehr .
Anne Bailey ( 1742 -- November 22 , 1825 ) was a famous story teller and frontier scout who served in the fights of the American Revolutionary War and the Northwest Indian War .
Helmut Rosenbaum ( 11 May 1913 -- 10 May 1944 ) was a Korvettenkapitän ( LT Commander ) in Nazi Germany 's Kriegsmarine during World War II who commanded U - boat U-2 , U-73 and the 30th U - boat Flotilla .
Sumner Ely Wetmore Kittelle ( June 14 , 1867 -- December 29 , 1950 ) was a rear admiral in the United States Navy and a veteran of the Spanish-- American War and World War I. He was also the third military Governor of the United States Virgin Islands .
Dabulamanzi kaMpande ( 1839 - -September 22 , 1886 ) was a Zulu commander in the Anglo - Zulu War , most noted for commanding the Zulus at the Battle of Rorke 's Drift .
Martin Steglich ( 16 July 1915 -- 20 October 1997 ) was an Oberstleutnant in the Wehrmacht during World War II , an Oberst in the Bundeswehr , and one of only 882 recipients of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves .
The Battle of Tarapacá occurred on November 27 , 1879 , during the Tarapacá Campaign of the War of the Pacific .
Seaman Philip Bazaar , born in Chile , South America , was a Navy seaman who was awarded the United States ' highest military decoration for valor in combat -- the Medal of Honor -- for having distinguished himself during the battle for Fort Fisher of the American Civil War .
Max Ritter von Müller ( 1 January 1887 -- 9 January 1918 ) Orden Pour le Mérite , Iron Cross , Military Order of Max Joseph was a German World War I fighter ace credited with 36 victories .
Vizefeldwebel Oskar Hennrich was a German World War I flying ace credited with 20 aerial victories .
Ettore Bastico ( 9 April 1876 -- 2 December 1972 ) was an Italian military officer before and during World War II . He held high commands during the Second Italo - Abyssinian War ( Ethiopia ) , the Spanish Civil War , and the North African Campaign .
George St Lo ( sometimes written as St Loe ; 19 April 1655 -- 20 September 1718 ) was an officer of the Royal Navy who saw service during the Nine Years ' War , and the War of the Spanish Succession .
Richard Coulter , Jr. ( October 3 , 1870 -- September 26 , 1955 ) was a World War I general , a businessman , a professional football player and a banker .
John Vale ( August 9 , 1835 -- February 4 , 1909 ) was a member of the Union Army during the American Civil War .
The StG 44 ( abbreviation of Sturmgewehr 44 , `` assault rifle 44 '' ) is a German selective - fire rifle developed during World War II that was the first of its kind to see major deployment and is considered to be the first modern assault rifle .
Miguel Cabanellas Ferrer ( 1 January 1872 in Cartagena -- 14 May 1938 ) was a Spanish Army officer during the Spanish Civil War .
Augustus Williams ( 1842 -- unknown ) was a seaman in the U.S. Navy stationed aboard the USS Santiago de Cuba ( 1861 ) during the American Civil War .
Don Federico Carlos Gravina y Nápoli , ( August 12 , 1756 - March 9 , 1806 ) , was a Spanish Admiral during the American Revolution and Napoleonic Wars .

IC 2391 ( also known as the Omicron Velorum Cluster or Caldwell 85 ) is an open cluster in the constellation Vela .
Messier 109 ( also known as NGC 3992 ) is a barred spiral galaxy approximately 83.5 ± 24 million light - years away in the constellation Ursa Major .
WISE 0410 + 1502 ( full designation WISEPA J041022.71 + 150248.5 ) is a brown dwarf of spectral class Y0 , located in constellation Taurus .
Abell 2218 is a cluster of galaxies about 2 billion light - years away in the constellation Draco .
Lambda Aquarii ( λ Aqr , λ Aquarii ) is the Bayer designation for a star in the equatorial constellation of Aquarius .
Gamma Corvi ( γ Crv , γ Corvi ) is the brightest star in the southern constellation of Corvus , having an apparent visual magnitude of 2.6 .
Pi Ceti ( π Ceti , π Cet ) is a Class B7 , fourth - magnitude star in the constellation Cetus .
UGC 5692 is a Magellanic spiral galaxy located 13 million light years away in the constellation of Ursa Major .
11 Boötis ( abbr . : 11 Boo ) is a blue - white giant star in the constellation Boötes .
NGC 2608 ( also known as Arp 12 ) is a barred spiral galaxy located 93 million light - years away in the constellation Cancer ( the Crab ) .
HD 120987 ( y Cen or y Centauri ) is a star located in the constellation Centaurus .
Tintyava Peak ( Bulgarian : връх Тинтява , `` Vrah Tintyava '' \'vr&h tin'tya - va\ ) is the ice - covered peak rising to 950 m in the north foothills of Louis - Philippe Plateau on Trinity Peninsula in Graham Land , Antarctica .
Laënnec Glacier ( 64 ° 12′S 62 ° 13′W ) is a glacier 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) long draining the northeast slopes of Stribog Mountains and the northwest slopes of Avroleva Heights , and flowing northeast into Hill Bay on the east side of Brabant Island , in the Palmer Archipelago , Antarctica .
Thurston Island is an ice - covered , glacially dissected island , 215 km ( 134 mi ) long , 90 km ( 56 mi ) wide and 15,700 km2 ( 6,062 sq mi ) in area , lying a short way off the northwest end of Ellsworth Land , Antarctica .
Zgorigrad Nunatak ( Bulgarian : нунатак Згориград , `` Nunatak Zgorigrad '' \'nu - na - tak zgo-'ri - grad\ ) is the rocky peak rising to 800 m in eastern Desudava Glacier on Nordenskjöld Coast in Graham Land , Antarctica .
Mount Hahn is a mountain , about 1,100 metres ( 3,600 ft ) high , situated between Walter Glacier and Hampton Glacier at the head of Schokalsky Bay , in northeastern Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Greene Ridge ( 83 ° 12′S 157 ° 10′E ) is a partially ice - covered ridge , 5 nautical miles ( 9 km ) long , extending northward from Martin Dome to the southern edge of Argosy Glacier in the Miller Range of Antarctica .
Oryahovo Heights ( Oryahovski Vazvisheniya \o-'rya - hov - ski v&-zvi-'she - ni - ya\ ) are the ice - covered heights of elevation 340 m extending 6 km in north - south direction in central and eastern Ioannes Paulus II Peninsula , Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Lewis Cliff ( 84 ° 17′S 161 ° 5′E ) is an irregular cliff , about 12 nautical miles ( 22 km ) long , extending south from Mount Achernar along the west side of Walcott Neve , Antarctica .
Gravenoire Rock ( 66 ° 21′S 136 ° 43′E ) is a small rock outcrop about 1 nautical mile ( 2 km ) southeast of Rock X , protruding above the coastal ice at the east side of Victor Bay , Antarctica .
Hut Point Peninsula is a long , narrow peninsula from 3 to 5 km ( 2 to 3 mi ) wide and 24 km ( 15 mi ) long , projecting south - west from the slopes of Mount Erebus on Ross Island , Antarctica .
Vittoria Buttress ( 69 ° 23′S 71 ° 47′W ) is a conspicuous rock cliff , rising to about 750 m , overlooking the southeast side of Lazarev Bay and forming the northwest extremity of the Lassus Mountains in northern Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Almirante Ice Fringe ( 64 ° 52′S 62 ° 41′W ) is a narrow ice piedmont bordering the southwest side of Andvord Bay on Danco Coast , Graham Land , Antarctica .
Polygon Spur ( 86 ° 0′S 126 ° 0′W ) is a broad , ice - free spur lying 2 nautical miles ( 3.7 km ) southeast of Tillite Spur at the south end of the Wisconsin Plateau , Horlick Mountains in Antarctica .
Holst Peak ( 71 ° 20′S 70 ° 6′W ) is a rocky pyramidal peak , rising to about 1,000 metres ( 3,300 ft ) , midway between the south end of the Walton Mountains and the LeMay Range in the central part of Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Explorers Cove is a cove at the northwest head of New Harbour , Victoria Land , Antarctica , on the west side of McMurdo Sound , where the Taylor Valley hits the seashore .
Palindrome Buttress ( 71 ° 6′S 70 ° 27′W ) is a conspicuous rock buttress , rising to about 905 m , marking the southern extremity of the north group of the Walton Mountains , in central Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Mount LeMasurier ( 75 ° 27′S 139 ° 39′W ) is an ice - free coastal mountain which rises to more than 800 metres ( 2,600 ft ) between Mount Vance and Mount Langway , in the central part of the Ickes Mountains of Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Möll Spur ( 76 ° 23′S 112 ° 9′W ) is a jagged rock spur which juts southward from the Jaron Cliffs on the southern slope of Mount Takahe in Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Martel Inlet ( 62 ° 5′S 58 ° 22′W ) is an inlet forming the northeast head of Admiralty Bay , King George Island , in the South Shetland Islands off Antarctica .

Beaman Glacier ( 70 ° 58′S 164 ° 38′E ) is a tributary to Ebbe Glacier lying close north of McLean Glacier in the southwest part of the Anare Mountains , a major mountain range situated within the geographical borders of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Helfert Nunatak ( 77 ° 53′S 87 ° 25′W ) is a prominent rock nunatak standing 15 nautical miles ( 28 km ) west of Mount Sharp of the Sentinel Range , in the Ellsworth Mountains of Antarctica .
Senokos Nunatak ( Bulgarian : нунатак Сенокос , `` Nunatak Senokos '' \'nu - na - tak se - no-'kos\ ) is the rocky hill rising to 663 m in Dreatin Glacier on Trinity Peninsula in Graham Land , Antarctica .
Mount Marston ( 76 ° 54′S 162 ° 12′E ) is a whaleback - shaped mountain , 1,245 metres ( 4,085 ft ) high , standing at the north side of Kar Plateau , 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) north of the terminus of Mackay Glacier in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Porphyry Bluff ( 64 ° 27′S 59 ° 11′W ) is a prominent rocky bluff extending from the coast to 2 miles inland , between Larsen Inlet and Longing Gap in Graham Land , Antarctica forming the northwest side of the entrance to Pizos Bay .
Gallup Glacier ( 85 ° 9′S 177 ° 50′W ) is a broad glacier , about 12 nautical miles ( 22 km ) long , flowing east between Mount Rosenwald and Mount Black to enter Shackleton Glacier , Antarctica , just north of Matador Mountain .
The Hyperion Nunataks ( 72 ° 4′S 68 ° 55′W ) are a group of about 10 nunataks lying south of Saturn Glacier and 8 nautical miles ( 15 km ) west of the Corner Cliffs , in the southeastern part of Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Jutland Glacier ( 71 ° 55′S 166 ° 12′E ) is a broad tributary glacier , 15 nautical miles ( 28 km ) long and 4 nautical miles ( 7.4 km ) wide , in the Victory Mountains of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Evans Névé ( 72 ° 45′S 164 ° 30′E ) is a large névé which nourishes Tucker Glacier , Mariner Glacier , Aviator Glacier , Rennick Glacier and Lillie Glacier in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Viskyar Ridge ( ' ' rid vis-''kyar ) is a rocky ridge rising to 600 m and extending 2.5 km in north - south direction in Breznik Heights , Greenwich Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Harrison Ice Ridge ( 79 ° 30′S 146 ° 0′W ) is an ice ridge between Echelmeyer Ice Stream and MacAyeal Ice Stream on the Shirase Coast of Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Furdesanden Moraine ( 71 ° 48′S 9 ° 37′E ) is a moraine extending in a north -- south direction for 17 nautical miles ( 31 km ) along the west side of the Conrad Mountains in the Orvin Mountains of Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Greaves Peak is a conspicuous sharp , dark , double - pointed rocky peak rising to 240 m in the northwest of Greenwich Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
The Appalachia Nunataks ( 69 ° 44′S 71 ° 4′W ) are a group of nunataks rising to about 600 metres ( 2,000 ft ) on the west side of the Elgar Uplands , Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Midbresrabben Hill ( 72 ° 44′S 2 ° 6′W ) is an isolated rock hill protruding above the ice between Penck Trough and Jutulstraumen Glacier , east of the Borg Massif in Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
The Kyle Nunataks ( 66 ° 47′S 51 ° 20′E ) are three nunataks 2.5 nautical miles ( 5 km ) east of Mount Hampson , in the northern part of the Tula Mountains in Enderby Land , Antarctica .
Enrique Hill ( Bulgarian : хълм Енрике , `` Halm Enrique '' \'h&lm en-'ri - ke\ ) is the ice - free hill rising to 156 m in Dospey Heights on the Ray Promontory of Byers Peninsula , Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Matikonis Peak ( 75 ° 21′S 138 ° 14′W ) is a small , rather isolated rock peak that protrudes through the snow mantle of the central Coulter Heights , near the coast of Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Cosmonauts Sea , sometimes misspelled Cosmonaut Sea , was a proposed sea name as part of the Southern Ocean , off the Prince Olav Coast and Enderby Land , Antarctica , between about 30 ° E and 50 ° E. It would have an area of 699,000 km² .
Galiche Rock ( Bulgarian : скала Галиче , `` Skala Galiche '' \ska-'la ' ga - li - che\ ) is the large rock off Somovit Point on the east coast of Robert Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
The Medmulen Spurs ( 72 ° 1′S 3 ° 8′E ) are a group of rock spurs extending from the north side of Risemedet Mountain , in the Gjelsvik Mountains of Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Minot Point is a rock point midway along the west coast of Brabant Island , in the Palmer Archipelago , Antarctica .
Frazier Glacier ( 77 ° 5′S 161 ° 25′E ) is a glacier between the Clare Range and Detour Nunatak , flowing northeast to join Mackay Glacier east of Pegtop Nunatak , in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Jaburg Glacier ( 82 ° 42′S 53 ° 25′W ) is a broad glacier draining westward between the Dufek Massif and the Cordiner Peaks in the Pensacola Mountains of Antarctica .
Frustration Dome ( 68 ° 0′S 64 ° 33′E ) is a large crevassed ice dome about 38 nautical miles ( 70 km ) southeast of Mount Henderson in Mac . Robertson Land , Antarctica .
Vergilov Rocks ( Vergilov Kamak ver-'gi - lov ' ka - m&k ) are a group of rocks off Bulgarian Beach on Hurd Peninsula in eastern Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica , consisting of one main rock and two adjacent smaller ones submerging at high water .
Mount Dergach ( 70 ° 36′S 163 ° 1′E ) is a flat - topped , ice - covered mountain located just west of Ob ' Bay and south of Lunik Point , in the Bowers Mountains , a major mountain range of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Mount Marr ( 66 ° 24′S 52 ° 7′E ) is a rock peak which rises above the surrounding ice surface 8 nautical miles ( 15 km ) south of Johnston Peak and 8 nautical miles west of Douglas Peak , in Enderby Land , Antarctica .
Glavinitsa Peak ( Bulgarian : връх Главиница , `` Vrah Glavinitsa '' \'vr&h gla-'vi - ni - tsa\ ) is the peak rising to 1500 m in the central part of Rudozem Heights on German Peninsula , Fallières Coast in Graham Land , Antarctica .
Lehaie Point ( 64 ° 30′S 62 ° 47′W ) is the southwestern point of Hulot Peninsula , Brabant Island , in the Palmer Archipelago , Antarctica .
Mount Elbert is the highest summit of the Rocky Mountains of North America and the highest point in the U.S. state of Colorado and the entire Mississippi River drainage basin .
Almond Point ( 63 ° 53′S 59 ° 30′W ) is a rocky point between Whitecloud Glacier and McNeile Glacier at the head of Charcot Bay , Trinity Peninsula , Antarctica .
Freeth Bay is a 5 mi wide bay on the coast of Enderby Land , Antarctica , lying 12 mi west of Spooner Bay in Alasheyev Bight .
Cape Gates ( 73 ° 35′S 122 ° 38′W ) is an ice - covered cape which marks the northwestern extremity of Carney Island along the coast of Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Holder Peak ( 69 ° 44′30``S 74 ° 31′13''E ) is the higher ( northern ) peak on a rock outcrop on the Ingrid Christensen Coast of Princess Elizabeth Land , Antarctica , about 4 kilometres ( 2.5 mi ) east of Mount Caroline Mikkelsen .
The Jule Peaks ( 72 ° 23′S 5 ° 33′W ) are a small group of isolated peaks located about 35 nautical miles ( 65 km ) west - northwest of Borg Mountain in Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Martens Peak ( 85 ° 34′S 131 ° 2′W ) is a rock peak in the northeastern part of the Ford Nunataks , in the Wisconsin Range of the Horlick Mountains , Antarctica .
Tombaugh Cliffs ( 71 ° 5′S 68 ° 18′W ) is a group of ice - free cliffs which stand at the north side of the mouth of Pluto Glacier and face towards the George VI Ice Shelf which occupies George VI Sound , on the east side of Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Taiwan ( i/ˌtaɪˈwɑːn/ ; Chinese : 臺灣 or 台灣 ; see below ) , officially the Republic of China ( ROC ; Chinese : 中華民國 ; pinyin : Zhōnghuá Mínguó ) , is a sovereign state in East Asia .
Barwick Valley is an ice - free valley north of Apocalypse Peaks , extending from Webb Glacier to Victoria Valley in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Isocline Hill ( 83 ° 31′S 157 ° 36′E ) is a hill in the southern part of the Augen Bluffs , in the Miller Range , Antarctica .
Strabane was once the most bombed town in Europe per size and was the most bombed town in Northern Ireland .
Kauffman Glacier ( 71 ° 15′S 61 ° 18′W ) is a broad , smooth glacier , 7 nautical miles ( 13 km ) long , flowing eastward into the head of Palmer Inlet on the east coast of Palmer Land , Antarctica .
The Jenkins Heights ( 74 ° 48′S 114 ° 20′W ) are a broad ice - covered area rising over 500 metres ( 1,600 ft ) and covering some 25 square miles ( 65 km2 ) , located south of McClinton Glacier and west of Mount Bray on the Bakutis Coast of Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Cape Sterneck ( British name Cape Herschel ) ( 64 ° 4′S 61 ° 2′W ) is a bold , black cliff on a projecting point forming the west extremity of Chavdar Peninsula on the west coast of Graham Land , Antarctica .
Exodus Glacier is a steep , smooth glacier 1 nautical mile ( 2 km ) northeast of Mount Ellis , flowing from the northern edge of Midnight Plateau to the southwest side of Island Arena , in the Darwin Mountains of Antarctica .
Nikopol Point ( Nos Nikopol \'nos ni-'ko - pol\ ) is a snow - free point on the south coast of Byers Peninsula , Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica projecting 650 m east - southeastwards into Bransfield Strait and linked by a spit to Vietor Rock to the south .
Kado Kendo ( Kendo 's Gift ) is a 2007 Indonesian film produced by Indonesian students studying in Melbourne , Australia .

Cancoillotte is sold pre - melted in supermarkets , especially in the east of France .

Xarabank is Malta 's most watched television programme and it is the only discussion programme in Malta that has a live audience who can participate by having his / her say live .
Lamban is a traditional dessert for the Bruneian Malay people in Labuan and in the states of Sabah and in East Malaysia .
Mirik meatballs ( Mirik köfte ) is a Turkish recipe of meatballs from Sivas province , eastern Central Anatolia Region , Turkey .
The Game of Death is an incomplete 1972 Hong Kong martial arts film directed , written , produced by and starring Bruce Lee , in his final film attempt .

The Beretta 9000 is a series of modern compact size semi - automatic pistols designed and manufactured by Beretta of Italy .

Chaser News Alert was an Australian satirical news program which ran in the form of ten 4-minute episodes produced by satire group The Chaser .

Carl Forster ( born 4 June 1992 ) is a professional English rugby league player who played for Salford in the Super League until the end of 2015 .
Felix Finster ( born 6 August 1967 , in Mannheim ) is a German mathematician working on problems in mathematical physics , geometry and analysis .
Lydia Auster ( 13 April 1912 -- 3 April 1993 ) was an Estonian composer who faced criticism for formalism by Soviet authorities .
Edna Moyle ( 19 January 1942 -- 21 May 2013 ) was a Caymanian politician who served as the Member of the Legislative Assembly for the district of North Side from 1992 to 2009 , including a tenure the Speaker of the Legislative Assembly of the Cayman Islands from May 2005 until May 2009 .
Diarmait mac Máel na mBó ( died 7 February 1072 ) was King of Leinster , as well as High King of Ireland ( with opposition ) .
Franz Ulrich , 11th Prince Kinsky of Wchinitz and Tettau ( German : Franz Ulrich Johannes Clemens Christophorus Antonius Bonaventura Maria Fürst Kinsky von Wchinitz und Tettau ; 7 October 1936 -- 2 April 2009 ) was the titular pretender Prince Kinsky of Wchinitz and Tettau as well the head of the House of Kinsky .
Liutold of Eppenstein ( c. 1050 -- 12 May 1090 ) was Duke of Carinthia and Margrave of Verona from 1077 until his death .
Nicolae Rainea ( 19 November 1933 -- 1 April 2015 ) , nicknamed The Locomotive of the Carpathians , was a Romanian football referee .
Hajji Nawab Hafiz Sir Hamidullah Khan ( 9 September 1894 - 4 February 1960 ) was the last ruling Nawab of Bhopal , which merged with the state of Madhya Pradesh in 1956 .
Allin Braund ( 1915 - -2004 ) was a British artist who was born in Devon and educated at Hornsey College of Art . He taught at Bideford Grammar School before World War II and returned to Hornsey thereafter to teach design and printmaking until his retirement in 1976 .
Slingsby Bethel ( 1617 - -1697 ) was a Member of Parliament with republican sympathies , during the period of the English Civil War .
Dr. Ghulam Mustafa Khan , PhD , D.Litt , SI ( 23 September 1912 -- 25 September 2005 ) was a researcher , critic , linguist , author , scholar of Urdu literature and linguistics , educationist and religious and spiritual leader belonging to Naqshbandi order of Sufism .
Rosa Giacinta Badalla ( ca . 1660 -- ca . 1710 ) was an Italian composer and Benedictine nun .
Canon Leonard Elliott Elliott - Binns ( previously Leonard Elliott Binns ) ( 18 September 1885 - -1963 ) was an English historian and theologian , whose works covered a broad range of topics in English and Western church history , as well as the history of the Biblical era .
Andrea di Aloigi ( or Alovigi , Aloisi , Aloysii , and Di Luigi ; 1480 - 1521 ) , called L'Ingegno , was an Italian Renaissance painter .
Johann Wilhelm Adolf Kirchhoff ( 6 January 1826 -- 26 February 1908 ) was a German classical scholar and epigraphist .
John Pollexfen Bastard ( 18 September 1756 -- 4 April 1816 ) was a British Tory politician , landowner and colonel of the East Devonshire Militia who lived at Kitley House , Yealmpton , Devon .
Clas Bjerkander ( 23 September 1735 , Skara -- 1 August 1795 ) was a Swedish meteorologist , botanist , and entomologist .
Johann Friedrich Ludwig Wachler ( 15 April 1767 , Gotha -- 4 April 1838 , Breslau ) was a German literary historian and theologian .
Fjalla - Eyvindur ( Icelandic for `` Eyvindur of the Mountains '' ; 1714 - -1783 ) was an Icelandic outlaw .
Philip Furley Fyson ( 1877 - -1947 ) was a botanist and educator who worked in India .
Petrit Dume ( 20 May 1920 - -†5 December 1975 ) was an Albanian general and politician of the Albanian Party of Labour ( PPSh ) .
Isabel Douglas , Countess of Mar ( c. 1360 -- 1408 ) was Countess of Mar. Isabel was the sister of the famous James 2nd Earl of Douglas and Earl of Mar , who died leading the Scots to victory at the Battle of Otterburn .
Josephine Clofullia ( 1827 - -1875 ) was a famous Swiss - born bearded lady who toured with P. T. Barnum 's `` American Museum '' .
Alexander Stewart Gray ( c. 1863 -- 13 April 1937 ) was a Scottish advocate , artist , and campaigner against unemployment .
Louis Austin ( 1898 - 1971 ) was an African American journalist , leader and social activist .
Claude Favre de Vaugelas ( 6 January 1585 -- 26 February 1650 ) was a Savoyard grammarian and man of letters .
Józef Łukaszewicz ( December 13 , 1863 -- October 19 , 1928 ) was a Polish physicist , geologist and mineralogist , as well as a 19th - century revolutionary .
Meir Rosenne ( Hebrew : מאיר רוזן‎‎ ; 19 February 1931 -- 14 April 2015 ) was an Israeli lawyer and diplomat .
Sir Patrick Kilvington ( 1922 - -1990 ) was an Australian artist .
Peter Browne , 2nd Earl of Altamont ( c. 1731 - 28 December 1780 ) was an Irish landowner and MP .
Leon Sash ( 19 October 1922 -- 25 November 1979 ) , born Leon Robert Shash was an American jazz accordionist .
John Ellor Taylor ( 1837 - -1895 ) was an English popular science writer , journalist and museum curator .
Lance Corporal Peter Goggins ( 1894 -- 18 January 1917 ) was a British soldier who was executed for desertion during the First World War .
Dr. S. M. Pandit ( Sambanand Monappa Pandit , 25 March 1916 -- 30 March 1993 ) was one of the most popular and much sought - after painters of his times , especially in the school of Realism in contrast to the contemporaneous net - traditionalist Bengal Renaissance and other Indian modern art movements .
Bela Gold , also Bill Gold , ( 30 January 1915 -- 14 April 2012 ) , was a Hungarian - born American businessman and professor .
Thomas Trentham ( 1538 - -1587 ) , was an English politician .
Bahaedin Adab ( Persian : بهاالدين ادب‎‎ ) , also spelled Bahaeddin or Bahaoddin Adab , Kurdish `` Baha Adab '' ( 1945 -- 16 August 2007 ) was a prominent Iranian Kurdish politician and engineer .
Walter Kohut ( 20 November 1927 -- 18 May 1980 ) was an Austrian film , television and theatre actor .
Edmund Blanchard ( c.1824 -- December 27 , 1886 ) was a lawyer and prominent businessman in Centre County , Pennsylvania .
Henry Harford Cumming ( 1799 - -1866 ) was an important figure in antebellum Augusta , Georgia .
Artashes Arakelian ( 1909 -- 1993 ) was an economist , member of the Armenian Academy of Sciences ( 1960 ) .
George Birimisa ( born 21 February 1924 - died 10 May 2012 ) was an American playwright , actor , and director who contributed to the explosion of gay theater in the mid-1960s during the early years of Off - Off - Broadway .
Charles Henry Thompson ( 1896 Jackson , Mississippi- 1980 ) was the first African American to obtain a doctoral degree in educational psychology .
Thomas Randolph , 2nd Earl of Moray ( died 11 August 1332 ) , a Scottish military commander , held his title for just 23 days .
Jack Keever ( c. 1938 -- July 18 , 2004 ) was an American journalist and author , best known his coverage of Charles Whitman 's 1966 shooting spree .
Jan Nisar Akhtar ( Urdu : جان نثار اختر‎ ; 18 February 1914 -- 19 August 1976 ) was an important 20th century Indian poet of Urdu ghazals and nazms , and a part of the Progressive Writers ' Movement , who was also a lyricist for Bollywood .
William Venn Gough ( 1842 - -1918 ) was an architect responsible for a number of prominent buildings in Bristol .
Tommaso Gherardini ( December 21 , 1715 - 1797 ) was an Italian painter , mainly of Rococo fresco decorations .
James Francis Helvetius Hobler died in Pentonville , London on 21 January 1844 ( aged 78 ) .
William of Wrotham or William de Wrotham ( died c. 1217 ) was a medieval English royal administrator and clergyman .
Ntim Gyakari ( died 1701 ) was the last fully independent ruler of Denkyira , a state in the boundaries of the modern nation of Ghana .
Noah Flug ( Hebrew : נח פלוג‎ ; 1925 -- 11 August 2011 ) was an Israeli economist , diplomat and advocate for the rights of Holocaust survivors .
Dhalia ( 10 February 1925 -- 14 April 1991 ) was an Indonesian actress active for over fifty years .
Richard Lansdale Munkittrick , better known as Howard Talbot ( 9 March 1865 -- 12 September 1928 ) , was an American - born , English - raised conductor and composer of Irish descent .
Herbert Morley ( 2 April 1616 -- 29 September 1667 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons variously between 1640 and 1667 .
Carlo Favetti ( 30 August 1819 - 1 December 1892 ) was an Italian politician and lawyer from Gorizia , who also wrote poetry in the Friulian language .
Mirko Androić ( 8 July 1922 , in Varaždin , Yugoslavia -- 7 June 1982 ) was a Croatian historian and archivist .
Wu Zhipu ( Chinese : 吴芝圃 ) ( 1906 - -1967 ) was the first CPC governor of Henan and CPC Committee Secretary of Henan .
John of Sahagún , O.E.S.A. ( Spanish : Juan de Sahagún ) , ( 24 June 1419 -- 11 June 1479 ) was a Spanish Augustinian friar and priest .
John Forest ( 1471 -- 22 May 1538 ) was an English Franciscan Friar and martyr .
Tahitoe ( 1808 - 1881 ) was the king of Raiatea from 1871 to 1881 .
Louis Victor Eytinge ( 1878 - 1938 ) was an American entrepreneur and career criminal who was convicted of murder and sentenced to life in prison in 1907 .
George Hennet ( 1799 - -1857 ) was a railway engineer and contractor .
Jean - Félix Krautheimer ( 1874 - 1943 ) was governor of French Indochina from 1929 - 1934 , subordinate to the then governor general fr :
John Bowdler ( 1746 - -1823 ) was a campaigner for moral reform in Britain and a founder of the Church Building Society .
Edward Dyne Fenton ( died 1880 ) , was a British author .
Tan Shuzhen ( 1907 -- 2002 ) was a Chinese violinist , teacher and violin maker .
John Fall Allison ( 1825 - -1897 ) was a pioneer settler , Justice of the Peace , Postmaster and Gold Commissioner in the Similkameen Country of the Southern Interior of British Columbia , Canada .
Todor Živanović ( Serbian Cyrillic : Тодор Живановић ; 27 September 1927 -- 20 June 1978 ) was a Serbian football player and a Yugoslav international .
Derrick Morris ( c.1930 -- 30 July 2005 ) was , at the time of his death , Europe 's longest - surviving heart transplant patient .
Alisz Goriupp ( also known as Alice Goriupp , 18 August 1894 in Buziásfürdő -- 4 February 1979 in Budapest ) was a Hungarian librarian , media historian and bibliographer .
Adrien Goybet ( 1922 - -1995 ) was the son of Admiral Pierre Goybet and grandson of General Mariano Goybet .
Om Prakash Jindal ( Hindi : ओम प्रकाश जिन्दल ) ( 7 August 1930 -- 31 March 2005 ) , popularly known as O.P. Jindal , was born in Hisar , Haryana .
Joseph Filkowski ( John Blake ) ( died 1931 ) was a Polish - American gangster in Cleveland , Ohio .
Timothy Oluwole Obadare ( April 1930 - March 2013 ) was a Nigerian religious colossus , renowned televangelist and the General Evangelist of Christ Apostolic Church ( CAC ) .
Papatzys ( died 704 ) was , in the account of Theophanes the Confessor , the Khazar tudun of Kerch during the sojourn of Byzantine emperor Justinian II in Phanagoria .
Kaya Sultan ( 1633 - -1659 ) was an Ottoman princess .
Sathyavani Muthu ( 15 February 1923 -- 11 November 1999 ) was an Indian politician and an influential leader from Paraiyar Community ( Sambavar ) .
Colonel John Cridlan Barrett VC , TD ( 10 August 1897 -- 7 March 1977 ) was an English recipient of the Victoria Cross , the highest and most prestigious award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces .
Nissim ben Jacob ( Hebrew : ניסים בן יעקב , also known as Rav Nissim Gaon or in Hebrew : רבנו נסים , lit . Nissim our teacher ; 990 - -1062 ) , was a rabbi best known today for his Talmudic commentary ha - Mafteach , by which title he is also known .
Niels Dorph ( 1681 -- 1758 ) was a Danish / Norwegian clergyman .
Herb Cornuelle ( died 1996 ) was a businessman and activist in Hawaii , who was involved in the development of free market think tanks during the mid - twentieth century .
Major - General William Carmichael Russell ( 1824 - 1905 ) was a senior Bengal Artillery officer who served in India .
Chee Kim Thong ( Chinese : 徐金棟 ; pinyin : Xú Jīndòng ; 1920 - 2001 ) was a Shaolin martial arts grandmaster .
Emile Touma ( Arabic : إميل توما , Hebrew : אמיל תומא , March 16 , 1919 -- Aug. 27 , 1985 ) , was a Palestinian and Israeli Arab political historian , journalist and theorist .
Vishwanath Kashinath Rajwade ( 24 June 1863 -- 31 December 1926 ) , popularly known as Itihasacharya Rajwade , was a historian , scholar , writer , commentator and orator from Maharashtra , India .
Thomas Bailie ( 15 July 1885 - 22 November 1957 ) was an Ulster Unionist Party ( UUP ) Member of Parliament ( 1941 - -1953 ) in the Parliament of Northern Ireland , based at Stormont , during which time he was Deputy Speaker .
Ivan Frankopan ( also known as Ivaniš ; died 20 November 1436 ) was a Croatian noble who ruled as Ban of Croatia from 1432 to 1436 .
George Waldron ( 1690 - -1730 ? ) was an English topographer and poet .
Esa Hietanen ( 15 July 1896 , Suonenjoki - 15 October 1962 ) was a Finnish logger , sawmill worker , journalist and politician .
Émile Coulaudon ( 29 December 1907 - 1 June 1977 ) , known as Colonel Gaspard , was one of the principal leaders of the French Resistance in Auvergne during the Second World War .
Francis Kirkman ( 1632 -- c. 1680 ) appears in many roles in the English literary world of the second half of the seventeenth century , as a publisher , bookseller , librarian , author and bibliographer .
Baron Mihály Mérey de Kaposmére ( Mérei ; 1500 -- 26 February 1572 ) was a Hungarian jurist and noble , who served as Palatinal Governor ( Hungarian : nádori helytartó ) in the Kingdom of Hungary , between 1562 and 1572 .
Hồ Thành Việt ( John Hồ ) ( July 20 , 1955 in Nha Trang -- August 28 , 2003 in Fountain Valley , California ) was founder of VNI Software Co. , California , USA in 1987 and was the first to develop software that eases use of Vietnamese language on computers .
Marco Marazzoli ( 1602 ? -- 26 January 1662 ) was an Italian priest and composer .
Sir Thomas Lauder Brunton , 1st Baronet , FRS ( 14 March 1844 -- 16 September 1916 ) was a Scottish physician who is most - closely associated with the use of amyl nitrite to treat angina pectoris .
George Clayden ( 14 August 1903 -- 25 March 1990 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Muriel George ( 29 August 1883 -- 22 October 1965 ) was an English singer and film actress .
István Sárkány ( Hungarian pronunciation : ( ˈiʃtvaːn ˈʃaːrkaːɲ ) ; 5 August 1913 -- 28 November 2009 ) was a Hungarian Olympic gymnast , Olympic judge , gymnastics coach and official .
Norman Rowlinson ( 1923 -- 18 August 2006 ) was a football chairman who chaired Crewe Alexandra .
Arne Austeen DFC ( 1 July 1911 -- 4 May 1945 ) was a Norwegian flying ace who was killed during World War II . He was born in Stokke to parents from Brunlanes and Ås .
Michael Wittmann ( 22 April 1914 -- 8 August 1944 ) was a German Waffen - SS tank commander during the Second World War .
William of Pagula ( died 1332 ) , also known as William Paull or William Poull , was a 14th - century English canon lawyer and theologian best known for his written works , particularly his manual for priests entitled the Oculus Sacerdotis .
Qutb al - Din Muhammad ( died 1346 ) was the Mihrabanid malik of Sistan from 1330 until his death .
Giles Hutchens ( before 1556 - 1624 ) , was an English politician .
Rexhep Demi ( 1864 - 1929 ) was a leading member of the Albanian independence movement and one of the signatories of Albanian Declaration of Independence , representing the region of Çamëria .
Sir Maurice Gerald Holmes GBE KCB ( 14 June 1885 - 4 April 1964 ) was a British civil servant .
Jacob Waxman , or in Yiddish Yankev Vaksman ( 1866 - -1942 ) was a Yiddish operetta writer .
Märta Helena Reenstierna ( 16 September 1753 -- 12 January 1841 ) , also von Schnell , known as Årstafrun ( The Årsta lady ) , was a Swedish diary writer .
Archibald Forbes ( 17 April 1838 -- 30 March 1900 ) was a British war correspondent .
Hermann Pauly ( 18 July 1870 -- 31 October 1950 ) was a German chemist and inventor .
Hezzelin I ( also called Hezilo or Hermann ) , Count in Zulpichgau ( died 1033 ) , son of count palatine Hermann I of Lotharingia .
Noel Rooke ( 1881 - -1953 ) was an English wood engraver and artist .
Gordon Hellwig ( 5 February 1901 -- 24 May 1964 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Dasari Yoganand shorty D. Yoganand ( Telugu : డి.యోగానంద్ ) ( b : 16 April 1922 - d : 23 November 2006 ) was a South Indian film director .
Giulio Alary ( sometimes Alari ) ( 1814 - 1891 ) was an Italian composer .
Apolosi Nawai ( 1876 - -1946 ) was a charismatic Fijian leader who challenged British colonial rule .
Sonam Lhundrup ( 1456 - -1531 ) was a great abbot of Mustang and the son of the second Mustang Dharma King , Agon Sangpo .
Emil Zsigmondy ( 11 August 1861 -- 6 August 1885 ) was an Austrian physician and mountaineer .
George Beer Endacott ( 28 February 1901 -- September 1971 ) was a British - born Hong Kong historian .
Aaron Zeitlin ( 1898 in Uvarovichi -- 1973 in New York ) , the son of the famous Jewish writer Hillel Zeitlin and Esther Kunin , authored several books on Yiddish literature , Poetry and Parapsychology .
Leonard Appelbee , ( 13 November 1914 -- 12 June 2000 ) , was an English painter and printmaker .
Eqrem Çabej ( Albanian pronunciation : ( ˌɛcrɛm ˈt͡ʃabɛj ) ) ( 6 August 1908 -- 13 August 1980 ) was an Albanian historical linguist and scholar who , through the publication of numerous studies gained a reputation as a key expert in the research into Albanian - language , literature , ethnology and linguistics .
Joshua Pusey ( March 27 , 1842 - May 8 , 1906 ( ? ) ) , was an American inventor and an attorney .
William Mackenzie , 5th Earl of Seaforth ( died 1740 ) was a Scottish nobleman , attainted for his part in the Jacobite rising of 1715 .
Thomas Bryn ( 29 March 1782 -- 6 September 1827 ) was a Norwegian jurist , magistrate and civil servant .
Josefa de Óbidos ( Portuguese : ( ʒuˈzɛfɐ ð(j ) ˈɔβiðuʃ ) ; 20 February 1630 -- 22 July 1684 ) was a Spanish - born , Portuguese painter .
Rear Admiral Thomas Benjamin Stratton Adair ( 6 November 1861 -- 12 August 1928 ) was Unionist Party ( Scotland ) MP for Glasgow Shettleston ( UK Parliament constituency ) from December 1918 to October 1922 .
Icchok Malmed ( יצחק מאַלמעד ) ( born 1903 in Brześć nad Bugiem - 8 February 1943 in Białystok , Poland ) was a Polish Jew and fighter of the Białystok Ghetto during the German occupation of Poland in World War II . On January 1943 German soldiers started the liquidation of the ghetto in Białystok .
When Macrinus was defeated on 8 June 218 , at Antioch , Diadumenian 's death followed his father 's .
Gabriel Plattes ( c.1600 - -1644 ) was an English writer on agriculture and science , and also now recognised as the author of the utopian work Description of the Famous Kingdome of Macaria , often attributed to Samuel Hartlib under whose name it was published .
John Hewer ( 13 January 1922 -- 16 March 2008 ) was an English actor and manager .
Spomenko Gostić ( Serbian Cyrillic : Споменко Гостић ; 14 August 1978 -- 20 March 1993 ) was a Serb soldier during the Bosnian War .

Roman Dumbadze ( Georgian : რომან დუმბაძე ; Russian : Роман Нодарович Думбадзе , Roman Nodarovich Dumbadze ) ( 17 March 1964 -- 21 May 2012 ) was a Georgian military commander , who led a mutiny during the 2004 crisis in Adjara .
Henry Martyn Scudder ( 5 February 1822 -- 4 June 1895 ) was a missionary under American Board of Commissioners for Foreign Missions and Board of Foreign Missions of the Reformed Church in America to Japan and South India -- to American Madura Mission and American Madras Mission .
John Colbatch ( 1664 - -1748 ) was an English churchman and academic , professor of moral philosophy at Cambridge .
Charles Douglass Smith ( ca 1761 -- February 19 , 1855 ) was a British army officer and colonial administrator .
Frederick Tracy Dent ( December 17 , 1820 - -December 23 , 1892 ) was an American general .
Johannes Frederik Fröhlich ( 21 August 1806 -- 21 May 1860 ) ( or Frølich ) , a Danish violinist , conductor and composer , was a precursor of Niels Gade and J.P.E. Hartmann , and a central figure in Danish musical circles during the Romantic era .
Maelimarchair ( died 746 ) was Bishop of Aughrim , County Galway .
Christopher William Puller ( 1807 - -1864 ) , from 1857 Christopher William Giles Puller , was an English barrister and politician .
Douglas Ferreira , O.B.E. , ( 1929 - -2003 ) was the longest serving General Manager of the Ravenglass & Eskdale Railway , a heritage railway in Cumbria , England known as the `` Ratty '' .
Harold A. Carter ( 1937 - 2013 ) was the senior pastor of New Shiloh Baptist Church in Baltimore , Maryland and a major religious leader in that city .
Nicholas de Moffat ( died 1270 ) was a 13th - century cleric who was twice bishop - elect of Glasgow .
Ezzedine Salim , ( Arabic : عزالدين سليم‎ ) , also known as Abdelzahra Othman Mohammed ( 1943 -- 17 May 2004 , عبدالزهرة عثمان محمد ) , was an Iraqi politician , author , educator , Islamist theorist and one of the leading members of the Iraqi Dawaa Movement between 1980 and 2004 .
John Duport ( died 1617 ) was an English scholar and translator .
Fulton Lewis , Jr. ( April 30 , 1903 in Washington D.C. -- August 20 , 1966 in Washington D. C. ) was a prominent conservative American radio broadcaster from the 1930s to the 1960s .
Gideon Wanton ( 20 October 1693 - 12 September 1767 ) was a governor of the Colony of Rhode Island and Providence Plantations who served for two separate one - year terms .
Friedrich Waismann ( 21 March 1896 -- 4 November 1959 ) was an Austrian mathematician , physicist , and philosopher .
Traian Ionescu ( 17 July 1923 - 4 October 2006 ) was a former Romanian football player and manager .
Paddy O'Donovan ( 1916 - -1990 ) was an Irish hurler who played as a right corner - back for the Cork senior team .
Eliyahu de Vidas ( 1518 - -1592 , Hebron ) was a 16th - century rabbi in Ottoman Palestine .
Marie of Korikos ( 1321 -- before 1405 ) was the daughter of Oshin of Corycos and his second wife , Jeanne of Anjou .
Eyvind Mehle ( 1895 -- 15 July 1945 ) was a Norwegian radio personality , media professor and Nazi collaborator .
Samuel Bradburn ( 1751 - -1816 ) , was a Methodist preacher .
Garry Dowling died in a car accident near Mt Tamborine on 5 March 1983 .
Harald Smith ( born June 29 , 1879 -- May 1977 ) was a Norwegian Nordic skier who won the Holmenkollen medal in 1904 .

Charles Henry O'Donoghue ( 1885 - -1961 ) was a English zoologist who studied molluscs , a malacologist .

Yostos or Justus ( Ge'ez ዮስቶስ , throne name Tsehay Sagad Ge'ez ፀሓይ ሰገድ , `` to whom the sun bows '' ) was nəgusä nägäst ( 14 October 1711 -- 19 February 1716 ) of Ethiopia .
Jotello Festiri Soga ( 1865 - 1906 ) was South Africa 's first black veterinary surgeon who played a leading role in eradicating rinderpest .
William Skirving ( c. 1745 - -1796 ) was one of the five Scottish Martyrs for Liberty .

Luitpold of Znojmo ( Czech : Litold znojemský , German : Luitpold von Znaim , Latin : Lutoldus Znoyemsis ; died 15 . March 1112 ) was the Duke of Moravia for twenty years - between 1092 and 1112 .

Pierce Tempest ( 1653 - -1717 ) was an English printseller , best known for the series Cryes of the City of London .
Richard Brocklesby ( 11 August 1722 -- 11 December 1797 ) , an English physician , was born at Minehead , Somerset .
William Armstrong , Baron Armstrong of Sanderstead GCB MVO PC ( 3 March 1915 -- 12 July 1980 ) was a British civil servant and banker .
Anne Jane Thornton ( 1817 - -1877 ) , also spelt Ann Jane Thornton , was a 19th - century adventurer from Donegal who in 1832 posed as a boy to go to sea , in pursuit of a lost lover who had gone to the United States .
Percy Shepherd , OBE ( 8 August 1878 -- March 1948 ) was an eminent British military and civil engineer specialising in docks , rivers and estuaries .
William Ingalton ( 1794 - -1866 ) , was an English painter and builder .
Julia Taft Bayne ( March 4 , 1845 -- December 14 , 1933 ) was an American author who wrote a memoir of the Lincoln White House entitled Tad Lincoln 's Father ( 1931 ) , based on her time visiting the household as a teenager with her younger brothers .
Lionel de Jersey Harvard ( 3 June 1893 -- 30 March 1918 ) was a young Englishman who , discovered to be collaterally descended from Harvard College founder John Harvard , was consequently offered the opportunity to attend that university , from which he graduated in 1915 .
Thomas Brand , 20th Baron Dacre ( 25 March 1774 -- 21 March 1851 ) was a British peer and Whig politician .
Reinhold Mannkopff ( 18 May 1894 -- 9 April 1978 ) was a German experimental physicist who specialized in spectroscopy .
Hans Renold ( 31 July 1852 - 2 May 1943 ) was a Swiss / British engineer , inventor and industrialist in Britain , who founded the Renold manufacturing textile - chain making business in 1879 , and with Alexander Hamilton Church is credited for introducing scientific management to England .
Eko Maulana Ali ( 26 September 1951 -- 30 July 2013 ) was the Governor of Bangka Belitung from April 2007 until his death in July 2013 .
Annie Altschul , CBE , FRCN ( b. 18 February 1919 , Vienna -- d. 24 December 2001 , Edinburgh ) was a British nurse , midwife , researcher and educator .
Joscelin of Louvain , also spelled Jocelin de Louvain and Jocelyn of Leuven , ( 1121 - -1180 ) was a nobleman from the Duchy of Brabant who settled in England having married an English heiress .
Richard Gifford ( 1725 - -1807 ) , English poet , was educated at Oxford .
Emma Azalia Hackley ( 1867 - -1922 ) was an African - American singer and political activist .
Isaac Aboab of Castile ( 1433 -- January 1493 ) , also known as Isaac Aboab II , was a Spanish - Jewish Rabbi , Posek and Torah commentator .
Georgius Merula ( c. 1430 -- 1494 ) was an Italian humanist and classical scholar .
Vance Muse ( 1890 - -1950 ) was an American businessman and conservative lobbyist from Texas who invented the Right - to - work movement against the unionization of American workers , and helped pass the first anti - union laws in Texas .
Humphrey Ely , LL.D. , ( died 1604 ) was an English Catholic divine .
Frank Gordy ( died 1983 ) is the founder of The Varsity chain of restaurants , which includes the world 's largest drive - in restaurant on North Avenue near Georgia Tech in Atlanta , GA .
Josef Frolík ( September 22 , 1928 - May 1989 ) was a Czechoslovak spy who , in 1969 , defected to the United States and joined the CIA .
Jalaluddin Ahsan Khan ( died 1340 ) was the first Sultan of Madurai Sultanate and father - in - law of the North African Arab traveler Ibn Batutah .
Alexander Skirving ( 1868 -- 28 June 1935 ) was a trade union secretary and member of the Queensland Legislative Council .
Jaroslav Hlava ( 7 May 1855 -- 31 October 1924 ) was a Czech anatomical pathologist .
Paulin Soumanou Vieyra ( 31 January 1925 -- 4 November 1987 ) was a Beninese / Senegalese film director and historian .
Palamede Gattilusio ( c. 1389 - 1455 ) was the Lord of Ainos from 1409 to his death , succeeding his great - uncle Niccolò .
Scofield Thayer ( 12 December 1889 -- 9 July 1982 ) was a wealthy American poet and publisher , best known for his art collection , now at the Metropolitan Museum of Art and as a publisher and editor of the literary magazine The Dial during the 1920s .
Hilda Mary Woods ( 1892 -- 1971 ) MBE , was a British statistician who began work in 1916 at the Medical Research Council 's Statistical Research Unit with Major Greenwood ( `` Major '' being his forename , not a military rank ) .
Ernest Clayton Andrews ( 18 October 1870 -- 1 July 1948 ) was an Australian geologist and botanist .
Pandatsang Rapga ( Tibetan : སྤོམ་མདའ་ཚང་རབ་དགའ་ , Wylie : spom mda ' tshang rab dga ; 1902 - -1974 ) was a Khamba revolutionary during the first half of the 20th century in Tibet .
Kanvar ( Prince ) Nau Nihal Singh ( 9 March 1821 -- 6 November 1840 ) was a Sikh ruler of the sovereign country of Punjab and the Sikh Empire .
Joseph Ashbury ( 1638 - -1720 ) , was an English actor and theatrical manager .
Sir Barry Sheen ( 31 August 1918 -- 25 October 2005 ) was a British judge who served as Admiralty Judge of the High Court from 1978 to 1993 .
Leila Hadley ( 22 September 1925 -- 10 February 2009 ) was an American travel writer and socialite .
Joe Bratty ( c. 1961 - 31 July 1994 ) was a Northern Irish loyalist paramilitary and a leading member of the Ulster Defence Association 's South Belfast Brigade .
Freda Thompson OBE ( 5 April 1909 - 11 December 1980 ) was a pioneer aviator , the first Australian woman to fly solo from the United Kingdom to Australia .
Frederick Villiers Meynell ( 24 March 1801 -- 27 May 1872 ) , known as Frederick Villiers during his political career , was a British Whig politician .
Lorentz Eichstadt ( 10 August 1596 -- 8 June 1660 ) was a German mathematician and astronomer .
' ( Pierre Louis ) Philippe de La Guêpière ' ( c. 1715 -- 30 October 1773 ) was a French architect whose main commissions were from Karl Eugen , Duke of Württemberg .
Martha Ray ( 1742 -- 7 April 1779 ) was a British singer of the Georgian era .
Ronald Harrison ( died 28 June 2011 , Cape Town , South Africa ) was a South African artist most well known for his 1962 painting Black Christ .
Juan del Vado y Gomez ( 1625 - -1691 ) was a Spanish composer , organist and violinist .
Valentin Ickelshamer ( also spelled Ikelschamer , Ikelsheimer , Eckelsheimer , Ikkersamer , Becklersheimer , Zangsthamer ; c.1500 - -1547 ) , was a German grammarian .
George Anderson Lawson ( Edinburgh 1832 - -1904 ) was a British Victorian era sculptor who was associated with the New Sculpture movement .
Ludwig Helmbold , also spelled Ludwig Heimbold , ( 21 January 1532 -- 8 April 1598 ) was a poet of Lutheran hymns .
Stephen Birch ( 1872 - -1940 ) was the President of the Kennecott Copper Company and one of the most revered business men of his time .
Margaret Tomkins ( 1916 - -2002 ) was an American Surrealist / Abstract expressionist painter .
Jorma Räty ( 15 October 1946 -- 29 September 2007 ) was a Finnish weightlifter who became a bodybuilder in the early 1960s .
Marian Chace ( 31 October 1896 -- 19 July 1970 ) is one of the founders of modern dance therapy .
George Montagu , 4th Duke of Manchester PC ( 6 April 1737 -- 2 September 1788 ) was a British politician and diplomat .
Count Alois von Beckh Widmanstätten ( 13 July 1753 -- 10 June 1849 ) was an Austrian printer and scientist .
Dame Beryl Paston Brown , DBE ( 7 March 1909 -- 25 July 1997 ) was a British academic and educator .
Louis - Alexandre des Friches de Menneval ( fl . 1687 - -1703 ) was a governor of Acadia from 1687 - 1690 .
Peter Hildreth ( 8 July 1928 -- 25 February 2011 ) was a British hurdling athlete .
Robert Dundas , Lord Arniston ( died 1726 ) was a Scottish ordinary lord of session .
John Michael Ingram ( 1 February 1931 -- 13 June 2014 ) was an influential British menswear designer and retailer of the 1950s and ' 60s who founded the John Michael fashion brand , followed by a range of successful retail concepts , before establishing one of the first fashion forecasting agencies in the 1970s .
Ralph Lancaster ( 25 November 1907 -- 28 August 1942 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for Geelong in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Philippe Curtius ( 1737 - -1794 ) was a Swiss physician and wax modeller who taught Marie Tussaud the art of wax modelling .
Benson Leavitt ( 21 June 1797 - -1 June 1869 ) was a Boston , Massachusetts , businessman , born in New Hampshire , who served as an Alderman of Boston , and later as acting mayor after the incumbent became incapacitated and died while in office .
Jones Morgan ( 23 October 1882 -- 29 August 1993 ) was an American supercentenarian who claimed he was the last surviving veteran of the Spanish--
John Bedford Leno ( 29 June 1826 -- 31 October 1894 ) was a Chartist , Radical , Poet and printer who acted as a `` bridge '' between Chartism and early Labour movements , as well as between the working and ruling classes .
Jose Manuel Nieto ( 1734 - -1804 ) was a soldier from the Presidio of San Diego who was assigned to the Mission San Gabriel at the time his land was granted by the Spanish Empire in 1784 .
Jonas Lidströmer ( 1755 - -1808 ) was a Swedish inventor and officer in the Swedish Navy .
James Laidlaw Maxwell Senior ( Pe̍h - ōe - jī : Má Ngá - kok ; Chinese : 馬雅各 ; born 18 March 1836 in Scotland -- March 1921 ) was the first Presbyterian missionary to Formosa ( Qing - era Taiwan ) .
Finguine mac Cathail Con - cen - máthair ( died 696 ) was a King of Munster from the Glendamnach branch of the Eoganachta .
Clement Plumsted ( 1680 , Norfolk , England ? -- 26 May 1745 , Philadelphia ) was Mayor of Philadelphia in 1723 , 1736 , and 1741 .
Atul Chandra Ghosh(1881 - 1961 ) was a prominent personality of the Indian freedom movement from Purulia district , West Bengal .
George Longstaff ( ? 1947 - 5 October 2003 ) was a British bicycle builder with a high reputation for tandem bicycles , tricycles and handbuilt touring bicycles .
Gilles de Roye ( or Egidius de Roya ) ( died 1478 ) , Flemish chronicler , was born probably at Montdidier , and became a Cistercian monk .
Daniel Delany Bulger ( 18 December 1865 -- 8 December 1930 ) was a leading Irish athlete .
Qurbān-ʻAlī Khālidī ( Russian : Курбангали Халиди , 1846 - 1913 ) was a Kazakh historian , focusing mainly on the history of the eastern Kazakh steppe .
Carl Theodor Anger ( Danzig , 31 July 1803 -- Danzig , 25 March 1858 ) was a German mathematician and astronomer .
Mehmet Kâzım Orbay ( 11 March 1887 -- 3 June 1964 ) was a Turkish general and senator .
Aino Taube ( 11 July 1912 -- 11 July 1990 ) was a Swedish film and theatre actress .
Samuel Horsley ( 15 September 1733 -- 4 October 1806 ) was a British churchman , bishop of Rochester from 1793 .
Henry O'Brien , 7th Earl of Thomond PC ( Ire ) ( c.1620 -- 2 May 1691 ) was an Irish peer , styled Lord Ibrackan from 1639 to 1657 .
Don Ramón Músquiz ( 1797 - -1867 ) was the Governor of Coahuila and Texas from 1830 to 1831 and in 1835 .
Jacques d'Arthois ( 12 October 1613 ( baptised ) - May 1686 ) was a Flemish Baroque painter who specialized in landscapes .
Daniel B. Smith ( July 14 , 1792 -- March , 1883 ) was an educator and pharmacist in Philadelphia , Pennsylvania .
Joseph Médard Carrière ( 1902 - -1970 ) , was a Franco - Ontarian French - language scholar .
Arthur Robins ( 1888 -- 12 March 1924 ) was an English footballer who played as an Outside right for Sheffield United in the Football League .
Marco Kartodikromo ( 1890 -- 18 March 1932 ) , also known by his pen name Mas Marco , was an Indonesian journalist and writer .
Simeon Ashe or Ash ( died 1662 ) was an English nonconformist clergyman , a member of the Westminster Assembly and chaplain to the Parliamentary leader Edward Montagu , 2nd Earl of Manchester .
Brigid Tunney ( née Gallagher ; 1886 -- 1975 ) was an Irish traditional singer , probably best known for being the mother of Paddy Tunney , a key personality in the Irish music scene and well known in British Folk circles from the 1950s up until his death in 2002 .
Sir Richard Rawdon Stawell KBE , ( 14 March 1864 -- 18 April 1935 ) was an Australian doctor , president of Victorian branch of the British Medical Association .
Gladys Johnston ( née Foster ; 1906 - -1983 ) was a Canadian artist known primarily for her landscapes .
B. M. Gafoor ( 4 May 1942 - 13 November 2003 ) was an Indian cartoonist and comic artist .
Pope John XIX ( Latin : Ioannes XIX ; died October 1032 ) was Pope from May 1024 to his death in 1032 .
Alfred Burke ( 28 February 1918 -- 16 February 2011 ) was an English actor , best known for his portrayal of Frank Marker in the drama series Public Eye , which ran on television for ten years .
Geng Zhongming ( Chinese : 耿仲明 ; pinyin : Gěng Zhòngmíng ; Wade -- Giles : Keng3 Chung4-ming2 ; 1604 - -1649 ) was a military leader who lived through the transition from the Ming ( 1368 - -1644 ) to the Qing ( 1644 - -1912 ) dynasty , during which he served both sides .
Erskine Barton Childers ( 11 March 1929 -- 25 August 1996 ) was a writer , BBC correspondent and United Nations senior civil servant .
Simon Sidon or Simon Szidon ( 1892 in Versec , Kingdom of Hungary -- 27 April 1941 , Budapest , Hungary ) was a reclusive Hungarian mathematician who worked on trigonometric series and orthogonal systems and who introduced Sidon sequences and Sidon sets .
Michael Schilkin ( 1 May 1900 -- 3 May 1962 ) was a Russian - born ceramist who is best known for having worked in the art department of Arabia .
Fang Gao ( 房暠 ) ( d. 944 ) was an official of the Chinese Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms Period states Later Tang and Later Jin , serving as the chief of staff ( Shumishi ) for Later Tang 's last emperor Li Congke .
James Ogilvy - Grant , 9th Earl of Seafield ( 27 December 1817 -- 5 June 1888 ) , known for most of his life as the Hon . James Ogilvy - Grant , was a Scottish peer and Conservative Member of Parliament ( MP ) .
Áed Uaridnach ( or Áed mac Domnaill ) ( died 612 ) was an Irish king who was High King of Ireland .
Peter Cantor ( or Peter the Chanter ) ( died 1197 ) was a French Roman Catholic theologian .
Jackie Coulter ( 1912 , Whiteabbey -- 1981 ) is a former Northern Irish footballer .
Bartłomiej Pękiel ( fl . from 1633 ; d. ca . 1670 ) was a notable Polish composer of classical music .
Nicolò Zen the younger ( 1515 - -1565 ) was a Venetian Senator .
Nathan Bryan Whitfield ( 19 September 1799 in Lenoir County , North Carolina-27 December 1868 in Demopolis , Marengo County , Alabama ) was a planter , architect and General of the North Carolina Militia during the American Civil War .
Louis Dugauguez ( 21 February 1918 -- 22 September 1991 ) was French former footballer and football manager .
Johann Jakob Frey ( 27 January 1813 - 30 September 1865 ) , a Swiss landscape painter , a native of Basle , studied principally in Italy , and his views of that country are much valued .
St. John Greer Ervine ( 28 December 1883 -- 24 January 1971 ) was an Irish author , writer , critic and dramatist .
Rovshan Mustafayev also known as Roshen Mustafayev ( born 5 October 1960 , Baku -- died 20 February 2009 , Istanbul ) was an Azeri political scientist .
N.M. Mohan ( 1949 - 2012 ) was an Indian comics writer , editor , magazine and advertisement designer , visualiser and architectural consultant .
Oscar Egg ( 2 March 1890 -- 9 February 1961 ) was a Swiss track and road bicycle racer .
Sweyn the Crusader ( Danish : Svend Korsfarer ; pronounced ( ˈsfen ˈkɔːsfɑːə ) ; c. 1050 -- 1097 ) was a Danish crusader .
Constantius II ( Latin : Flavius Julius Constantius Augustus ; 7 August 317 -- 3 November 361 ) was Roman Emperor from 337 to 361 .
Berthold Heinrich Kämpfert , ( 16 October 1923 -- 21 June 1980 ) , better known as Bert Kaempfert , was a German orchestra leader and songwriter .
Doru Davidovici ( 1945 - -1989 ) , was an aviator and writer .
Wang Gong ( 王珙 ) ( d. 899 ) was a warlord late in the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , who controlled Baoyi Circuit ( 保義 , headquartered in modern Sanmenxia , Henan ) from 887 , when he succeeded his father Wang Chongying , to his death in 899 .
James Bronterre O'Brien ( 1805 -- 23 December 1864 ) was an Irish Chartist leader , reformer and journalist .
Nelson Fu or Fu Lianzhang ( Chinese : 傅连暲 ; 1894 - -1968 ) was a Chinese doctor .
Antoni Protazy Potocki ( 11 September 1761 -- 1801 ) , aka Prot , was a Polish noble ( szlachcic ) .
Carlos Noguera ( 28 October 1943 -- 3 February 2015 ) was a Venezuelan writer and psychologist .
Pierre Audouin ( 1768 - -1822 ) was a French engraver , and pupil of Beauvarlet .
Lucien Aigner ( 14 September 1901 -- 29 March 1999 ) was a Hungarian photographer and pioneering photojournalist .
Michael Flagstad ( 1869 - -1930 ) was a Norwegian musician and conductor from Hamar .
Józef Lewoniewski ( 1899 - 11 September 1933 ) was a Polish military and sports aviator .
F. A. Forbes ( 16 March 1869 -- 1936 ) was the nom de plume of Mother Frances Alice Monica Forbes , RSCJ , a member of the Society of the Sacred Heart from Scotland and a religious author .
Roland Pertwee ( 17 May 1885 -- 26 April 1963 ) was an English playwright , film and television screenwriter , director and actor .
Sir Samuel Ferguson ( 10 March 1810 -- 9 August 1886 ) was an Irish poet , barrister , antiquarian , artist and public servant .
Jasper Wilson Johns ( 1824 -- 26 July 1891 ) was a civil engineer , merchant , railway promoter and Liberal Party politician .
Marta Flores ( 1913 - -2005 ) was a Spanish actress who appeared in more than ninety productions during her lengthy career .
Thomas Kurton Heath ( 1853 - -1938 ) was a vaudeville actor with James McIntyre .
Philip I de Croÿ ( 1435 - -1511 ) was Seigneur de Croÿ and Count of Porcéan .
Johann Friedrich August Borsig ( 23 June 1804 -- 6 July 1854 ) was a German businessman who founded the Borsig - Werke factory .
Niku Kheradmand ( Persian : نیکو خردمند ‎‎ , also Romanized as Nikoo Kheradmand ) ( 27 October 1932 -- 17 November 2009 ) was an Iranian actress and film dubber .
Fu Xunying ( 苻訓英 ) ( died 407 ) was an empress of the Chinese / Xianbei state Later Yan .
Kostas Karras ( Greek : Κώστας Καρράς ) ( 21 June 1936 -- 6 May 2012 ) was a Greek actor and politician .
Archduchess Maria Isabella of Austria , Princess of Tuscany ( 21 May 1834 -- 14 July 1901 ) was a princess of Bourbon - Two Sicilies and later Archduchess of Austria .
Bayantömöriin Khaisan ( Mongolian : Баянтөмөрийн Хайсан ) , also spelled Khayishan ( ᠬᠠᠶᠢᠱᠠᠨ , qayišan ) ( c. 1862 - 1917 ) , was one of leading figures of the Outer Mongolian revolution of 1911 for Mongolian independence from China .
Ippolito Borghese ( late 16th century -- March 1627 ) was an Italian painter of the late - Renaissance , born in Sigillo ( near Perugia ) in the late 16th century .
Angelica Balabanoff ( or Balabanov , Balabanova ; Russian : Анжелика Балабанова -- Anzhelika Balabanova ; c. 1878 -- 25 November 1965 ) was a Russian - Jewish - Italian communist and social democratic activist .
Marian Grzybowski ( 15 June 1895 in Chardzhou - 11 December 1949 ) was a Polish dermatologist .
General Sir Arthur Power Palmer GCB GCIE ( 25 June 1840 -- 28 February 1904 ) was Commander - in - Chief , India between March 1900 and December 1902 .
John Ewer ( died 1774 ) was an English bishop of Llandaff and bishop of Bangor .
Henry Wylie ( 1844 - -1918 ) was an administrator in British India , he served as the acting Chief Commissioner of Balochistan in 1899 .
Robert D. Yates ( December 27 , 1857 in Brooklyn ; September 19 , 1885 ) was an American draughts champion and medical doctor .
François Crépieul ( March 16 , 1638 --1702 ) was a Jesuit missionary in Canada and vicar apostolic for the Montagnais Indians .
Xiao Wenshou ( 蕭文壽 ) ( 343 - -423 ) , formally Empress Xiaoyi ( 孝懿皇后 , literally `` the filial and benevolent empress '' ) was an empress dowager of the Chinese dynasty Liu Song .
Mascezel ( Latin : Masceldelus or Mascezel ) ( † circa 398 ) was briefly ruler of Roman North Africa after the defeat of his brother Gildo during the Gildonic revolt in 398 AD .
Ehud Avriel ( born Georg Überall ; Hebrew : אהוד אבריאל‎ ; 1917 -- 27 August 1980 ) was an Israeli diplomat and politician who served as a member of the Knesset for Mapai between 1955 and 1957 .
Edward F. Allodi AIA ( 1893 - 1987 ) was an Italian American architect who designed a number of important buildings for Roman Catholic Clients in Connecticut and New York during the early part of the 20th century .
Edmund Wyndham ( 1600 -- 2 March 1681 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons variously between 1640 and 1679 .
Lettice Sandford , née Mackintosh Rate , ( 1902 - -1993 ) was a draftsman , wood - engraver , pioneer corn dolly revivalist and watercolourist of her beloved Herefordshire .
Adolphe Pierre Sunaert , Adolphe Sunaert or Adolf Sunaert ( Ghent , 27 November 1825 -- Ghent , 17 April 1876 ) was a Belgian painter , printmaker , teacher and author .
Martin Booth ( 7 September 1944 -- 12 February 2004 ) was a prolific British novelist and poet .
Marius Ormestad ( 13 December 1874 -- 28 May 1964 ) was a Norwegian trade unionist and civil servant .
Birgitte Price ( earlier known as Birgitte Bruun ; 29 April 1934 -- 17 July 1997 ) was a Danish actress of the 1950s and 1960s .
James Corcoran ( c.1780 -- 1804 ) was an Irish rebel who fought during the rebellion of 1798 and was the leader of the last rebel guerrilla band to be defeated in the years following the suppression of the rebellion .
George Binney Dibblee ( 1868 - 27 August 1952 ) was a newspaperman and academic who was manager of the Manchester Guardian and a noted authority on the idea of supply and demand .
Gustav , Landgrave of Hesse - Homburg ( 17 February 1781 -- 8 September 1848 ) was landgrave of the German state of Hesse - Homburg from 1846 to 1848 .
John Charles Van Dyke ( 1861 - -1931 ) was an American art historian and critic .
General Seong Seung ( Hangul : 성승 ; hanja : 成勝 ? - 1456 ) was a Korean Joseon Dynasty politician and soldier .
Quirijn Jansz Damast ( 1580 -- 1638 ) , was a Dutch linen weaver and mayor of Haarlem , best known today for his portrait painted by Frans Hals .
Arthur Fonjallaz ( 2 January 1875 - 24 January 1944 ) was a Swiss military figure , publisher and fascist .
Karl Otto Hunziker ( 13 August 1841 -- 23 May 1909 ) was a Swiss professor of pedagogy , pastor , and politician .
Whyghtone Kamthunzi ( 31 July 1956 - 18 May 2000 ) was a leading writer in the Chichewa language of Malawi in the 1980s and 1990s .
Emanoil Bacaloglu ( Romanian pronunciation : ( emanoˈil bakaˈloɡlu ) ; 11 April 1830 -- 30 August 1891 ) was a Wallachian and Romanian mathematician , physicist and chemist and a scubadiver , medic , shoe salesman , a vegetarian , policeman and fireman .
Before the troops of Southern Han entered the territory of Tĩnh Hải quân , Ngô Quyền got ahead by defeating and executing Kiều Công Tiễn in 938 and prepared to catch the army of Liu Yan in Bạch Đằng River .
Heinrich - Wolfgang Leopoldt ( 22 August 1927 -- 28 July 2011 ) was a German mathematician , who worked on algebraic number theory .
Ahmed Abdallah Abderemane ( Arabic : أحمد عبد الله عبد الرحمن‎ , Ahmad Abd Allah Abd ar - Rahman , 12 June 1919 -- 26 November 1989 ) was a Comorian politician .
Jens Håkan Schleimann - Jensen , known as Jens S. Jensen ( 25 May 1946 -- 1 July 2015 ) was a Swedish photographer and writer .
Konrad Eubel or Conradus Eubel ( 19 January 1842 -- 5 February 1923 ) was a German Franciscan historian .
Sylvester Emmons ( 28 February 1808 -- 15 November 1881 ) was an American attorney born in New Jersey .
John Keith McBroom Laird ( 12 January 1907 -- 12 November 1985 ) was a Canadian author , barrister , and solicitor .
Archbishop Abraham Kattumana ( 21 January 1944 -- 4 April 1995 ) was an Indian Syro Malabar Catholic Archbishop .
Argentina Díaz Lozano ( 1912 - -1999 ) was the pseudonym for the Honduran writer Argentina Bueso Mejía .
Louis Médard ( 1768 - 1841 ) was a French indiennes merchant and rare books bibliophile .
Gioacchino Prati ( 1790 - -1863 ) was an Italian revolutionary and patriot , a supporter of the Risorgimento who was exiled for his activities in 1821 .
Evelyn Baring , 1st Baron Howick of Glendale KG GCMG KCVO ( 29 September 1903 -- 10 March 1973 ) was Governor of Southern Rhodesia from 1942 to 1944 and Governor of Kenya from 1952 to 1959 .
George Dupre ( 1903 - -1982 ) was a Canadian man who falsely claimed to have been an Special Operations Executive operative during World War II . In 1953 , Quentin Reynolds , an ex - war correspondent , had written a book The Man Who Would n't Talk about George Dupre 's alleged wartime experiences .
Ladislau Brosovszky ( Romanian : Broşovschi ) ( 23 March 1951 -- 23 December 1990 ) was a Romanian football midfielder .
William Hamper ( 12 December 1776 - -3 May 1831 ) was an English businessman , magistrate and antiquary .
Geoffrey Eggleston ( 15 January 1944 -- 2 December 2008 ) , more usually known as `` Geoff '' , was an Australian poet , prominent in the performance poetry scene .
Francis B. Foley ( July 7 , 1887 - February . 1973 ) , was an American ferrous metallurgist .
Sir Samuel Goldman KCB ( 10 March 1912 -- 28 July 2007 ) was Second Permanent Secretary at Her Majesty 's Treasury and later an international banker .
Giuseppe Jannacconi ( Janacconi , Gianacconi ; 1740 -- 16 March 1816 ) was an Italian composer , one of the last in the style of Palestrina .
Nicholas Nugent ( c. 1525 - -1582 ) was an Anglo - Irish judge , who was hanged for treason by the ( British ) government that appointed him .
Robert Bennett Bean , M.D. ( 1874 -- 1944 ) was a Professor of Anatomy and ethnologist .
John Hays Hammond ( 31 March 1855 -- 8 June 1936 ) was a mining engineer , diplomat , and philanthropist .
Ole Tobias Olsen ( 18 August 1830 -- 6 July 1924 ) was a Norwegian teacher and minister .
Adunni Bankole ( March 1959 -- 3 January 2015 ) was a Nigerian society matriarch and businesswoman .
Brigadier General Julian Stachiewicz ( Polish pronunciation : ( ˈjuljan staˈxʲɛvʲit͡ʂ ) ; 1890 - 1934 ) was a Polish Army officer and a historian and writer .
Helmut Bantz ( 14 September 1921 -- 4 December 2004 ) was a German gymnast and Olympic champion .
Onesimo Makani Kabweza ( 1939 - d. 27 April 1993 ) is the late editor of Moto Magazine in Zimbabwe .
Francis John Govier Ebling ( 21 June 1918 -- 29 May 1992 ) , generally known as John Ebling , was Professor of Zoology at the University of Sheffield from 1968 to 1983 , and subsequently Emeritus Professor of Dermatology 1983 - 1992 .
Alan Carrington CBE , FRS ( 6 January 1934 -- 31 August 2013 ) was a British chemist and one of the leading spectroscopists in Britain in the late twentieth century .
Major - General Lord Charles Wellesley ( 16 January 1808 -- 9 October 1858 ) was a British politician , soldier and courtier .
Andrew Greenwood ( 20 August 1847 -- 12 February 1889 ) was an English cricketer , who played in the first two cricket Tests .
Kesar Lall ( Devanagari : केसर लाल ) ( 15 July 1926 - 26 December 2012 ) ( alternative name : Kesar Lall Shrestha ) was a Nepalese folklorist and writer .
Laurentius Andreae ( c. 1470 -- 14 April 1552 ) was a Swedish clergyman and scholar who is acknowledged as one of his country 's preeminent intellectual figures during the first half of the 16th century .
Sir James Langham , 7th Baronet ( 31 January 1736 -- 7 February 1795 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1784 to 1790 .
Fritz Stiedry ( born 11 October 1883 , Vienna - died 8 August 1968 , Zurich ) was an Austrian conductor and composer .
Arthur James Seymour ( 12 January 1914 - -25 December 1989 ) , or A. J. Seymour , was a Guyanese , poet , essayist , memoirist , and founding editor of the literary journal Kyk - Over - Al .
Louis Levy ( 20 November 1894 -- 18 August 1957 ) was an English film composer and music director , who worked in particular on Alfred Hitchcock and Will Hay films .
Samuel Winter D.D. ( 1603 - -1666 ) was an English clergyman and academic , who became Provost of Trinity College , Dublin .
Hermarchus or Hermarch ( Greek : Ἕρμαρχoς , Hermarkhos , `` reign of Hermes '' ; c. 325-c . 250 BCE ) , sometimes incorrectly written Hermachus ( Greek : Ἕρμαχoς , Hermakhos ) , was an Epicurean philosopher .
Adnan al - Malki ( Arabic : عدنان المالكي‎‎ ) ( 1918 -- 22 April 1955 ) was a Syrian Army officer and political figure in the mid-20th century .
