Edward Rosen ( 12 December 1906 -- 28 March 1985 ) was an American historian , whose main field of study was early modern science and , in particular , the work of Copernicus , Galileo and Kepler .
Charles Morgan Lemann ( 1806 - -1852 ) was an English botanist who collected a large number of plant specimens , including from Madeira and Gibraltar .
Mary Fitton ( or Fytton ) ( Baptised 24 June 1578 -- 1647 ) was an Elizabethan gentlewoman who became a maid of honour to Queen Elizabeth .
Blessed Ralph Crockett ( b. at Barton , near Farndon , Cheshire ; executed at Chichester , 1 October 1588 ) was an English Roman Catholic priest .
General Sir John Dalling , 1st Baronet ( c. 1731 -- 16 January 1798 ) was a British soldier and colonial administrator .
John Charles Molteno , Jr. ( 4 March 1860 -- 23 March 1924 ) M.L.A. , was a South African exporter and Member of Parliament .
Sir William Godfrey , 1st Baronet ( 1739 -- 1817 ) was an Anglo - Irish member of the Irish House of Commons .
Nicolae Crețulescu ( Romanian pronunciation : ( nikoˈla.e kret͡suˈlesku ) , surname also spelled Kretzulescu ; 1 March 1812 -- 26 July 1900 ) was a Wallachian - born Romanian politician and physician .
Saint Stephanie ( died 160 ) is an Eastern Orthodox saint .
Stjepan Đureković ( born 1926 -- 28 July 1983 ) was a Croatian businessman , best known as the politically - appointed CEO of the state - owned INA petrol company .
Maria Anna of Austria ( Maria Anna Josepha ; 7 September 1683 -- 14 August 1754 ) was an Archduchess of Austria and Queen consort of Portugal .
Augustus Hopkins Strong ( 3 August 1836 -- 29 November 1921 ) was a Baptist minister and theologian who lived in the United States during the late 19th and early 20th centuries .
Vimala Thakar ( born 15 April 1921 Ramnavmi day at Bilaspur and died on 11 March 2009 at Falgun Poornima at Mt. Abu ) was an Indian social activist and spiritual teacher .
Jagat Jakhar died in the PGI hospital of Chandigarh at the age of 55 on 17 December 2011 due to a liver infection .
Ion Ferguson Royal Army Medical Corps ( 1913 - 1990 ) was an Irish volunteer for the British army who escaped from Oflag IV - C , Colditz Castle , during the Second World War .
Leif Aronsson ( 27 January 1938 -- 17 January 1987 ) was a Swedish footballer .
Stimson Joseph Brown ( 1854 - 1923 ) was an American astronomer , born at Penn Yan , N. Y. He was educated at Cornell University and at the United States Naval Academy .
Yves Brunsvick ( 1921 - -1999 ) was a famous humanist and philosopher of education .
Renato Peduzzi ( active 19th Century , died 1894 ) was an Italian sculptor .
James Edmeston ( 10 September 1791 -- 7 January 1867 ) was an English architect and surveyor ; he was also known as a prolific writer of church hymns .
Philetaerus ( /ˌfɪlᵻˈtɪərəs/ ; Ancient Greek : Φιλέταιρος , Philetairos , ca . 343 BC--263 BC ) was the founder of the Attalid dynasty of Pergamon in Anatolia .
Henry Maudsley FRCP ( 5 February 1835 -- 23 January 1918 ) was a pioneering British psychiatrist , commemorated in the Maudsley Hospital in London and in the annual Maudsley Lecture of the Royal College of Psychiatrists .
Marten von Barnekow ( 18 March 1900 in Kronburg -- 29 January 1967 near Hof ) was a German equestrian and Olympic champion .
William Barry Pennington ( 9 July 1923 -- 5 March 1968 ) was a British mathematician best known for his work on Ramanujan 's tau function .
Michael McVerry ( 1 December 1949 -- 15 November 1973 ) , was a Provisional Irish Republican Army volunteer and Officer Commanding of the First Battalion of the Provisional IRA South Armagh Brigade .
Francisco Ferreira Drummond ( 21 January 1796 -- 9 November 1858 ) was a historian , palaeograph , musician and politician from a locality of Vila de São Sebastião on the island of Terceira , the Portuguese Azores .
Peder Christian Holst ( 27 April 1798 -- 14 December 1873 ) was a Norwegian politician , military officer and businessperson .
Lewis Hallam ( circa 1714 - -1756 ) was an English - born actor and theatre director in the colonial United States .
Bianca Maria Visconti ( 31 March 1425 -- 28 October 1468 ) was Duchess of Milan from 1450 to 1468 .
James Quin ( 24 February 1693 -- 21 January 1766 ) was an English actor of Irish descent .
Bill Gnaden ( 11 July 1932 -- 12 November 1995 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Tibors de Sarenom ( French Tiburge ; c. 1130 -- aft . 1198 ) is the earliest attestable trobairitz , active during the classical period of medieval Occitan literature at the height of the popularity of the troubadours .
Irawati Karve ( 1905 -- 11 August 1970 ) was an Indian sociologist , anthropologist , educationist , and writer from Maharashtra , India .
Frederick Preston Rubidge , ( 10 March 1806 -- 16 August 1897 ) , was a surveyor and an architect .
Shakeel Badayuni ( Hindi : शकील बदायुनी , Urdu : شکیل بدایونی ) ( 3 August 1916 -- 20 April 1970 ) was an Indian Urdu poet , lyricist and songwriter in Hindi films .
Marian Auerbach also known as Majer Auerbach ( 1882 -- July 1941 , Lwów ) was a Polish classical philologist of Jewish background .
Bernhard Kamnitzer ( 25 October 1890 -- 15 July 1959 ) was a German jurist and Senator of the Free City of Danzig .
Edmund Hoffmeister ( 1893 - -1951 ) was an officer in the German Army , mainly notable for his service in the Wehrmacht Heer during World War II . Hoffmeister 's military service began in 1914 in the Imperial German army .
Sanborn Young ( ? --1964 ) was a California State Senator , best known for being the husband of author Ruth Comfort Mitchell Young .
Cornelius van Zierikzee ( ca 1405 -- 1462 ) was a Dutch priest known for his work in Scotland .
Sir Thomas Dolman ( 13 January 1622 - 18 July 1697 ) was an English landowner and politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1661 to 1679 .
Jeremiah Joyce ( 1763 - 1816 ) was an English Unitarian minister and writer .
John VIII Palaiologos or Palaeologus ( Greek : Ίωάννης Η ' Παλαιολόγος , Iōannēs Ē ' Palaiologos ; 18 December 1392 -- 31 October 1448 ) , was the penultimate reigning Byzantine Emperor , ruling from 1425 to 1448 .
Mary Cecil Hay ( 1840/1841 -- 24 July 1886 ) was a British novelist of thirteen books of romantic sensation fiction .
Zhang Bu ( died 264 ) was a military general of Eastern Wu during the Three Kingdoms period of Chinese history .
Gerhard Bockman ( 1686 - -1773 ) was a Dutch portrait painter and mezzotint engraver .
Monsignor Dilwyn Lewis ( 28 April 1924 -- 10 July 2000 ) was a British clothes designer turned Roman Catholic priest who oversaw the restoration of the ancient Basilica di Santa Maria Maggiore in Rome .
Rossello di Jacopo Franchi ( c. 1377 -- c. 1456 ) was an Italian painter and illuminator in Florence .
George F. Cram ( 1842 - 1928 ) , served in the U.S. Army during the American Civil War .
Giuseppe Maria Ficatelli ( 1639 -- 3 September 1703 ) was an Italian mathematician and painter of the Baroque period .
William Eure , 1st Baron Eure ( c.1483 - -1548 ) of Witton was an English knight and soldier active on the Anglo - Scottish border .
Christian Ulrik Kastrup ( 1784 -- 6 September 1850 ) was a Norwegian jurist , military officer and politician .
William Seguier ( /ˈsiːɡər/ ; 9 November 1772 -- 5 November 1843 ) was a British art dealer , painter , and official functionary in the art world .
Norman Evans ( 11 June 1901 -- 25 November 1962 ) was a variety and radio performer , born in Rochdale , Lancashire , England .
Peter Reville ( 5 October 1904 -- 4 March 1970 ) , Christened `` Henry James '' , but adopted his father 's Christian name , was an Australian rules footballer who played with South Melbourne and Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Asenath Barzani , also Asenath Barazani ( 1590 - -1670 ) ( in Kurdish : Asênat Barzanî ) , the daughter of the eminent Rabbi Samuel HaLevi Barzani , was a renowned Kurdish Jewish woman who lived in Mosul , Iraq .
Cardinal Albert of Brandenburg ( German : Albrecht von Brandenburg ; 28 June 1490 -- 24 September 1545 ) was Elector and Archbishop of Mainz from 1514 to 1545 , and Archbishop of Magdeburg from 1513 to 1545 .
Joseph Škoda ( 10 December 1805 -- 13 June 1881 ) was a Czech physician , medical professor and dermatologist .
Paul Maximilian Heinrich Schneider von Esleben ( 28 August 1915 -- 19 May 2005 ) , known as Paul Schneider - Esleben , was a German architect .
John Alexander Barry ( c. 1790 - -1872 ) was born in Shelburne County , Nova Scotia and was the son of Robert Barry , a loyalist who came to Shelburne in 1773 .
John de Ros , 5th Baron de Ros of Helmsley , KB ( d. 6 August 1393 ) took a prominent part in the pageantry at the coronation of Richard II . Following the coronation he was made a Knight of the Bath .
Robert Richardson - Gardner ( 15 June 1827 - 4 January 1898 ) was a British barrister , militia officer and Conservative politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1874 to 1890 .
Jim Addison ( 1 January 1884 -- 2 May 1957 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Melba Johnson Kgositsile ( 1940 - -1994 ) was an American civil rights activist .
Nilda Elvira Vattuone ( 10 September 1911 -- 20 December 2013 ) , better known by her stage name Nelly Omar , was an Argentine actress and singer during the Golden Age of Argentine Cinema .
Jabez Willes ( December 6 , 1790 -- March 24 , 1842 Potsdam , St. Lawrence County , New York ) was an American manufacturer and politician from New York .
Herri met de Bles ( also known as Henri Blès , Herri de Dinant , Herry de Patinir , and Civetta ) ( c. 1510 -- c. 1555 - -1560 ) was a Flemish Northern Renaissance and Mannerist landscape painter , native of Bouvignes or Dinant ( present - day Belgium ) .
Paul Héger ( 1846 - -1925 ) was a Belgian biologist , and was born to Constantin Heger and Claire Zoe Parent .
Henry Cabourn Pocklington FRS ( 28 January 1870 , Exeter -- 15 May 1952 , Leeds ) was an English physicist and mathematician .
Frances Stackhouse Acton ( née Knight ; 7 July 1794 -- 24 January 1881 ) , known as Fanny , was a British botanist , archaeologist , writer and artist .
Sir John Bright , 1st Baronet ( 14 October 1619 -- 13 October 1688 ) was an English parliamentarian , of Carbrook and Badsworth , Yorkshire .
Dietrich of Anhalt - Dessau ( b. Dessau , 2 August 1702 - d. Dessau , 2 December 1769 ) , was a German prince of the House of Ascania and later regent of the principality of Anhalt - Dessau .
Louise Fatio Duvoisin ( August 18 , 1904 -- July 26 , 1993 ) was a Swiss - born American writer of children 's books .
Gautam Paul Bhattacharjee ( 4 May 1960 -- c. 12 July 2013 ) was a British actor of Indian ethnicity of stage , film and television .
Kenji Urada ( c. 1944 -- July 4 , 1981 ) was a Japanese engineer who was one of the first persons reported to have been killed by a robot .
Philip Hunsu Ajose ( 10 August 1932 - 2 March 2001 ) was the third Pastor of the Celestial Church of Christ ( CCC ) , succeeding Alexander Abiodun Adebayo Bada on 2 October 2000 and being formally declared leader on 24 December 2000 .
Charles Fox Hovey ( 1807 - -1859 ) was a businessman in Boston , Massachusetts who established C.F. Hovey and Co. , a department store on Summer Street .
Józef Motyka ( 23 March 1900 -- 6 July 1984 ) was a Polish botanist and lichenologist .
Charles Kirkpatrick Sharpe ( 1781?--1851 ) was a Scottish antiquary and artist .
Carl August Benjamin Siegel ( 27 April 1757 , Dresden - 15 October 1832 , Dresden ) was a German architecture professor and chief of works , active in Leipzig and Dresden .
Jiřina Petrovická ( 30 January 1923 -- 10 October 2008 ) was a Czechoslovak film actress .
Rou Shi ( Chinese : 柔石 ; 28 September 1902－7 February 1931 ) , formerly romanized as Jou Shih , was a prominent left - wing Chinese writer and member of the May Fourth Movement .
Grigore I Ghica ( 1628 - 1675 ) , a member of the Ghica family , was Prince of Wallachia between September 1660 and December 1664 and again between March 1672 and November 1673 .
George Dibdin Pitt ( born George Pitt , 30 March 1795 -- 16 February 1855 ) was an English actor , stage manager and prolific playwright , specializing in melodrama .
Johannes Hinderikus Egenberger , originally Joannes Henricus ( 28 April 1822 , Arnhem - 14 May 1897 , Utrecht ) was a Dutch painter , photographer and art educator .
Sera Khandro ( 1892 - -1940 ) was a Tibetan Buddhist teacher .
Carlos Bellucci ( 1895 - -1953 ) was an Argentine actor who appeared in thirty one films during his career .
Giovanni della Casa ( 28 July 1503 -- 14 November 1556 ) , was a Florentine poet , writer on etiquette and society , diplomat , and inquisitor .
Suzanne Goodwin , née Suzanne Ebel ( 27 September 1916 -- 28 February 2008 ) , was a British writer of over 40 romantic novels and was translated into some 15 languages .
Isabel Jeans ( 16 September 1891 -- 4 September 1985 ) was an English stage and film actress known for her roles in several Alfred Hitchcock films and her portrayal of Aunt Alicia in the 1958 musical film Gigi , among others .
Harry Greenbank ( 11 September 1865 -- 26 February 1899 ) was an English author and dramatist best known for contributing lyrics to the successful series musicals produced at Daly 's Theatre by George Edwardes in the 1890s .
Nevada N. Stranahan ( February 27 , 1861 -- July 6 , 1928 ) was a Collector of the Port of New York who was born in Oswego County , New York .
William H. Hardy ( 1837−1917 ) founded the cities of Hattiesburg and Laurel , Mississippi , and co - founded the city of Gulfport , Mississippi .
William Hurst Rees ( 12 April 1917 -- 6 January 2004 ) was a leading British valuation surveyor , a Member of the Lands Tribunal from 1973 until his retirement in 1989 .
Alse Young ( ca . 1600 -- 26 May 1647 ) of Windsor , Connecticut -- sometimes Achsah Young or Alice Young -- was the first recorded instance of execution for witchcraft in the thirteen American colonies .
Sir John Pringle , 1st Baronet , PRS ( 10 April 1707 -- 18 January 1782 ) was a Scottish physician who has been called the `` father of military medicine '' ( although Ambroise Paré and Jonathan Letterman have also been accorded this sobriquet ) .
Sampson Erdeswicke ( date of birth unknown , in the reign of Henry VIII ; died 1603 ) was an English antiquarian and chorographer .
Stanley Leslie Balcombe ( born 1904 , died 1938 ) was an English professional footballer of the 1930s .
Harriet Evans Martin ( died 1846 ) was an Anglo - Irish novelist .
Waroch I ( Breton : Gwereg ; modern French : Guérech ; d. c. 550 ) was an early ruler of the Bro Wened ( Vannetais ) in southern Brittany .
Les Scollard ( 11 June 1908 -- 11 September 1973 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Saroj Dey ( Bengali : সরোজ দে ) ( 1921 -- 26 November 1997 ) was a Bengali film director who was part of the collective Agragami which made several notable films in Bengali cinema , from 1950s to the 1970s .
José Luis Rodríguez Vélez ( Santiago de Veraguas , 12 March 1915 - Ciudad de Panamá , Panamá , 21 December 1984 ) was a Panamanian composer , musical director , saxophonist , clarinetist and guitarist .
Joseph Crosfield ( 5 October 1792 -- 16 February 1844 ) was a businessman who established a soap and chemical manufacturing business in Warrington , which was in the historic county of Lancashire and is now in the ceremonial county of Cheshire .
Drakpa Changchub ( Tibetan : གྲགས་པ་བྱང་ཆུབ , Wylie : Grags pa byang chub , 1356 - -1386 ) was a ruler of Central Tibet in 1374 - -1381 .
Albert Cavens ( 1 October 1906 -- 17 December 1985 ) was a Belgian - born American silent film child actor .
Helian Ding ( Chinese : 赫連定 ; died 432 ) , nickname Zhifen ( 直獖 ) , was the last emperor of the Xiongnu state Xia .
Slobodan Anđelković ( Serbian Cyrillic : Слободан Анђелковић ) ( 1 March 1913 -- 6 December 1985 ) was a Serbian football player .
John Foster Kirk ( March 23 , 1824 , Fredericton , New Brunswick -- 1904 ) was an American historian , journalist , educator and bibliographer .
Joy Postle died on June 1 , 1989 and her ashes were spread at her home at Lake Rose in Florida .
Carl Friedrich Kotschy ( Polish : Karol Fryderyk Kotschy , 26 January 1789 -- 9 February 1856 ) was an Austrian Protestant theologian and botanist born in Teschen ( today Cieszyn , Poland ) .
Christian Victor Hely - Hutchinson ( 26 December 1901 -- 11 March 1947 ) was a British composer , born in Cape Town , Cape Colony ( now in South Africa ) .
Father Charles Felix Van Quickenborne died on 17 August 1837 at age 49 and is buried at Florissant , Missouri .
Sir ( Ernest ) Donald Acheson KBE ( 17 September 1926 -- 10 January 2010 ) was a British physician and epidemiologist who served as Chief Medical Officer of the United Kingdom from 1983 to 1991 .
Paul Maxwell ( 12 November 1921 -- 19 December 1991 ) was a Canadian actor who worked mostly in British cinema and television , in which he was usually cast as American characters .
Johan Fredrik Höckert ( 26 August 1826 -- 16 September 1866 ) was a well - known Swedish artist from Jönköping known for his colorful , dramatic oil paintings depicting historical events .
Tycho Kielland ( 25 March 1854 - 3 May 1904 ) was a Norwegian jurist and journalist .
Theodore William Chaundy ( 19 January 1889 - -14 April 1966 ) was an English mathematician who introduced Burchnall--
Krishna Gopal Saxena ( 1912 - 2003 ) was an Indian homoeopathic physician .
Johann Baptist Wendling ( baptised 17 June 1723 -- 27 November 1797 ) was a flute player and composer of the Mannheim School .
James Granger ( 1723 - -1776 ) was an English clergyman , biographer , and print collector .
Baruch Elron ( 1934 - -2006 ) was an Israeli painter best known for his unique Fantastic Realist style rich in symbols and allegories .
Liam Bennett ( 1950 - -2006 ) was a former Wexford senior hurler .
Sir William Markby , KCIE ( 1829 - -1914 ) was an English judge and legal writer , the fourth son of the Rev. William Henry Markby , rector of Duxford , St. Peters .
Pritilata Waddedar ( 5 May 1911 -- 23 September 1932 ) was a Bengali revolutionary nationalist .
Charles Russell Ridgway ( 30 January 1891 -- 26 October 1946 ) was an English cricketer active in the 1910s and 1920s , making a single appearance in first - class cricket .
Robert Thyer ( 1709 - -1781 ) was an English librarian and literary editor , known for his connection with Chetham 's Library .
Abraham Resnick ( 1867 - -1942 , Rochester , New York ) was an American Rabbi , writer and publisher .
Sydney Hodgson ( died 10 December 1591 ) was an English Roman Catholic lawyer .
Ingeborg Rönnblad , born Hansson 10 April 1873 in Gränna - 2 June 1915 in Blidö was a Swedish actress .
Jean Depassio ( date of birth unknown , died April 1925 ) was a French sports shooter .
Xiao Zhaowen ( 蕭昭文 ) ( 480 - -494 ) , formally Prince Gong of Hailing ( 海陵恭王 ) , courtesy name Jishang ( 季尚 ) , was an emperor of the Chinese dynasty Southern Qi .
John Stanbridge ( 1463 - -1510 ) was an English grammarian and schoolmaster .
Benjamin Hazard ( 1770 - -1841 ) was a Rhode Island legislator , attorney and member of the Hartford Convention .
John Luxmoore or Luxmore ( 1766 - -1830 ) was an English bishop of three sees .
Sir Thomas Tyldesley ( 1612 -- 25 August 1651 ) was a supporter of Charles I and a Royalist commander during the English Civil War .
Manfred Kremser ( 30 July 1950 -- 3 March 2013 ) was an Austrian ethnologist and researcher of the human consciousness .
Sir John Lancelot Stirling KCMG ( 5 November 1849 -- 24 May 1932 ) , generally known as Sir Lancelot Stirling , was an Australian politician and grazier .
Sergio Fiorentino ( 22 December 1927 -- 22 August 1998 ) was a 20th - century Italian classical pianist whose sporadic performing career spanned five decades .
Richard Altmann ( 12 March 1852 -- 8 December 1900 ) was a German pathologist and histologist from Deutsch Eylau in the Province of Prussia .
Thomas Green Fessenden ( 22 April 1771 -- 11 November 1837 ) was an American author and editor who worked in England and the United States .
André Caplet ( 23 November 1878 -- 22 April 1925 ) was a French composer and conductor now known primarily through his orchestrations of works by Claude Debussy .
Milton Terris ( 1915 - -2002 ) was an American public health physician and epidemiologist .
Princess Hermine of Waldeck and Pyrmont ( born : 29 September 1827 ; died : 16 February 1910 ) was a German princess .
Morgan W. Phillips ( 1943 - -1996 ) was an American founder of the field of architectural conservation .
Neophytos Vamvas ( Greek : Νεόφυτος Βάμβας ; 1770 -- 9 January 1856 ) was a Greek cleric and educator of the 19th century .
Andrew Keller FRS(22 August 1925 -- 7 February 1999 ) was a British polymer scientist .
Louise Fawcett ( 1904 − 1990 ) was a British javelin and discus thrower .
Adolf Ferdinand Weinhold ( 19 May 1841 -- 1 July 1917 ) was a German chemist , physician and inventor .
The first Henry , Duke of Cornwall ( 1 January -- 23 February 1511 ) was the second oldest child and heir apparent of King Henry VIII of England , born by Catherine of Aragon .
Gregorio Walerstein Weinstock ( 22 February 1913 -- 24 January 2002 ) was a Mexican film producer and screenwriter of Jewish descent .
Henry Cullen FRSE FRCPE ( c.1758 - -1790 ) was a Scottish physician .
Clarence Elliot Coe ( 1873 - -1943 ) , known as Clarence E. Coe , was one of the first settlers and farmers in Palms , California , and a member of the Los Angeles Police Commission from 1929 to 1931 and of the Los Angeles City Council from 1931 to 1933 .
Emperor Fei of Northern Qi ( ( 北)齊廢帝 ) ( 545 - -561 ) , personal name Gao Yin ( 高殷 ) , courtesy name Zhengdao ( 正道 ) , posthumously Prince Mindao of Ji'nan ( 濟南閔悼王 ) , was briefly an emperor of the Northern Qi .
Tom Iredale ( 24 March 1880 -- 12 April 1972 ) was an English - born ornithologist and malacologist who had a long association with Australia , where he lived for most of his life .
Nicholas Devine ( born 1739 ? - May 29 , 1830 ) , Co. Cavan , Ireland ( also spelt Divine ) was superintendent of convicts for Newtown , New South Wales .
Oruno Lara ( 1879 - 1924 ) was a Guadeloupean poet , author and historian born in Guadeloupe not to be confused with his grandson Dr. Oruno D. Lara , also a historian .
Henry Throop Stanton ( 1834 - -1899 ) was an American poet , best known for his poem `` The Moneyless Man '' .
Zwide kaLanga ( 1758 - -1825 ) was the King of the Ndwandwe ( Nxumalo ) nation from about 1805 to around 1820 .
Bob Benge ( c. 1762 - -1794 ) , also known as `` Captain Benge '' ( or `` The Bench '' to frontiersmen ) , was one of the most feared Cherokee leaders on the frontier during the Cherokee--
Hoàng Châu Ký ( xã Cẩm Kim , Hội An , Quảng Nam , 1921 - Đà Nẵng 31 January 2008 ) was a Vietnamese professor of literature and playwright .
Racho Petrov Stoyanov ( Bulgarian : Рачо Петров Стоянов ) ( 3 March 1861 -- 22 January 1942 ) was a leading Bulgarian general and politician .
Margot Pardoe ( 8 August 1902 -- 5 January 1996 ) was a children 's author whose career spanned over 20 years from the late 1930s to the early 1960s .
Sara Chacón Zúñiga , or `` Sarita '' Chacón Zúñiga ( Guayaquil , June 1914 -- New York , January 1998 ) became the first winner of the Miss Ecuador title , awarded on February 11 , 1930 .
John Leak Springston `` Oo ne qua ti '' ( 1844 - -1929 ) , a Cherokee , is best known as an Indian activist ; during his life he was a Cherokee Interpreter , Editor , Lawyer , and Keetoowah Revivalist .
James Francis McMillan ( 10 April 1948 -- 22 February 2010 ) was a Scottish historian and author , head of the History Department of Strathclyde University , a fellow of the Royal Society of Edinburgh and Professor of History at Edinburgh University .
Esther Howland ( 1828 - -1904 ) was an artist and businesswoman who was responsible for popularizing Valentine 's Day greeting cards in America .
Marius Aventicensis or , popularly , Marius of Avenches ( 532 -- 31 December 596 ) was the Bishop of Aventicum ( modern Avenches ) from 574 , remembered for his terse chronicle .
Patrick Whitefield ( born Patrick R. Vickers , 11 February 1949 -- 27 February 2015 ) was a British permaculture teacher , designer , author , and consulting editor for Permaculture Magazine .
Gabinius Barbarus Pompeianus ( died in Rome , February 409 ) was a politician of the Western Roman Empire , praefectus urbi of Rome during the first siege of Alaric I.
Nikephoros II Orsini - Doukas ( Greek : Νικηφόρος Β΄ Δούκας , Nikēphoros II Doukas ) , was the ruler of Epirus from 1335 to 1338 and from 1356 until his death in 1359 .
Kåre Norum ( 14 November 1907 -- 2 August 1981 ) was a Norwegian educator and resistance member .
Ellis Ashton ( born 1 December 1919 - 31 October 1985 ) , MBE , was an English comedian and theatre historian .
Debra Holloway ( January 23 , 1955 -- 2011 ) is a former U.S. Olympian in taekwondo .
John Scrope , 4th Baron Scrope of Masham ( c.1388 -- 15 November 1455 ) was an English peer , Privy Councillor and Treasurer of England .
Maciej Dunal ( 20 December 1953 -- 8 January 2014 ) was a Polish actor and singer .
Ralph Brideoake ( 1612/13 - -1678 ) was an English clergyman , who became Bishop of Chichester .
Marsilius of Padua ( Italian Marsilio or Marsiglio da Padova ; born Marsilio dei Mainardini or Marsilio Mainardini , c. 1275 -- c. 1342 ) was an Italian scholar , trained in medicine who practiced a variety of professions .
Gao Kelin ( Chinese : 高克林 ) ( March 11 , 1907 -- June 18 , 2001 ) original name Gao Wenmin ( Chinese : 高文敏 ) , was a People 's Republic of China politician .
Eusebius Fermendžin ( also Fermendzhin , Fermendjin ; Bulgarian : Евсевий , Еузебий , Еусебий , or Еусебиус Ферменджин ) ( 21 September 1845 -- 25 June 1897 ) was an Austro - Hungarian high - ranking Roman Catholic cleric , Franciscan friar and academic of Banat Bulgarian origin .
James Judson Harmon ( 21 April 1933 -- 16 February 2010 ) , better known as Jim Harmon , was an American short story author and popular culture historian who wrote extensively about the Golden Age of Radio .
Robert Garnock ( c. 1660 -- 1681 ) was a Scottish covenanter .
Rev. Thomas Huyck DCL ( died 1575 ) was Chancellor of the Diocese of London for 13 years and one of the founding fellows of Jesus College , Oxford .
Ervin Cseh ( 23 March 1838 -- 12 June 1918 ) was a Hungarian politician from Slavonia , who served as Minister without portfolio of Croatian Affairs twice : between 1898 - -1903 and between 1903 - -1905 .
Hugo Hirst , 1st Baron Hirst ( 26 November 1863 -- 22 January 1943 ) , known as Sir Hugo Hirst , Bt , between 1925 and 1934 , was a German - born British industrialist .
Thomas Cautley Newby ( 1797/1798 -- 1882 ) was an English publisher and printer based in London .
Thomas Christopher Banks ( 1765 - -1854 ) , who for a while styled himself by the bogus title `` Sir T.C. Banks , Baronet of Nova Scotia '' was a British genealogist and lawyer .
John Stewart Collis ( 1900 - -1984 ) was a British biographer , rural author , and pioneer of the ecology movement .
Abdulcelil Levni or Abdulcelil Çelebi ( died 1732 ) was an Ottoman court painter and miniaturist .
William Bulfin ( 1864 - -1910 ) was the fourth son in a family of nine boys and one girl , the children of William Bulfin , of Derrinlough , Birr , County Offaly , Ireland , and Ellen Grogan of Croghan , County Offaly .
Antonín Heveroch ( 19 January 1869 -- 2 March 1927 ) was a Czech psychiatrist and neurologist .
Murchad mac Diarmato ( died 715 ) , called Murchad Midi ( Murchad of Meath ) , was an Irish king .
Haidara Kontorfilli ( born 1890 - 1931 ) was a Sierra Leonean charismatic Islamic religious reformer and an anti - colonialist from the Mandingo ethnic group who championed the cause of the rural masses in Kambia in the Northern Province of Sierra Leone .
Josef Jennewein ( 21 November 1919 -- 26 July 1943 ) was a German alpine skier and world champion .
Mark Duncan de Cérisantis ( died 1648 ) , was the son of an Scott who was born in France and became a French and Swiss diplomat , before becoming secretary to Henry II , Duke of Guise .
James Edmund Vincent ( 1857 - -1909 ) was a Welsh barrister , known as a journalist and author .
Everett Klipp ( 1926 - 2011 ) was known as the `` Babe Ruth '' of the Chicago Board of Trade , and a mentor to Mark Spitznagel .
Sir Vincent Corbet , 1st Baronet ( 13 June 1617 -- 1656 ) was an English lawyer and politician who sat for Shropshire in the House of Commons in the Short Parliament of 1640 .
Johann von Kelle ( March 15 , 1828 in Regensburg -- January 30 , 1909 in Prague ) was a German philologist who studied the German language .
Matthias Knutzen ( also : Knuzen , Knutsen ) ( 1646 -- after 1674 ) was a German - languaged critic of religion and the author of three atheistic pamphlets .
Alejo Vera y Estaca ( 14 July 1834 , Viñuelas - 4 February 1923 , Madrid ) was a Spanish painter in the Romantic style who specialized in history painting .
John Alexander Voules Brown ( 8 January 1852 - 14 March 1945 ) was a South Australian businessman who represented the South Australian House of Assembly multi - member seat of Northern Territory from 1910 to 1911 for the Liberal Union .
John Silly ( c 1621 - 1672 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1659 and 1660 .
Iain Fraoch MacDonald ( died 1368 ) was a younger son of Angus Og of Islay , and founder of Clan MacDonald of Glencoe .
After years of heartbreak , Hannah Arnold died on August 15 , 1758 .
Henri Temianka ( 19 November 1906 -- 7 November 1992 ) was a virtuoso violinist , conductor , author and music educator .
Louis - Philippe Crépin ( 1772 - -1851 ) was a French naval painter , one of the first Peintres de la Marine .
Sir Francis Bigod ( 4 October 1507 -- 2 June 1537 ) was the leader of Bigod 's Rebellion .
Aaron Sherritt ( 1855 - 26 June 1880 ) was an associate of the gang of outlaws led by Ned Kelly .
Tomás Bobadilla y Briones ( 30 March 1785 -- 21 December 1871 ) was a Dominican writer , intellectual and politician .
Jože Privšek ( 19 March 1937 -- 11 June 1998 ) , who also presented himself with the pseudonyms Jeff Conway and Simon Gale , was one of the most acclaimed Slovene jazz and pop musicians .
William Arthur Sewell ( 9 August 1903 -- 19 April 1972 ) was a university professor of English .
Thomas West , 8th Baron De La Warr and 5th Baron West , KB , KG ( c.1457 -- 11 October 1525 ) was a courtier and military commander during the reigns of Henry VII and Henry VIII .
Joseph Luker ( c1765 - 1803 ) was a Sydney foot police officer who was recorded as the first police officer to be killed on duty in Australia .
George Llewellyn Christian ( April 13 , 1841 -- 1924 ) was a Confederate soldier in the American Civil War who later became a judge and city councilman in Richmond , Virginia .
Wayland Drew ( 1932 - -1998 ) was a writer born in Oshawa , Ontario .
Pier Francesco Silvani ( 1620 - -1685 ) was an Italian architect and designer , active during the Baroque period , in Florence and other sites in Tuscany .
Henri van der Haert / Hendrik van der Haert / Henri Anne Victoria van der Haert ( 1790 - -1846 ) was a Belgian portrait painter , sculptor , illustrator and engraver .
Henry Bromley , 1st Baron Montfort ( 20 August 1705 -- 1 January 1755 ) , was a British landowner and politician .
Maria Brizzi Giorgi ( 7 August 1775 -- 7 January 1812 in Bologna ) was an Italian organist , composer and pianist noted for her improvisational ability .
Sir John Pirie , 1st Baronet ( 1781 -- 26 February 1851 ) , was a British shipbroker and Lord Mayor of London .
John Luis Shaw ( 1870 - -1952 ) was a Seventh - day Adventist missionary , educator , and treasurer .
Gaetano Orsolini ( 7 March 1884 -- July 1954 ) was an Italian sculptor , medallist and engraver .
Peter Bridgwater ( 7 March 1935 -- 21 June 2005 ) was the first president of the San Jose Clash -- later known as the San Jose Earthquakes--
Leonard Wilson Forster ( 30 March 1913 -- 18 April 1997 ) was Professor of German at University College London , and Schröder Professor of German at the University of Cambridge .
Peter Campbell Scarlett CB , DL ( 27 November 1804 -- 15 July 1881 ) , styled The Honourable from 1830 , was a British diplomat .
Asen Gavrilov ( Bulgarian : Асен Гаврилов ; 10 June 1926 - 21 May 2006 ) was a famous Bulgarian ballet dancer and choreographer .
Hans Kristian Eriksen ( 2 April 1933 -- 8 June 2014 ) was a Norwegian non - fiction writer , magazine editor , novelist and short story writer .
George Ratcliffe Woodward ( 27 December 1848 -- 3 March 1934 ) was an English Anglican priest who wrote mostly religious verse , both original and translated from ancient authors .
Francis Sempill ( 1616 ? -- March 1682 ) was a son of Robert Sempill the younger .
Rudolf of Żagań ( Polish : Rudolf żagański ) ( ca . 1418 -- 18 September 1454 ) was a Duke of Żagań - Przewóz since 1439 ( with his brothers as co - rulers until 1449 ) , from 1449 Duke of Żagań ( as co - ruler of his older brother ) .
Alessandro Arrigoni ( Barzio , Province of Como , 1764 - 1819 ) was an Italian painter , mainly depicting still lifes with flowers .
John Haighton MD , FRS ( c. 1755 -- 23 March 1823 ) , was an English physician and physiologist .
Emma Gramatica ( 25 October 1874 -- 8 November 1965 ) , was an Italian stage and film actress .
Frederic Whitaker ( 1891 - 1980 ) was an award - winning American designer , painter and author .
Stephen Bekassy , born Istavan Bekassy in Nyíregyháza , ( 1907 - -1995 ) , was a Hungarian born American film actor .
Sir John Maunsell ( c. 1190/1195 -- 1265 ) , also Sir John Mansel , Provost of Beverley , was king 's clerk , and a judge .
Maria Bergamas ( Italian pronunciation : ( maˈriːa berɡaˈmas ) ; 1867 - -1952 ) was an Italian woman who was chosen to represent all Italian mothers who had had lost a son during World War I not knowing where he was buried .
Francis M. Bunce ( 25 December 1836 -- 19 October 1901 ) was a rear admiral of the United States Navy who distinguished himself as a junior officer during the American Civil War ( 1861 - -65 ) .
Professor Man Mohan Singh Ahuja , better known as M. M. S. Ahuja ( 1929 -- 12 July 1998 ) was famous Indian Physician and Endocrinologist .
Priya Rajvansh ( 1937 -- 27 March 2000 ) , born Vera Sunder Singh , was an Indian film actress , who is known for her performance in films like , Heer Raanjha ( 1970 ) and Hanste Zakhm ( 1973 ) , amongst a handful of films she did during her career .
Henry Haight ( 1820 - -1869 ) was an American exchange banker and pioneer .
Sir John Ernley ( or Ernle ) ( 1464 -- 22 April 1520 ) was a British justice .
Sir Arthur Haselrig , 2nd Baronet ( 1601 -- 7 January 1661 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1640 and 1659 .
Frank Bottrill ( 1 April 1871 -- 7 January 1953 ) was an Australian blacksmith and inventor , known for his giant `` Big Lizzie '' traction engine , thought to be at one time the largest in the world .
Anthony Bull CBE CStJ ( 18 July 1908 -- 23 December 2004 ) was a British transport engineer and was president of the Institute of Transport .
Jules Petiet ( 5 August 1813 -- 29 January 1871 ) was a French mechanical engineer who worked on the early development of the French railway network .
Hua Tianyou ( Chinese : 滑田友 ; 1901 - -1986 ) , courtesy name Shunqing ( 舜卿 ) , was a Chinese artist and a pioneer of the field of sculpture in modern China .
Myron Leskiw ( 1909 - -1997 ) was born in Pidtarkiv , Russian Empire in 1909 and emigrated to the United States in 1930 .
Theodore Spencer ( 1902 - -1949 ) was an American poet and academic .
Della Moore ( 1880 - 1926 ? ) , also known as Annie Rogers or Maude Williams , was a woman working as a prostitute during the closing years of the Old West , best known as being the girlfriend of outlaw Harvey Logan ( Kid Curry ) , who rode with Butch Cassidy 's Wild Bunch gang .
James Arthurs ( 4 October 1866 -- 7 October 1937 ) was a Canadian senator for the Conservative party , representing the province of Ontario .
Enrico Forcella Pelliccioni ( October 18 , 1907 -- October 25 , 1989 ) was a Venezuelan shooter .
William Ewart Astill ( 1 March 1888 , Ratby , Leicestershire , England -- 10 February 1948 , Stoneygate , Leicester , England ) was , along with George Geary , the mainstay of the Leicestershire team from 1922 to about 1935 .
Ralph Wightman ( 26 July 1901 -- 28 May 1971 ) was an English lecturer , journalist , author , and radio and television broadcaster .
Rolf Hachmann ( 19 June 1917 -- 5 June 2014 ) was a German archaeologist who specialized in pre- and protohistory .
George Ishiyama ( 1914 - -2003 ) was a Japanese - American businessman who was president of Alaska Pulp Corporation ( APC ) in Sitka , Alaska between 1983 and 2003 .
Dave Bell ( 24 December 1909 -- 16 April 1986 ) was a Scottish professional footballer .
Rodrigo Alfonso de León ( 1200s-1268 ) was a Spanish nobleman , Lord of Alexer .
Pierce Dod FRS , FRCP ( 1683 - -1754 ) was a British physician and opponent of smallpox inoculation .
Hugh Carleton , 1st Viscount Carleton PC ( I ) SL ( 11 September 1739 -- 25 February 1826 ) , was an Irish judge .
Andrea Adami da Bolsena ( 30 November 1663 -- 22 July 1742 ) was an Italian castrato , musician later secretary to Cardinal Ottoboni .
Esther Szekeres ( Hungarian : Klein Eszter ; 20 February 1910 -- 28 August 2005 ) was a Hungarian--
Eustațiu Stoenescu ( Craiova , 1884-New York , 1957 ) was a Romanian painter principally known for his portraiture .
Andreas von Auersperg , Lord of Schönberg und Seisenberg ( Slovene : Andrej Turjaški ; Croatian and Bosnian : Andrija Auersperg ) ( 9 April 1556 -- 5 September 1593 ) was a Carniolan noble and leader of the defending forces at the Battle of Sisak in 1593 .
Sir Adam de Gurdon or Gordon ( died 1305 ) , was an English knight who rebelled against King Henry III and fought in single combat against the Prince Edward , the king 's son and the future King Edward I. They were reconciled and he served Edward faithfully from then on .
Isabel Leigh ( c. 1495/97 or 1506 -- 16 Feb 1573 ) was a lady - in - waiting during the reign of her younger half - sister , Catherine Howard , fifth wife and Queen Consort to Henry VIII .
Darrel Chapman died of cancer on 10 October 1992 , aged 55 .
Gustave Pellet ( 1859 - -1919 ) was a French publisher of art . He is best known for publishing prints of erotic artworks by Henri de Toulouse - Lautrec and Louis Legrand .
John Leigh Philips ( 1761 - -1814 ) , was a manufacturer in Manchester , England .
Saado Ali Warsame ( Somali : Saado Cali Warsame , Arabic : سادو علي ورسمه‎ ) ( b. 1950 - -d . 23 July 2014 ) was a Somali - American singer - songwriter and politician .
Louis Ferrari ( Borgo Val di Taro ( Parma ) 1910 - -1988 ) was an Italian musette accordionist and composer who was active in France beginning in the 1930s .
Alexander Nowell ( c. 1517 -- 13 February 1602 ) was an English Protestant theologian and clergyman .
Xenophon Paionidis ( Greek : Ξενοφών Παιονίδης ; 1863 - 1933 ) was a Greek architect from Chalkidiki ( Fourka ) , notable for his works in the city of Thessaloniki .
Louis Rollet ( 6e arrondissement , Paris , 3 May 1895 - Saché , 1988 ) was a French painter of the school of `` peintres voyageurs '' of the early 20th Century .
Yehuda Ben - Haim ( 29 September 1955 -- 5 March 2012 ) was an Israeli boxer .
Nolfo da Montefeltro ( born Sighinolfo ; c. 1290 -- 1364 ) was count of Montefeltro from 1323 to 1360 .
Ernie Sheil ( 2 May 1906 -- 26 December 1970 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton and Hawthorn in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Eric Anundsson or Eymundsson ( died 882 ) was a Swedish king who ruled during the 9th century .
Jean - Jacques Meyer ( 1804 - -1877 ) was a French engineer , noted for his work with steam engines and steam locomotives .
Hugh Cecil Asterley ( born 10 May 1902 - 1973 ) was a British author and colonial administrator , who wrote crime and mystery stories and novels , usually with a south - east Asian setting , as H. C. Asterley .
Louis Fischer ( 29 February 1896 -- 15 January 1970 ) was a Jewish - American journalist .
Francis Chenevix Trench ( 1805 - -1886 ) was an English divine and author .
Roy Schuiten ( 16 December 1950 -- 19 September 2006 ) was a Dutch track and road racing cyclist .
Arthur Brian Sellers ( 5 March 1907 -- 20 February 1981 ) was an English amateur first - class cricketer , who played in 334 first - class matches for Yorkshire County Cricket Club between 1932 and 1948 , and later became a prominent administrator at the club .
August Hoch ( 1868 - -1919 ) was the third director of the New York State Psychiatric Institute in New York City .
Bhai Mardana Ji ( Punjabi : ਭਾਈ ਮਰਦਾਨਾ ) ( 1459 - -1534 ) was the first follower and longtime companion of Guru Nanak Dev , the founder of Sikhism .
Prince Ivan Andreyevich Khovansky ( Russian : Иван Андреевич Хованский ) ( died 1621 ) was a Russian boyar , Voyevoda of Novgorod , and Namestnik of Ryazan .
Antun Mavrak ( 1899 - 1938 ) was a Croatian revolutionary and top functionary of the Communist Party of Yugoslavia ( KPJ ) .
Joanna of Flanders ( c. 1295 -- September 1374 ) was Duchess of Brittany by her marriage to John of Montfort .
Elsie Suddaby ( 1893 - 1980 ) was a leading British lyric soprano of the years between World War I and World War II . She was born in Leeds , a first cousin once removed to the organist and composer , Francis Jackson .
Jean Overton Fuller ( 7 March 1915 -- 8 April 2009 ) was a British author best known for her book Madeleine , the story of Noor Inayat Khan , an Allied SOE agent during the Second World War ..
Raúl Gándara Cartagena ( 1895 - -1989 ) was fire chief in Ponce , Puerto Rico , and the first and longest - serving Commonwealth of Puerto Rico fire chief .
Gustavo Pittaluga ( 1876 in Florence , Italy -- 1956 in Havana , Cuba ) was an Italian doctor and biologist .
Jefferson Lowndes ( 1858 - 1893 ) was an English rower who won the Diamond Challenge Sculls at Henley Royal Regatta five times and who also won the Wingfield Sculls twice .
Giovanni Henrico Albicastro was the italianized name of Bavarian composer Johann Heinrich von Weissenburg ( c. 1660 -- 26 January 1730 ) , a talented amateur musician who published his compositions pseudonymously .
Travers Vale ( 31 January 1865 -- 10 January 1927 ) was an English - born silent film director .
Karl Ewald Maximilian Burret , commonly known as Max Burret ( 6 June 1883 -- 19 September 1964 ) was a German botanist .
Captain Emma Churchill ( 1862 -- 16 May 1957 ) was the founder of The Salvation Army in Newfoundland .
Reverend Laurence George Bomford ( 1847 -- 1926 ) was an English painter , and clergyman .
Frederik Jacobsen ( 12 September 1876 -- 4 September 1922 ) , was a Danish actor .
Friedrich Harms ( 24 October 1819 -- 5 April 1880 ) was a German realist philosopher , much influenced by Fichte .
Theophilus Aneurin Rees ( 9 April 1858 - 11 September 1932 ) was a Welsh rugby union forward who represented Llandovery College at club level .
Miguel Serrano ( 10 September 1917 -- 28 February 2009 ) was a Chilean diplomat , journalist and author of poetry , books on spiritual questing and Esoteric Hitlerism .
Patrick Murdoch ( died 1774 ) was an author , publisher and mathematician , who published a biography of poet James Thomson , and also An account of Sir Isaac Newton 's philosophical discoveries by Colin MacLaurin .
Maury Gertsman ( 17 April 1907 -- 13 December 1999 ) was a senior - ranked cinematographer at Universal Pictures from the mid-1940s through the mid-1950s .
William Morris Colles ( 23 November 1865 -- 11 October 1926 , Slindon ) was an English literary agent , the founder and managing director of The Authors ' Syndicate , Ltd. William Morris Colles was the son of Rev. William Morris Colles , Vicar of Melton Mowbray .
Colonel John Anstruther - Thomson of Charleton ( 15 April 1776 -- 10 April 1833 ) was a Scottish nobleman and Colonel of the Royal Fifeshire Yeomanry Cavalry .
On 20 August 1972 , in Ensenada , Baja California , Mexico , one of Ervil 's followers Daniel Jordan ( who was married to one of their nieces ) shot Joel LeBaron in the head while Joel 's young son was asleep in a car in the driveway .
Arcangelo Resani ( 1670 - -1740 ) was an Italian painter of the Baroque period .
Jakub Plichta ( died 7 February 1407 ) was a Polish Catholic priest and the second bishop of Wilno .
George Estye ( 1566 - -1601 ) was an English clergyman .
George Fisk Comfort ( September 20 , 1833 -- May 5 , 1910 ) was a 19th - century American scholar and art exponent , and founder of both the Metropolitan Museum of Art , NY , and Everson Museum of Art , Syracuse , NY .
Jimmy Clements ( c. 1847 -- 28 August 1927 ) was an Aboriginal elder from the Wiradjuri tribe in Australia , and was present at the Opening of the Provisional Parliament House in Canberra on 9 May 1927 .
Kurt von Trojan ( born Vienna , Austria , 1937 22 March 2006 ) was an Australian journalist and science fiction author .
Alv Knutsson ( c. 1420 - -1496 ) was a Norwegian nobleman who descended on his father 's side from the influential and wealthy Swedish Tre Rosor noble family .
Henry Clutterbuck M.D. ( 1767 - -1856 ) was an English medical writer .
Thomas Holenstein ( 7 February 1896 -- 31 October 1962 ) was a Swiss politician and member of the Swiss Federal Council ( 1955 - -1959 ) .
Yashwant Dinkar Pendharkar ( यशवंत दिनकर पेंढरकर ) ( 9 March 1899 -- 1985 ) was a Marathi poet from Maharashtra , India .
Arthur Tatham ( 1808 - -1874 ) , was a member of the Shoreham Ancients , a group of followers of William Blake .
Heinrich Michael Neustetter ( 14 June 1874 , Vienna- 13 February 1958 Offenhausen ) was an Austrian entomologist who specialised in Lepidoptera .
Scott Meredith , born Arthur Scott Feldman ( 1923 , New York City , NY -- 1993 , Manhasset , NY ) was a prominent American literary agent , and founder of the Scott Meredith Literary Agency .
Infante Carlos of Portugal ( Carlos João Manuel Alexandre ; Portuguese pronunciation : ( ˈkaɾluʃ ) ; English : Charles ; Lisbon , May 2 , 1716 -- Lisbon , 1 April 1736 ) was a Portuguese infante ( prince ) , the fourth child of King John V and his wife Mary Anne of Austria .
Indrit Cara ( also known as Ushtar Kavaja ; 11 July 1971 -- 31 March 1999 ) was an Albanian activist volunteer and soldier who died fighting during the Kosovo War .
Andrew Wilkinson ( 1697 - -1784 ) was a British politician and racehorse breeder .
Sir John Tudor Walters PC ( 1868 -- 16 July 1933 ) , was a British architect , surveyor and Liberal politician .
Robert Armour ( 1781 - -1857 ) was a Canadian businessman , militia officer , and office holder .
Wilhelm Heinrich Funk ( 1866 - -1949 ) was a German - American portrait painter .
Len Metherell ( 17 November 1908 - 30 October 1992 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Geelong in the VFL during the 1930s .
Zalman Ben - Ya'akov ( Hebrew : זלמן בן - יעקב‎ , born 1897 , died 2 March 1959 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for Agudat Yisrael and the Religious Torah Front between 1953 and 1959 .
Colonel William Francis Frederick Waller VC ( 20 August 1839 -- 29 January 1885 ) was a recipient of the Victoria Cross , the highest and most prestigious award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces .
Laurie Ayton , Snr ( 1884 - -1962 ) was a Scottish golfer .
Aristeidis Chasapidis ( Greek : Αριστείδης Χασαπίδης , 1875 - -1941 ) was a Greek army officer who reached the rank of Lieutenant General and served as Chief of the Hellenic Army General Staff in 1935 - -36 .
Annette Mills ( 1894 -- 10 January 1955 ) was an English actress , dancer and broadcaster .
Catterina Vizzani , alias Giovanni Bordoni ( 1719 - 1743 ) , was an Italian woman who disguised herself as a man .
Robert Home ( 1752 - -1834 ) was a British oil portrait painter who travelled to the Indian subcontinent in 1791 .
Oswald Hope Robertson ( 2 June 1886 -- 23 March 1966 ) was an English - born medical scientist who pioneered the idea of blood banks in the `` blood depots '' he established in 1917 during service in France with the US Army Medical Corps .
Giovanna Garzoni ( 1600 - 1670 ) was an Italian painter who was prominent in Europe during the Baroque period .
Irene E. Parmelee , her surname also spelled Parmely ( 1847 -- 1934 ) , was an American painter and portrait artist .
Thomas Houston , ( c1777- 27 December 1803 ) was a Tyneside based poet / songwriter , who , according to the information given by W & T Fordyce ( publishers ) on page 233 in The Tyne Songster published in 1840 , has the poem or song `` Mary Drew '' attributed to his name .
James Westoll DL ( 26 July 1918 -- 7 February 1999 ) , known as Tim Westoll , was an English barrister , country landowner , politician , ornithologist , and racehorse owner .
Joseph Mertens ( 17 January 1921 at Tienen -- 1 July 2007 at Wezembeek , Belgium ) was an accomplished 20th century Belgian archaeologist , known for his excavations of Alba Fucens and Herdonia .
Phan Huy Chú ( 1782 - -1840 ) was a Vietnamese mandarin administrator , scholar and historian .
Đuro Jakčin ( 22 February 1889 - 16 February 1944 ) was a Croatian naval commander and first commander of Croatian Navy .
Gertrude of Merania ( 1185 -- 28 September 1213 ) was Queen of Hungary as the first wife of Andrew II from 1205 until her assassination .
William Lee Hankey ( 1869 - -1952 ) RWS , RI , ROI , RE , NS was a British painter and book illustrator .
Prince Ivane Machabeli ( Georgian : ივანე მაჩაბელი ) ( January 28 , 1854 -- c. 1898 ) was a Georgian writer , translator , publicist , public figure , active member of the National - Liberation Movement , and a founder of the new Georgian literary language .
Louis of Nassau , Lord of De Lek and Beverweerd ( 1602 -- 28 February 1665 ) was a Dutch soldier .
Samia Gamal ( Arabic : سامية جمال‎ , born as Zaynab Ibrahim Mahfuz , 5 March 1924 -- 1 December 1994 ) was an Egyptian belly dancer and film actress .
William Michael Duane ( 1915 - -1997 ) was a British teacher known for his progressive educational views , his belief in inclusivity and a multi - racial approach , his encouragement of informal relationships between staff and pupils and his opposition to corporal punishment .
Elmer Rosenberg ( 1885 -- April 1951 ) was an American politician and labor leader from New York .
Saul Rosenzweig ( 1907 - -2004 ) was an American psychologist and therapist .
Norm Henderson ( 7 March 1901 -- 7 January 1968 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
James Crosbie Smith ( 26 September 1894 - -19 February 1980 ) was an English cricketer who played 16 first - class matches for Worcestershire in the 1920s .
Aleksander Kazimierz Sapieha ( 13 May 1624 -- 22 May 1671 ) was a Polish nobleman and bishop of Samogitia since 1660 and Wilno since 1667 .
Sher Zaman Taizi ( 3 November 1931 -- 22 December 2009 ) was Pashtun writer , poet , intellectual and journalist from Pakistan .
Godfrey Haga ( born in Isingen , Duchy of Württemberg , 30 November 1745 ; died in Philadelphia , Pennsylvania , 5 February 1825 ) was a United States merchant , politician and philanthropist .
Piet van Reenen born ( 17 January 1909 -- 8 June 1969 ) was a Dutch former professional footballer who was a prolific goalscorer at Ajax .
John T. Garner ( 1809 - -1888 ) was a soldier in the Texas Army during the Texas Revolution , noted for a daring action during the Battle of San Jacinto that helped seal the decisive Texian victory .
Charles Oswald Lelean ( O.B.E ) was born in 1867 in Tasmania , Australia and died at the age of 72 on 14 September 1942 .
Bernard Benjamin ( 8 March 1910 -- 15 May 2002 ) was a noted British health statistician , actuary and demographer .
Juan de Dios Castillo González ( 31 January 1951 -- 1 May 2014 ) was a Mexican footballer and coach , last with C.D. Motagua of Liga Nacional de Fútbol de Honduras , the top tier of the league .
Neil Meitzler ( 1930 - -2009 ) was an American painter , well known in the Pacific Northwest for his landscapes and scenes of nature , rendered in a distinctive , modern style .
Jacob J. Rabinowitz ( 1899 - 1960 ) was a professor of law , notable for his English translation of one of the Mishneh Torah books .
Sir George Chudleigh , 1st Baronet ( c. 1578 -- 15 January 1658 ) of Ashton , Devon , was an English landowner and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1601 and 1625 .
Catharni Stern ( 22 August 1925 -- 16 June 2015 ) was an English sculptor and art teacher .
Markku Peltola ( 12 July 1956 -- 31 December 2007 ) was a Finnish actor and musician .
Flaianus ( 883 - -885 ) was a medieval Galician clergyman .
Albert III , Prince of Anhalt - Zerbst ( died ca . 1 August 1359 ) was a German prince of the House of Ascania and ruler of the principality of Anhalt - Zerbst .
Baron Johann Nepomuk von Kutschera ( born 1766 in Prague , died 20 April 1832 in Vienna ) was an Austrian General , who served as Field Marshal Lieutenant from 1813 and as Feldzeugmeister in 1832 .
Henry Blosse Lynch ( 1807 - -1873 ) was an Anglo - Irish explorer .
Ambrose Jones ( died 15 December 1678 ) was a Welsh - Irish cleric who served as Anglican Bishop of Kildare 1667 - 8 .
Marretje Arents ( c. 1712 - -28 June 1748 Amsterdam ) , known as Mat van den Nieuwendijk , and het limoenwijf ( i.e. the limewoman ) , was a Dutch fishwife and rebellion leader , sentenced to death as one of the three instigators and leaders responsible for the so - called Pachter riots of 1748 .
Sir Thomas Spert ( spelled in some records as Pert ) ( died December 1541 ) was a mariner who reached the rank of vice admiral in service to King Henry VIII of England .
Claus Helberg ( 31 January 1919 -- 6 March 2003 ) was a Norwegian resistance fighter and mountain guide .
Daniel Blain , M.D. ( 1898 - -1981 ) was an American physician and was the first Medical Director of the American Psychiatric Association ( APA ) , the first professional medical society founded in the United States in 1844 .
Lakshman Singh Jangpangi died at Haldwani , aged 71 , in 1976 .
Anna Leibbrand ( 2 May 1902 -- 24 July 1972 ) was a left - wing German political activist and writer .
Maurice Cook ( 10 December 1931 -- 31 December 2006 ) was an English professional association footballer , and also an amateur cricketer for Hertfordshire .
Allison Sudradjat died in the crash of Garuda Indonesia Flight 200 on 7 March 2007 .
Elsie Ward ( also known as Elsie Ward Hering ) ( 1872 or 1874 -- 1923 ) was an American sculptor born in Fayette , Missouri .
Josephine Powell ( 15 May 1919 -- 19 January 2007 ) was an American photographer and a collector of ethnographic objects .
Monseigneur Jean Cadilhac ( 1931 -- 27 October 1999 ) was the Bishop of Nimes , France .
Raymond Pearl ( 3 June 1879 -- 17 November 1940 ) was an American biologist , regarded as one of the founders of biogerontology .
Eadberht of Lindisfarne ( died 6 May 698 ) , also known as Saint Eadberht , was Bishop of Lindisfarne , England , from 688 until 698 .
Sir Gordon Shattock ( born 12 May 1928 , Exeter -- died 10 April 2010 ) was a British Conservative Party 's Western - area Chairman , who survived the 1984 Brighton bombing , which claimed the life of his first wife , Jeanne .
Howard Squadron ( born 1926 in the Bronx , New York ; died 2001 ) was senior partner in the law firm Squadron Ellenoff Plesent & Sheinfeld with powerful clients such as Rupert Murdoch , Playboy magazine , Helmsley - Spear management company , mortgage brokers , and developers .
Jim Doman ( April 8 , 1949 -- May 1992 ) was an American professional poker player who won two World Series of Poker bracelets .
Sam Eig ( c. 1899 -- 1982 ) was an American real estate developer active in the Washington D.C. metropolitan area .
Sir Edward Poole ( 1617 -- 1673 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1640 and 1673 .
Aaron Shearer ( 6 September 1919 -- 21 April 2008 ) was an American classical guitarist known primarily as a pedagogue .
Salvi Castellucci ( 1608 - -1672 ) was an Italian painter of the Baroque period , active mainly in Arezzo .
Antonia of Württemberg ( 24 March 1613 -- 1 October 1679 ) was a princess of the Duchy of Württemberg , as well as a literary figure , patroness , and Christian Kabbalist .
Jean - Théodore Laurent ( 6 July 1804 - 20 February 1884 ) was the Apostolic Vicar of Luxembourg from 1841 to 1856 .
Princess Elisabeth Vilma Lwoff - Parlaghy ( 15 April 1863 - 28 August 1923 ) was a Hungarian - born portrait painter who worked in Germany and the United States .
Eleanor Davies - Colley FRCS ( 21 August 1874 ; Petworth , Sussex -- 10 December 1934 ; London ) was a British surgeon .
Geoffrey de Muschamp ( died 6 October 1208 ) was a medieval Bishop of Coventry .
Terence Fisher ( 23 February 1904 -- 18 June 1980 ) was a British film director who worked for Hammer Films .
Iver Hesselberg ( 4 November 1762 -- 26 January 1838 ) was a Norwegian businessman who served as a representative at the Norwegian Constitutional Assembly .
Rosanna Schiaffino ( 25 November 1939 -- 17 October 2009 ) was an Italian film actress .
Tsangnyön Heruka ( Tibetan : གཙང་སྨྱོན་ཧེ་རུ་ཀ་ , Wylie : gtsang smyon He ru ka `` The Madman Heruka from Tsang '' , 1452 - 1507 ) , was an author and a master of the Kagyu school of Tibetan Buddhism .
Mirtha Dermisache ( 1940 - 2012 ) was an Argentinian artist whose works of asemic writing have been published and exhibited internationally at venues including the Centre Georges Pompidou in Paris and MACBA in Barcelona , and collected by leading international arts institutions .
Théophile Raynaud ( 15 November 1583 -- 31 October 1663 ) was a French Jesuit theologian and writer .
Max Hirschberg ( 1883 - 1964 ) was a German Jewish Weimar era anti - Nazi criminal defense lawyer and scholar .
Dhondutai Kulkarni , ( 23 July 1927 -- 1 June 2014 ) was an eminent Indian classical singer and the last living legend of Orthodox Jaipur - Atrauli Gharana . The gharana was founded by legendary classical singer Alladiya Khan and is known for its full - throated singing .
Henry Roy Dean , MD , LL.D , D.Sc , FRCP ( 19 February 1879 -- 13 February 1961 ) , also known as Prof . H. R. Dean , was a professor of Pathology at the University of Cambridge and Master of Trinity Hall , Cambridge .
John Talman ( July 1677 , King 's Street , Westminster -- 3 November 1726 , London ) was a British antiquary and art collector .
Constantin Brăiloiu ( 13 August 1893 - 20 December 1958 ) was a Romanian composer and internationally known ethnomusicologist .
Juan Sepulveda ( 1814 - -1898 ) was an early California politician and pioneer in Los Angeles .
Alice Ayres ( 12 September 1859 -- 26 April 1885 ) was an English nursemaid honoured for her bravery in rescuing the children in her care from a house fire .
Norbert Barlicki ( 6 June 1880 , Sieciechów , Radom Governorate - 27 September 1941 , Auschwitz ) was a Polish publicist , lawyer and politician .
Alfredo Salazar Southwell ( 1913 -- 14 September 1937 ) was a Peruvian aviator , celebrated as a national hero .
Max Fesca ( 31 March 1846 -- 31 October 1917 ) was a German specialist in agricultural science and agronomy , hired by the Meiji government of Japan as a foreign advisor from 1882 - 1894 .
Leonora Baroni ( December 1611 -- 6 April 1670 ) was an Italian singer , theorbist , lutenist , viol player , and composer .
John Dudley North ( 1893 - -1968 ) , CBE , HonFRAeS , MIMechE , was Chairman and Managing Director of Boulton Paul Aircraft .
Sigfús Eymundsson ( 1837 - -1911 ) was an Icelandic photographer and bookseller .
Joseph Burstyn ( 1900 - -1953 ) was a U.S. film distributor who specialized in the commercial release of foreign - language and American independent film productions .
Richard Kingston ( 1635 ? -- 1710 ? ) was an English political pamphleteer , clerical impostor , and spy .
Honius , born Cornelis Henricxz Hoen ( c. 1440 , The Hague -- 1524 , The Hague ) was a Dutch jurist and humanist , known for his views on the Eucharist .
Ethel Hudson ( 1896 ? , Salem , Massachusetts -- 1992 , Concord , New Hampshire ) was the last surviving member of the Canterbury Shaker Village in New Hampshire .
Nigel Boocock ( 17 September 1937 -- 3 April 2015 ) was a British speedway rider who appeared in eight Speedway World Championship finals and was a reserve in one other ( 1962 ) .
Francis Ormond ( 23 November 1827 -- 5 May 1889 ) was a Scottish - born Australian pastoralist , member of the Parliament of Victoria and philanthropist in the areas of education and religion .
Donald Buka ( 1920 - -2009 ) was an American supporting actor in films and television from 1943 ( Watch on the Rhine ) to 1971 when he appeared in A Memory of Two Mondays .
Sir Isaac Wake ( 1580/81 - 1632 ) was an English diplomat and political commentator .
Kersy Katrak ( 1936 - -2008 ) was an Indian advertising man and poet of the 1970s .
Jan Mączyński ( c. 1520 -- c. 1587 ) was a Polish humanist and lexicographer .
Jim Percy ( 1948 -- 12 October 1992 in Sydney , Australia ) , was a founder of the Socialist Workers League of Australia , later called the Socialist Workers Party and the Democratic Socialist Party , and served as national secretary for almost twenty years .
William Phelip , 6th Baron Bardolf , KG ( died 6 June 1441 ) was Treasurer of the King 's Household and Royal Chamberlain .
Clay Lancaster ( 30 March 1917 -- 25 December 2000 ) , was an authority on American architecture , an orientalist , and an influential advocate of historical preservation .
Ivor Griffiths ( 19 June 1918 -- October 1993 ) was a Welsh footballer .
Herb Brunning ( 26 May 1886 -- 12 December 1947 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with St Kilda in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Isaac Grout Bliss ( Springfield , Massachusetts , 1822 - -1889 ) was a missionary and agent of the American Bible Society ( ABS ) in the Near East .
Asbjørn Lindboe ( 19 June 1889 -- 8 March 1967 ) was the Norwegian Minister of Justice , serving two terms from 1931 - 1932 and 1932 - 1933 .
June Jago ( c. 1926 -- August 2010 ) was an Australian - born actress .
Henry Manners , 2nd Earl of Rutland , 13th Baron de Ros of Helmsley , KG ( 23 September 1526 -- 17 September 1563 ) was an English nobleman .
Gerhard Werner ( 1921 - -2012 ) was a medical doctor and scholar active in research covering areas of pharmacology , psychiatry , cognitive neuroscience , especially neurodynamics , artificial intelligence , and complexity theory .
George Brooke , 9th Baron Cobham ( c. 1497 - 29 September 1558 ) KG , was an aristocrat during the early Tudor dynasty in England .
Ced Hay ( 27 September 1880 -- 8 November 1953 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Michael Greer ( born James Robert `` Jimmie '' Malley , April 20 , 1938 -- September 14 , 2002 ) was an American actor , comedian and cabaret performer .
Bayan I was an Avar khagan , between 562 and 602 .
Jørgen Lunge ( 11 October 1577 -- 19 August 1619 ) was a Danish nobleman who served as Rigsmarsk from 1616 to 1619 .
Sigismondo Caula ( 1637 - -1724 ) was an Italian painter of the Baroque style .
Owen Thomas Jones , FRS FGS ( 16 April 1878 -- 5 May 1967 ) was a Welsh geologist .
Jockey Shabalala ( 4 November 1943 -- 11 February 2006 ) was a member of Ladysmith Black Mambazo , a South African choral group founded and still led by his brother Joseph .
Sir Charles Arthur Mander , 2nd Baronet JP , DL , TD ( 25 June 1884 -- 25 January 1951 ) was a public servant , philanthropist , and manufacturer , as managing director of Mander Brothers , the family paint , varnish and inks business established in 1773 .
Hartbert van Bierum ( died 12 November 1150 ) was a bishop of Utrecht from 1139 to 1150 Hartbert was consecrated as bishop on July 24 , 1139 .
George Lennon ( 1900 - -1991 ) was an Irish Republican Army leader during the Irish War of Independence and the Irish Civil War .
William W. Woollcott ( 24 March 1876 -- 2 February 1949 ) was an ink - and - paste manufacturer who lived in Baltimore , Maryland .
José Antonio Jimenes Domínguez ( Cabo Haitiano , 1887 - 1938 ) was a Dominican Republic judge and president of the Supreme Court .
Terence De Marney ( 1 March 1908 -- 25 May 1971 ) was a British film , stage , radio and television actor , as well as theatre director and writer .
Jim Marking ( 26 April 1927 -- 19 January 2013 ) was an American professional coach , best known for his career at South Dakota State .
Sardar Bahadur Khan ( Urdu : سردار بہادر خان‎ ) ( born 8 July 1908 - - 31 December 1975 ) was a Pakistani politician .
Humphrey Hopkin ( 1774 -- 11 January 1840 ) was an English professional cricketer who made 2 known appearances in major cricket matches from 1791 to 1800 .
Alfred Galpin ( 1901 - -1983 ) was an American literary academic and musical composer of classical works .
Fanny Furner ( 1864 - -1938 ) was an activist who worked to further the rights of women and children in the early 1900s in Sydney .
Joe Mensah ( died 2003 ) was a Ghanaian singer and musician .
Branko Hofman ( 29 November 1929 -- 12 June 1991 ) was a Slovene poet , writer and playwright .
Dr Edward Bright Vedder ( 1878 - -1952 ) was a U.S. Army physician , a noted researcher on deficiency diseases , and a medical educator .
Arthur Stuart Michael Cummings MBE ( born Leeds , Yorkshire , 1 June 1919 , died London , 9 October 1997 ) was a British newspaper cartoonist .
Air Commodore Douglas Douglas - Hamilton , 14th Duke of Hamilton and 11th Duke of Brandon KT GCVO AFC PC DL FRCSE FRGS ( 3 February 1903 -- 30 March 1973 ) was a Scottish nobleman and pioneering aviator .
Rikard Lenac ( March 16 , 1868 - 1949 ) was a lawyer and a one - time governor of the city of Fiume ( Rijeka ) .
Wilhelm Halbfass ( 11 May 1940 in Northeim -- 25 May 2000 ) was a German - born Indologist .
Jean Marlin ( 1833 - 1872 ) was a non - commissioned officer , a sergeant of the French 8th Battalion of infantry .
Sheng Aiyi ( Chinese : 盛爱颐 ; pinyin : Shèng Àiyí ; 1900 - -1983 ) , was the first Chinese women entrepreneur in the entertainment industry , the general manager of Shanghai BaiLeMen company .
E. Martin Browne ( 29 January 1900 -- 27 April 1980 ) was a British theatre director , known for his production of twentieth century verse plays .
Andreas Borum ( 1799 , Hamburg - 29 April 1853 , Munich ) was a German painter and lithographer who also worked in stone , and a collector .
The Hon . James Francis Edward Keith ( 11 June 1696 -- 14 October 1758 ) was a Scottish soldier and Prussian field marshal .
Stevan Hristić ( Serbian Cyrillic : Стеван Христић ; 19 June 1885 -- 21 August 1958 ) was Serbian composer , conductor , pedagogue , and music writer .
Tomás Ripoll ( died 1747 ) was the Master of the Order of Preachers from 1725 to 1747 .
Samina Raja ( Urdu : ثمینہ راجہ ‎‎ 11 September 1961 -- 30 October 2012 ) was a Pakistani Urdu poet , writer , editor , translator , educationist and broadcaster .
Father Guy Mary - Rousselière ( Le Mans , France 1913 - 1994 Mittimatalik ) was a French - Canadian anthropologist , missionary priest at Mittimatalik , and string figure collector .
Berthold VII , Count of Henneberg - Schleusingen ( nicknamed the Wise , born : 1272 in Schleusingen ; died : 13 April 1340 , Schleusingen ) was Count of Henneberg- Schleusingen from 1284 to 1340 .
Giles d'Argentan ( c. 1280 -- 24 June 1314 ) was a Norman knight who was slain at the Battle of Bannockburn .
Sir George Albu , 1st Baronet ( 26 October 1857 -- 27 December 1935 ) was a mining magnate in the diamond and gold industries of South Africa .
Dag Heyerdahl Larsen ( 25 October 1955 -- 7 January 2012 ) was a Norwegian translator .
Georg Jacob Bull ( born 1 August 1785 in Christiania , died 12 December 1854 ) was a Norwegian jurist and politician .
Charles Symmons ( 1749 -- 27 April 1826 ) was a Welsh poet and priest .
Joseph Callaerts ( 22 August 1838 -- 3 March 1901 ) was a Belgian organist , carilloneur , composer and music teacher .
Sir James Clavering , 1st Baronet ( 3 February 1620 -- 24 March 1702 ) was an English landowner .
Charles O'Hara Booth ( 31 August 1800 -- 11 August 1851 ) , was commandant - in - chief of Port Arthur penal colony and had jurisdiction over all stations on the Tasman Peninsula .
Edward Reichmann ( Hebrew : אדוארד רייכמן‎ ; 1925 - July , 2005 ) was an Israeli businessman .
William Linford Rees ( 24 October 1914 -- 29 July 2004 ) was a Welsh psychiatrist , who was professor of psychiatry at St Bartholomew 's Hospital , London , and president of the Royal College of Psychiatrists from 1975 to 1978 .
Carlos Salzedo ( 6 April 1885 -- 17 August 1961 ) was a French harpist , pianist , composer and conductor .
William Robert Pearmain ( 1888 - -1912 ) was an American painter , and activist .
Herbert Berghof ( 13 September 1909 -- 5 November 1990 ) was an Austrian - American actor , director and acting coach .
William Livingstone , 6th Lord Livingston , ( died 1592 ) , Scottish lord of Parliament .
Sheena Duncan ( 7 December 1932 -- 4 May 2010 ) was a South African anti - Apartheid activist and counselor .
John Deyell ( c. 1775 -- November 21 , 1878 ) was assistant to the original surveyor of Cavan Township in Durham County , Ontario , and founder of the town of Millbrook , Ontario .
Saul Yaffie , aka Paul Jeffay , ( 1898 - -1957 ) was a Scottish Jewish artist .
Venerable Rachelina Ambrosini ( 2 July 1925 -- 10 March 1941 ) was an Italian teenager who is venerated by the Roman Catholic Church .
David Ramsay Anderson ( 2 May 1888 -- 17 May 1962 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon and University in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Maurie Connell ( 9 March 1902 -- 4 February 1975 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton and South Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Professor Joseph Gloag ( 1906 or 1907 -- 21 April 1977 ) was a marketing theorist and Scottish nationalist political activist .
Anne Camm or Anne Newby ( August , 1627 -- 30 September 1705 ) was an early British Quaker preacher .
Dr Gilbert Rule ( 1629 ( approx ) -- 1701 ) was a nonconformist divine and the Principal of Edinburgh University from 1690 to 1701 .
Furioso II ( 1965 - 1986 ) is one of the most influential sires in sport horse history .
Emil August Fieldorf `` Nil '' ( 20 March 1895 -- 24 February 1953 ) was a Polish Brigadier General .
Dhikru'llah Khadem ( Arabic : ذكر الله خادم‎ , transliterated as Zikru'llah and Khádem or Khadim ; 1904 - -1986 ) was a prominent follower of the Bahá'í Faith , appointed to be a Hand of the Cause by Shoghi Effendi in 1952 .
Barzillai Quaife ( 29 December 1798 -- 3 March 1873 ) was an English - born editor , Congregational and Presbyterian minister , bookseller and teacher active in both Australia and New Zealand .
Stephen Lett ( 4 April 1847 -- 11 October 1905 ) was born in Ireland but raised and educated in Canada .
Karl Fredrik Wilkama , born Wilkman , ( 27 March 1876 , Helsinki -- 15 July 1947 , Helsinki ) was a Finnish General of the Infantry .
Vishnudas Bhave ( Marathi : विष्णुदास भावे ) ( d. 9 August 1901 ) , was the leading dramatist of Maharashtra in India and the pioneer of Marathi theatre , as he staged the first Marathi - language play Sita Swayamvar in Sangli 1843 .
Merkury Vagin ( Russian : Меркурий Вагин ) ( died 1712 ) was a Russian Arctic explorer .
Denis Granville ( name altered from Grenville ) ( 1637 - -1703 ) was an English non - juring cleric , Dean of Durham and then Jacobite exile .
Bruno Touschek ( 3 February 1921 - -25 May 1978 ) was an Austrian physicist , a survivor of the Holocaust , and initiator of research on electron - positron colliders .
Georg Christian Lehms ( German : ( leːms ) ; 1684 -- 15 May 1717 ) was a German poet and novelist who sometimes used the pen - name Pallidor .
James Smoot Coleman ( 4 February 1919 -- 20 April 1985 ) was an American scholar , professor and administrator in political science , but more specifically in African studies .
John Hullier or Hulliarde , Huller or Hullyer , ( c. 1520 -- 16 April 1556 ) was an English clergyman and a Protestant martyr under Mary I of England .
Dinah Lauterman ( 1899 -- 1945 ) , was a Canadian musician , artist and sculptor .
Professor Cemil Topuzlu ( 18 March 1866 -- 25 January 1958 ) , also known as Cemil Pasha , was a leading surgeon in Turkey who was internationally recognized for his pioneering work in several areas , including open chest cardiac massage , and described in several papers published in Ottoman Turkish , French and German .
George Meriton ( or Meryton ) ( died 1624 ) was an English churchman , Dean of Peterborough in 1612 and Dean of York in 1617 .
Joseph La France , ( c. 1707 -- c. 1745 ) , was a Metis fur trader in Canada , and an explorer of the inland route from Montreal to Hudson Bay .
Joseph Joachim ( 28 June 1831 -- 15 August 1907 ) was a Hungarian violinist , conductor , composer and teacher .
Abel Kingué ( 1924 -- 16 April 1964 ) was a political leader in the struggle for the independence of Cameroon from France .
Karl Heeremans ( 1 June 1937 -- 12 April 2010 ) was an artist - painter with very personal norms of colours and forms .
Gaspare Antonio Cavalcabò Baroni ( Pieve di Sacco , 1682 - Rovereto , 1759 ) was an Italian painter in a late Baroque style .
Sir Thomas Englefield ( also known as Inglefield ) ( ca . 1455 -- 3 April 1514 ) was Speaker of the House of Commons .
Patrick Joseph O'Brien ( 1835 -- 10 January 1911 ) was Irish Nationalist Member of Parliament for North Tipperary , 1885 - 1906 .
Sarah Dazley ( 1819 -- 5 August 1843 ) , later known as the `` Potton Poisoner '' , was an English murderess convicted of the poisoning of her husband William Dazley .
James Gunter ( 25 July 1731 -- 19 September 1819 ) was an English confectioner , market gardener and property developer who laid the foundations for what became one of the great residential estates in West London , developed by his descendants , the `` Redcliffe Estate '' and The Boltons in Little Chelsea and West Brompton .
Hernando de Miranda ( 1550 - -1593 ) was a Spanish conquistador and explorer who was governor of Spanish Florida from 1575 - -1577 .
Yang Shao - hou or Yang Shaohou ( 1862 - 1930 ) along with Yang Chengfu ( 楊澄甫 ; 1883 - 1936 ) represent the third generation of Yang family taijiquan ( 楊氏太極拳 ) .
Sir Jeremiah Colman , 1st Baronet ( 24 April 1859 - 16 January 1942 ) was an industrialist who developed Colman 's Mustard into an international concern .
James Mansfield , Sr . ( 9 April 1939 -- 29 January 2014 ) , known as Jim Mansfield , was an Irish businessman , with a property portfolio that included the Citywest Hotel and Golf Resort , several developments local to the Saggart and Tallaght areas , and Weston Airport .
Tiffany Leong ( simplified Chinese : 梁丽芳 ; traditional Chinese : 梁麗芳 ; pinyin : Liáng Lìfāng ; 24 October 1985 -- 28 December 2015 ) , also known as 绰琦 ( pinyin : Chuō Qí ) , was a Malaysian actress and host and former model contracted to MediaCorp .
SS - Unterscharführer Willi Mentz ( 30 April 1904 -- 25 June 1978 ) was a member of the German SS in World War II and a Holocaust perpetrator who worked at Treblinka extermination camp during the Operation Reinhard phase of the Holocaust in Poland .
Kerala Varma Valiya Koil Thampuran CSI ( Malayalam : കേരളവർമ്മ വലിയ കോയിത്തമ്പുരാൻ ; February 19 , 1845 -- 1914 ) also spelt Kerala Varma Valiya Koilthampuran and known as Kerala Varma , was a Malayalam - language poet and translator who had an equal facility in writing in English and Sanskrit from the Indian state of Kerala .
Martyn Hedges was a British slalom canoeist who competed from the mid-1970s until his death in 1992 .
Gao Gan ( died 206 ) was a governor of Bing Province during the late Han Dynasty period of Chinese history .
Paulus van Beresteyn ( 1582 -- 1666 ) , was a Dutch lawyer in Haarlem , known best today for his portrait painted by Frans Hals in 1619 .
Elisabeth Marschall ( 27 May 1886 -- 3 May 1947 ) was the Head Nurse ( Oberschwester ) at the Ravensbrück concentration camp .
Nicholas Goudanus ( also de Gouda ) ( c.1517 - -1565 ) was a Dutch Jesuit and papal diplomat .
Edward Bentham ( 23 July 1707 -- 1 August 1776 ) was an Oxford based theologian who in 1763 , with some evident reluctance , became Regius Professor of Divinity at Oxford University .
Sir Uvedale Price , 1st Baronet ( baptised 14 April 1747 -- 14 September 1829 ) , author of the Essay on the Picturesque , As Compared with the Sublime and The Beautiful ( 1794 ) , was a Herefordshire landowner who was at the heart of the ' Picturesque debate ' of the 1790s .
Benjamin Glover Shields ( 1808 -- 1850 ) was an American politician and a member of the United States House of Representatives from Alabama .
Dirck Dicx ( 1603 -- after 1650 ) , was a Dutch Golden Age brewer in Haarlem who moved to Brazil .
Viacheslav Frantsevich Zagonek ( 1919 - -1994 ) People 's Artist of the USSR , full member of the Russian Academy of Sciences and Laureate of I.E.Repin State Prize , Viacheslav Zagonek , is known as an outstanding lyrical scenery master .
Bessie Louise Pierce ( 20 April 1888 -- 3 October 1974 ) was an American historian known for her three - volume work , A History of Chicago .
Marpa Lotsawa ( 1012 - -1097 ) , sometimes known fully as Lhodak Marpa Choski Lodos or commonly as Marpa the Translator , was a Tibetan Buddhist teacher credited with the transmission of many Vajrayana teachings from India , including the teachings and lineages of Mahamudra .
Giuseppe Arrighi ( 1642 in Volterra -- 1706 in Volterra ) was an Italian painter of the Baroque period .
Emmanuel Scheffer ( Hebrew : עמנואל שפר‎‎ ; 1 February 1924 -- 28 December 2012 ) was an Israeli football player and coach who was born in Germany .
George Archer - Shee ( 6 May 1895 -- 31 October 1914 ) was a young Royal Navy cadet whose case of whether he stole a five shilling postal order was decided in London 's High Court in 1910 .
Joseph Alan Cordner ( 6 May 1890 -- 25 April 1915 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Geelong and Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Jorge Maria O'Neill ( Lisbon , Encarnação , 7 November 1908 - Lisbon , 15 December 1988 ) was the head of a branch of one of the principal Irish Royal Families , the Clanaboy O'Neill dynasty , which has resided in Portugal since the 18th century .
Hermann Abeken ( 27 June 1820 -- 27 April 1854 ) was a German political writer and statistician .
Alfred Ernest Wileman ( 1860 - -1929 ) was a British diplomat and entomologist .
Peter Post ( 12 November 1933 -- 14 January 2011 ) was a Dutch professional cyclist whose career lasted from 1956 to 1972 .
