Jan Goossen died on cancer in the hospital of Goes on 1 January 2005 .
Lady Iris Mountbatten ( 13 January 1920 - 1 September 1982 ) was an English actress and model , and a member of the Battenberg / Mountbatten family .
Mary Hillevi Lagerstam ( since 1958 Mannermaa , 9 August 1923 -- 21 October 1998 ) was a Finnish actress .
Thomas Hamilton , 7th Earl of Haddington ( 1721 -- 19 May 1794 ) was a Scottish nobleman .
Giuseppe Missori ( 11 June 1829 - 25 March 1911 ) was an Italian patriot , military leader during the Italian unification , and politician .
Maria Stella ( 16 April 1773 - 23 December 1843 ) was the self - styled legitimate daughter of Louis Philip II , Duke of Orléans .
Antonino Barges ( fl . 1546 - -1565 ) was a Franco - Flemish composer of the Renaissance , active in Venice and Treviso .
Johannes Gijsbertus Bastiaans ( 31 October 1812 , Wilp - 16 February 1875 , Haarlem ) was a Dutch organist , composer and music theorist .
Giulia Turco , or Giulia Turco Lazzari ( Italian pronunciation : ( ˈdʒulja ˈturko ) ; 1848 - -1912 ) , was a baroness best known as a naturalist and writer in her native Trento , Italy .
Renato Fondi ( 1887 - -1929 ) was a poet , writer and music critic .
Maria Eleonora I Boncompagni ( 1686 - -1745 ) was the Princess of Piombino , Marchioness of Populonia , Princess of Venosa and Countess of Conza , Lady di Scarlino , Populonia , Vignale , Abbadia del Fango , Suvereto , Buriano , Isola d’Elba , Montecristo , Pianosa , Cerboli e Palmaiolan , from 1733 until her death .
Betty Warren ( 31 October 1907 -- 15 December 1990 ) was a British actress during the 1930s to 1950s , best known for her comedy roles in such films as Champagne Charlie ( 1944 ) and Passport to Pimlico ( 1949 ) .
Sir John Wylde ( 11 May 1781 -- 13 December 1859 ) was Chief Justice of the Cape Colony , Cape of Good Hope and a judge of the Supreme Court of the colony of New South Wales born at Warwick Square , Newgate Street , London .
Edward Roworth ( 1880 in Lancashire -- 1964 ) is a South African artist .
Edgar Alfred Bowring ( /ˈboʊrɪŋ/ ; 1826 - -1911 ) was a British translator , author and civil servant , serving as librarian and registrar to the Board of Trade ( 1848 - -1863 ) , secretary to the Royal Commission for the Exhibition of 1851 , and Liberal Member of Parliament for Exeter ( 1868 - -1874 ) .
Chester William Harrison ( 1913 in Indiana -- 1994 ) was a prolific American author who wrote under the names C. William Harrison , Coe Williams and Will Hickok .
Blessed Tommaso Maria Fusco ( 1 December 1831 - 24 February 1891 ) was an Italian Roman Catholic priest who established the Daughters of Charity of the Most Precious Blood .
John Beaumont , 1st Viscount Beaumont ( c. 1409 - -1460 ) , was an English magnate , the eldest son of Henry , 5th Baron Beaumont of Folkingham , Lincolnshire .
Dongseong of Baekje ( ? -501 , r. 479 - 501 ) was the 24th king of Baekje , one of the Three Kingdoms of Korea .
Emmeline Pankhurst ( née Goulden ; 15 July 1858 -- 14 June 1928 ) was a British political activist and leader of the British suffragette movement who helped women win the right to vote .
Jacob ben Aaron of Karlin ( died 1855 at Karlin , government of Minsk ) was a Russian rabbi and author .
Ambalal Jhaverbhai Patel ( died 1961 ) was an Indian photographer and film producer .
Zecharia Glosca ( Hebrew : זכריה גלוסקא‎ , born 1894 , died 19 September 1960 ) was Yemenite Jew and Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for the Yemenite Association between 1949 and 1951 .
Hugh Aston ( also spelled Asseton , Assheton , Ashton , Haston ; c. 1485 -- buried 17 November 1558 ) was an English composer of the early Tudor period .
Robert Brian Shillinglaw , nicknamed `` Shill '' , ( 1 July 1939 -- 17 October 2007 ) was a Scottish rugby union and rugby league player .
Jules Boucherit ( 29 March 1877 -- 1 April 1962 ) was a French violinist and renowned violin pedagogue .
Charles Grey , 1st Earl Grey KB PC ( circa 23 October 1729 -- 14 November 1807 ) was a British general of the 18th century .
Henry Nathaniel Andrews , Jr. ( born June 15 , 1910 , Melrose , Massachusetts ; d. March 3 , 2002 Concord , New Hampshire ) was an American paleobotanist recognized as an expert in plants of the Devonian and Carboniferous periods .
Sir John Stoddart ( 6 February 1773 -- 16 February 1856 ) was a writer and lawyer , and editor of The Times .
John Northampton ( also known as John Comberton ) ( died 1398 ) was a reformist Lord Mayor of London in 1381 and 1382 , during dissension in favor of reform of its Common Council in the early years of Richard II 's reign .
Meshach Dean ( probably born March 1870 -- 1916 ) was a footballer who played for Burslem Port Vale in the 1890s .
Robert Buckner ( May 28 , 1906 -- August , 1989 ) was a film screenwriter , producer and short story writer .
Halfdan Olaus Christophersen ( 13 December 1902 -- 27 May 1980 ) was a Norwegian historian of ideas and non - fiction writer .
Puthanpurayil Ramunni Kurup , commonly known as P. R. Kurup ( 30 September 1915 -- 17 January 2001 ) , was an Indian socialist leader and former minister of Kerala state .
Gennady Riger ( Hebrew : גנדי ריגר‎‎ ; 24 May 1948 -- 12 October 2015 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for Yisrael BaAliyah between 1999 and 2003 .
Luca De Filippo ( 3 June 1948 -- 27 November 2015 ) was an Italian actor and director of theatre .
Sir Henry Channon ( 7 March 1897 -- 7 October 1958 ) , often known as Chips Channon , was an American - born British Conservative politician , author and diarist .
Rabbi Shimon Hakham ( Hebrew : שמעון חכם‎ ; 1843 , Bukhara- 1910 , Jerusalem ) was a Bukharian rabbi residing in Jerusalem who promoted literacy by translating Hebrew religious books into Bukhori .
Dr Robert Laws ( 1851 - -1934 ) was a Scottish missionary who headed the Livingstonia mission in the Nyasaland Protectorate ( now Malawi ) for more than 50 years .
Sir John Croft , 1st Baronet ( 1778 - -1862 ) was an English diplomat , and spy for Wellington against Napoleon .
James Henry Monahan ( 1803 -- 8 December 1878 ) was one of the outstanding Irish judges of his time , and one of the first Irish Roman Catholics to achieve judicial eminence .
Rice Charleton ( 1710 - -1789 ) was an English physician , medical researcher , and Fellow of the Royal Society .
Frederik Peter Brandt ( 24 July 1825 -- 2 May 1891 ) was a Norwegian legal historian and Professor at the Faculty of Law of the Royal Frederick University ( 1866 - -1890 ) .
Albert Bernard Hollowood ( 3 June 1910 -- 28 March 1981 ) was an English writer , cartoonist and economist .
P. Lankesh ( Kannada : ಪಿ. ಲಂಕೇಶ್ , 8 March 1935 -- 25 January 2000 ) , was an Indian poet , fiction writer , playwright , translator , screenplay writer and journalist who wrote in the Kannada language .
Albert Stohr ( 13 November 1890 -- 3 June 1961 ) was Bishop of Mainz from 15 July 1935 until his death .
Eftichia Papagianopoulos ( Greek : Ευτυχία Παπαγιαννοπούλου ) , also spelled as Eftihia Papagianopoulou ( 1893 -- 7 January 1972 ) , was a Greek lyricist .
Jan Bekker Teerlink ( baptized 17 August 1759 -- 4 December 1832 ) was a Dutch plant and seed collector and winemaker .
Ferdinando Paer ( 1 July 1771 -- 3 May 1839 ) was an Italian composer known for his operas and oratorios .
Mirza Abbas Khan Sheida , or Sheida - ye - Esfahani ( 1873 -- 1949 ) , was an Iranian sufi , poet and Journalist .
Laurent Bénard ( 1573 - -1620 ) was a chief founder of the Maurist Congregation .
Sir Edward Henry Sieveking ( 24 August 1816 -- 24 February 1904 ) was an English physician .
Sir James Joseph Allport ( 27 February 1811 -- 25 April 1892 ) was an English railway manager .
Noura bint Abdul Rahman Al Saud ( 1875 -- 1950 ) was a member of the House of Saud and the elder sister of King Abdulaziz .
Cadwgan ap Bleddyn ( 1051 - -1111 ) was a prince of the Kingdom of Powys ( Welsh : Teyrnas Powys ) in eastern Wales .
Norman Stuart Sutherland ( 26 March 1927 -- 8 November 1998 ) , always known professionally as Stuart Sutherland , was a British psychologist and writer .
Dingiswayo ( Zulu pronunciation : ( diŋɡisʷaːjo ) ) ( c.1780 -- 1817 ) ( born Godongwana ) was a Mthethwa chief , well known for his mentorship over a young Zulu general , Shaka Zulu , who rose to become the greatest of the Zulu kings .
Ramchundra ( Ramachandra Lal ) ( Devanagari,रामचन्द्र लाल ) ( 1821 -- 1880 ) was a British Indian mathematician .
George Faulkner Wetherbee , R.I. , R.O.I. ( Cincinnati , 1851 - -1920 ) was a notable painter .
Tullio Biscuola ( 12 July 1899 -- 13 February 1963 ) was an Italian marathon runner .
Edmund Sheffield , 2nd Duke of Buckingham and Normanby ( 11 January 1716 -- 30 October 1735 ) was an English nobleman , styled Marquess of Normanby from 1716 to 1721 .
Thomas Pickering Pick ( 13 June 1841 - 6 September 1919 ) was a British surgeon and author .
Pope John XVIII ( Latin : Ioannes XVIII ; died June or July 1009 ) was Pope and ruler of the Papal states from January 1004 ( 25 December 1003 - NS ) to his abdication in June 1009 .
Frederick Lloyd Roche CBE ( 11 March 1931 -- 9 November 1992 ) , better known as Fred Roche , was an architect , most known for his work in Milton Keynes during the 1970s and for his company Conran Roche in the 1980s .
The Reverend Henry Herbert Symonds ( 1885 -- 28 December 1958 ) was an English Anglican priest , teacher and conservationist .
Ashkharbek Kalantar ( Armenian : Աշխարհբեկ Լոռիս-Մելիք Քալանթար ; February 11 , 1884 in Ardvi , Armenia -- June 1942 ) was an Armenian archaeologist , historian .
Reidar Jørgensen ( 5 October 1904 -- 22 September 1985 ) was a Norwegian middle distance runner , cross - country skier , botanist and educator .
Professor Dr. Ernst Décsey ( 13 April 1870 -- 12 March 1941 ) , was an Austrian author and music critic .
Adolph Reuss ( 28 November 1804 , Frankfurt am Main -- 7 May 1878 ) was a German - American physician and zoologist , known for his work in the fields of herpetology and arachnology .
Jean - Baptiste Stouf ( Paris 1742 - -Charenton - le - Pont 1826 ) was a French sculptor known especially for his commemorative portrait busts and expressive emotional content .
Kekoo Gandhy ( 2 February 1920 -- 10 November 2012 ) was an Indian art gallerist , art collector and art connoisseur , who pioneered the promotion of Indian modern art from the 1940s .
Laure Moghaizel ( 1929 - -1997 ) was a Lebanese attorney and prominent women 's rights advocate .
Chen Yonggui ( Chinese : 陈永贵 ; pinyin : Chén Yǒngguì ; Wade -- Giles : Chen Yung - kuei ; 14 February 1915 - -26 March 1986 ) was a Chinese politician .
Marcin Zborowski ( c. 1495 -- 25 February 1565 ) was a Polish castellan ( Polish : kasztelan ) of Kalisz ( since 1543 ) , voivod ( wojewoda ) of Kalisz ( since 1550 ) , voivod of Poznań ( since 1558 ) and castellan of Kraków ( since 1562 ) .
Maria Bard ( 7 July 1900 -- 8 April 1944 ) was a German stage actress , who made a handful of films in the silent era for Rimax , her first husband Wilhelm Graaff 's company .
Raghunath Singh Verma ( 7 September 1948 -- 20 December 2009 ) , was an influential Indian politician involved mainly in the state affairs of Uttar Pradesh , Rajasthan , Uttarakhand , Bihar and Madhya Pradesh .
Angad Paul ( 6 June 1970 -- 8 November 2015 ) was a British businessman and film producer .
John Allde , also Aldaye , Alde or Aldye ( fl . 1555 - -1592 ) was a Scottish stationer and printer .
Daniel Block ( 1802 - -1853 ) was a Jewish leader who founded the B'nai B'rith synagogue is St. Louis , Missouri .
Carlo Saraceni ( 1579 -- 16 June 1620 ) was an Italian early - Baroque painter , whose reputation as a `` first - class painter of the second rank '' was improved with the publication of a modern monograph in 1968 .
Joachim Jacob Unger ( born November 25 , 1826 , at Humenné , Zemplén County , Hungary - 1912 ) was an Austrian rabbi .
Lars Trygg , woodcarver , ( 29 May 1929 -- 29 June 1999 ) was one of the recognized masters of 20th century wood carving , most famous for Scandinavian flat - plane style of woodcarving .
Lankapalli Bullayya ( 1918 - -1992 ) was an innovative Indian educator and vice - chancellor of Andhra University , Andhra Pradesh .
Wayne Shannon was reported missing by his family in September 2011 .
Auguste - Jean Gaudin was a French painter and engraver born 29 July 1914 in Argentré - du - Plessis ( Ille - et - Vilaine ) , died 23 May 1992 .
Joseph Willcox Jenkins ( 15 February 1928 -- 31 January 2014 ) was an American composer , professor of music , and musician .
Frank Preston Stearns ( 1846 - -1917 ) , the son of abolitionist George Luther Stearns , was a writer and abolitionist from Massachusetts during the 19th century .
Benoni Aubert ( 4 August 1768 -- 21 April 1832 ) was a Norwegian military officer and cartographer .
Willard Somers Elliot ( 18 July 1926 in Fort Worth , Texas -- 7 June 2000 in Fort Worth , Texas ) was an American bassoonist and composer .
Trần Duệ Tông ( Hán tự : 陳睿宗 , 1337 - -1377 ) , given name Trần Kính ( 陳曔 ) , was the ninth emperor of the Trần Dynasty who reigned Đại Việt from 1373 to 1377 .
Wulfwig died at Winchester ( Flor . Wig . ii . 1 , Engl . Hist . Soc . ) in 1067 , and was buried in his own church at Dorchester ( A .- S. Chron . ii . 171 ) .
Vicko Krstulović ( 27 April 1905 -- 28 September 1988 ) was a Croatian Yugoslav military commander and politician from Dalmatia .
Thanos Leivaditis ( also Thanos Livaditis ) ( Greek : Θάνος Λειβαδίτης , 1934 -- 1 September 2005 ) was a Greek actor and screenwriter .
Ahmed al - Ghazzal or , in full , Abu l - Abbas Ahmed ibn Al - Mahdi al - Ghazzal al - Andalusi al - Maliqi ( died in Fes , 1777 ) was the secretary of the Moroccan Sultan Mohammed ibn Abdallah ( 1757 - 89 ) .
Ryan Tandy ( 20 September 1981 -- 28 April 2014 ) was an Australian professional rugby league player of the 2000s and 2010s .
Timothy Mwitwa ( 21 May 1968 -- 27 April 1993 ) was a Zambian footballer and member of the national team .
Wang Hao - te ( 1921 - -1999 ) was the founder of the Great Way of Maitreya ( Chinese : 彌勒大道 ; pinyin : Mílè Dà Dào ) , which is based in Hsinchu , Taiwan .
Charles Boot JP ( 1874 - 1945 ) was the eldest son of Henry Boot and the driving force behind the growth of Henry Boot & Sons in the inter - war period .
Chief Hunter Jack ( died 1905 ) was a 19th - century chief of the Lakes Lillooet ( today 's N'quatqua and Seton Lake bands ) .
Mohammad Khaksar ( died 14 January 2006 ) was an Afghan Taliban intelligence chief and deputy Minister of the Interior .
White Eyes , named Koquethagechton ( c. 1730 -- 5 November 1778 ) , was a leader of the Lenape ( Delaware ) people in the Ohio Country during the era of the American Revolution .
William Handyside ( 1793 - -1850 ) was a Scottish engineer who was involved in several important construction projects in St. Petersburg .
Anne Naysmith ( 1937 - 10 February 2015 ) was a British classical pianist who became notable later in life for sleeping rough in Chiswick , West London .
John J. Mooney better known as J. D. Mooney ( died 1966 ) was an American jockey and trainer who won the 1924 Kentucky Derby on Black Gold and the 1929 King 's Plate on Shorelint .
Grey Brydges , 5th Baron Chandos ( c. 1580 -- 10 August 1621 ) was an English nobleman and courtier .
Frederick , Duke of Opava ( Czech : Bedřich Opavský ; German : Friedrich von Troppau ; c. 1440 -- 1470 ) was a member of the Opava branch of the Bohemian Přemyslid dynasty .
Lt . Col . Karol Gwido Langer ( Zsolna , Austria - Hungary , 2 September 1894 -- 30 March 1948 , Kinross , Scotland ) was , from at least mid-1931 , chief of the Polish General Staff 's Cipher Bureau , which from December 1932 decrypted Germany 's military Enigma - machine ciphers .
Dorothy Jessie Tait ( 6 March 1928 -- 14 January 2010 ) was a prolific English ceramic designer working in the Stoke - on - Trent pottery industries , most prominently for Midwinter , from the 1940s to the 1980s .
Austin Conrad Shafer ( 1844 - -1944 ) was a schoolteacher , property owner and real estate agent who served on the Los Angeles , California , Common Council , the legislative branch of the city , in the 19th Century and was president of that city 's school board .
Ludmila Jeske - Choińska - Mikorska ( 1849 -- 2 November 1898 ) was a Polish singer and composer .
Philippe Parrot ( born 13 May 1831 in Excideuil , died 1894 ) was a French painter .
Cristóbal de León ( died 1729 ) was a Spanish painter , active near Seville .
Jagjit Singh Lyallpuri ( 10 April 1917 , Lyallpur - 27 May 2013 , Ludhiana ) was an Indian politician .
Squadron Leader Robert Kronfeld , AFC ( 5 May 1904 -- 12 February 1948 ) was an Austrian - born gliding champion and sailplane designer of the 1920s and 30s .
Stoffel Muller ( 1776 -- 3 August 1833 ) was a Dutchman who led a small Protestant sect in the early nineteenth century .
Jean Armand de Maillé - Brézé , Duke of Fronsac , Marquis of Brézé ( 18 October 1619 -- 14 June 1646 ) was a French admiral .
Otto Lagerfeld ( 20 September 1881 in Hamburg -- 4 July 1967 in Baden - Baden ) was a German businessman , who in 1919 founded the German company Lagerfeld & Co , which imported evaporated milk .
William Nantlais Williams ( 30 December 1874 -- 18 June 1959 ) , better known simply as Nantlais , was a Welsh poet and a Presbyterian Christian leader during the 1904 - 1905 Welsh Revival .
Sir Edward Stafford Howard KCB , DL , JP ( 28 November 1851 -- 8 April 1916 ) , was a British Liberal politician and magistrate .
José María Pasquini Durán ( Salta , 1939 -- Buenos Aires , 13 February 2010 ) was an Argentine journalist , writer , teacher , political analyst , and one of the main writers of the newspaper Pagina 12 , that he helped to found .
Leon Greenman ( 18 December 1910 -- 7 March 2008 ) was a British anti - fascism campaigner and survivor of the Auschwitz concentration camp .
Anna Maria Seymour or Mrs Seymour ( c. 1692 -- 10 July 1723 ) was a British actress
Ram Karmi ( Hebrew : רם כרמי‎ ; 1931 -- 11 April 2013 ) was a leading Israeli architect .
Finbarr Dwyer ( often misspelled as `` Finbar Dwyer '' ) ( 20 September 1946 -- 8 February 2014 ) was a traditional Irish accordion player from the famed Dwyer musical family .
Sir James Malcolm Monteith Erskine ( 18 July 1863 -- 5 November 1944 ) , sometimes referred to as J. M. M. Erskine , was a British politician .
John Depeden ( died 1460 ) was a Canon of Windsor from 1430 to 1460 .
Heinrich Lienhard died on 19 December 1903 after a brief illness and , like his wife and seven of their children , was buried in Nauvoo 's Presbyterian cemetery .
Helias de Say ( died 1165 ) , also called Hellias , was a Norman nobleman who lived in Clun near Shrewsbury , along the medieval Welsh Marches .
Frank Hedges Butler ( 17 December 1855 -- 27 November 1928 ) was a British wine merchant , and a foundering member of the Aero Club of Great Britain .
James Mirams ( 2 January 1839 -- 21 June 1916 ) was an Australian politician who was jailed for fraud .
Miles Salley ( died 1516 ) was a late 15th - century Abbot of Eynsham Abbey and Abingdon Abbey and an early 16th - century Bishop of Llandaff .
Bartlett Mullins ( born 13 August 1904 in Crosby , Lancashire -- died 15 May 1992 in Devon ) was a British actor .
David Bathurst ( 15 December 1937 - 20 September 1992 ) was the chairman of the auction house Christie Manson & Woods .
Matej Ninoslav ( died 1250 ) was the Ban of Bosnia in the period of 1232 - -50 .
Hugh Bonfoy ( c. 1720 -- 12 March 1762 ) was a naval officer and colonial governor of Newfoundland .
Philip Avery Stone ( 1893 - -1967 ) , also known as Phil Stone , was an attorney from Oxford , Mississippi and mentor to William Faulkner .
Elisha H. Groves ( 1797 - -1867 ) , at times misidentified as Elisha B. Groves , was a 19th - century mid - level leader in The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter - day Saints ( LDS Church ) and a member of the first Utah Territorial Legislature .
Jóhannes Jónsson ( 31 August 1940 -- 27 July 2013 ) was an Icelandic businessman and one of the founders of the investment company Baugur Group , which applied for bankruptcy protection in February 2009 .
Sofija Korkutytė ( 22 July 1939 -- 23 May 2000 ) was a Lithuanian rower who won three European titles in the eights event in 1963 , 1965 and 1967 ; she finished second in 1964 and 1966 .
William Mair ( died 14 October 1897 ) was a politician in the British colony of South Australia .
Fred Ayers ( 8 May 1912 -- 18 August 1986 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Rosanne Kohake , née Lipps ( b. 20 July 1951 in Cincinnati , Ohio , U.S.A. - d. 7 March 2012 in Cincinnati , Ohio , U.S.A. ) was an American writer , who has written three historical romance novels published from 1984 to 1985 by Avon Books .
Eilís Dillon ( 7 March 1920 -- 19 July 1994 ) was an Irish author of 50 books .
Peter van de Velde or Peter van den Velde ( 1634 -- after 1723 ) , was a Flemish Baroque marine painter who lived well into the 18th century .
George Gulliver ( 1804 - 1882 ) , was an English anatomist and physiologist .
Pasquale Amati ( 1716 - -1796 ) was an Italian antiquary , born at Savignano di Romagna ( now Savignano sul Rubicone - province of Forlì ) , and educated at Cesena , Rimini , and Rome .
Frederic Festus Kelly ( died 3 June 1883 ) was a high official in the British Post Office .
Herbert ' Ertl ' Erhard ( 6 July 1930 -- 3 July 2010 ) , also known as Herbert Erhardt , was a German footballer .
John Chetwode Eustace ( b. in Ireland , c. 1762 ; d. at Naples , Italy , 1 August 1815 ) was an Anglo - Irish Catholic priest and antiquary .
Charles Stansfeld Jones ( 1886 - -1950 ) , aka Frater Achad , was an occultist and ceremonial magician .
Sir Mark Masterman - Sykes , 3rd Baronet ( 20 August 1771 -- 16 February 1823 ) , born Mark Sykes , was an English landowner and politician , known as a book - collector .
Maya Dolas ( Marathi : माया डोळस ) , ( 15 October 1966 -- 16 November 1991 ) , born Mahindra Dolas , was an Indian underworld gangster who used to work for the D - Company don , Dawood Ibrahim .
Michail Stasinopoulos ( Greek : Μιχαήλ Στασινόπουλος ; 27 July 1903 -- 31 October 2002 ) was a Greek jurist .
Henry Aaron Stern ( Unterreichenbach , near Gelnhausen , 11 April 1820 - Hackney , 13 May 1885 ) was an Anglican missionary and captive in Abyssinia .
Fiorenzo di Lorenzo ( c. 1440 -- 1522 ) was an Italian painter , of the Umbrian school .
Lotika Sarkar ( 4 January 1923 -- 23 February 2013 ) was a noted Indian feminist , social worker , educator and lawyer , who was a pioneer in the field of women 's studies and women 's rights in India .
Ruaidhrí Gilla Dubh Ó Seachnasaigh Irish Knight and Chief of the Name ( died 1569 ) ; known in English as Sir Roger O'Shaughnessy .
Ma Wanfu ( 1849 - -1934 ) , also known as Hajji Guoyuan 果园哈只 , was a Dongxiang Imam of the village Guoyuan ( 果园村 ) in Hezhou ( present day Dongxiang Autonomous County in Linxia Hui Autonomous Prefecture , Gansu province ) .
John McLeish ( 19 December 1926 -- 10 December 2005 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Thomas Mar Makarios ( born on 26 May 1926 in India and died on 23 Feb 2008 in Newcastle , England ) was the founder of the diocese of the United States and Canada of the Malankara Orthodox Church .
Sir William Morice , 1st Baronet ( c. 1628 -- 7 February 1690 ) , of Werrington ( then in Devon but now in Cornwall ) , was an English Member of Parliament .
Hans Gillesberger ( 29 November 1909 -- 4 March 1986 ) was an Austrian choir director .
An alleged member of the Irish Republican Army , William James Carson was killed in 1979 .
Henry VI the Good ( also known as of Wrocław ) ( Polish : Henryk VI Dobry or Wrocławski ) ( 18 March 1294 -- 24 November 1335 ) was a Duke of Wrocław since 1296 ( with his brothers as co - rulers until 1311 ) .
In June 2004 , the Maoists blocked the pipe that brought water to the district capital , and Dekendra Thapa and other journalists walked to the Maoist - controlled area to try to persuade them to open it .
Ludovico Racaniello ( 1352 - -1441 ) was an Italian condottiero active in Tuscany .
Tadeusz Estreicher ( 19 December 1871 -- 8 April 1952 ) was a Polish chemist , historian and cryogenics pioneer .
Sir Nicholas Fairfax ( 1498/99 - -1571 ) , of Gilling Castle and Walton , Yorkshire , was an English politician .
Eugene Grebenik CB , known as `` Grebby '' ( 20 July 1919 , Kiev -- 14 October 2001 , Oxford ) was a central figure in the development of demography in Britain and the first director of the British Civil Service College .
Loingsech mac Flaithbertaig ( died 754 ) was a chief of the Cenél Conaill of the northern Uí Néill in modern County Donegal .
Richard Handcock , 4th Baron Castlemaine ( 25 July 1826 -- 26 April 1892 ) , styled The Honourable from 1840 to 1869 , was an Irish peer .
Muttawmp ( ? - died September , 1676 in Boston ) was a sachem of the Nipmuc Indians in the middle of 17th century , originally based in Quaboag .
Rosaire Gauthier ( 28 February 1904 -- 15 December 1992 ) was a Canadian politician , the mayor of Chicoutimi , Quebec and a Liberal party member of the Canadian House of Commons .
Jang Ja - yeon ( Hangul : 장자연 ; 25 January 1982 -- 7 March 2009 ) was a South Korean actress .
Alexander Balloch Grosart ( 18 June 1827 -- 16 March 1899 ) was a Scottish clergyman and literary editor .
Walter Feist ( 1907 -- 1977 ) was a German luger who competed from the late 1920s to the late 1950s .
Elizabeth Home , Countess of Home ( née Gibbons ; 1703/1704 -- 15 January 1784 ) was a Jamaican - English heiress .
Otto Kröber ( 22 May 1882 in Hamburg--5 January 1969 ) was a German entomologist specialising in Diptera .
Du Ji ( early 160s -- 224 ) , courtesy name Bohou , was a commandery governor who lived in the late Eastern Han Dynasty .
Lieutenant General Mohammed Saad Eddin Mamoun , usually known in English as Saad Mamoun ( 14 May 1922 -- 28 October 2000 ) , is an Egyptian war hero and was the commander of the Egyptian Second Army during the Yom Kippur War .
Herbert Windsor , 2nd Viscount Windsor ( 1 May 1703 -- 25 January 1758 ) , styled The Honourable Herbert Windsor until 1738 , was a British landowner and politician .
Marion Ryan ( 4 February 1931 -- 15 January 1999 ) was a popular British singer in the 1950s .
Conrad Bonnevie - Svendsen ( 11 April 1898 -- 12 June 1983 ) was a Norwegian priest and government minister .
Lucas Malet was the pseudonym of Mary St Leger Kingsley ( 4 June 1852 -- 1931 ) , a Victorian novelist .
Louise Marion Bosworth ( July 11 , 1881 -- August 1982 ) was an American researcher at the Women 's Educational and Industrial Union ( WEIU ) who extensively surveyed working women in order to learn about their working and living conditions .
Arthur Hedley ( 12 November 1905 -- 8 November 1969 ) was a British musicologist , scholar and biographer of Frédéric Chopin .
William Stourton , 11th Baron Stourton ( c. 1594 - 25 April 1672 ) was the son of Edward Stourton and Frances Tresham .
Magnus Heimannsberg ( 1881 - -1962 ) was the commander of the Berlin Schutzpolizei during the Weimar Republic , and played a pivotal role in protecting the republic against political extremists to the right and left ( i.e. , against Nazis and Communists ) .
Susan Kodicek ( born Zuzana Oprsalova , 1948 - 2011 ) , also known as Hannah Kodicek , was a Czech actress whose most prominent role was as Irina in Tinker Tailor Soldier Spy .
Carl Gabriel Adelsköld , ( 6 October 1830 -- 4 November 1914 ) , was a Swedish painter .
Lambert Folkers ( died 1761 ) was a baker and politician .
Antonio di Ciocco ( died July 1984 ) was a politician in Montreal , Quebec , Canada .

Sir Patrick Threipland , 1st Baronet ( died after 18 February 1689 ) was a Scottish merchant and politician .
James Handford ( 1 February 1890 - 14 August 1948 ) was an English cricketer for Derbyshire .
Ciril Bergles ( 18 July 1934 -- 25 August 2013 ) was a Slovene poet , essayist and translator .
Jacob Willekens or Wilckens ( 1564 -- 1649 ) was a Dutch admiral on a fleet to the Dutch Indies , and a herring seller , who went to sea again at the age of fifty for the Dutch West Indies Company .
Sir William Knighton , 1st Baronet GCH ( 1776 -- 11 October 1836 ) was Private Secretary to the Sovereign , George IV 1822 - -1830 .
Sir Cecil Dennistoun Burney , 3rd Baronet ( 1923 - 2002 ) was a British businessman and Zambian politician .
William Murray , Marquess of Tullibardine ( 14 April 1689 -- 9 July 1746 ) was a Scottish army officer and Jacobite leader .
Clamor Heinrich Abel ( 1634 -- 25 July 1696 ) was a German composer , violinist and organist .
Mikael Sehul ( Tigrinya `` Mikael the Astute '' -- his name at birth was Blatta Mikael ; c. 1691 -- 23 June 1779 ) was a Ras or governor of Tigray 1748 - -71 and again from 1772 until his death .
John Sidney , 6th Earl of Leicester , PC ( 14 February 1680 -- 27 September 1737 ) was a British MP and Privy Councillor during the Georgian era .
Ferdinando Orlandi ( 7 October 1774 -- 5 January 1848 ) , also referred to as Orland and Orlando .
Nafisa Joseph ( 3 March 1978 -- 29 July 2004 ) was an Indian model and MTV video jockey .
Rhoemetalces II was a Client Ruler in association with his mother Antonia Tryphaena of the Odrysian kingdom of Thrace under the Romans from 18 to 38 .
Tanya Halesworth ( 1935 -- 8 October 2008 ) was best known as an Australian television personality , but was also a teacher , actor , public relations adviser and manager , and psychologist .
James Bovell ( 1817 - 1880 ) was a prominent Canadian physician , microscopist , educator , theologian and minister .
Jon Simonssøn ( 9 November 1512 -- 29 July 1575 ) or Jon Simonsson , was a Norwegian city manager , lawspeaker and a humanist .
Dénis Lindbohm ( 1927 - -2005 ) was a Swedish author and occultist and is considered one of the founders of Swedish science fiction .
Carl Heinrich Hopffer ( 1810 - -1876 ) was a German entomologist who specialised in Lepidoptera .
James Jolley , was born in 1813 in Argyllshire , Scotland , and died on 28 November 1892 in Hamilton , Ontario .
Constantino Romero García ( 29 May 1947 -- 12 May 2013 ) was a Spanish TV and radio host and actor .
Robert James Martin Wight ( 26 November 1913 -- 15 July 1972 ) , also known as Martin Wight , was one of the foremost British scholars of International Relations in the twentieth century .
George Forbes , 4th Earl of Granard ( 15 March 1710 -- 16 October 1769 ) was an Irish soldier and politician .
Major Wilhelm Trapp or Papa Trapp ( Nitzow , 4 September 1889 -- executed 18 December 1948 , Siedlce ) was a career policeman , the commander of the Reserve Police Battalion 101 formation of Nazi German Ordnungspolizei ( Order Police ) .
Bernard Knowles ( 20 February 1900 -- 12 February 1975 ) was an English film director , producer , cinematographer and screenwriter .
Dmytro Klyachkivsky ( Ukrainian : Клячківський Дмитро ( Роман ) ; 4 November 1911 - 12 February 1945 ) , also known by his pseudonyms Klym Savur , Okhrim , Bilash , was a colonel of the Ukrainian Insurgent Army ( UPA ) , first head - commander of the UPA - North .
William Tallack ( 1831 - -1908 ) was an English prison reformer and writer .
Sir John Dineley Goodere , 2nd Baronet ( c. 1680 -- 1741 ) was a British aristocrat and murder victim .
Joseph Paton Maclay , 1st Baron Maclay PC ( 6 September 1857 -- 24 April 1951 ) , known as Sir Joseph Maclay , 1st Baronet , from 1914 to 1922 , was a Scottish businessman and public servant .
Frederick Grant Dunn ( 1905 - -1959 ) was an American criminal , burglar and bank robber whose career spanned over four decades from 1919 until his mysterious death in 1959 .
Leo George Hertlein ( 1898 -- 1972 ) was an American paleontologist and malacologist who studied the Recent and fossil mollusks of the eastern Pacific Ocean .
Aldo Buzzi ( 10 August 1910 -- 9 October 2009 ) was an author and architect .
Guy Hastings ( died 15 March 1941 ) was an English - born actor who worked extensively in Australian theatre , radio and film .
Bartholomew of Brescia ( b. probably in the second half of the 12th century at Brescia ; died 1258 ) was an Italian canonist .
Đào Sĩ Chu ( 1911 - 1974 ) was a Vietnamese painter who studied in France and was known for following the traditional style of the EBAI school .
Benjamin Huntsman Williams ( 10 June 1944 -- 3 August 1978 ) was a Rhodesian first - class cricketer .
David Skae ( 5 July 1814 -- 18 April 1873 ) was a Scottish physician who specialised in psychological medicine .
Sylvia Breamer ( 9 June 1897 -- 7 June 1943 ) was an Australian - born actress who performed in American silent motion pictures beginning in 1917 .
Naomi Datta , FRS ( 17 September 1922 -- 30 November 2008 ) was a distinguished British geneticist .
Julio Ugarte y Ugarte ( b. Lima , 1890 , d. Brazil , 17 August 1949 ) was a Peruvian writer and founder of the Society of Transcendental Philosophy in Brazil .
Gaspar Casal ( 1681 - -1759 ) was a Catalan physician remembered for describing the Casal collar in pellagra .
August Högn ( 2 August 1878 -- 13 December 1961 ) was a German teacher , composer and historian .
Maruša Krese ( 13 April 1947 -- 7 January 2013 ) was a Slovene poet , writer and journalist .
María Jesús Alvarado Rivera ( 27 May 1878 -- 6 May 1971 ) was a Peruvian rebel feminist , educator , journalist , writer and social activist .
Alice Thorner ( USA ? , 1917 -- France , 24 August 2005 ) was an American - born social scientist and statistician whose main research effort seems to have been partly devoted to the role assigned to women in the Indian society .
Hans Paludan Smith Schreuder ( 18 June 1817 - 27 June 1882 ) was a 19th century Norwegian missionary who developed a close relationship with both the Zulu and British authorities .
Johannes Pieter de Frey or Freij ( February 1 , 1770 -- 1834 ) was a Dutch printmaker , painter and publisher .
Nigel Stepney ( 14 November 1958 -- 2 May 2014 ) was a British mechanic .
Sir George Hayter ( 17 December 1792 -- 18 January 1871 ) was a notable English painter , specialising in portraits and large works involving in some cases several hundred individual portraits .
Ernest Sheldon Friel ( 1888 -- 2 February 1970 ) , was an Irish dentist who was the first specialist orthodontist to practice in the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland , and the second in Europe , going on to become the first Professor of Orthodontics in Europe .
Beer Léon Fould ( 5 March 1767 -- 14 May 1855 ) was a French - Jewish banker , and the founder of the Fould banking dynasty .
Woldemar Ludwig Grenser ( 2 January 1812 , Dresden - Neustadt - 2 June 1872 , Dresden ) was a German obstetrician .
William Henry Ralph Reader CBE ( 25 May 1903 -- 18 May 1982 ) , known as Ralph Reader , was a British actor , theatrical producer and songwriter , known for staging the original Gang Show , a variety entertainment presented by members of the Scouting movement , and for leading community singing at FA Cup Finals .
Minouche Barelli ( 13 December 1947 -- 20 February 2004 ) , born Mary - Pierre Barelli , was a French singer , best - known internationally for her participation in the 1967 Eurovision Song Contest .
Karvannan ( died 13 February 2015 ) was an Indian film director , producer and screenwriter who worked on Tamil films .
Matthew O'Neill , 1st Baron Dungannon ( Irish : Feardorcha Ó Néill ) ( 1520 - 1558 ) was an Irish aristocrat .
Terri Sharp ( born March 24 , 1948 -- 17 December 2015 ) was a gold record winning American songwriter and vocalist .
John Dennys ( died 1609 ) , a poet and fisherman , pioneered Angling poetry in England .
Jean Roemer ( born in England about 1815 ; died in Lenox , Massachusetts , 31 August 1892 ) was a Dutch soldier and a United States professor of French language and literature at the City College of New York .
Elizabeth Tyldesley ( or Clare Mary Ann , OSC ) ( 1585 - -1654 ) was a 17th - century abbess at the Poor Clare Convent at Gravelines .
Richard de Redvers , 2nd Earl of Devon ( died 1162 ) was Earl of Devon from 1155 until his death and was feudal baron of Plympton in Devon .
Amir Chupan , also known as Choban or Coban ( امیر چوپان سلدوز ) , ( d. November 1327 ) , was a Chupanid noble of the Ilkhanate , and nominal general of the Mongol Empire .
George Henry Walton ( 3 June 1867 Glasgow -- 10 December 1933 London ) , was a noted Scottish architect and designer of remarkable diversity .
Sir Alexander Dundas Young Arbuthnott ( 1789 -- 8 May 1871 ) was a British Rear Admiral during the Victorian era .
Maria Murărescu , ( 1 October 1947 -- 30 January 2014 ) better known as Marioara Murărescu , was a well - known Romanian producer of folkloric television shows , being renowned for TVR 's Tezaur folcloric .
Silas Taylor ( 1624 - -1678 ) was an English army officer of the Parliamentarian forces , known also as an antiquary and musical composer .
Avraham Chaim Naeh ( 1890 - -1954 ) was a Lubavitcher chassid and major posek ( halachic authority ) active during the first half of twentieth century .
John E. Pickering ( 27 April 1918 -- 19 September 1997 ) was a pioneer in the field of radiobiology , aviation medicine and space medicine and a Colonel in the United States Air Force .
Thomas Rawson Birks ( 28 September 1810 -- 19 July 1883 ) was an English theologian and controversialist , who figured in the debate to try to resolve theology and science .
Onoulphus , also Onoulf , Unulf and Hunulf ( died 493 ) was a general of the late fifth century of Scirian origin .
Giovanni Antonio Rigatti ( c. 1613 -- 24 October 1648 ) was an Italian composer and choirmaster of the early Baroque period .
William Prest ( 1 April 1832 -- 10 February 1885 ) was a cricketer and footballer born in York .
John Patrick Hayden ( 25 April 1863 -- 3 July 1954 ) was an Irish nationalist politician and MP in the House of Commons of the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland and as member of the Irish Parliamentary Party represented South Roscommon from 1897 to 1918 .
Thomas Michael Whalen III , also known as Thomas M. Whalen III , and more simply , Tom Whalen , ( 1934 - -2002 ) was an attorney and politician , a three - term mayor of Albany , New York , serving from 1983 to 1993 .
General Sir George Digby Barker GCB ( Chinese Translated Name : 白加 ) ( 1833 -- 15 April 1914 ) was a British soldier and colonial administrator .
Manuel Pineda Munoz ( 1804 -- 1891 ) , Mexican Army officer that led the Mexican resistance to the forces of the United States in Baja California Sur , during the Mexican American War .
Pieter Leermans ( ca.1635 , Leiden -- 1706 ) , was a Dutch Golden Age painter .
Francis Scott , 2nd Duke of Buccleuch KT FRS ( 11 January 1695 -- 22 April 1751 ) was a Scottish nobleman .
Anna Catherine of Nassau - Ottweiler ( 31 January 1653 in Ottweiler -- 15 February 1731 in Ottweiler ) was a daughter of John Louis , Count of Nassau - Ottweiler and his wife , Countess Palatine Dorothea Catherine of Birkenfeld - Bischweiler .
Sonam Drakpa ( Tibetan : བསོད་ནམས་གྲགས་པ , Wylie : Sod nam grags pa , 1359 - -1408 ) was a regent of Central Tibet who ruled in 1381 - -1385 .
Georgia Caine ( 30 October 1876 -- 4 April 1964 ) was an American actress who performed both on Broadway and in more than 80 films in her 51 year career .
Edmund Hobhouse ( 1817 - -1904 ) was the English - born bishop of Nelson , New Zealand , and an antiquary .
Leo Eloesser ( July 29 , 1881-October 4 , 1976 ) , a noted thoracic surgeon , was born in San Francisco .
John Lewis Petit ( 1736 - -1780 ) was an English physician and Fellow of the Royal Society .
Frank Considine ( 1 April 1934 -- 4 March 2001 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played in the Victorian Football League during the 1950s .
Johann Christian Siebenkees ( 20 August 1753 -- 22 November 1841 ) was a German jurist , poet , and writer .
Spyromilios ( Greek : Σπυρομήλιος ; 1800 - -1880 ) or Spyros Milios ( Σπύρος Μήλιος ) , was a Greek revolutionary , general and politician .
Stephan Bergler ( ca . 1680 - 1738 ) was a Transylvanian Saxon classical scholar and antiquarian .
Batty Langley ( Twickenham , Middlesex , baptised 14 September 1696 -- London 1751 ) was an English garden designer , and prolific writer who produced a number of engraved designs for `` Gothick '' structures , summerhouses and garden seats in the years before the mid-18th century .
Horacio Casarín Garcilazo ( 25 May 1918 -- 10 April 2005 ) was a Mexican football player and coach who established himself as one of his country 's most popular sports figures in the 1940s and 50 's .
Sheila Beryl Grant Attenborough , The Lady Attenborough ( née Sim ; 5 June 1922 -- 19 January 2016 ) , known professionally by her maiden name Sheila Sim , was an English film and theatre actress .
Adina Beg Khan ( died 15 September , 1758 Lahore , ) was the governor of the Punjab including Lahore , Jalandhar and Multan for 1755 to 1758 .
Trojden II of Płock ( pl : Trojden II płocki ; 1403/06 - 25 July 1427 ) , was a Polish prince member of the House of Piast from the Masovian branch .
Guy M. Brandborg ( 1893 - -1977 ) was supervisor of Montana 's Bitterroot National Forest from 1935 to 1955 and later became a conservation activist .
Adolphus Ballard ( 22 February 1867 -- 1915 ) was an English historian and solicitor .
Sir Daniel Donne ( or Dunn ) ( died 1617 ) was an English jurist .
Li Gui ( Chinese : 李軌 ; died 619 ) , courtesy name Chuze ( 處則 ) , was the emperor of a short - lived state of Liang , which he established at the end of the Chinese Sui Dynasty .
Hilde Sessak ( 27 July 1915 -- 17 April 2003 ) was a German actress who appeared in more than ninety film and television series during her career .
Félix Pierre Jousseaume ( 12 April 1835 Charente - Maritime -- 3 November 1921 ) was a French zoologist and malacologist .
Rose Quong ( 15 August 1879 -- 14 December 1972 ) was a Chinese Australian actor , performer and writer .
James Kinlay ( 17 October 1926 -- 8 June 2010 ) was a Scottish journalist and assistant editor of the Sunday Express , where for thirty years he was the right - hand man of the late editor in chief John Junor .
Ota Čermák ( 1919 - -1963 ) was a Czech organist ( Hammond organ ) and composer of easy listening music .
Madudan mac Gadhra Mór ( died 1008 ) was the namesake and ancestor of the Ó Madden family .
Matti Makkonen ( 16 April 1952 -- 26 June 2015 ) was a Finnish engineer in the field of mobile communications .
William Joy ( fl . 1329 -- 1348 ) was an English master mason , or architect , of the Decorated Gothic style , known for his work on several English cathedrals .
İbrahim Şinasi ( 5 August 1826 -- 13 September 1871 ) was a pioneering Ottoman author , journalist , and translator , and newspaper editor .
Gael Turnbull ( 7 April 1928 -- 2 July 2004 ) was a Scottish poet who was an important precursor of the British Poetry Revival .
Ethel Léontine Gabain ( 26 March 1883 Le Havre - 1950 London ) was a French - English artist .
Liliya Vasilchenko ( Russian : Ли́лия Васи́льченко ; 8 June 1962 in Novosibirsk -- 19 December 2011 ) was a former Soviet cross country skier who competed from 1982 to 1986 , training at Trudovye Rezervy in Novosibirsk .
Andreas Rudolph Bodenstein von Karlstadt ( 1486 -- 24 December 1541 ) , better known as Andreas Karlstadt or Andreas Carlstadt or Karolostadt , was a German Christian theologian during the Protestant Reformation .
John de Welles , 5th Baron Welles ( 1352 - -1421 ) was an English soldier and noble .
Robert Mapletoft ( 1609 - -1677 ) was an English churchman and academic , Master of Pembroke College , Cambridge and Dean of Ely .
Kurt Lück ( 1900 - -1942 ) was a German historian and SS Obersturmbannführer .
William Penney , Lord Kinloch ( 1801 - -1872 ) was a Scottish judge ,
Roy Kitchin ( 6 December 1926 -- 1997 ) was a British sculptor and art educator who worked primarily with steel .
Abdul Salam Sabrah ( Arabic : عبد السلام صبره‎ ) ( 1912 - -2012 ) was the acting Prime Minister of the Yemen Arab Republic three times .
Brita Biörn , or Brita Biörns ( 1667 - 1745 ) , was a Swedish cunning woman .
Anne François Augustin de La Bourdonnaye ( 18 July 1745 -- 6 October 1793 ) briefly commanded three armies during the early years of the War of the First Coalition .
Alessandro Casagrande ( 1922 -- 1964 ) was an Italian composer and pianist .
Samuel Gott ( 20 January 1614 -- 18 December 1671 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons of England between 1645 and 1648 and between 1660 and 1661 .
Edvin Hevonkoski ( 10 September 1923 , Alavus -- 8 September 2009 , Vaasa ) was a Finnish sculptor and contemporary artist who lived his later years in Vaasa .
Amina Chifupa ( 20 May 1981 -- 26 June 2007 ) was a Tanzanian CCM politician and a special seat Member of Parliament .
Benvenuto Campesani ( c. 1250 -- 1323 ) was a Vicentine poet and notary .
Asep Sunandar Sunarya ( 3 September 1955 -- 31 March 2014 ) was a Sundanese wayang golek dalang ( Sundanese rod puppet master ) .
Paul Jenisch , ( also known as Paulus Jenisch , Jenisius or Jenischius ; 1551 - 9 November 1612 ) was a German Lutheran pastor and academic .
William James Blacklock ( 3 March 1816 -- 12 March 1858 ) was an English landscape painter , painting scenery in Cumbria , the Lake District and the Scottish Borders .
Sir Douglas Osmond ( 27 June 1914 -- 20 April 2006 ) was the chief constable of Shropshire Constabulary and later Hampshire Constabulary .
Elizabeth Upton , Baroness Templetown ( 1746/47 - 1823 ) was an English artist whose designs were used by Josiah Wedgwood the potter .
Ímar ( Old Norse : Ívarr ; died c. 873 ) was a Viking leader in Ireland and Scotland in the mid - late ninth century who founded the Uí Ímair dynasty , and whose descendants would go on to dominate the Irish Sea region for several centuries .
Claude Dufourmentel ( 1915 - -2012 ) is a plastic surgeon from Paris who described a skin flap for reconstructing rhomboid defects in 1962 .
Gary Catalano ( 30 October 1947 -- 8 December 2002 ) was an Australian poet and art critic .
Count Henry of Stolberg ( 2 January 1509 at Stolberg Castle in Stolberg -- 12 November 1572 at Stolberg Castle ) was a German nobleman .
Hyacinth Graf Strachwitz von Groß - Zauche und Camminetz ( 30 July 1893 -- 25 April 1968 ) was a German Army officer of aristocratic descent .
Seosamh Ó Duibhginn ( 1914 - -1994 ) was an Irish editor and publisher who wrote mostly in the Irish language .
Poghos Bek - Pirumyan ( Armenian : Պողոս Բեկ-Փիրումյան ; 8 June 1856 -- 19 January 1921 ) was an Armenian military commander .
Sir Oliver Napier ( 11 July 1935 -- 2 July 2011 ) was the first leader of the Alliance Party of Northern Ireland .
Kari Diesen ( née Heide - Steen ; 24 June 1914 -- 18 March 1987 ) was a Norwegian singer and revue actress .
John McDonogh ( 29 December 1779 - -26 October 1850 ) was a United States entrepreneur and philanthropist , described as miserly , controversial , and eccentric .
Dafydd Ddu o Hiraddug ( died 1371 ) , also known as Dafydd Ddu Athro o Hiraddug , was a Welsh language poet , grammarian , and cleric in the diocese of Llanelwy ( St Asaph ) .
Henry `` Ole Pete '' Peterson ( ca.1854 - 1934 ) is an American folk Legend and `` Big Man '' , who lived in Port Tampa , Florida .
Perpète Evrard ( 1662 - -1727 ) was a Flemish painter of portraits and miniatures , born at Dinant and employed at several foreign courts .
William Ross , 12th Lord Ross ( c.1656 -- 15 March 1738 ) , was a Scottish nobleman , soldier and politician .
John Frederick , Prince of Schwarzburg - Rudolstadt ( 8 January 1721 in Rudolstadt -- 10 July 1767 in ibid ) was the ruling Prince of Schwarzburg - Rudolstadt from 1744 to 1767 .
John Busby ( 24 March 1765 -- 10 May 1857 ) was an English - born surveyor and civil engineer , active in Australia .
Ernesta De Mola , best known as Tina De Mola ( 28 October 1923 - 18 April 2012 ) , was an Italian actress , singer and television personality .
António Carvalho de Silva Porto ( 11 November 1850 -- 11 June 1893 ) was a Portuguese naturalist painter .
Per Tønder ( 6 April 1911 -- 18 July 2015 ) was a Norwegian priest and politician for the Labour Party .
Gyula Moór ( 11 August 1888 -- 3 February 1950 ) was a Hungarian jurist , Professor , Member of Parliament , President of the Hungarian Academy of Sciences between 1945 and 1946 .
Roger Pepys ( 3 May 1617 - 4 October 1688 ) was an English lawyer and politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1661 to 1678 .
William Frederick Rock ( 29 January or 8 February 1801 -- 1890 ) founded the London publishers Rock & Co. , who published steel engraved vignette views in the form of cards , fancy stationery , and books and booklets .
Leonard Kip ( 1826 - -1906 ) was a scion of Old New York who joined the Gold Rush to California for a year of adventure before returning to his home state for a long career in law and literature .
Robert Lloyd Praeger ( 25 August 1865 -- 5 May 1953 ) was an Irish naturalist , writer and librarian .
Edward Ernest Hughes ( 7 February 1877 -- 23 December 1953 ) was the first professor of history at University College , Swansea .
Michele Ferrero ( Italian pronunciation : ( miˈkɛːle ferˈrɛːro ) ; 26 April 1925 -- 14 February 2015 ) was an Italian entrepreneur .
Cecciolo Gabrielli ( 1375 - June 26 , 1420 ) was an Italian nobleman , self - styled Duke of Gubbio ( Duca di Gubbio or Duca d'Agobbio ) .
Austrovald , Astrobald , and Austrevald ( died 607 ) was the Duke of Aquitaine from 587 .
Boroldai ( or Burulday , Borolday ) , also known as Burundai , ( Cyrillic : Боролдай ) ( died 1262 ) was a notable Mongol general of the mid 13th century .
Dick Bayford ( 10 May 1885 -- 14 August 1939 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Recep Peker died on 2 April 1950 , and was laid to rest at the Edirnekapı Martyr 's Cemetery in Istanbul .
Plautius Quintillus ( died by 175 ) was a Roman Politician that lived in the Roman Empire in the 2nd century .
Sir William Mackworth Young KCSI ( 1840 - -1924 ) was a member of the Indian Civil Service , who became Lieutenant - Governor of the Punjab 1897 - -1902 .
David Bruce Cowan AM ( 15 January 1926 -- 7 April 2011 ) was an Australian politician and Minister of the Crown in the cabinets of Tom Lewis and Sir Eric Willis .
Edward Bigland ( ca . 1620 -- 5 August 1704 ) was an English lawyer and politician .
Sir D'Arcy Wentworth Thompson CB FRS FRSE ( 2 May 1860 -- 21 June 1948 ) was a Scottish biologist , mathematician and classics scholar .
Aisha Abd al - Rahman ( Arabic : عائشة عبد الرحمن ; c. 1913 -- 1 December 1998 ) was an Egyptian author and professor of literature who published under the pen name Bint al - Shati ( `` Daughter of the Riverbank '' ) .
Thomas de Berkeley , 5th Baron Berkeley the Magnificent ( 5 January 1352/53 -- 13 July 1417 ) was an English peer .
Eleanor Evans ( 1893 -- 20 December 1969 ) was a Welsh actress , singer and stage director .
Shankar Vaman Dandekar ( Devanagari : शंकर वामन , उपाख्य सोनोपंत , दांडेकर ; 1896 - 1969 ) was a philosopher and educationist from Maharashtra , India .

James Brunton Stephens ( 17 June 1835 -- 29 June 1902 ) was a Scottish - born Australian poet , author of Convict Once .

Jindřich Pokorný ( 12 April 1927 -- 23 August 2014 ) was a Czech translator , editor and writer .
Jeanne - Marie Chavoin ( 29 August 1786 - 30 June 1858 ) and Jean - Claude Colin together founded the Marist Sisters , a Catholic religious institute of women .
Count Angelo Geraldini ( 1422 - -1486 ) was an Italian humanist and diplomat , who became a bishop .
Russell Kimball ( 1903 - -1979 ) was an American art director who worked on more than a hundred and fifty films and television series during his career .
Thomas Leslie Teevan ( July 1927 -- 11 October 1954 ) was an Ulster Unionist Party politician and lawyer , notable for his extreme youth , brief career , and very early death .
George Chinnery ( Chinese : 錢納利 ; 5 January 1774 -- 30 May 1852 ) was an English painter who spent most of his life in Asia , especially India and southern China .
Franco Sassi ( 26 February 1912 -- 11 November 1993 ) was an Italian painter , printmaker and engraver .
Argyris Chionis ( Greek : Αργύρης Χιόνης ; 22 April 1943 - 25 December 2011 ) was a Greek poet .
Pierre Boquin ( also known as Bouquin , Boucquin , or Petrus Boquinus ; post 1518 --1582 in Lausanne ) was a French Reformed Theologian who played a critical role in the Reformation of the Electoral Palatinate .
Edward Payson Weston ( 1839 - -1929 ) was a notable pedestrian , who was largely responsible for the rise in popularity of the sport in the 1860s and 1870s .
William Beauclerk , 8th Duke of St Albans ( 18 December 1766 -- 17 July 1825 ) was the son of Aubrey Beauclerk , 5th Duke of St Albans .
Malik Ibrahim ( died 7 April 1419 ) , also known as Sunan Gresik or Kakek Bantal , was the first of the Wali Songo , the nine men generally thought to have introduced Islam to Java .
Christie Fuller ( died 15 August 1933 ) was an Australian singer of the late Victorian period .
Robert Elijah Jones ( 1872 -- 1960 ) was an American Bishop of the Methodist Episcopal Church and The Methodist Church in the U.S. , elected in 1920 .
Raden Wijaya ( also known as Nararya Sangramawijaya , regnal name Kertarajasa Jayawardhana ) , Raden Vijaya , ( reigned 1293 - -1309 ) was a Javanese King , the founder and the first monarch of Majapahit empire .
Robert Mackenzie Beverley ( 1798 - 1868 ) was an author , magistrate , and controversialist .
Pedro Angulo ( died 1561 ) was a Spanish Dominican missionary in Guatemala , in the sixteenth century .
K. Sukumaran ( 8 January 1903 -- 18 September 1981 ) , was the Editor of Kerala Kaumudi Daily , the third most circulated newspaper in Malayalam which celebrated its centenary in 2011 .
George Bowman Ferry ( 1851 - -1918 ) was an architect who was a partner in the architectural firm Ferry & Clas .
Peter Mathers ( 1931 in England -- 8 November 2004 in Melbourne ) was an English - born Australian author and playwright .
Hugh Douglas , Earl of Ormonde ( died 1455 ) was a Scottish Soldier and nobleman , a member of the powerful Black Douglases .
John Sandys ( 1550 or 1555 in Lancashire -- 11 August 1586 executed at Gloucester ) was an English Roman Catholic priest .
Harald Bergseth ( 11 July 1923 -- 28 April 2012 ) was a Norwegian soil scientist .
Kirsten Thorndahl ( also known as Kirsten Granlund ) ( born 9 April 1928 , died 21 September 2007 ) was a Danish badminton player .
George Pike England ( ca.1765 - -1816 ) was one of the main organ builders in England during the late 18th and early 19th centuries .
Magnus Jensen ( 30 January 1902 -- 15 July 1990 ) was a Norwegian historian and educator .

Jean - Allarmet de Brogny ( 1342 - 16 February 1426 ) was a French Cardinal .

Richard Oswald ( 5 November 1880 - 11 September 1963 ) was an Austrian director , producer , and screenwriter .
Göte Strandsjö ( 1916 - -2001 ) was a Swedish hymnwriter .
William Hastings Alexander ( died 22 February 1876 ) was a Hong Kong judiciary officer and acted in many positions including Colonial Secretary , Colonial Treasurer , member of the Legislative Council and Executive Council .

Clemente Primieri ( 12 May 1894 -- 15 February 1981 ) was an Italian general , best known for being the leader of Gruppo di Combattimento Cremona , one of the units of the Italian Co - Belligerent Army which fought alongside the Allies in the latter part of World War II .
Sidney Edward Daniels ( 19 November 1893 -- 25 May 1983 ) , known as Sid Daniels , was a British merchant seaman and the last surviving member of the crew of the RMS Titanic .
Geoffrey Wykes ( 22 November 1890 -- 1 May 1926 ) was an English cricketer who played for Leicestershire .
Amy Ella Blanchard ( June 28 , 1856 -- 1926 ) was an American writer of children 's literature .
François - Xavier Berlinguet ( 4 December 1830 -- 3 August 1916 ) was a Canadian wood - carver , engineer , and architect .

George J. Gruen ( 1877 -- 1911 ) was an American watchmaker who managed the Gruen Watch Co. He was the second son of the founder Dietrich Gruen .
Stanislava Brezovar ( 7 November 1937 -- 18 December 2003 ) , married name Kleiber , was a Slovenian ballerina .
Sir Thomas Estcourt ( c 1570 -- 4 July 1624 ) was an English lawyer and politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1624 .
Mihail Lozanov ( Bulgarian : Михаил Лозанов ; 15 June 1911 -- 3 December 1994 ) , nicknamed The Tank ( Танка , Tanka ) was a Bulgarian footballer .

Gábor Obitz also known as Gábor Óbecsei and Gábor Ormai ( born 18 January 1899 , died 20 March 1953 ) was a Hungarian football player and manager .

Francisco Xavier Sepúlveda ( 1742 -- 1788 ) was a Mexican colonial soldier and patriarch of the prominent Spanish Mexican Sepúlveda family in the early days of Las Californias and Alta California in present day Southern California , United States .
John Lindesay ( died 1751 ) was the founder of the settlement of Cherry Valley , in Otsego County , New York .

Go Uru remained Prime Minister for 24 years until his death in 230 .
Anthony Rushe D.D. ( died 1 April 1577 ) was a Canon of Windsor from 1566 - -1577 and Dean of Chichester from 1570 - -1577 .
Pier Antonio Mezzastris ( or Pierantonio Mezastris ; c. 1430 -- c. 1506 ) was an Italian painter of the Quattrocento , painting in a somewhat provincial style for the time .
Jan Kubiš ( 24 June 1913 -- 18 June 1942 ) was a Czech soldier , one of a team of Czechoslovak British - trained paratroopers sent to assassinate acting Reichsprotektor ( Reich - Protector ) of Bohemia and Moravia , SS - Obergruppenführer Reinhard Heydrich , in 1942 as part of Operation Anthropoid .
Les Devonshire ( 13 June 1926 -- 19 December 2012 ) was an English professional footballer who made more than 100 appearances in The Football League for Chester and Crystal Palace between 1950 and 1955 .
Frederick Wilhelm von Pfalz - Neuburg ( 20 July 1665 -- 23 July 1689 ) , was by birth Count Palatine of Neuburg and Imperial General .
Cajetan Roos ( 1690 , Rome -- 1770 , Vienna ) , was an Italian landscape painter of German descent .

William Pleydell - Bouverie , 3rd Earl of Radnor ( 11 May 1779 -- 9 April 1869 ) , styled Viscount Folkestone until 1828 , was the son of Jacob Pleydell - Bouverie , 2nd Earl of Radnor and Hon . Anne Duncombe .
Benjamin Backhouse ( 1829 - 1904 ) was an architect and politician in Australia .
Julian Phelps Allan , OBE ( 1892 - -1996 ) was a sculptor active between 1923 and 1960 .
Joseph Norman Dolley ( 1860 - -1940 ) was the bank commissioner of State of Kansas who pushed for the passage of the first state securities laws , known as the blue - sky laws .
Clemente Fernández López ( 23 November 1919 -- 17 July 1996 ) , known simply as Clemente , was a Spanish professional footballer who played as a right back .
Baksh Nasikh ( Urdu : امام بخش ناسخ ) ( 1776 - -1838 ) was an Urdu poet of the Mughal era .
Giulio Serafini , J.U.D. ( 12 October 1867 -- 16 July 1938 ) was a Cardinal of the Roman Catholic Church who served as President of the Pontifical Commission for the Authentic Interpretation of Code of Canon Law and Prefect of the Congregation of the Council .
Frederick Ryan ( 1876 -- April 1913 ) , was an Irish , Dublin - born playwright , journalist and socialist .
Charles Catton the younger ( 30 December 1756 -- 24 April 1819 ) was an English topographical artist , illustrator and theatrical scene - painter .
Yao Sui 姚燧(1238 - -1313 ) , writer of Chinese Sanqu poetry and official , was the nephew of the noted official Yao Shu 姚樞 ( 1203 - -1280 ) and uncle of the dramatist and sanqu poet Yao Shouzhong 姚守中.
Henry Lowther , 3rd Earl of Lonsdale ( 27 March 1818 -- 15 August 1876 ) was a British nobleman and Conservative politician , the eldest son of Hon Henry Cecil Lowther and Lady Lucy Sherard .
Tadhgo Crowley ( 24 April 1921 -- 4 December 1963 ) was an Irish Gaelic footballer who played as a centre - back for the Cork senior team .
Pandit Jitendra Abhisheki ( Devanagari : जितेंद्र अभिषेकी ; 21 September 1929 -- 7 November 1998 ) was an Indian vocalist , composer and scholar of Indian classical , semi - classical , and devotional music .

Horace Coignet ( 13 May 1735 - 29 August 1821 ) was a French amateur violinist , singer and composer .

Falak al - Ma'ali Manuchihr ( Persian : فلک آل مالی منوچهر‎ ) , better known as Manuchihr ( died c. 1030 ) , was the ruler of the Ziyarids ( 1012 at the latest -- c. 1030 ) .
Edith Pechey ( 7 October 1845 -- 14 April 1908 ) was one of the first women doctors in the United Kingdom and a campaigner for women 's rights .
Les Marden ( 23 September 1919 -- 20 January 2002 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
René Sim Lacaze ( 27 July 1901 -- 5 January 2000 ) was a French jewellery designer and artist .
Thomas Shadrach James ( 1 September 1859 -- 9 January 1946 ) was a Methodist lay preacher , linguist and herbalist .
Billy Ternent ( 10 October 1899 -- 23 March 1977 ) was a British orchestra leader , popular from the 1940s to the 1970s , best known for backing Frank Sinatra and his work at the London Palladium .
Mary Jane Megquier ( 1813 - -1899 ) participated in the California Gold Rush .
Isaac Hoyle ( 1828 -- 2 September 1911 ) was a British mill - owner and Liberal politician .
Mikhail Dmitriyevich Ageyev ( Russian : Михаил Дмитриевич Агеев ; 14 May 1931 Cheremhovo ( now Irkutsk Oblast ) -- 19 November 2005 ) was a Soviet and Russian scientist , an expert in the field of navigation and control systems of moving objects , a member of the Russian Academy of Sciences ( 1992 ) .
Brigadier John de la Hay Gordon ( 30 March 1887 - 22 December 1959 ) was a British army officer , administrator and diplomat who served as Resident to the Mysore Kingdom from 1937 to 1942 and Chief Commissioner of Coorg Province from 1937 to 1940 .
Titus Petronius Secundus ( 40 - -97 ) was a prefect of the Roman imperial bodyguard , known as the Praetorian Guard , under emperor Domitian , from 94 until 96 .
Syed Muhammad Zauqi Shah ( 1878 - -1951 ) was a Sufist scholar considered a Waliullah or Sufist saint .
Sir John Goodricke , 1st Baronet ( 20 April 1617 - November 1670 ) was an English landowner and politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1661 to 1670 .
Paolo Falciani ( Salerno , 1790 - 1851 ) was an Italian painter , depitcting portraits and history painting in a neoclassical style .
Sir Norman Boyd Kinnear ( 11 August 1882 -- 11 August 1957 ) was a Scottish zoologist and ornithologist .
Richard Goldner ( 23 June 1908 -- 27 September 1991 ) was a Romanian - born , Viennese - trained Australian violist , pedagogue and inventor .
Andrey Yefimovich Martynov ( Андрей Ефимович Мартынов ; 1768 - -1826 ) was a Russian painter and engraver .
Astaman ( also known as Tirtosari ; 1903 - -1980 ) was an Indonesian actor active from the 1910s until the mid-1970s .
Hassan Jandoubi was a French national ( born 1 March 1966 , in Toulouse ) of Tunisian parents , who was killed on 21 September 2001 , in the AZF chemical factory explosion in Toulouse in south - western France .
Juan Cornago ( Johannes Cornago ) ( c. 1400 -- after 1475 ) was a Spanish composer in the transition from Ars nova to the Renaissance .
Du Yuanying ( 杜元穎 ) ( 769 - -833 ) , formally the Baron of Jian'an ( 建安男 ) , was an official of the Chinese dynasty , serving as a chancellor during the reign of Emperor Muzong .
Henry Burnell ( c.1540 - -1614 ) was an Irish judge and politician ; he was briefly Recorder of Dublin and a justice of the Court of King 's Bench .
Commander Herbert Roff Newton OBE DL JP ( 1900 - 1973 ) , was a senior officer in the Royal Navy , a Deputy Lieutenant for Bedfordshire and for many years a Justice of the Peace .
Pithukuli Murugadas ( 25 January 1920 -- 17 November 2015 ) was a religious singer from Tamil Nadu .
Ginés de Lillo ( 1566 , Murcia - 24 January 1630 , Arauco ) , a high - ranking officer in the Spanish army , was in 1603 nominated official visitor to the lands between the towns of Los Cauquenes and Choapa , part of modern day Chile .
Llywelyn Goch ap Meurig Hen ( fl . c. 1350 - 1390 ) was a Welsh language court poet from Merionethshire , in the north west of Wales .
Margaret Catherine Alice Hyson ( also known as M.C. Alice Hyson ; Alice Hyson ) ( Feb. 22 , 1861 - -March 8 , 1915 ) was an American missionary .
Dame Agnes Jekyll DBE ( née Graham ; 12 October 1861 -- 28 January 1937 ) was a Scottish - born British artist , writer and philanthropist .
Eliyahu Eliezer Dessler ( 1892 -- 30 December 1953 ) was an Orthodox rabbi , Talmudic scholar , and Jewish philosopher of the 20th century .
Brett Usher ( 10 December 1946 -- 13 June 2013 ) , was an English actor , writer and ecclesiastical historian .
Steven Anson Coons ( March 7 , 1912 -- August 1979 ) was an early pioneer in the field of computer graphical methods .
Arthur O'Bree ( 31 May 1886 -- 27 December 1943 ) was an Indian - born English cricketer who played first - class cricket for Glamorgan .
Dwivedula Visalakshi ( 1929 -- 7 November 2014 ) , was a well - known Telugu writer .
Caradog Prichard ( 3 November 1904 -- 25 February 1980 ) was a Welsh poet and novelist writing in Welsh .
Živorad Kovačević ( Cyrillic Живорад Ковачевић ; 30 May 1930 -- 23 March 2011 ) was a Yugoslav ( Serbian ) diplomat , politician , NGO activist , academic and writer .
Šimun Milinović ( 24 February 1835 in Lovreć -- 24 March 1910 in Bar ) was a Croatian Roman Catholic priest and Franciscan who was the Serbian Primate ( Primas Serbiae ) and Archbishop of Antivari from 1886 to 1910 .
Cille Gad ( 1675 - 1711 ) , was a Norwegian poet and culture personality .
Bedwyr Lewis Jones ( 1 September 1933 -- 28 August 1992 ) was a Welsh scholar , literary critic and linguist .
Thomas Bagard or Baggard ( died 1544 ) , was an English civilian , nominated in 1525 by Cardinal Wolsey one of the first eighteen canons of his college at Oxford , which afterwards became Christ Church .
Evan Herber Evans ( 5 July 1836 - 30 December 1896 ) , was a Welsh Nonconformist minister .
Ivanuš Pergošić ( 1521 - 1592 ) ( Latin : Ioannes Pergossich ) was early Kajkavian author from Habsburg Slavonia and author of the 1574 translation of Tripartitum ( written by István Werbőczy ) which is the first printed Kajkavian book .
Igor Kipnis ( 27 September 1930 -- 23 January 2002 ) was a well - known American harpsichordist and pianist .
Pedro Pablo Bermúdez Ascarza ( 27 June 1793 -- 30 March 1852 ) was a Peruvian politician and a member of the Peruvian military .
Crowfoot ( 1830 -- 25 April 1890 ) or Isapo - Muxika ( Blackfoot Issapóómahksika , `` Crow - big - foot '' ) was a chief of the Siksika First Nation .
William Sinclair , 2nd Earl of Caithness ( 1459 -- 9 September 1513 ) was a Scottish nobleman
Isidoor Teirlinck ( Zegelsem , 2 January 1851 - Vorst - Brussels , 27 June 1934 ) was a Belgian writer .
Jean Aerts ( 8 September 1907 -- 15 June 1992 ) was a Belgian road bicycle racer who specialized as a sprinter .
Heinz Werner Höber ( 1931 , Bärenstein -- 15 May 1996 ) was a very prolific pulp fiction author who produced many novels about the fictitious FBI - agent Jerry Cotton and eventually sued his publisher because he felt he had been entitled to receive royalties .
John Inigo Richards ( 1731 - - 18 December 1810 ) was an English landscape painter who became one of the founding members of the Royal Academy in 1768 , and was secretary to the Academy from 1788 until his death .
Silver Horn or Haungooah ( 1860 - -1940 ) was a Kiowa ledger artist from Oklahoma .
Leo of Ohrid ( died 1056 ) was a leading 11th - century Byzantine churchman as Archbishop of Ohrid and advocate of the Patriarchate of Constantinople 's views in the theological disputes with the See of Rome , which culminated in the East--
Amerigo Tot ( 27 September 1909 -- 13 December 1984 ) was a Hungarian sculptor and occasional actor .
Theophilus Brabourne ( 1590 - 1662 ) was an English Puritan clergyman and theological writer on the Christian Sabbath question .
Rhys Prichard ( 1579 - -1644 ) was a Welsh clergyman and poet .
Cyrille Duquet ( Quebec , 31 March 1841 - Québec , 1 st December 1922 ) is a goldsmith , flutist and inventor Quebec .
John Elgin Woolf ( born Atlanta , 1908 ; died Beverly Hills , California , 1980 ) , was an American architect noted for the Hollywood homes he created with partner and adopted son Robert Koch Woolf .
Richard Izacke ( c.1624 - -1698 ) of Devon was an antiquarian and lawyer who served as Chamberlain of the City of Exeter .
Ralph Neville , 3rd Earl of Westmorland ( c. 1456 -- 6 February 1499 ) was an English peer .
Arthur Napoleão dos Santos ( 6 March 1843 - 12 May 1925 ) was a Portuguese composer , pianist , instrument dealer and music publisher .
Gondioc ( Proto - Germanic : * Gunþawīgaz ; died 473 ) , also called Gundioc and Gundowech , was King of the Burgundians following the destruction of Worms by the Huns in 436 , succeeding Gundahar .
Henry Ballow or Bellewe ( 1707 - -1782 ) , was a lawyer , and held posts in the Exchequer which exempted him from the necessity of practice .
Ferdinand von Miller ( 18 October 1813 -- 11 February 1887 ) was a German artisan who is noted for his furtherance of bronze founding .
Sir Ernest Roy Griffiths ( 8 July 1926 -- 28 March 1994 ) was a British businessman .
On 6 January 2009 , Maria Dimitriadi died at the age of 58 in the Evangelismos General Hospital in Athens from a rare lung disease .
Michael Cavendish ( c. 1565 -- 1628 ) was an English composer of the Elizabethan and Jacobean periods .
Mieczysława Ćwiklińska - Steinsberg ( 1 January 1879 -- 28 July 1972 ) , née Mieczysława Trapszo was a Polish film actress , stage actor , and singer .
Sir Robert Spottiswoode ( Spottiswood , Spotiswood , Spotswood ) ( 1596 - 20 January 1646 ) was Lord President of the Court of Session and member of the Privy Council to James I of England , and Lord President of the College of Justice and Secretary for Scotland , appointed by Charles I of England .
Courtney Stanhope Kenny ( 18 March 1847 -- 18 March 1930 ) was a British jurist , academic and Liberal politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1885 to 1888 .
Alonso de Aragón or Alfonso de Aragón ( 1470 -- 24 February 1520 ) was Archbishop of Zaragoza , Archbishop of Valencia and Lieutenant General of Aragon .
Anne Darquier ( 1930 - -September 1970 ) , a psychiatrist , was the daughter of the French collaborationist Louis Darquier de Pellepoix and his Tasmanian wife , Myrtle Jones .
Lieutenat Colonel John Murray Prain DSO OBE TD DL(1902 - -1985 ) was a British Yeomanry officer in the Second World War and prominent Scottish businessman .
Gerald Aste ( 30 July 1900 -- 17 September 1961 ) was an English born Indian cricketer .
Wilhelmus Wilhelmius ( 1720 - -1771 ) was a Dutch minister , mathematician and philosopher .
Henry Nicholson Ellacombe ( 1822 - 1916 ) was a plantsman and author on botany and gardening .
Charles Boon ( 9 May 1877 - 2 December 1943 ) was a publisher who , along with Gerald Rusgrove Mills founded the publishing company Mills & Boon in 1908 .
Abraham Straski ( 1903 -- 1987 ) was a Polish born painter who moved to the United States after surviving the Nazi concentrations camps in the Holocaust .
Soliman Pasha al - Faransawi ( Süleyman Pasha the French ; May or July 1788 -- 12 March 1860 ) , born Joseph Anthelme Sève , was a French - born Egyptian commander .
Helen Eugenia Hagan ( 10 January 1893 -- 6 March 1964 ) was an American pianist , music educator and composer of African descent .
Reinhard of Blankenburg ( 11th century -- 1123 ) was Bishop of Halberstadt from 1107 to 1123 .
Barbara Gilmour ( married name Barbara Dunlop ; died 1732 ) was a significant figure in 17th century Ayrshire having introduced a method of cheese making which became common throughout Ayrshire and beyond , providing employment and extra income for farmers and others .
Oldradus de Ponte ( died 1335 ) was an Italian jurist born in Lodi , active in the Roman curia in the early fourteenth century .
Mehetabel Wesley Wright ( nicknames , `` Hetty '' and `` Kitty '' ; 1697 -- 21 March 1750 ) was an English poet , a member of the influential religious Wesley family .
Matthew Adams ( died 1753 ) was a distinguished writer in Boston , Massachusetts , though a mechanic , or `` tradesman , '' yet had a handsome collection of books and cultivated literature .
Corrado della Torre , also called Mosca ( c. 1251 -- 24 October 1307 ) was an Italian medieval politician and condottiero , a member of the Torriani family .
John Steere ( ca . 1634 -- 1724 ) was one of the earliest settlers of the state of Rhode Island , a town official , and a founder of the town of Smithfield , Rhode Island .
Michael Maltman Barry ( 1842 -- 5 April 1909 ) , often known as Maltman Barry , was a Scottish political activist who described himself as a Marxist but stood in elections for the Conservative Party .
Nicolas Adolphe Bellevoye ( 9 April 1830 , Metz- 29 November 1908 , Rheims ) was a French artist , designer and entomologist .
Sir George Bowyer , 6th Baronet and 2nd Baronet , KStJ , GCSG , KCPO ( 3 March 1783 -- 1 July 1860 ) was a British politician .
John Flavel ( c.1627 - -1691 ) was an English Presbyterian clergyman , puritan , and author .
Fuad al - Rikabi ( 1931 -- November 1971 ) was an Iraqi politician and a founder of the Iraqi Regional Branch of the Arab Socialist Ba'ath Party .
Ludwig Crüwell ( 20 March 1892 -- 25 September 1958 ) , was a German general known for his involvement with the Afrika Korps .
Jacob Julius Max Nord ( 1 April 1916 -- 28 February 2008 ) was a Dutch journalist , writer , and translator .
Edmund ter Meer ( 31 July 1852 -- 5 November 1931 ) was a German chemist who discovered the ter Meer reaction and founded in 1877 the ter Meer dye company in Uerdingen .
Jovan Rašković ( Serbo - Croatian pronunciation : ( jǒʋan râʃkoʋit͡ɕ ) , Serbian Cyrillic : Јован Рашковић ; 5 July 1929 -- 29 July 1992 ) was a Croatian Serb psychiatrist , academic and politician .
Turab Ali ( died 5 June 2009 ) was a Pakistani professional footballer , who was dubbed as `` Wall of China '' , `` Pillar of Hercules '' during his hey days in the 1960s .
Edward Walters ( December 1808 , Fenchurch Buildings , London - 22 January 1872 , 11 Oriental Place , Brighton ) was an English architect .
Sir Kevin Victor Anderson ( 1912 -- 14 October 1999 ) was a 20th - century Australian jurist .
George Jackman II ( 1837 - -1887 ) was an English horticulturist and nurseryman , known for his work on early clematis hybrids .
Robert Ciboule ( died 1458 ) was a French Roman Catholic theologian and moralist .
Captain Thomas Symonds , R.N. ( 1731 - 1792 ) was a British naval captain of the American Revolutionary War .
Werner Meyer - Eppler ( 30 April 1913 -- 8 July 1960 ) , was a Belgian - born German physicist , experimental acoustician , phoneticist and information theorist .
Walter Bellamy ( 6 November 1904 in Tottenham -- 1978 ) was a professional footballer who played for Ilford , Tufnell Park , Dulwich Hamlet , Tottenham Hotspur and Brighton & Hove Albion .
Sir Samuel Roberts , 1st Baronet PC , DL ( 30 April 1852 -- 19 June 1926 ) was a British politician and businessman .
William Harold Bidmead ( December 1882 -- 16 March 1961 ) , generally known as Bill Bidmead , was an English professional footballer who played in the Football League for Small Heath ( renamed Birmingham during his time with the club ) and Grimsby Town .
Curt Stoermer ( born Kurt Karl August Störmer , 26 April 1891 -- 29 January 1976 ) was a German painter , a representative of the Worpswede branch of expressionist art .
Krishna I ( Kannada : ಅಕಾಲವರ್ಷ ಶುಭತುಂಗ ಕೃಷ್ಣ ) ( 756 - -774 CE ) , an uncle of Dantidurga , took charge of the growing Rashtrakuta Empire by defeating the last Badami Chalukya ruler Kirtivarman II in 757 .
Dovid Bornsztain ( 1876 -- 17 November 1942 ) , also spelled Borenstein , Bornstein and Bernstein , known as the Chasdei Dovid , was the third Rebbe of the Sochatchov Hasidic dynasty .
Ted Roberts ( 17 April 1931 - 23 February 2015 ) was an Australian television screenwriter and supervising producer .
Isaack Luttichuys ( 25 February 1616 ( baptized ) -- 6 March 1673 ( buried ) ) was a Dutch Golden Age painter .
Mahendra Lal Bose ( Bengali : মহেন্দ্র লাল বোস ; October 1893 -- 9 December 1978 ) was an educationalist and philanthropist during the Bengal Renaissance .
Sperantza Vrana ( Greek : Σπεράντζα Βρανά ; 6 February 1928 -- 29 September 2009 ) was a Greek actress and writer .
Charles Ignatius White ( born at Baltimore , Maryland , U.S.A. , 1 February 1807 ; died at Washington , D.C. , 1 April 1878 ) was an American editor , historian , and Catholic priest .
Matej Sternen ( 20 September 1870 -- 28 June 1949 ) was a leading Slovene Impressionist painter .
Salukaphathwa Gwebi'nkumbi Sigcawu was the 7th chief of the Gcaleka sub - group of the Xhosa nation from 1902 until his death on the 30 May 1921 .
Lieutenant - General James Webber Smith CB ( c. 1778 - -1853 ) was a British Royal Artillery officer during the Napoleonic Wars .
William Banting ( c. December 1796 -- 16 March 1878 ) was a notable English undertaker .
Elizabeth Leyburne , Duchess of Norfolk ( 1536 -- 4 September 1567 ) , was a member of the English nobility .
Robert R. Wark ( 7 October 1924 - 8 June 2007 ) was a Canadian art historian who was curator of the Huntington Museum of Art from 1956 to 1990 .
John Delabere ( before 1559 - 1607 ) , of the Middle Temple , London and Southam , Gloucestershire , was an English politician .
Kazelin ( died around 1092 ) was a nobleman with estates in Friuli and Carinthia .
Royal Earl House ( 9 September 1814 -- 25 February 1895 ) was the inventor of the first printing telegraph , which is now kept in the Smithsonian Institution .
Andreas Schlüter ( 20 May 1664 -- May 1714 ) was a German baroque sculptor and architect associated with the Petrine Baroque style of architecture and decoration .
Waldemar Philippi ( 13 April 1929 -- 4 October 1990 ) was a German footballer who played internationally for Saarland .
Sefer Daja ( Tirana , 1897 - 1977 , Tirana ) was the head figure in Bejte nga Sefer Daja in the book of Haxhi Deliu .
Joseph Harrop ( 17 September 1867 - 6 July 1936 ) was an English mill owner and mayor of Morley , West Yorkshire .
Alexander Charles Farquharson ( 15 March 1864 -- 27 May 1951 ) was a Scottish doctor , barrister , soldier and Liberal Party politician .
Charles Rivière - Hérard also known as Charles Hérard aîné ( 16 February 1789 -- 31 August 1850 ) was an officer in the Haitian Army under Alexandre Pétion during his struggles against Henri Christophe .
Humphrey Dyson ( 1582 - -1633 ) was a London scrivener and notary , and notable early book collector in England .
Professor Ervín Černý - Křetínský ( born 1913 in Podomí - died 30 July 2001 ) was a Doctor of Medicine and Professor of Charles University in Prague .
