Jean - Fleury Baudrand ( or Baudran ) , O.M.I. ( 9 March 1811 -- 1 October 1853 ) , was a French Roman Catholic priest and missionary who served in North America , where he died .
Richard Rennison ( 29 October 1889 -- 5 August 1969 ) was the last `` anvil priest '' at Gretna Green , Scotland .
Joe Jorgenson ( 12 September 1921 -- 7 May 1993 ) was an Australian rugby league footballer .
Sir Hew Dalrymple , 3rd Baronet ( 26 October 1746 -- 13 February 1800 ) was the Member of Parliament ( MP ) for Haddingtonshire 1780 - 1786 .
Sima Wang ( 205 - -271 ) , courtesy name Zichu , was a military general of the state of Cao Wei during the Three Kingdoms period .
Elizabeth Heyrick ( 4 December 1769 -- 18 October 1831 ) was a British philanthropist and campaigner against the slave trade .
Nicholas Purslow ( by 1533 - 1563 ) , of the Inner Temple , London , was an English politician .
( Master ) Yin Shun ( 印順導師 , Yìnshùn Dǎoshī ) ( 12 March 1906 -- 4 June 2005 ) was a well - known Buddhist monk and scholar in the tradition of Chinese Mahayana Buddhism .
Wahib al - Ghanim ( 1919 - 2003 ) was a Syrian physician who confounded the Ba'ath Party .
Matthaeus Pipelare ( c. 1450 -- c. 1515 ) was a Netherlandish composer , choir director , and possibly wind instrument player of the Renaissance .
Chris Laird(20 May 1893 -- 14 December 1968 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for South Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
George Clutesi , CM ( 1905 -- 27 February 1988 ) , was a Tseshaht artist , actor and writer , as well as an expert on and spokesman for Native Canadian culture .
Mihailo Olćan ( Serbian Cyrillic : Михаило Олћан ; 18 September 1894 -- 1961 ) was a Serbian soldier and politician .
Rodolfo Hurtado ( full name Rodolfo Hurtado Duhart ) ( b. 1940 -- d. 2005 ) was a Mexican artist , considered to be part of the `` Intermediate Generation '' or that which came to prominence after the Generación de la Ruptura .
Rabbi Dr Werner van der Zyl ( Schwerte , Germany , 11 September 1902 -- Palma , Majorca , Spain , 10 April 1984 ) was a rabbi in Berlin and in London , where he came in 1939 as a refugee rabbi from Germany .
Esther Liebmann ( née Schulhoff ; 1649 -- 15 April 1714 ) was a German Jewish financier .
Memeskia ( c. 1695 -- June 21 , 1752 ) , known as `` Old Briton '' by the British and as `` La Demoiselle '' by the French , was an eighteenth - century Piankashaw chieftain who fought against the French in 1747 .
Isaac Karo ( 1458 - 1535 ) was a famous posek , preacher , Rosh Yeshiva , and physician .
Karel Plicka ( in Slovak : Karol Plicka ) ( 14 October 1894 -- 6 May 1987 ) was a Czechoslovak photographer , film director , cinematographer , folklorist , and pedagogue .
Vice Admiral Sir Cecil Ponsonby Talbot KCB KBE DSO & Bar ( 31 August 1884 -- 17 March 1970 ) was a senior Royal Navy officer .
Dan Pender ( 17 March 1873 -- 14 April 1968 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Morris Rajapaksa ( b. - d. 1995 ) was the 3rd Chief Minister of Western Province .
Nicholas Dennys ( 13 November 1616 -- 31 May 1692 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1660 to 1678 .
Bliss Perry ( 25 November 1860 -- 13 February 1954 ) , was an American literary critic , writer , editor , and teacher .
George Aloysius Carrell , S.J. ( June 13 , 1803 - -September 25 , 1868 ) was an American prelate of the Roman Catholic Church who served as the first bishop of the Diocese of Covington , Kentucky from 1853 until his death in 1868 .
Selig Brodetsky ( 10 February 1888 -- 20 May 1954 ) was a Russian - born English mathematician , a member of the World Zionist Executive , the president of the Board of Deputies of British Jews , and the second president of the Hebrew University of Jerusalem .
Thomas William Dobson ( 9 November 1853 -- 13 May 1935 ) was a Liberal Member of Parliament ( MP ) representing Plymouth from 1906 to 1910 .
Charles Gordon Bell ( 31 May 1889 -- 29 July 1918 ) was an early British pilot .
Sir Nicholas Throckmorton ( or Throgmorton ) ( circa 1515/1516 -- 12 February 1571 ) was an English diplomat and politician , who was an ambassador to France and played a key role in the relationship between Elizabeth I and Mary , Queen of Scots .
Khan Shakir Ali Khan ( 1904 - 1978 ) , popularly known as Sher - e - Bhopal , was an Indian politician , activist , trade unionist and journalist .
George Gaskin ( 1751 - -1829 ) was a lecturer ( assistant curate ) at St Mary 's , Islington for forty - six years , resigning in 1822 , to become a prebendary at Ely Cathedral .
Mosse Jørgensen ( 3 January 1921 -- 30 June 2009 ) was a Norwegian school principal and non - fiction writer .
Ralph Gubion ( died 6 July 1151 ) was a native Englishman and abbot of St Albans Abbey from 1146 to 1151 .
Bengt Ronnie Peterson ( Swedish pronunciation : ( ˈrɔni ˈpɛtɛˈʂon ) ; 14 February 1944 -- 11 September 1978 ) was a Swedish racing driver .
Binoy Majumdar ( Bengali : বিনয় মজুমদার ) ( 17 September 1934 - 11 December 2006 ) was a Bengali poet .
Reino Häyhänen ( May 14 , 1920 -- 1961 ) was an Ingrian Finnish origin Soviet - born Lieutenant Colonel who defected to the United States .
Antonio Maspes ( 14 January 1932 -- 19 October 2000 ) was an Italian world champion sprinter cyclist .
Daniel Day Williams ( 1910 - -December , 1973 ) was a process theologian , professor , and author .
Zdeněk Lev of Rožmitál ( Czech : Zdeněk Lev z Rožmitálu , German : Zdeniek Lev von Rosental ; c. 1470 -- 14 July 1535 ) was a Bohemian nobleman .
Marco Mazzaroppi ( 1550 - 1620 ) was an Italian painter , mainly painting religious subjects .
Ivan Meshchaninov ( 24 November 1883 -- 16 January 1967 ) was a Soviet linguist and ethnographer .
Willem Pieter Landzaat ( Leiden , 7 April 1886 - Rhenen , 13 May 1940 ) was a Dutch military officer who died during the Battle of the Grebbeberg .
Isobel Elsom ( 16 March 1893 -- 12 January 1981 ) was an English screen , stage and television actress .
William Ansel Kinney ( 1860 - -1930 ) was a lawyer and politician in the Kingdom of Hawaii , through the Republic of Hawaii and into the Territory of Hawaii .
Céline Marie Tabary ( 29 July 1908 -- 23 May 1993 ) was an artist and arts professor at Howard University who championed African - American art in 1940s Washington , D.C. She emigrated from France in 1938 , teaching and working in Washington , D.C. through the 1950s , before returning to France .
Carl , Prince of Wied ( German : Friedrich August Maximilian Wilhelm Carl Fürst zu Wied ; 27 October 1961 -- 12 March 2015 ) was the son of Frederick William , 7th Prince of Wied .
Lippmann Moses Büschenthal ( 1784 in Strassbourg -- 27 December 1818 ) was a German rabbi , poet and dramatist .
Armine von Tempski ( or Tempsky ) ( 1892 , Maui , Hawaiian Islands -- December 2 , 1943 , Fresno , California ) was an American writer and one of Hawaii 's best known authors .
Leo Geoghegan ( 16 May 1936 - 2 March 2015 ) was a former Australian racing driver .
Robert Henry Gibbs , Jr. ( 1929 - -1988 ) was an American ichthyologist .
Frederick Cuthbert ( born 1800 in England ; died 29 March 1821 in England ) was an English amateur cricketer who played first - class cricket from 1816 to 1817 .
Shahzada Mumtaz Shikoh ( 16 August 1643 -- 6 December 1647 ) also known as Mumtaz Shukoh , was the third son of Mughar prince Dara Shikoh .
Juan García de Miranda ( 1677 - -1749 ) , was a Spanish painter of the baroque period , a disciple of Juan Delgado and the uncle of Pedro Rodriguez de Miranda .
Strategios Podopagouros ( Greek : Στρατήγιος Ποδοπάγουρος ; died 25 August 766 ) was a Byzantine military commander and with his brother Constantine leader of a conspiracy against Emperor Constantine V ( r. 741 - -775 ) .
Francis Willoughby , 5th Baron Willoughby of Parham ( baptised 1614 -- 23 July 1666 ) was an English peer of the House of Lords .
Golindouch , Golindukht , Golindokht , or Dolindokht ( died 591 ) was a noble Persian lady who converted to Christianity and became a saint and martyr .
Robert Michael Winner ( 30 October 1935 -- 21 January 2013 ) was an English film director and producer , and a restaurant critic for The Sunday Times .
Nigel De Brulier ( 8 July 1877 - 30 January 1948 ) , born Francis George Packer , was an English film actor , born in Bristol , Gloucestershire , who launched his career in the theatre stage in his native country and transferred to films after moving to the USA .
Arthur James Arnot ( 26 August 1865 -- 15 October 1946 ) was an Australian electrical engineer and inventor , best known for patenting the world 's first electric drill .
Morris Barnett ( 1800 -- 18 March 1856 ) , was a British actor and dramatist .
Andrew Fuller ( 6 February 1754 -- 7 May 1815 ) was an English Particular Baptist minister and theologian .
Audrey Hepburn ( /ˈɔːdri ˈhɛpˌbɜːrn/ ; born Audrey Kathleen Ruston ; 4 May 1929 -- 20 January 1993 ) was a British actress and humanitarian .
Sir Reo Stakis ( born Argyros Anastasis ) ( 13 March 1913 - 28 August 2001 ) was a Scottish - Cypriot hotel magnate , longtime head of Stakis Hotels .
Bjørn Helland - Hansen ( 16 October 1877 -- 7 September 1957 ) was a Norwegian pioneer in the field of modern oceanography .
Dyneley Hussey ( 27 February 1893 -- 6 September 1972 ) was an English war poet , journalist , art critic and music critic .
Dr. Nikolai Mossolow ( 1910 - 1988 ) was a well known Russian - born Namibian historian and archivist .
Ole Clausen Mørch ( 2 August 1774 -- 4 July 1829 ) was a Norwegian merchant , banker and politician .
Arthur O'Friel ( or O’Frigil ) ( died circa 1573 ) was an Irish Roman Catholic clergyman who attempted , but failed , to get possession of the archbishopric of Tuam in the 16th century .
Charles Creswell ( born 10 March 1813 at Radford , Nottinghamshire ; died 22 November 1882 at Heaton Norris , Cheshire ) was an English cricketer who played first - class cricket from 1836 to 1843 .
Johnny Răducanu ( born Răducan Creţu ; 1 December 1931 -- 19 September 2011 ) was a Romanian jazz pianist of Romani ethnic background , whose family has a long musical tradition dating back to the 17th century .
Rachel Thomas OBE ( 10 February 1905 - 8 February 1995 ) , was a Welsh character actress .
William Augustus Bowles ( 1763 - -1805 ) , also known as Estajoca , was a Maryland - born English adventurer and organizer of Native American attempts to create their own state outside of Euro - American control .
Isak Wilho Laine ( 5 July 1875 , Köyliö - 21 May 1918 , Hämeenlinna ; original surname Kivelä ) was a Finnish carpenter and politician .
Lieutenant - Colonel Edward Lisle Strutt , CBE , DSO ( 8 February 1874 -- 7 July 1948 ) was a British soldier and mountaineer , and President of the Alpine Club from 1935 - -38 .
Shlomo Zalman Shragai ( Hebrew : זלמן שרגאי‎ , 1899 - -1995 ) was an Israeli politician and Jerusalem 's first elected mayor .
Bekim Berisha ( Albanian : Bekim Berisha ; Croatian : Bekim Beriša ) ( 15 June 1966 -- 10 August 1998 ) was a Kosovar Albanian soldier who gained prominence in the Yugoslav Wars .
Azzo VII d'Este , Marquis of Ferrara ( also known as Novello ; 1205 - 16 February 1264 ) was marquis of Ferrara from 1215 to 1222 , and again from 1240 until his death .
Rudolf II , Margrave of Baden - Baden ( died 14 February 1295 ) was the second son of Margrave Rudolf I and his wife Kunigunde of Eberstein .
John de Cogan was an Anglo - Irish knight who lived in the period between 1233 - 1278 .
Sir James Shaw , 1st Baronet ( 26 August 1764 -- 22 October 1843 ) , became Lord Mayor of London in 1805 .
Rufus Early Clement ( 1900 - -1967 ) was the sixth and longest - serving president of historically black Atlanta University in Atlanta , Georgia .
Suvi Raj Grubb ( 7 October 1917 -- 22 December 1999 ) was a South - Indian record producer who worked for EMI during the mid-20th Century , initially as assistant to Walter Legge , succeeding Legge on his resignation from EMI in 1964 .
Tone Kralj ( 23 August 1900 -- 9 September 1975 ) was a Slovene sculptor and painter also known for his wall paintings and illustrations .
Alexander Martin Sullivan ( 1830 -- 17 October 1884 ) was an Irish Nationalist politician , lawyer and journalist from Bantry , County Cork .
Jewel Flowers Evans ( 22 July 1923 -- 6 February 2006 ) was an American pin - up model best known for her work with Rolf Armstrong as a `` Calendar Girl '' during the 1940s and 1950s .
Huw Robert Jones ( 1894 - -August 1930 ) , known as H. R. Jones , was a Welsh nationalist politician .
Adelaide Phillipps ( 26 October 1833 in Stratford - on - Avon , England -- 3 October 1882 in Carlsbad , Germany ) was an opera singer .
Henry Sherfield ( 1572 ( baptised ) -- 1634 ) was an English lawyer and politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1621 to 1629 .
Fernão de Loronha ( c. 1470 or before -- Lisbon , c. 1540 ) , whose name is often corrupted to Fernando de Noronha or Fernando della Rogna , was a prominent 16th - century Portuguese merchant of Lisbon , of Jewish descent .
Saint Anthimus of Rome ( ( Italian ) Sant'Antimo ) ( died 303 ) is a Christian saint .
María Teresalina Sánchez , F.M.M. ( 13 July 1918 - 27 October 1947 ) was a Spanish Franciscan Religious Sister who served as a missionary to Kashmir .
William Paty ( 1758 -- 11 December 1800 ) was a British surveyor , architect and mason working mainly in Bristol .
Thomas Culpeper ( c. 1514 -- 10 December 1541 ) was a courtier and close friend of Henry VIII , and related to two of his queens , Anne Boleyn and Catherine Howard .
Jordan of Osnabrück ( c. 1220 -- 15 April 1284 ) was a significant German political writer of the 13th century .
Nicolas Jarry ( c. 1620 -- c. 1674 ) was a noted 17th - century French calligrapher , whose works included his renditions of the poems of Guirlande de Julie by Charles de Sainte - Maure , duc de Montausier .
Frank Mason Robinson ( 1845 in Corinth , Maine -- 1923 in Atlanta , Georgia ) , was an important early marketer and advertiser of what became known as Coca - Cola .
Morris Cafritz ( 1887 ? - 1964 ) was a Washington , D.C. real estate developer , and philanthropist .
James William Cleland ( 1874 - -21 October 1914 ) was a Scottish Liberal Party politician and Barrister .
Anne Julie de Melun ( Anne Julie Adélaïde ; 1698 -- 18 May 1724 ) was a French noblewoman and mother of Charles de Rohan , the famous general of Louis XV as well as Madame de Marsan .
Andrea Vaccà Berlinghieri ( 3 February 1772 -- 6 September 1826 ) was an Italian surgeon born in Montefoscoli , a village in the municipality of Palaia .
Lytton Burgo Partridge ( 1935 - -1963 ) was an English author and member of the Bloomsbury Group .
Ambrose Palmer ( 16 October 1910 -- 16 October 1990 ) was a talented world - class professional prize fighter and a leading Australian rules footballer of the 1930s and early 1940s .
Sir James MacGill of Nether Rankeillour , Fife ( died 1579 ) was a Scottish courtier .
Saul M. Ginsburg ( Sha'ul Moiseevich Ginsburg , שאול גינזבורג ; born Minsk , 1866 -- died New York , 16 November 1940 ) was a Jewish - Russian American author , editor , and historian of Russian Jewry .
Robert de Den ( † 1349 ) was a 14th - century bishop - elect of Dunkeld , Scotland .
Zhang Yaoling ( Chinese : 張曜靈 ; 344 - -355 ) , courtesy name Yuanshu ( 元舒 ) , formally Duke Ai of Xiping , was briefly the ruler of the Chinese state Former Liang in 353 and early 354 .
Vince Kenny ( 29 December 1924 -- 2006 ) was an English professional footballer who played as a full back .
John Thomas Quekett ( 1815 - -1861 ) was an English microscopist and histologist .
Zdravko Kajmaković ( Serbian : Здравко Кајмаковић ) , ( Modran ( Bijeljina ) , 10 October 1929 -- Sarajevo , 19 March 2009 ) was an art historian and ranks among the leading scholars of the latter half of the twentieth century in Bosnia and Herzegovina .
Richard Kress ( alternative writing Richard Kreß ) ( 6 March 1925 -- 30 March 1996 ) was a German footballer .
Henning Grenander ( 1874 , Stockholm - 1958 ) was a Swedish figure skater .
Admiral Sir Thomas Frankland , 5th Baronet ( 26 June 1718 -- 21 November 1784 , Bath ) was a British naval officer , MP and slave trader .
Otto Fabricius ( 6 March 1744 -- 20 May 1822 ) was a Danish missionary , naturalist , ethnographer and explorer of Greenland .
James Lorrain Smith ( 21 August 1862 - -18 April 1931 ) was a Scottish pathologist known for his works in human physiology , especially his research on respiration in collaboration with John Scott Haldane .
Thomas Phipps ( c.1648 -- 1715 ) was an English merchant who became briefly a Member of Parliament for , first , Wilton and , secondly , Westbury .
Countess Erzsébet Thurzó de Bethlenfalva ( 20 February 1621 -- 4 July 1642 ) was a Hungarian noblewoman , daughter of Count Imre Thurzó and Baroness Krisztina Nyáry .
Sir Harold Hood , 2nd Baronet ( 23 January 1916 -- 5 September 2005 ) was the son of Sir Joseph Hood .
Ferenc Fricsay ( Hungarian pronunciation : ( ˈfɛrɛnt͡s ˈfrit͡ʃɒi ) ; 9 August 1914 -- 20 February 1963 ) was a Hungarian conductor .
Reza Fallah ( 1909 - -1982 ) was an Iranian businessman and political advisor .
James Basset ( 1526 - -1558 ) was a gentleman from an ancient Devonshire family who became a servant of Stephen Gardiner ( c. 1483 - 1555 ) , Bishop of Winchester , by whom he was nominated MP for Taunton in 1553 , for Downton in 1554 , both episcopal boroughs .
Sultan Sri Alam , also known as Sultan Mughal ( d. 1579 ) was the sixth sultan of Aceh in northern Sumatra .
John Doreward ( died 1420 ) was a Serjeant - at - law and Speaker of the House of Commons of England .
K. P. Krishnakumar ( born Kuttipuram , Kerala in 1958 - 26 December 1989 ) was an Indian sculptor and painter .
Francis Alexander FitzGerald ( 1807 - 1897 ) was an Irish barrister and judge , who had a distinguished career , but resigned from the Bench in somewhat unusual circumstance on a point of principle .
Louw Wepener ( died 1865 ) was a military leader ( kommandant in Afrikaans ) in the Orange Free State who was killed during the Second Orange Free State - Basuto War at Thaba Bosiu , while trying to storm the mountain stronghold of Moshoeshoe I , founder of the Basotho nation .
Ted Jarrard ( 15 April 1922 - 25 November 2010 ) was an Australian rules footballer in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Christian Gottfried Schütz ( 19 May 1747 -- 7 May 1832 ) was a German classical scholar and humanist , known for his contributions in philosophy and philology , and for his work as an academic and literary editor and publisher .
Ostap Ortwin ( real name Oskar Katzenellenbogen ) ( born November 23 , 1876 , died spring 1942 in Lwów ) was a Polish journalist and literary critic .
The Hon . Frederick Walpole ( 18 September 1822 -- 1 April 1876 ) , was a British naval commander and Conservative politician .
Jacob Baden ( 4 May 1735 -- 5 July 1804 ) , was a Danish philologist , pedagogue , and critic .
Frances Bannerman ( née Jones ) ( 1855 -- 1940 ) was a Novascotian painter and poet .
`` Uncle '' H. Geoffrey Elwes ( ? 1873 - 1936 ) was a prominent early member of the Scouting Movement and before that was involved in the Boys Brigade .
Henry Raper ( 1799 -- 6 January 1859 ) was a British Royal Naval lieutenant who became a nineteenth - century authority on navigation .
Prince Wilhelm Victor of Prussia ( Wilhelm Viktor Ernst Freund Friedrich Georg Adalbert ) ( 15 February 1919 in Kiel , Schleswig - Holstein , 7 February 1989 in Donaueschingen , Baden - Württemberg ) was a German nobleman , soldier and diplomat .
Nicky Imber ( 1920 - -1996 ) was a multidisciplinary Jewish artist best known for his sculptures on Jewish themes .
Philip III , Count of Nassau - Weilburg ( 20 September 1504 at Neuweilnau Castle in Weilrod -- 4 October 1559 in Weilburg ) was a Count of the Nassau - Weilburg .
Thomas Edmondston ( 1825 - -1846 ) was a British - born botanist , born in Buness , Unst .
Charles Ollier ( 1788 - -1859 ) was an English publisher and author , associated with the works of Percy Bysshe Shelley and John Keats .
Anton Wilhelm Solnitz ( or Sollnitz , c.1708 - -1752 ) was a German - Bohemian composer .
Richard Wyot MA ( also Wyott ) ( d 1463 ) was a Canon of Windsor from 1436 - 1449 and Archdeacon of Middlesex from 1443 - 1463 .
Tai Sing Loo ( 1886 - -1971 ) was a photographer of Pearl Harbor and many sporting events in Hawaii .
Anne de Chantraine ( 1605 -- 17 October 1622 ) was one of the many people to be accused and burned for witchcraft in the Great Witch Hunts of the 17th century .
James Comrie ( 31 March 1881 -- 9 August 1916 ) was a Scottish football player who played in both Scotland and England , for Third Lanark , Reading , Glossop North End , Bradford City , Lincoln City , Grantham Town and Stenhousemuir .
Kathy Secker ( 18 February 1945 -- 15 December 2015 ) was a British broadcaster , best known for her work at Tyne Tees Television and BBC Radio Newcastle .
Santhosh Jogi ( 1974/1975 -- 13 April 2010 ) was a Malayalee film actor and singer who acted in more than 30 films .
David Rothe ( 1573 -- 20 April 1650 ) was a Roman Catholic Bishop of Ossory .
Gerald Glatzmayer ( 14 December 1968 -- 11 January 2001 ) was an Austrian footballer who took part in the 1990 World Cup .
Elizabeth Handley - Seymour ( c. 1873 - -1948 ) was a London - based fashion designer and court - dressmaker operating as Madame Handley - Seymour between 1910 and 1940 .
Henry Abyngdon , Abingdon or Abington ( ca . 1418 -- 1 September 1497 ) was an English ecclesiastic and musician , perhaps the first to receive a university degree in music .
William Jardine Herries Maxwell ( 4 March 1852 -- 31 July 1933 ) was a Liberal Unionist politician in Scotland .
Hotep Idris Galeta ( 7 June 1941 -- 3 November 2010 ) was a South African jazz pianist and educator .
Douglas Geoffrey Bridson ( 21 August 1910 - 19 October 1980 ) , commonly known as D. G. Bridson , was a radio producer and author who became the `` cultural boss of the BBC '' .
Sidney Harry Fox ( born ?- died 8 April 1930 ) was a British petty swindler and murderer .
Alice of Saluzzo , Countess of Arundel ( died 25 September 1292 ) , also known as Alesia di Saluzzo , was an Italian - born noblewoman and an English countess .
Mar Dionysius I , also known as Mar Thoma VI ( died 8 April 1808 ) , was the Metropolitan of the Malankara Church from 1765 until his death .
Laetitia Matilda Hawkins ( baptized 8 August 1759 -- 22 November 1835 ) was an English novelist , associated with Twickenham .
Theodore Howard Somervell OBE , FRCS ( 16 April 1890 -- 23 January 1975 ) was an English surgeon , mountaineer , painter and missionary who was a member of two expeditions to Mount Everest in the 1920s , and then spent nearly 40 years working as a doctor in India .
Anthony Middleton was an English Roman Catholic Priest and martyr who was hanged , drawn and quartered in 1590 .
Manuel Requena ( 1802 - -1876 ) was president of the Los Angeles Common Council in the early 1850s .
Akshay Kumar Datta ( also spelt Akshay Kumar Dutta ) ( Bengali : অক্ষয় কুমার দত্ত ) ( 15 July 1820 -- 18 May 1886 ) was born in Chupi in Bardhaman .
Augusto Céspedes Patzi ( 6 February 1904 , Cochabamba -- 9 May 1997 , La Paz ) was a Bolivian writer , politician , diplomat , and journalist .
Professor George Francis Mitchell , generally known as Frank Mitchell , ( 15 October 1912 -- 25 November 1997 ) was an Irish geologist and naturalist .
Giuseppe Crastoni or Gioseffo Crastone or Crastona ( 1674 in Pavia -- 1718 ) was an Italian painter , mainly active as a landscape painter .
Sir John Duncan Bligh KCB , DL ( 11 October 1798 -- 8 May 1872 ) , styled The Honourable from birth , was a British diplomat .
Gustav Paganetti - Hummler ( 20 December 1871- January 1949 , Bad Vöslau ) was an Austrian naturalist and entomologist .
The abbé Augustin Nadal ( 1659 -- 7 August 1741 ) was the author of plays , through the failure of which he became the butt of a withering public reply from Voltaire that has rendered the abbé immortal .
Antonio Ferreira Batalha Silva - Netto ( 2 April 1876 -- 15 December 1962 ) was a Hong Kong Macanese businessman and member of the Legislative Council of Hong Kong .
Daniel Oliver Guion ( London , 20 April 1776 -- Ringkøbing , 24 December 1811 ) was an officer of the Royal Navy .
Charles Raff ( 9 October 1878 -- 4 August 1948 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with St Kilda and Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
John Tiedtke ( 1907 - -2004 ) was an American businessman and philanthropist .
Gustave Langenus ( 1883 - -1957 ) was a Belgian clarinetist .
Patrick Tyrrell ( or Tyrell ) , O.F.M. ( died 1692 ) was an Irish prelate of the Roman Catholic Church who served as the Bishop of Clogher ( 1676 - -1689 ) , Vicar Apostolic of Kilmore ( 1678 - -1689 ) , and Bishop of Meath ( 1689 - -1692 ) .
Bashir Saadawi ( Arabic : بشير السعداوي‎ ) , also transcribed Basher Es'sadawy , ( 1884 -- 17 January 1957 ) was a Libyan politician and the founder and leader of the Libyan National Congress Party .
Yomo Toro ( 26 July 1933 -- 30 June 2012 ) was a guitarist and a Puerto Rico cuatro player .
Rose Gaffney ( 1895 - -1979 ) was an environmental activist known for fighting the construction of the Bodega Bay Nuclear Power Plant in Sonoma County , California .
Samuel Stennett ( 1 June 1727 -- 24 August 1795 ) was a Seventh Day Baptist minister and hymnwriter .
In 1236 Iltutmish died , and was buried in the Qutb complex in Mehrauli .
Azniv Hrachia ( 1853 - 1920 ) was an Ottoman Armenian actress and director .
George Fitzmaurice ( 13 February 1885 -- 13 June 1940 ) was a French - born film director and producer .
Anne Ziegler ( 22 June 1910 - 13 October 2003 ) was an English singer , known for her light operatic duets with her husband Webster Booth .
At the end of 1943 , Rexhep Jusufi went along with Gajur Deralla and the Luboten division to Kicevo to help the Balli Kombëtar forces of Mefail Shehu against the Yugoslav partisans .
Thomas Arundell , 1st Baron Arundell of Wardour ( ca . 1560 -- 7 November 1639 ) was the eldest son of Sir Matthew Arundell of Wardour Castle in Wiltshire ( ca . 1532/34 - -24 December 1598 ) , and Margaret Willoughby , the daughter of Sir Henry Willoughby , of Wollaton , Nottinghamshire .
Jenő Szemák ( 4 February 1887 -- 30 July 1971 ) was a Hungarian jurist , who served as President of the Curia Regia from 1944 to 1945 .
Zubir Said B.B.M. ( 22 July 1907 -- 16 November 1987 ) was a Singaporean composer originally from the Minangkabau highlands of Indonesia who composed the national anthem of Singapore , `` Majulah Singapura '' ( `` Onward Singapore '' ) .
Carmen Soler ( 1924 - -1985 ) was a Paraguayan educator , poet and member of the Paraguayan Communist Party .
Marie Christine de Pardaillan de Gondrin ( 17 November 1663 -- 1675 ) was the eldest legitimate child of Françoise de Rochechouart de Mortemart and her husband , the Marquis of Montespan .
Andrew Stewart , 2nd Lord Ochiltree ( c.1521 - 1591 ) fought for the Scottish Reformation .
Richard James Morrison ( 15 June 1795 -- 5 April 1874 ) was an English astrologer , commonly known by his pseudonym Zadkiel .
Marie Taglioni ( 23 April 1804 -- 22 April 1884 ) was a ballet dancer of the Romantic ballet era , a central figure in the history of European dance .
Elzy Burroughs ( 1771/77 - -1825 ) was an American stonemason , engineer , lighthouse builder and keeper .
John Whitehead Peard ( 1811 - -1880 ) was a British soldier , renowned as ' Garibaldi 's Englishman ' .
Pearl Carter Pace ( January 25 , 1896 - -January 1970 ) was the first woman elected sheriff in the Commonwealth of Kentucky , 1938 - 1941 .
Marco II Sanudo ( died ca . 1303 ) was the third Duke of the Archipelago from 1262 to his death .
Sophia Magdalena of Denmark ( Danish : Sofie Magdalene ; 3 July 1746 -- 21 August 1813 ) was Queen of Sweden as the spouse of King Gustav III .
William Brabazon , 1st Earl of Meath ( c.1580 - 18 December 1651 ) was an Anglo - Irish peer .
Georg Frederik Hallager ( 20 March 1816 -- 10 November 1876 ) was a Dano - Norwegian legal scholar and judge .
Martin Howy Irving ( 21 February 1831 -- 23 January 1912 ) was an English rower and educationist who spent nearly all his career in Australia .
West Nkosi ( born Johannes Hlongwane , 1940 -- 8 October 1998 ) was a South African music producer , saxophonist and songwriter .
Alexander Cooper ( 11 December 1609 -- 1660 ) was an English Baroque miniature painter .
Peter Braestrup ( 1929 -- 10 August 1997 ) was a correspondent for The New York Times and The Washington Post , founding editor of the Wilson Quarterly , and later senior editor and director of communications for the Library of Congress .
John Stokesley ( c. 1475 -- 8 September 1539 ) was an English church leader who was Catholic Bishop of London during the reign of Henry VIII .
John Robertson Hare ( 17 December 1891 -- 25 January 1979 ) was an English actor , who came to fame in the Aldwych farces .
Edward Wolley was an Anglican bishop in Ireland in the 17th - century ; he succeeded William Bailey as Bishop of Clonfert and Kilmacduagh in 1664 , and died in 1684 .
Giacomo Vincenti ( died 1619 ) was an Italian bookseller and music printer from Venice .
Dandy Nichols ( 21 May 1907 -- 6 February 1986 ) was an English actress most noted for her role as Else Garnett , the long - suffering wife of the racially bigoted and misogynistic character Alf Garnett in the BBC sitcom Till Death Us Do Part .
Frank Maloy Anderson ( Feb. 3 , 1871 - Apr. 26 , 1961 ) was an author , historian and professor of history .
Mordecai Karmi ( 1749 - -1825 ) was the son of Abraham Karmi and one of the most learned rabbis of France , distinguished both for the nobility of his character as well as for his writings .
Christian Bakkerud ( 3 November 1984 -- 11 September 2011 ) was a Danish racing driver , who competed in the 2007 and 2008 GP2 Series seasons , albeit hindered by a recurrent back injury .
Susan Morgan ( née Susan ( Sue ) Dyson , pen name : Zoe Barnes ) ( 20 July 1957 -- 31 October 2009 ) of Cheltenham was a best - selling English author of Chick lit genre .
Prof James Syme FRCS FRSE DDL ( 7 November 1799 -- 26 June 1870 ) was a pioneering Scottish surgeon .
Warren Clive Christian ( 17 August 1914 - 19 January 2003 ) Served as Magistrate of the British Overseas Territory of Pitcairn Island twice , in 1950 - 51 and 1958 - 60 .
Wilhelm Roux ( 9 June 1850 -- 15 September 1924 ) was a German zoologist and pioneer of experimental embryology .
Herbert Busemann ( 12 May 1905 -- 3 February 1994 ) was a German - American mathematician specializing in convex and differential geometry .
Edwin Helfant ( 12 April 1926 -- 15 February 1978 ) was an American lawyer in Atlantic City , New Jersey .
Norman Curtis ( 10 September 1924 -- 7 September 2009 ) was an English - born footballer , who played as a full back in the Football League in the 1950s and 1960s .
William Grey , 9th Earl of Stamford ( 18 April 1850 -- 24 May 1910 ) was an English peer .
Hubert Marcoux ( February 2 , 1941 -- 2009 ) was a French - Canadian solo sailor , author and travel writer .
Theodora Kimball Hubbard ( 1887 - 1935 ) was the first librarian of the Harvard School of Landscape Architecture , and a contemporary of and collaborator with many significant figures in landscape architecture in expanding the body of knowledge in that subject area .
Ronny Coaches ( died 21 November 2013 ) , also known as Ronnie , was a Ghanaian - born musician and a member of the Buk Bak hiplife music group .
Alby McDonald ( 27 February 1881 -- 8 June 1961 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Carlos Clarens ( 1930 - -1987 ) was a film historian and writer on the cinema particularly noted for his sensitive , pioneering Illustrated History of the Horror Film ( 1967 , revised 1968 ) .
Herbert Greenhough Smith ( 1855 -- 14 January 1935 ) was the first editor of The Strand Magazine which published many of Arthur Conan Doyle 's Sherlock Holmes stories .
Robert Robson ( c.1765 - -1838 ) was a horse trainer , known as the Emperor of Trainers who ran `` the outstandingly successful stable of the first quarter of the 19th century . ''
K. Hugo Fernando ( 1912 - -1999 ) , popularly known as Hugo Master , was a Sri Lankan film personality .
Charles Sackville , 2nd Duke of Dorset PC ( 6 February 1711 -- 5 January 1769 , London ) was a British nobleman , politician , opera impresario and cricketer .
Ashok Chandwani ( 1950 - -2003 ) was a Canadian journalist of Sindhi descent based in Montreal .
Charles Wilson Murray ( died 15 August 1873 ) was an English businessman and member of the Legislative Council of Hong Kong .
Juan de los Reyes ( c. 1652 -- 1676 ) was a Spanish Catholic priest and evangelist who was among the protomartyrs of Guam .
Eric Westwood ( 25 September 1917 -- 2001 ) was an English professional footballer who played as a left back .
Giovanni Battista Morgagni ( 25 February 1682 -- 6 December 1771 ) was an Italian anatomist , celebrated as the father of modern anatomical pathology .
Leonard Salzedo ( 24 September 1921 -- 6 May 2000 ) was an English composer and conductor of Spanish descent .
Baldwin de Redvers , 1st Earl of Devon ( died 4 June 1155 ) , feudal baron of Plympton in Devon , was the son of Richard de Redvers and his wife Adeline Peverel .
Flavia Maxima Fausta ( 289 - -326 ) was a Roman Empress , daughter of the Roman Emperor Maximianus .
Katherine Swift ( 1956 - -2004 ) was an Irish - born Portuguese painter , illustrator and ceramicist .
Charlotte Wilder ( 1898 - -1980 ) was an American poet and the eldest sister of author Thornton Wilder , Isabel Wilder , Janet Wilder Dakin , and Amos Wilder .
Bradhurst Schieffelin ( born New York City , 21 September 1824 ; died Staten Island , 9 March 1909 ) was a United States druggist and activist .
John Henry Gurney Jr. ( 1848 - 1922 ) , was British ornithologist , son of John Henry Gurney Sr . and member of the Gurney family .
Heinrich Gutkin ( 13 June 1879 -- 11 October 1941 Sverdlovsk Oblast ) was a trader and the Estonian National Assembly member .
Huan Fan ( died 249 ) , courtesy name Yuanze ( 元則 ) , was a minister of the state of Cao Wei during the Three Kingdoms period .
Ernest Weekley ( 27 April 1865 -- 7 May 1954 ) was a British philologist , best known as the author of a number of works on etymology .
Stell Haggas ( 18 April 1856 -- 14 March 1926 ) was an English first - class cricketer , who played 31 times for Yorkshire County Cricket Club from 1878 to 1882 , and reappeared in three more games for Lancashire in 1884 and 1885 .
Shaun Cummins ( 8 February 1968 -- September 2012 ) was a British boxer who won the WBA Inter - Continental super welterweight title in 1992 and went on to fight for the British and European middleweight titles .
Jerzy Żyszkiewicz ( 17 January 1950 ; Oleśnica -- 12 July 2014 ; Wrocław ) was a Polish politician .
Alexander Annesley ( died 1813 ) , was an English legal and political writer of the late eighteenth century .
Jing Dianying ( Chinese : 敬奠瀛 , 1890 - -1957 ) was the founder of the Jesus Family , a major Chinese Pentecostal church movement .
Wolfram Freiherr von Richthofen ( 10 October 1895 -- 12 July 1945 ) was a German Generalfeldmarschall ( Field Marshal ) of the Luftwaffe ( German Air Force ) during the Second World War .
Waneta ( ca . 1795 - -1848 ) , also Wahneta , was a Yanktonai Dakota chief .
Jesús García Corona ( 13 November 1881 -- 7 November 1907 ) was a Mexican railroad brakeman who died while preventing a train loaded with dynamite from exploding near Nacozari , Sonora , in 1907 .
Dragotin Kette ( 19 January 1876 -- 26 April 1899 ) was a Slovene Impressionist and Neo - Romantic poet .
Alfred John Ellory or Jack Ellory ( 18 June 1920 , Cornwall -- 5 July 2009 ) was a British musician best known for playing flute on several of the James Bond films in the 1960s .
F. Ray Comstock ( 27 August 1878 -- 15 October 1949 ) was an American theatrical producer and theater operator .
Paul Vincent Carroll ( 10 July 1900 -- 20 October 1968 ) was an Irish dramatist and writer of movie scenarios and television scripts .
Thomas Haxby ( 25 January 1729 -- 31 October 1796 ) was an English instrument maker , particularly of keyboard instruments , including harpsichords , pianos , and organs .
Charles Gabriel Seligman FRS ( 24 December 1873 -- 19 September 1940 ) was a British physician and ethnologist .
Robert Barltrop ( 6 November 1922- 26 April 2009 ) was an English socialist activist , essayist , and biographer , as well as being an artist and illustrator .
Veborg ( died 750 ) , was a legendary Scandinavian shieldmaiden , famous for having participated in the legendary Battle of Bråvalla , which occurred in Sweden in approximately 750 .
Anthony Reckenzaun ( 1850 - -1893 ) was an electrical engineer who worked in the UK and the United States .
Mavelikkara Prabhakara Varma ( 1928 - -2008 ) was an Indian carnatic singer .
Daniel Haberman ( 1933 - -1991 ) was an American poet , translator and graphic designer .
Sir Gooroodas Banerjee , today also written Gurudas Banerjee , also Gurudas Bandyopadhyay ( Bengali Sir Gurudasa Banerjee স্যার গুরুদাশ ব্যানার্জী ) ( Calcutta , 26 July 1844- Calcutta , 2 December 1918 ) was a Bengali Indian judge of the Calcutta High Court .
Lieutenant - Colonel James Thomas Morisset ( 1780 -- 17 August 1852 ) , penal administrator , was commandant of the second convict settlement at Norfolk Island , from 29 June 1829 to 1834 .
Mary Fedden , OBE ( 14 August 1915 -- 22 June 2012 ) was a British artist .
Arne Hestenes , pen name Plut ( 29 January 1920 -- 3 January 1995 ) was a Norwegian journalist .
Eugeniusz Abrahamowicz ( 1851 - 1905 ) was a Polish conservative politician , lawyer , and landowner .
Tom Norman , born Thomas Noakes , ( 7 May 1860 -- 24 August 1930 ) , was an English businessman , showman and the last exhibitor of Joseph Merrick who was otherwise known as the `` Elephant Man '' .
Qarin I ( Persian : کارین ) , was the eight ruler of the Bavand dynasty from 839 to 867 .
Major - General Peter Raymond Leuchars , GCStJ , CBE ( b. 29 October 1921 , London ; d. 17 July 2009 ) was a British soldier who saw service in World War II in north west Europe .
Francis Henry Taylor ( 1903 - -1957 ) was a distinguished American museum director and curator , heading the Metropolitan Museum of Art for fifteen years .
Tommaso Caccini ( 1574 - -1648 ) was an Italian Dominican friar and preacher .
Henry Augustus Sims ( 1832 -- 1875 ) was a Philadelphia architect of the 19th century .
Maurice O'Doherty ( 17 November 1932 -- 5 April 1998 ) was an Irish broadcaster best known as a newsreader for the RTÉ News from 1966 until 1983 .
Antonios Mavromichalis ( Greek : Αντώνης Μαυρομιχάλης ; 1792 - -1873 ) was a Greek revolutionary , military officer and politician .
John McPhail ( 27 December 1923 -- 6 November 2000 ) was a Scottish international football player who spent his entire playing career with Celtic .
Benito Ruíz de Salazar Vallecilla ( ? --1651 ) was twice governor of Spanish Florida , from 1645 to 1646 and from 1648 to 1651 .
Henry Hatton ( ca 1793 -- July 31 , 1853 ) was an Irish - born merchant , ship builder and political figure in Nova Scotia .
Amal Kumar Raychaudhuri ( Bengali : অমল কুমার রায়চৌধুরী ; 14 September 1923 -- 18 June 2005 ) was a leading Indian physicist , renowned for his research in general relativity and cosmology .
Marie Wulf ( 1685 - -1738 ) , was a Danish preacher ; a pietist and later a follower of the Moravian Church .
Thomas Hiram Holding ( 1844 -- 1930 ) was a British traveling tailor and often considered the founder of modern camping .
Dagfinn Flem ( 28 July 1906 -- 28 May 1976 ) was a Norwegian politician , newspaper editor , non - fiction writer and translator .
Barten Holyday or Holiday ( 1593 - -1661 ) was a clergyman , author and poet .
Ernest - Eugène Hiolle ( 5 May 1834 - 5 October 1886 ) was a French sculptor who specialized in classical and allegorical figures in plaster and bronze , as well as many contemporary portrait busts .
Harinder Singh Giani ( born 2 September 1938 at Gujranwala and died 9 February 2007 at Chandigarh ) was an eminent jurist , who practiced at the bar of the Punjab and Haryana High Court at Chandigarh for over 42 years .
Ira Vail ( 22 November 1893 in Montreal , Canada -- 21 April 1979 in Daytona Beach , Florida ) was a Canadian - American racecar driver .
Timothy Cathcart ( 7 July 1994 -- 15 August 2014 ) was a Northern Irish rally driver from Enniskillen who was killed at the 2014 Todds Leap Ulster Rally , a round of the 2014 British Rally Championship season , after his car , a Citroën DS3 R3 T left the road and crashed near Fivemiletown .
Ralph Merrifield ( 22 August 1913 9 January 1995 ) was an English museum curator and archaeologist .
Jane Teller ( July 5 , 1911 -- December 23 , 1990 ) was an American printmaker and sculptor .
Jenő Takács ( Hungarian pronunciation : ( ˈjɛnøː ˈtɒkaːt͡ʃ ) ; 25 September 1902 -- 14 November 2005 ) was an Austrian composer of Hungarian extraction .
Paul of Edessa ( died 30 October 526 ) was the Syrian Orthodox bishop of Edessa .
Martino da Verona , also Marco del Buono Giamberti , ( died 1412 ) was an Italian painter .
Ferhad Pasha Sokolović ( Turkish : Sokollu Ferhad Paşa , Bosnian : Ferhad - paša Sokolović ) ( died 1586 ) was an Ottoman general and statesman from Bosnia .
Anna Kael ( 2 February 1908 -- 24 February 1985 ) was a Hungarian all - round sportswoman and university professor .
Henry Vaughan ( 17 April 1621 -- 23 April 1695 ) was a Welsh author , physician and metaphysical poet .
Jo Eisinger ( 1909 - 1991 ) was a film and television writer whose career spanned more than forty years from the early forties well into the eighties .
John Crew , 1st Baron Crew of Stene ( 1598 -- 12 December 1679 ) was an English lawyer and politician , who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1624 and 1660 .
John Jortin ( 23 October 1698 -- 5 September 1770 ) was an English church historian .
John Gage Marvin ( 1815 - -1855 ) was an American lawyer , known as a legal bibliographer and figure of the history of California .
Yang Shou - chung or Yang Shouzhong , birth name Yang Zhenming , ( 1910 - -1985 ) was the eldest son of Yang Chengfu .
Tommaltach Ua Conchobair , bishop of Elphin and archbishop of Armagh , lived from c. 1150 - 1201 .
Daniele Farlati ( 22 February 1690 -- 25 April 1773 ) was an ecclesiastical historian .
Teodor Dimitrijević ( Serbian Cyrillic : Теодор Димитријевић ; 1730 - -10 April 1781 ) , known as Teodor Kračun ( Теодор Крачун ) was a Serbian icon- and altar painter .
( Caspar ) Ferdinand Stadler ( 23 February 1813 -- 24 March 1870 ) was a Swiss architect of the generation before Gottfried Semper .
Richard Talbot , 1st Earl of Tyrconnell PC ( 1630 -- 14 August 1691 ) was an Irish royalist and Jacobite soldier .
Eliot Janeway ( January 1 , 1913 - -February 8 , 1993 ) , born Eliot Jacobstein , was an American economist , journalist and author , widely quoted during his lifetime , whose career spanned seven decades .
Guy de Beauchamp , 10th Earl of Warwick ( c. 1272 -- 12 August 1315 ) was an English magnate , and one of the principal opponents of King Edward II and his favourite Piers Gaveston .
André Raymond ( 7 August 1925 -- 18 February 2011 ) was professor emeritus at the University of Provence .
Tom Sweetman ( 5 January 1873 -- 5 May 1945 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Gösta Backlund ( 10 July 1893 -- 26 November 1918 ) was a Swedish footballer .
Sven Magnus Aurivillius was a Swedish zoologist born 12 August 1892 in Stockholm and died 4 March 1928 in Mörby .
Walter Earl Durand ( 1913 - -1939 ) was an American from Wyoming who became known as an outlaw after he escaped from jail and killed a number of officers who tried to apprehend him during an 11 day manhunt in the Teton mountains of Wyoming .
Branko Souček ( 25 April 1930 -- 12 December 2014 ) was a Croatian scientist , academic , pioneer of Croatian computer science .
Liao Chongzhen ( Chinese : 廖崇真 ; 25 May 1898 -- 12 September 1971 ) , ( Cantonese romanization : Chan Sung Liu ) , was a Chinese government official and president of the College of Agriculture at Sun Yat - sen University .
György Bernády ( Bethlen , 10 April 1864 -- Târgu Mureş , 22 October 1938 ) was the mayor of Târgu Mureş twice , 1900 - -1912 and 1926 - -1929 .
Princess Sudawadi , the Princess Yothathep ( Thai : สุดาวดี ; rtgs : Sudawadi , 1656 - -1735 ) was the only child of Narai and Princess Kasattri , one of his concubines .
Michael Heilprin ( Hungarian : Heilprin Mihály , 1823 -- 1888 ) was a Polish - American Jewish biblical scholar , critic , and writer , born at Piotrków , Russian Poland , to Jewish parents .
Vaughan Nash ( 1861 - -1932 ) was a British journalist , an economist and the husband of Rosalind Nash .
Edwin Mims ( 1872 - 1959 ) was an American university Professor of English literature .
María Díaz Cortés ( 4 January 1892 ? -- 15 January 2009 ) claimed to be the oldest living person .
Sir Francis Floud KCB KCSI KCMG ( 18 May 1875 -- 17 April 1965 ) was a British diplomat .
Ni Zhifu ( Chinese : 倪志福 ; Wade -- Giles : Ni Chih - fu ; May 1933 -- 24 April 2013 ) was a Chinese engineer , inventor , and high - ranking politician .
Francis Hare - Naylor ( 1753 - -1815 ) was an English historical author .
`` Count '' Byron Khun de Prorok ( 1896 - -1954 , born in Philadelphia as Francis Byron Kuhn ) was a Polish - American amateur archaeologist , anthropologist , and author of four heroic travelogues .
Toussaint de Forbin - Janson also known simply as Cardinal de Janson ( 1 October 1631 - 24 March 1713 ) was a French Catholic Cardinal and Bishop of Beauvais .
Laurel Martyn ( born Laurel Gill , 23 July 1916 -- 16 October 2013 ) was an Australian ballerina .
Giovanni Andrea Donducci ( 1575 - -1655 ) , also known as Mastelletta , was an Italian Baroque painter of the Bolognese School ( painting ) .
Thomas Ruthall ( also spelled Ruthal , Rowthel or Rowthall ; died 4 February 1523 ) was an English churchman , administrator and diplomat .
Gordon Colling ( 1932 or 1933 -- 4 June 2011 ) was a British trade unionist .
Thomas Dundas , 2nd Earl of Zetland , KG KT ( 5 February 1795 -- 6 May 1873 ) was a British nobleman and politician .
Salih Omurtak ( 1889 - -23 June 1954 ) was a Turkish general and the fourth Chief of the General Staff of the Turkish Armed Forces .
Edouard Zeckendorf ( 2 May 1901 -- 16 May 1983 ) was a Belgian doctor , army officer and mathematician .
Randolph Guggenheimer ( 1907 - -1999 ) was a lawyer and philanthropist .
George Willoughby , 17th Baron Willoughby of Parham ( c.1748/49 - -1779 ) was an English peer of the House of Lords .
Robert Evett ( 16 October 1874 -- 15 January 1949 ) was an English singer , actor , theatre manager and producer .
Francesco Anelli ( 1805 - -1878 ) was an Italian - American Romantic period artist .
Camille Alphonse Faure ( 21 May 1840 -- 14 September 1898 ) was a French chemical engineer who in 1881 significantly improved the design of the lead - acid battery , which had been invented by Gaston Planté in 1859 .
Ian Carr ( 21 April 1933 -- 25 February 2009 ) was a Scottish jazz musician , composer , writer , and educator .
William Dakins ( died 1607 ) was an English academic and clergyman , Gresham Professor of Divinity and one of the translators of the King James Bible .
Arno Nadel ( October 5 , 1878 -- March 1943 ) was a Jewish musicologist , composer , playwright , poet , and painter .
Yorick Smythies ( 1917 - -1980 ) was a pupil of philosopher Ludwig Wittgenstein .
Jules Ferdinand Fallou ( 9 August 1812 , Paris- 19 June 1895 , Paris ) was a French entomologist who specialised in Lepidoptera and Coleoptera Jules Fallou was a manufacturer of surgical instruments . His collection of European Lepidoptera , mostly from France and Switzerland is held by Muséum national d'histoire naturelle in Paris .
Saint Symeon Stylites of Lesbos ( 765/766 - 844 ) was a monk who survived two attempts on his life during the second period of Byzantine Iconoclasm ( 814 - -842 ) .
Maurice Jouvet ( Hendaye , 3 February 1923 -- Buenos Aires , 5 March 1999 ) was a French - born Argentine actor .
James MacCash ( 1834 - -1922 ) was the founder of the Order of Scottish Clans and founded it while celebrating his birthday in St. Louis in 1878 .
Ephraim Kibbey ( 1754 or 1756 -- 1809 ) was a United States soldier in the American Revolution , a frontiersman and early settler of Ohio , the leader of Mad Anthony Wayne 's famous forty scouts in the Northwest Indian War , and a member of the 1st Ohio General Assembly .
René of Savoy ( 1473 -- 31 March 1525 ) was a French nobleman and soldier .
Thomas Harrison Butler , DM , FRCS(Eng ) ( 19 March 1871 -- 29 January 1945 ) was a British ophthalmologist and amateur boat designer .
Adalram ( died 836 ) was an early 8th - century prelate active in Bavaria .
Leif Holbæk - Hanssen ( 27 March 1917 -- 10 April 1991 ) was a Norwegian professor of economics and anthroposophist .
Lancelotto Politi ( name in religion Ambrosius Catharinus ) ( 1483 - -1553 ) was an Italian Dominican canon lawyer .
George Carpenter , 3rd Earl of Tyrconnell ( 1788 -- 20 December 1812 ) , known as George Carpenter until 1805 , was a British peer and soldier who died fighting the French forces led by Napoleon Bonaparte at Wilna , Russia in December 1812 .
W. Bryan Dockrell ( 1929 - -2010 ) was a Scottish education researcher , with degrees from the University of Manchester , Trinity College Dublin , Edinburgh University and the University of Chicago .
Helmichis ( fl . 572 ) was a Lombard noble who killed his king , Alboin , in 572 and unsuccessfully attempted to usurp his throne .
Rudolf Gundlach ( 1894 - 1957 ) was a Polish engineer , inventor and tank designer .
Sir Edward Coey ( March 1805- 26 June 1887 ) was a 19th Century entrepreneur and philanthropist from Larne in County Antrim .
Harry Greaves ( 18 February 1895 -- 5 April 1974 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Nripa Kama II ( r. 1026 - -1047 CE ) was an early king of the Hoysala Empire from the malnad region of Karnataka and was possibly a feudatory of the Western Ganga Dynasty and fought many wars against the Cholas .
Bernardino de Cárdenas y Ponce , O.F.M. , ( 1579?--1668 ) was a friar of the Franciscan order and Bishop of Asunción and later Santa Cruz de la Sierra .
Thomas Guidott ( 1638 - -1706 ) , an English `` doctor of physick '' and writer , became one of the 17th century 's most prolific physical scientists .
Giorgio Mainerio ( ca . 1530 - 1540 -- 3 or 4 May 1582 ) was an Italian musician , composer , and cultist .
John Badby ( died 1410 ) , one of the early Lollard martyrs , was a tailor ( or perhaps a blacksmith ) in the west Midlands , and was condemned by the Worcester diocesan court for his denial of transubstantiation .
John Saxby ( 17 August 1821 -- 22 April 1913 ) was a British engineer from Brighton , noted for his work in railway signalling and the invention of the interlocking system of points and signals .
Geraint Dyfed Barri Jones ( 4 April 1936 -- 16 July 1999 ) was a classical scholar and archaeologist .
Sir William Earle Welby , 1st Baronet ( c. 1734 -- 6 November 1815 ) was a British land - owner , baronet and Member of Parliament for Grantham from 1802 to 1806 .
Theodor Riedel ( died 31 May 1916 ) was a Korvettenkapitän of the Imperial German Navy killed in World War I. He was commander of the 6th Torpedoboat half flotilla during the Battle of Jutland and was killed in action .
Przemysław of Toszek ( Polish : Przemysław Toszecki ) ( 1425 -- December 1484 ) was a Duke of Oświęcim during 1434 - -1445 ( with his brothers as co - rulers ) and Duke of Toszek since 1445 until his death .
Waldemar , Lord of Rostock ( before 1241 -- 9 November 1282 ) was the ruling Lord of Rostock from 1278 until his death .
Walter Stuart Surridge ( 3 September 1917 -- 13 April 1992 ) was a cricketer who played for Surrey .
Charles Eustache Gabriel ( 29 July 1788 - October 1862 ) , known as Rainulphe d'Osmond , count then 5th Marquis ( 1838 ) of Osmond .
Giacomo Antonio Fancelli ( 1619 - -1671 ) was an Italian sculptor in stone and stucco of the Baroque era .
Thomas C. O'Sullivan ( c.1858 Michigan -- July 29 , 1913 Spring Lake , Monmouth County , New Jersey ) was an American lawyer and politician from New York .
Tony Jay ( 2 February 1933 -- 13 August 2006 ) was a British actor , voice actor and singer .
Jack F. T. Ryan ( 3 December 1914 -- 31 July 1976 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Footscray and North Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Johannes Hubertus Leonardus de Haas ( 25 March 1832 -- 4 August 1908 ) was a Dutch animal and landscape painter , and a peripheral figure of the Hague School .
Gilbert Phelps ( 3 January 1915 -- 15 June 1993 ) was a British educationist and author , best known for nine distinguished novels that he wrote between 1953 and 1975 and for his literary criticism which embraces several foreign literatures , chiefly Russian and African .
Lennie Mayne ( 8 November 1927 -- 20 May 1977 ) was an Australian television director , who started out as a dancer before becoming a choreographer and then spent much of his career working in British television .
Kustaa Walter Kuusela ( 3 August 1903 , Honkilahti - 31 July 1985 ) was a Finnish farmworker , farmer and politician .
William Sutherland Dun ( 1 July 1868 -- 7 October 1934 ) was an Australian palaeontologist , geologist and president of the Royal Society of New South Wales .
Swarupadas ( 1801 - -1863 ) was a Rajasthani poet of the medieval era .
Princess Teresa Sapieha ( died c. 1784 ) was a Polish noble lady .
Count Alessandro Pompei ( 1705 - -1772 ) was an Italian architect and author of a prominent treatise on architecture :
Howard Mehring ( 1931 - -1978 ) was a twentieth - century painter born in Washington , D.C. Howard Mehring is associated with Color Field painting and the Washington Color School and the artists at Jefferson Place Gallery .
Anders Porsanger ( 1735 -- 10 October 1780 ) was the first Sami who received a higher education .
Bernard Daly ( 17 February 1858 -- 4 January 1920 ) was an American country doctor , businessman , banker , rancher , state representative , state senator , county judge , and regent of Oregon State Agricultural College ( today 's Oregon State University ) .
Benjamin Moloise ( 1955 -- 18 October 1985 ) was a South African poet and political activist .
Sir Richard Pryse , 1st Baronet ( died 1651 ) was a Welsh politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1646 to 1648 .
D. Miguel da Silva ( c. 1480 - 1556 ) was a Portuguese nobleman , the second son of Diogo da Silva , 1st Count of Portalegre and of his wife Maria de Ayala , a Castilian noblewomen .
Ambrose Barnes ( 1627 - -1710 ) , was an English nonconformist and Mayor of Newcastle .
Paddie Bell ( 8 April 1931 -- 3 August 2005 ) was an Irish folk singer and musician .
William Edward Julian Cayo - Evans ( 22 April 1937 - -28 March 1995 ) , was a Welsh political activist and one time leader of the Free Wales Army .
Zaka Siddiqi ( 1937 - 2003 ) was an Urdu poet and a critic of Urdu and Persian poetry .
Christian Geist ( c. 1640 -- 27 September 1711 ) was a German composer and organist , who lived and worked mainly in Scandinavia .
Mary Vivian Hughes ( 2 October 1866 -- May 1956 ) , usually known as Molly Hughes and published under M. V. Hughes , was a British educator and author .
Murasoli Maran died aged 69 on 23 November 2003 at Apollo Hospital in Chennai .
Justo Ángel Azpiazú ( Cienfuegos , 11 February 1893 -- Havana , 20 January 1943 ) , better known as Don Azpiazú , was a leading Cuban orchestral director in the 1920s and ' 30s .
Boris de Zirkoff ( 1902 - -1981 ) was the editor of the Collected Writings of H. P. Blavatsky .
Zoë Dominic OBE ( 4 July 1920 -- 11 January 2011 ) was a British dance and theatre photographer .
Col . Alan Coulston Gardner ( 1846 -- 25 December 1907 ) was a British Liberal Party politician and soldier .
Alain Glavieux ( French : ( glavjø ) ; 4 July 1949 , Paris -- 25 September 2004 ) was a French professor in electrical engineering at École Nationale Supérieure des Télécommunications de Bretagne .
Paul Langen ( 12 January 1893 -- 16 March 1945 ) was a German teacher who opposed the national socialist regime and spoke out against nazi propaganda and the continuation of World War II . He was arrested by the Gestapo and convicted of Wehrkraftzersetzung ( `` subversion of the war effort '' ) in 1943 .
John Lhotsky ( 1795 - -1866 ) was a Galicia - born Austrian naturalist , lecturer , artist and author .
Karl Klasen ( 23 April 1909 -- 22 April 1991 ) was a German jurist and served as president of the Bundesbank from 1970 to 1977 .
Domenico de ' Rossi ( 1659 - -1730 ) was an Italian sculptor and engraver .
Josefina Brdlíková née Mourková ( 20 March 1843 -- 21 April 1910 ) was a translator , singer , pianist and composer .
Pablo Hurus ( also Paul Hurus , Paul Hyrus , Paul Huros , Paulus de Constantia , born in Constance ; died after 1505 ) was a German printer of the late 15th - century , active in Zaragoza , Aragon during 1484 - -1499 .
Ross Jungnickel ( 1875 - 1962 ) was an American music publisher and arranger , and founder of a Baltimore Symphony Orchestra , a precursor to the modern organization of that name .
Miguel Costansó ( 1741 - -1814 ) , original name Miquel Constançó , was a Catalonian engineer , cartographer and cosmographer .
Sir Curzon Wyllie was assassinated on 1 July 1909 in London by the Indian revolutionary Madan Lal Dhingra .
António Xavier Machado e Cerveira ( Tamengos , Anadia , 1 September 1756-Caxias , 14 September 1828 ) was a Portuguese organbuilder .
Elizabeth Branwell ( 1776 in Penzance , Cornwall -- 29 October 1842 in Haworth , Yorkshire ) was the aunt of the literary sisters Charlotte Brontë , Emily Brontë , and Anne Brontë .
Ehud Netzer ( Hebrew : אהוד נצר‎ 13 May 1934 -- 28 October 2010 ) was an Israeli architect , educator and archaeologist , known for his extensive excavations at Herodium , where in 2007 he found the tomb of Herod the Great ; and the discovery of the Wadi Qelt Synagogue , the oldest known synagogue ever found .
Abu Amir Ahmad Ibn Gharsiya al - Bashkunsi ( Arabic : أبو عامر أحمد بن غرسية البشكنسي ‎ ) ( died 1084 ) , popularly known as Ibn Gharsiya was a Muwallad poet and katib ( writer ) in the taifa court of Denia .
Thomas Bower ( 1838 - -1919 ) was an English architect and surveyor based in Nantwich , Cheshire .
Alexander van Gaelen ( 1670 - 1728 ) , who was born at Amsterdam , was the scholar of Jan van Huchtenburgh , and , like his master , painted battles and subjects of the chase , which he treated with great fire and spirit .
Angela Vode ( Slovene pronunciation : ( aŋˈɡɛla vɔˈde ) ; 5 January 1892 -- 5 May 1985 ) was a Slovenian pedagogue , feminist author and human rights activist .
Gavin Douglas ( c. 1474 -- September 1522 ) was a Scottish bishop , makar and translator .
Rabbi Yechezkel Sarna ( 1890 - -1969 ) was a disciple of Rabbi Nosson Tzvi Finkel , ( known as the `` Alter ( elder ) of Slabodka '' ) , spiritual mentor of the Slabodka yeshiva .
Jakob Schaffner ( 14 November 1875 -- 23 September 1944 ) was a leading Swiss novelist who became a supporter of Nazism .
Sir Henry Turner Irving , GCMG ( 1833 - -1923 ) was a British Civil Servant and Colonial Administrator .
William Stukeley FRS , FRCP , FSA ( 7 November 1687 -- 3 March 1765 ) was an Anglican clergyman and English antiquarian who pioneered the archaeological investigation of the prehistoric monuments of Stonehenge and Avebury .
Adolf Diekmann ( 18 December 1914 -- 29 June 1944 Normandy ) was a German military officer and accused war criminal .
George O'Keeffe ( 12 August 1930 -- 3 March 2012 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Sir Richard Quain , 1st Baronet ( 30 October 1816 -- 13 March 1898 ) , was an Irish physician .
Humphrey Slade EBS ( 1905 -- 10 August 1983 ) was a Kenyan lawyer and member of parliament who served as the inaugural Speaker of the National Assembly , from 1967 to 1970 .
Raymond Anne ( 17 December 1922 -- 21 July 1944 ) was a member of the French Resistance during World War II ( 1939 - -45 ) .
Henry I , Count of Schwerin ( c. 1155 -- 17 February 1228 ) , also known as Henry the Black , was a German nobleman .
Decima Norman , MBE ( 9 September 1909 -- 29 August 1983 ) was an Australian athlete , who won five gold medals at the 1938 British Empire Games .
Henry Eric Bergman ( born Heinrich Erich Bergmann , 1893 - -1958 ) was a Canadian artist born in Germany .
Cenan Akın ( Şebinkarahisar , 1932 - Istanbul , 3 November 2006 ) was a Turkish composer , conductor and music educator .
Haldor Lillenas ( 19 November 1885 - 18 August 1959 ) was `` one of the most important twentieth - century gospel hymn writers and publishers '' and is regarded as `` the most influential Wesleyan / Holiness songwriter and publisher in the 20th century '' .
Garth Boomer ( died 1993 ) was an influential educationalist working in Australia .
William Bampton ( 1787 - -1830 ) , along with James Peggs , was the first English General Baptists protestant missionary to Cuttack , Orissa ( present Odisha ) in India .
Mansfield Markham ( 13 December 1905 -- 1971 ) was the second son of Sir Arthur Markham , Bt . , and his wife , Lucy , Lady Markham .
Jan Niezer ( 1756 - -1822 ) was a famous and influential Afro - European trader in the Dutch Gold Coast .
Policarpa Salavarrieta ( c. 26 January 1795 -- 14 November 1817 ) , also known as `` La Pola , '' was a Neogranadine seamstress who spied for the Revolutionary Forces during the Spanish Reconquista of the Viceroyalty of New Granada .
John Gardner Coolidge ( July 4 , 1863 -- February 28 , 1936 ) was an American collector , diplomat , author , and nephew of Isabella Stewart Gardner .
Aleksandra Marianna Wiesiołowska ( died on 14 August 1645 ) was the daughter of magnate Marek Sobieski and Jadwiga Snopkowska .
Henry Borlase ( ca . 1590 -- ca . 1624 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1621 and 1624 .
James Ireland Craig FRSE CBE ( 1868 - -1952 ) was a Scottish mathematician and meteorologist .
Sir William Muir , KCSI ( 27 April 1819 -- 11 July 1905 ) was a Scottish Orientalist , scholar of Islam , and colonial administrator .
Prince Varlam Cherkezishvili ( Georgian : ვარლამ ჩერქეზიშვილი ) ( Tiflis , 15 September 1846 -- London , 18 August 1925 ) was a Georgian politician and journalist , involved in anarchist communist movement , and later in the Georgian national liberation movement .
Bozoklu Mustafa Pasha ( 1638 -- December 1698 ) was an Ottoman statesman who served as grand vizier from 1693 to 1694 .
William Burkitt ( 25 July 1650 in Hitcham , Suffolk , England -- 24 October 1703 in Essex ) was a biblical expositor and vicar in Dedham , Essex , England .
Tajudeen Abdul - Raheem ( 6 January 1961 -- 25 May 2009 ) was the general secretary of the Pan - African Movement , director of Justice Africa , the Deputy Director of United Nations Millennium Campaign for Africa , as well as a writer for newspapers and journals across Africa .
William Miller Christy ( 1778 - -1858 ) was an English Quaker hat and textile manufacturer , known also as a banker .
Ikbal Hanimefendi ( Arabic : اقبال هانم افندی‎)(Turkish : İkbal Hanımefendi ) ( 22 October 1876 - 10 February 1941 ) , originally a Circassian slave brought to Egypt , became the Khediva consort of Egypt from 1895 to 1900 as the first wife of Abbas Hilmi II Pasha , the last Khedive of Egypt and Sudan .

Harry Saltau ( 17 September 1891 -- 25 July 1956 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with South Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Zev Hirsch Bernstein ( 1847 in Kudirkos Naumiestis , Augustów Governorate , Congress Poland -- 1907 in Tannersville , New York ) was the author and compiler of the Hatsofe B'Erez Hachadosho , the first Hebrew periodical in the United States .
Joseph Rodolphe Mathieu ( 10 July 1890 -- 29 June 1962 ) was a Canadian composer , pianist , writer on music , and music educator .
Robert Sithole ( 1945 -- 7 June 2006 ) , was a South African musician .
Lionel Cooper ( 1923 - -1987 ) was an Australian professional rugby league footballer of the 1940s and 1950s .
Sir Charles Bent Ball Hon FRCS MD FRCSI ( 21 February 1851 -- 17 March 1916 ) was an Irish surgeon and an honorary surgeon to the King in Ireland .
Joel Bean ( 1825 -- 1914 ) was a Quaker ( Religious Society of Friends ) minister whose name has been associated with a branch of Quakerism that some label `` Beanite . ''
Marguerite Beaubien ( 29 January 1797 -- 11 August 1848 ) was born in Nicolet , Lower Canada the daughter of a farm family in the Trois - Rivières region .
Max Drischner ( 31 January 1891 -- 25 April 1971 ) was a German composer , Kantor , organist , and harpsichordist .
Dr. Anugrah Narayan Sinha ( Singh ) ( 18 June 1887 -- 5 July 1957 ) , known as Bihar Vibhuti , was an Indian statesman who was the first Deputy Chief Minister cum Finance Minister of the Indian state of Bihar ( 1946 - -1957 ) .
Henry Peter Bosse ( 1844 - -1903 ) German - American photographer , cartographer and civil engineer .
Thirumalai Nayak ( well known as - Thirumalai Nayakkar ) ruled Madurai between A.D 1623 and 1659 .
Dawar or Dawar Bakhsh ( 1603 - 23 January 1628 ) , which means `` God Given '' was the ruler of the Moghul Empire for a short time between 1627 - 1628 , immediately after the death of his grandfather Jahangir ( r. 1605 - 1627 ) .
Odd Wang Sørensen ( 22 December 1922 -- 10 April 2004 ) was a Norwegian international footballer .
Ken Flower ( died 1987 ) was of Cornish extraction and worked for H.M. Customs & Excise before joining the British South Africa Police in Southern Rhodesia in 1937 .
Archibald McDonald ( 3 February 1790 -- 15 January 1853 ) was Chief Trader for the Hudson 's Bay Company at Fort Langley , Fort Nisqually and Fort Colvile and one - time deputy governor of the Red River Colony .
Antonino Votto ( 30 October 1896 - 9 September 1985 ) was an Italian operatic conductor .
Carl Kruse - Jensen ( 9 August 1889 -- 17 February 1981 ) was a Norwegian jurist , diplomat and international judge .
Ki no Tomonori ( 紀 友則 ) ( c. 850 -- c. 904 ) was an early Heian waka poet of the court , a member of the sanjūrokkasen or Thirty - six Poetry Immortals .
Georg von Vincke ( 5 May 1811 -- 3 June 1875 ) was a Prussian politician , officer , landowner and aristocrat of the Vincke family .
Edward Bullough ( 28 March 1880 -- 17 September 1934 ) was an English aesthetician and scholar of modern languages , who worked at the University of Cambridge .
Countess Maria Aurora von Königsmarck ( sv : Aurora Königsmarck ) ( 28 August 1662 -- 16 February 1728 ) was a Swedish and German noblewoman of Brandenburg extraction and mistress of Augustus the Strong , Elector of Saxony and King of Poland .
Wendell Milliman ( 1905 - -1976 ) was a founder of Milliman , Inc. , formerly Milliman & Robertson , one of the largest actuarial and business consulting firms in the world .
Anna Whitlock ( 13 June 1852 -- 16 June 1930 ) , was a Swedish reform pedagogue , journalist , suffragist and feminist .
Jackson Miles Abbott ( January 25 , 1920 -- 1988 ) was an American Lieutenant Colonel in the United States Army Corps of Engineers , a birdwatcher and painter .
Georgina Evelyn Cave Gaskin ( née France ) ( 8 December 1866 -- 29 October 1934 ) , known as Georgie Gaskin , was an English jewellery and metalwork designer .
Monk Basil von Burmann , OSB ( 1891 - 30 October 1959 ) was a Russian Greek Catholic deacon of German origin .
Pecksuot ( died 1624 ) was a chief of a Massachusett tribe in the early 17th century until his death in 1624 .
Gaetano Guadagni ( 16 February 1728 -- 11 November 1792 ) was an Italian mezzo - soprano castrato singer , most famous for singing the role of Orpheus at the premiere of Gluck 's opera Orfeo ed Euridice in 1762 .
Contra Force is an action shooting game released by Konami for the Nintendo Entertainment System in 1992 exclusively in North America .
Attack of the Zolgear ( also known as Galaxian3 : Attack of the Zolgear ) is an arcade game for one to six players released by Namco .
Micro Maniacs ( known as FoxKids.com Micro Maniacs Racing in North America and Denku Sekka Micro Runner in Japan ) is a racing video game developed by Codemasters for PlayStation and Game Boy Color .
Ultimate Soccer is a 1993 soccer video game by Rage Software released for the Mega Drive / Genesis by request of Sega which even allowed their mascot , Sonic , to be featured in the game menus .
SX Superstar is a video game of the racing genre by Climax Studios and published by Acclaim under their AKA Acclaim brand .
Lara Croft and the Temple of Osiris is an action - adventure game developed by Crystal Dynamics and published by Square Enix for Microsoft Windows , PlayStation 4 and Xbox One .
Hello Kitty Online ( HKO ) is a free - to - play massively multiplayer online role playing game developed by Sanrio Digital and Typhoon Games .
MountainsMap is a surface imaging and metrology software published by the company Digital Surf .
Left 4 Dead is a cooperative first - person shooter video game with survival horror elements , developed by Turtle Rock Studios and published by Valve Corporation .
TOCA 2 Touring Cars ( called TOCA 2 : Touring Car Challenge in the USA ) is a British racing video game developed and published by Codemasters , and released in 1998 .
Eurolot ended operations on 31 March 2015 .
The Great Atlantic & Pacific Tea Company , better known as A&P , was an American and Canadian chain of grocery stores that ceased supermarket operations in 2015 after 156 years in business .
In 1866 , Hesse - Homburg was inherited by the grand - duke of Hesse - Darmstadt , while Meisenheim fell to Prussia .
The Kingdom of Mapungubwe ( 1075 - -1220 ) was a pre - colonial state in Southern Africa located at the confluence of the Shashe and Limpopo rivers ( 22 ° 2′S 29 ° 36′E ) , south of Great Zimbabwe .
P&O Irish Sea was the trading name of P&O Ferries in the Irish Sea from 1998 to 2010 , when it was merged back into and rebranded P&O Ferries .
On 3 August 1802 , Prussian troops came into Warburg in anticipation of the decisions of German Mediatisation ( Reichsdeputationshauptschluss ) .
Samois was a lesbian - feminist BDSM organization based in San Francisco that existed from 1978 to 1983 .
The first Socialist Party of Canada ( SPC ) existed from 1904 to 1925 led by E. T. Kingsley .
Alexander Military Law Academy ( Russian : Александровская военно-юридическая академия ) ( 1867 - -1917 ) was an educational institution in Russian Empire that provided military law education for officers of Russian Army and Fleet .
LSV Berlin was lost in September 1944 , before the start of the 1944 - -45 season , its place in the Oberliga being taken by SG OrPo Berlin .
Aaja Chemnitz Larsen studied Master of Science ( MSc ) in Business Economics and Auditing at the University of Greenland and has a Executive management degree from INSEAD .
Sani Ndanusa obtained an MSc in Waste and Water Engineering from Loughborough University , United Kingdom .
Michael Harsegor ( 15 March 1924 -- 10 February 2011 ) was an Israeli historian and a professor of history at the Tel Aviv University .
Robert Cassen was born on 24 March 1935 and educated at Bedford School , at New College , Oxford , at the University of California , Berkeley , and at Harvard University , where he completed his doctorate in Economics .
Gert Korthof is a Dutch biologist who is trained in Utrecht University .
Paul Guiraud was a professor of Greek history to the faculties at Douai and Toulouse , and later a lecturer at the École Normale Supérieure .
Michael Shall graduated from Lycoming College in Williamsport , Pennsylvania and taught high school English before moving to New York City in 1974 to try to make a living as an origami professional .
In 1964 Asrani joined the Film Institute in Poona ( now Film and Television Institute of India , Pune ) and finished his course in 1966 .
The Rev. William Jewett Tucker ( July 13 , 1839 -- September 29 , 1926 ) served as the 9th President of Dartmouth College in New Hampshire , United States , from 1893 to 1909 .
Krishna Chandra Bhattacharya ( 12 May 1875 -- 11 December 1949 ) was a philosopher at the University of Calcutta who studied one of the central questions of Hindu philosophy , which is how mind , life or consciousness creates an apparently material universe .
Pierre Rosanvallon ( born 1 January 1948 , Blois ) is a French intellectual and historian , named professor at the Collège de France in 2001 .
Ali H. Sayed ( born Sao Paulo , Brazil , to parents of Lebanese descent ) is Professor of Electrical Engineering at the University of California , Los Angeles ( UCLA ) , where he teaches and conducts research on Adaptation , Learning , Statistical Signal Processing , and Signal Processing for Communications .
Pierre Ramond ( French : ( ʁamɔ̃ ) ; born 31 January 1943 ) is Distinguished Professor of Physics at University of Florida in Gainesville , Florida .
Kyeong - Hee Choi is an associate professor of modern Korean literature at the University of Chicago .
Harold Loukes ( died 7 August 1980 ) was a British academic in India and at the University of Oxford .
Lorraine Smith Pangle is a professor of political philosophy in the Department of Government and Co - Director of the Thomas Jefferson Center for the Study of Core Texts and Ideas at the University of Texas at Austin .
Vijay K. Thadani ( born 1951 ) is an Indian businessman who co - founded NIIT along with Rajendra S. Pawar in 1981 .
Akiko Yuge currently serves as Assistant Administrator and Director of the Bureau of Management at the United Nations Development Programme .
Carl Bereiter is an education researcher , professor emeritus at the Ontario Institute for Studies in Education , University of Toronto known for his research into Knowledge Building .
Nayan Shah is Professor of American Studies and Ethnicity at University of Southern California .
Jack Rudin ( June 20 , 1924 ) is a New York real estate developer and son of Samuel Rudin .
Sukhumala Marasri ( Thai : สุขุมาลมารศรี ; rtgs : Sukhumanmarasi ; 10 May 1861 -- 9 July 1927 ) was a daughter of King Mongkut ( Rama IV ) and his concubine , Samli ( เจ้าคุณจอมมารดาสำลี ) .
Leul Dejazmach ( `` Prince of the Cadet line '' ) Aberra Kassa was the second son of Ras ( `` Duke '' ) Kassa Haile Darge .
Jan Zamoyski was born on 19 March 1542 to Stanisław Zamoyski and Anna Herburt in Skokówka .
Anthea Askey was born in Golders Green , London , to the comedian and actor Arthur Askey , and his wife Elizabeth May Swash ( b. 1899 , m. 1925 , d. 1974 ) .
John II , Count of Nassau - Dillenburg ( c. 1365-May 1443 at Dillenburg ) was Count of Nassau - Dillenburg in Siegen and Dillenburg and son of Count John I , Count of Nassau - Dillenburg and Margareta of the Marck .
Nikolay Krasnov was born in the stanitsa Veshenskaya of the Don Host Oblast , the son of lieutenant - general Ivan Krasnov ( 1800 --1871 ) .
Archduchess Mechthildis of Austria ( 11 October 1891 -- 6 February 1966 ) was a daughter of Archduke Charles Stephen of Austria and a first cousin of King Alphonso XIII of Spain .
Ida de Grey or Edith de Grey ( 1368 -- 1 June 1426 ) , was a Cambro - Norman noblewoman , and the daughter of Reginald Grey , 2nd Baron Grey de Ruthyn , a powerful Welsh Marcher lord .
Muawiya II or Muawiya ibn Yazid ( Arabic : معاوية بن يزيد‎ , translit . Mu``āwiyah ibn Yazīd ; c. 664 - -684 CE ) succeeded his father Yazid I as the third Umayyad caliph and last caliph of the Sufyanid line . He ruled briefly in 683/684 ( 64 AH ) before he died .
IGS Energy , also known as Interstate Gas Supply , Inc. , is an independent retail natural gas and electric supplier based in Dublin , Ohio , United States .
Visiscience Corporation , headquartered in Chapel Hill , North Carolina , is a developer of scientific presentation tools and content for use in research and development , diagnostics and publishing .
Minecode , LLC was a privately held IT consulting company based in Bellevue , Washington , United States .
Porterbrook is one of the three major rolling stock operating companies ( ROSCO ) in the United Kingdom ( the other two being Angel Trains and Eversholt Rail Group ) .
American Capital has eight offices in New York , Boston , Chicago , Annapolis , London , Paris and Signapore , with its home office in Bethesda , MD .
Tidyman 's was a chain of grocery stores founded and based in Spokane , Washington .
National Institute on Retirement Security ( NIRS ) is a nonpartisan non - profit research institute based in Washington , D.C. , United States .

The Vyoksa River runs 84 kilometres ( 52 mi ) and drains into the Kostroma River in the town of Buy .
