The Bramau is an eastern tributary of the Stör in the German state of Schleswig - Holstein .
The Donaukanal ( `` Danube Canal '' ) is a former arm of the river Danube , now regulated as a water channel ( since 1598 ) , within the city of Vienna , Austria .
The Mohican River is a principal tributary of the Walhonding River , about 40 miles ( 64 km ) long , in north - central Ohio in the United States .
The Lam Takhong River is a river in Thailand and a tributary of the Mun River in eastern Thailand .
The Tigre River ( Spanish pronunciation : ( ˈtiɣɾe ) ) is a Peruvian tributary of the Marañón River west of the Nanay River .
The Schmutter is a river in Bavaria , Germany , a right tributary of the Danube .
The Acher is a river in the district of Ortenau , Baden - Württemberg , Germany and a right tributary of the Rhine River .
The Orlanka or Orlanka River , in eastern Poland , is a tributary of the Narew River .
Nerekhta River ( Russian : Нерехта ) is a river in Vladimir Oblast in Russia , a right tributary of the Klyazma River ( Volga 's basin ) .
The Rems is a right tributary of the Neckar in eastern Baden - Württemberg .
The Ciron is a left tributary of the Garonne , in Gironde , Southwest France .
After a length of 98 km ( 61 mi ) the Kaczawa empties into the Oder river at Prochowice .
The Klehini River is about 42 miles ( 68 km ) long from its source in British Columbia to its mouth at the Chilkat River , of which it is the largest tributary .
The Darby River rises below Mount Latrobe , part of the Latrobe Range , north of Wilsons Promontory and flows generally west by southwest before reaching its river mouth and emptying into Whisky Bay within Bass Strait in the South Gippsland Shire .
The Schlenze is a River in Germany and a left - bank tributary of the Saale .
The Höttinger Bach is a shortly 4 km long left tributary of the Inn in Innsbruck , Tyrol , Austria .
A left tributary of the Danube river , the Váh is 406 kilometres ( 252 mi ) long , including its Čierny Váh branch .
It originates on the slopes of Mount Kosciuszko , Australia 's highest mainland peak , draining the eastern slopes of the Snowy Mountains in New South Wales , before flowing through the Alpine National Park and the Snowy River National Park in Victoria and emptying into Bass Strait .
The Väike Emajõgi , is a river in southern Estonia that drains into Lake Võrtsjärv .
Ango River ( Russian : Анго ) is a tributary of the Omolon River in Russia 's Magadan Oblast in northeast Siberia .
Olinda Creek is a major tributary of the Yarra River in Victoria , Australia .
The Syas River flows from Valdai Hills north into Lake Ladoga .
Duffesbach is a river of North Rhine - Westphalia , Germany .
The source of the Dim River are the river systems in the highlands of Konya Province , with the river itself around 60 kilometres ( 37 mi ) flowing westwards into the Mediterranean Sea .
Nowendoc River , a perennial river of the Manning River catchment , is located in the Northern Tablelands and Mid North Coast districts of New South Wales , Australia .
Cobark River rises in the Barrington Tops within the Great Dividing Range , near Tunderbolts Lookout in the Barrington Tops National Park , and flows generally east by south , joined by the Dilgry River before reaching its confluence with the Barrington River , south southwest of the village of Upper Bowman .
The Harts River ( Afrikaans : Hartsrivier ) is a northern tributary of the Vaal River , which in turn is the largest tributary of the Orange River ( also known as the Gariep River , the largest river in South Africa ) .
The Unstrut is a river in eastern Germany and a left tributary of the Saale .
The Léez ( Leez , Lées , Léès , Lees ) , is a left tributary of the Adour , in the Southwest of France .
The Mekong Basin can be divided into two parts : the ' Upper Mekong Basin ' in Tibet of China , and the ' Lower Mekong Basin ' from Yunnan downstream from China to the South China Sea .
The Sirba River is a tributary of the Niger River in western Africa .
Mølleåen , also Mølleå , sometimes translated as the Millstream , is a small river in North Zealand , Denmark , which runs 36 kilometres ( 22 mi ) from the west of Bastrup Sø near Lynge to the Øresund between Taarbæk and Skodsborg .
The Sherabad River , Shirabad River or Sherabad Darya ( Darya meaning river ) is a right tributary of the Amu Darya in south - central Uzbekistan .
Mitta Mitta River , a perennial river and a direct tributary of the Murray River within the Murray - Darling basin , is located in the alpine district of Victoria , Australia .
The Souhegan River is a tributary of the Merrimack River in the northeastern United States .
Nassawango Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Maryland ; it is the largest tributary of the Pocomoke River , located on the Delmarva Peninsula .
The Oredezh River ( Russian : О́редеж ) is a river in Volosovsky , Gatchinsky , and Luzhsky Districts in the south - western part of Leningrad Oblast , Russia , a right tributary of Luga River .
The Lenne River is a tributary of the Ruhr River , and has caused flooding in recent years .
The Lokoro River is a river in the Democratic Republic of the Congo , one of the largest affluents of Lake Mai - Ndombe .
The Zusam is a small river in Bavaria , Germany and a right tributary of the Danube .
The Luján River ( Spanish , Río Luján ) runs from its source near Espora about 100 kilometres ( 62 mi ) east of Buenos Aires , Argentina , to its outflow into the Río de la Plata north of the city .
The Oxley Creek ( Yagara : Benarrawa ) is a creek that is a tributary of the Brisbane River , located in suburban Brisbane in the South East region of Queensland , Australia .
The Garonne follows the Aran Valley northwards into France , flowing via Toulouse and Agen towards Bordeaux , where it meets the Gironde estuary .
The Korolistskali ( Georgian : ყოროლისწყალი , alternative name Karolitskhali ) is a river by the East coast of the Black Sea , near Batumi , Georgia .
The Siuslaw River ( /saɪˈjuːslɔː/ sy - YEW - slaw ) is a river , about 110 miles ( 180 km ) long , that flows to the Pacific Ocean coast of Oregon in the United States .
The Teslin River is a river in southern Yukon Territory and northwestern British Columbia , Canada , that flows 632 kilometres ( 393 mi ) from its source south of Teslin Lake to its confluence with the Yukon River .
Glenne ( Möhne ) is a river of North Rhine - Westphalia , Germany .
Southampton Water is a tidal estuary north of the Solent and the Isle of Wight in England .
Rowleys River rises on the eastern slopes of the Great Dividing Range , southeast of Yarrowitch , and flows generally south southeast , joined by two tributaries including the Cells River , before reaching its confluence with the Nowendoc River , southeast of Nowendoc .
The Malše ( German : Maltsch ) is a river in Austria and in the Czech Republic , and a right tributary of the Vltava .
The Khulm River is one of the tributaries of the Amu Darya River , a major river in Central Asia .
The Nagel point is named after Christian Heinrich von Nagel , a nineteenth - century German mathematician , who wrote about it in 1836 .
The Plougastel Bridge , or Albert - Louppe Bridge , is a bridge over the Elorn River near Brest , France , connecting Plougastel - Daoulas and Le Relecq - Kerhuon .
The generic name honours Michel Adanson , the French naturalist and explorer who described Adansonia digitata .
San Francisco ( Spanish for Saint Francis ) was founded on June 29 , 1776 , when colonists from Spain established Presidio of San Francisco at the Golden Gate and Mission San Francisco de Asís named for St. Francis of Assisi a few miles away .
The Pioneer anomaly or Pioneer effect was the observed deviation from predicted accelerations of the Pioneer 10 and Pioneer 11 spacecraft after they passed about 20 astronomical units ( 3×109 km ; 2×109 mi ) on their trajectories out of the Solar System .
In mathematics , Karamata 's inequality , named after Jovan Karamata , also known as the majorization inequality , is a theorem in elementary algebra for convex and concave real - valued functions , defined on an interval of the real line .
Hilbert 's fifteenth problem is one of the 23 Hilbert problems set out in a celebrated list compiled in 1900 by David Hilbert .
A Weber bar is a device used in the detection of gravitational waves first devised and constructed by physicist Joseph Weber at the University of Maryland .
The Lyndon B. Johnson Space Center ( JSC ) is the National Aeronautics and Space Administration 's Manned Spacecraft Center , where human spaceflight training , research , and flight control are conducted .
The Gabriele Possanner State Prize ( German : Gabriele - Possanner - Staatspreis ) is a state award for feminist research in Austria , named for Gabriele Possanner .

The International János Bolyai Prize of Mathematics is an international prize for mathematicians founded by the Hungarian Academy of Sciences .
Rafflesia was found in the Indonesian rain forest by an Indonesian guide working for Dr. Joseph Arnold in 1818 , and named after Sir Thomas Stamford Raffles , the leader of the expedition .
AKB48 ( pronounced A.K.B. Forty - eight ) is a Japanese idol girl group named after the Akihabara ( Akiba for short ) area in Tokyo , where the group 's theater is located , and its original roster of 48 members .
Stibiopalladinite is a mineral containing the chemical elements palladium and antimony .
Some sources state that Petri nets were invented in August 1939 by Carl Adam Petri -- at the age of 13 - -for the purpose of describing chemical processes .
GNU GRUB was developed from a package called the Grand Unified Bootloader ( a play on Grand Unified Theory ) .
Jötunheimr ( or Jǫtunheimr ; often anglicized as Jotunheim ) is the homeland of the Jötnar , the giants in Norse mythology .
Legendre 's constant is a mathematical constant occurring in a formula conjectured by Adrien - Marie Legendre to capture the asymptotic behavior of the prime - counting function \scriptstyle\pi(x ) .
Max - Schmeling - Halle is a multi - purpose arena , in Berlin , Germany , named after the famous German boxer Max Schmeling .
The Atwood machine ( or Atwood 's machine ) was invented in 1784 by the English mathematician George Atwood as a laboratory experiment to verify the mechanical laws of motion with constant acceleration .
The Atkinson index ( also known as the Atkinson measure or Atkinson inequality measure ) is a measure of income inequality developed by British economist Anthony Barnes Atkinson .

The Bogardus social distance scale is a psychological testing scale created by Emory S. Bogardus to empirically measure people 's willingness to participate in social contacts of varying degrees of closeness with members of diverse social groups , such as racial and ethnic groups .
Marinism ( Italian marinismo , or secentismo , `` 17th century '' ) is the name now given to an ornate , witty style of poetry and verse drama written in imitation of Giambattista Marino ( 1569 - 1625 ) , following in particular La Lira and L'Adone .
Skeppsholmsbron ( Swedish : `` The Skeppsholm Bridge '' ) is in central Stockholm , Sweden , connecting Blasieholmen to Skeppsholmen .

The Mare Smythii is named for the 19th century British astronomer William Henry Smyth .

Meet the Press is a weekly American television news / interview program that is broadcast on NBC .
Born to the Wind is an American drama series that aired on NBC from August 19 , 1982 to September 5 , 1982 .
Wired For Sex is a television program on the former TechTV network showcasing how technology and the Internet have affected sex , including topics ranging from pornography to cyber sex .
Underworld , Inc. is an American documentary television series on the National Geographic Channel that explores the illegal , underground market .
The Hogan Family ( originally titled Valerie , and later , Valerie 's Family ) is an American sitcom that aired on NBC from March 1 , 1986 , to May 7 , 1990 , and on CBS from September 15 , 1990 , until July 20 , 1991 .
The Hat Squad is a crime drama television series that ran for only one season on CBS , during the 1992 - -1993 season .
Do Not Adjust Your Set ! ( DNAYS ! ) is a television series produced originally by Rediffusion , London , then , by the fledgling Thames Television for British commercial television channel ITV from 26 December 1967 to 14 May 1969 .
Back at the Barnyard is a Nickelodeon computer - animated television series that is a spin - off from the 2006 film , Barnyard .
From 3 May 2008 until April 2009 , Playr aired Saturday and Sunday mornings on Bravo .
Prized Apart is an adventure game show presented by Emma Willis and Reggie Yates that began airing on 13 June 2015 on BBC One .
Culpable de este Amor ( Guilty of this Love ) is an Argentine telenovela produced and broadcast by Telefe in 2004 .
Bad Girls Club ( abbreviated BGC ) is an American reality television series created by Jonathan Murray for the Oxygen network in the United States .
Boys Nxt Door is an award - winning youth oriented situation comedy from GMA Network .
Hits a Poppin was a Canadian music television series which aired on CBC Television in 1968 .
The CollegeHumor Show was an American television sitcom that premiered on MTV on February 8 , 2009 and also aired on MuchMusic .
The Inbetweeners is a British sitcom that originally aired on E4 from 2008 to 2010 .
The Danny Kaye Show is an American variety show hosted by Danny Kaye that aired on CBS from 1963 to 1967 on Wednesday nights .
Eisenhower and Lutz is an American sitcom which aired for thirteen episodes on CBS in 1988 .
Murder Call was an Australian television series , created by Hal McElroy for the Southern Star Entertainment and seen on the Nine Network between 1997 and 2000 .
Celebrity Time ( also known as The Eyes Have It ) was an American game and audience participation television series which aired originally aired on CBS and ABC from November 1948 to September 1952 .
On Your Way was an American game show that aired on the DuMont Television Network from September 9 , 1953 to January 20 , 1954 before moving to ABC from January 23 to April 17 .
Punk'd is an American hidden camera - practical joke reality television series that first aired on MTV in 2003 .
Pícara Sonhadora ( The Mischievous Dreamer ) is a Brazilian telenovela that was produced and aired by SBT from August 27 to December 27 , 2001 .
Oki Doki Doc ( also known as Oki Doki Dok ) is an ABS - CBN comedy sitcom which was shown from 1993 to 2000 .
Saturday Night Football ( branded for sponsorship purposes as Saturday Night Football on ABC presented by Wells Fargo ) is a weekly presentation of prime time broadcasts of NCAA Division I FBS college football games that are produced by ESPN , and televised on the American Broadcasting Company ( ABC ) .
Doctors to Be : 20 Years On is a biographical documentary series first broadcast on BBC Four by the BBC in 2007 .
Bracken 's World is an American drama series broadcast on NBC from September 19 , 1969 to December 25 , 1970 .
The Brotherhood of Poland , New Hampshire is an American drama series created by David E. Kelley that aired on CBS in 2003 .
American Experience is a television program airing on the Public Broadcasting Service ( PBS ) Public television stations in the United States .
Fantastikids is a fantasy / action - adventure series produced by GMA Network , Inc. and directed by Jun Lana and actor Zoren Legaspi .
Newsweek Views the News ( also known as Newsweek Analysis ) is an American television program broadcast Mondays at 8 pm ET on the DuMont Television Network .
Dara Ó Briain 's Science Club is a British science television series presented by Dara Ó Briain which first aired on BBC Two in 2012 .
Bright Promise is an American daytime soap opera that ran on NBC from September 29 , 1969 to March 31 , 1972 .
The Last 10 Pounds Bootcamp is a Canadian television show on the Slice network that puts participants through an intense fitness and nutrition routine designed to help them reach a target weight in four weeks .
H8R ( a texting abbreviation for Hater ) is an American television series for The CW .
Erin Burnett OutFront is an hour - long television news program hosted by Erin Burnett on CNN .
Cash in the Attic ran each weekday morning on BBC One , usually at 11:30 .
Sa Re Ga Ma Pa L'il Champs , a sub - series of Sa Re Ga Ma Pa , is a singing competition television series , which airs on Zee TV .
Closing Bell can refer to two CNBC programs , the original Closing Bell on CNBC ( which debuted on February 4 , 2002 ) , and European Closing Bell on CNBC Europe .
Father Murphy is an American western drama series that aired on the NBC network from November 3 , 1981 to September 18 , 1983 .
O Cravo e a Rosa ( English : The Carnation and the Rose ) is a Brazilian telenovela produced and broadcast by Rede Globo .
Saturday Night Live from Milano was the Italian localisation of the popular US - comedy television series Saturday Night Live , shown on Mediaset television channel Italia 1 from 2006 .
My Mad Fat Diary is a BAFTA - nominated British comedy - drama television series that debuted on E4 on 14 January 2013 .
Pulse of the City is an American television anthology drama series on the now - defunct DuMont Television Network .
The Men 's Room is a British television drama miniseries that was produced by the BBC and originally aired in 1991 .
Mutual Friends is a British comedy drama television series broadcast in six episodes on BBC One in 2008 .
You 're Whole is an American satirical television series created by Michael Ian Black for Adult Swim .
As the Bell Rings is a Disney Channel UK Original Interstitial program .
İntikam is a Turkish primetime television series that aired on Kanal D , starring Beren Saat and Yiğit Özşener .
Adventure Theater is a dramatic anthology series that aired on NBC in 1956 .
The Paradise Club is a BBC television drama starring Don Henderson and Leslie Grantham as Frank & Danny Kane .
Strong Medicine is a medical drama with a focus on feminist politics , health issues and class conflict , that aired on the Lifetime network from 2000 to 2006 .
Happy New Year , America was an American television special that aired on the CBS television network to celebrate the New Year .
Reborn in the USA was a British reality television show broadcast on ITV , in which ten British pop acts were transported to the USA , where they were supposedly not known in the hope of revitalising their music career .
Strange Empire is a Canadian television drama series , airing on CBC Television in the 2014 - -15 television season .
The Evermoor Chronicles is a British television series that airs on Disney Channel .
Street Crime UK was originally shown on Bravo and was later repeated on Virgin 1 ( which was later re - branded Channel One ) .
Inside Dish with Rachael Ray , hosted by Rachael Ray was a hybrid cooking / talk show on the Food Network .
Show Champion ( Korean : 쇼 챔피언 ) is a South Korean music television program that broadcasts live every Wednesday 6:00 PM KST at Bitmaru Broadcasting Center in Ilsan by MBC Music .
The New Inventors was an Australian television show , broadcast on ABC1 and hosted by broadcaster and comedian James O'Loghlin .
CNBC Market Wrap is a brief market update show airing on MSNBC weekday afternoons at the half - hour .
The Ultimate Christmas Present is a 2000 Disney Channel Original Movie starring Brenda Song and Hallee Hirsh .
DJ & the Fro is an animated series that aired on MTV .
I Want to Work for Diddy 2 is a reality show on VH1 .
Best of the Worst was a show aired by Fox Broadcasting Company as a part of its 1991 - 92 schedule .
The House That £ 100k Built is a British factual television series that was first broadcast on BBC Two on 18 September 2013 .
Tommy Zoom is a children 's animated television series , shown regularly on CBeebies in the UK .
Sin identidad ( English : No identity ) is a Spanish television series produced by Diagonal TV for Antena 3 .
Quick Fix Meals with Robin Miller is an American television program on the Food Network hosted by Robin Miller .
The New Bob Cummings Show is an American situation comedy which was broadcast by CBS during the 1961 - 62 television season .
A Case for the Court was a weekly CBC Television show that ran from July 1960 to September 1962 .
The Yemen thrush ( Turdus menachensis ) is a Middle Eastern member of the thrush family Turdidae .
The Crioceratidae constitute a family of loosely to closely coiled Ammonitida included in the Ancyloceratoidea that lived during the Early Cretaceous ; characterized by Crioceratites and other genera such as Hoplocrioceras and Paracrioceras .
Calydorea is a small genus of perennial , herbaceous and bulbous plants in the iris family ( Iridaceae ) native to Mexico and South America .
Ascoceratidae is a family of Ascocerida , bizarre nautiloid cephalopods , with longiconic , deciduous early growth stages which undergo period truncation and an inflated breviconic mature ascoceroid stage .
The Timneh parrot ( Psittacus timneh ) , also known as the Timneh grey parrot or Timneh African grey parrot , is a West African parrot that is variously considered a subspecies of the African grey parrot Psittacus erithacus timneh , or a full species Psittacus timneh .
The Mediterranean house gecko ( Hemidactylus turcicus ) ( not to be confused with the Asian species Hemidactylus frenatus known as common house gecko ) is a small gecko common to the Mediterranean which has spread to many parts of the world .
The Guatemalan flicker ( Colaptes mexicanoides ) is a woodpecker in the Picidae family .
The Sind sparrow ( Passer pyrrhonotus ) is a passerine bird of the sparrow family Passeridae , found around the Indus valley region in South Asia .
The Seram white - eye ( Zosterops stalkeri ) is a small passerine bird in the white - eye family .
Phaxas is a genus of small razor shells in the family Pharidae .
The European rhinoceros beetle ( Oryctes nasicornis ) is a large flying beetle belonging to the subfamily Dynastinae .
Discotectonica is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Architectonicidae , the staircase shells or sundials .
Aepsera ferruginea is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Aepsera .
Pseudolycopodiella is a genus of non - seed plants in the Lycopodiaceae , long considered part of Lycopodium but now recognized as a separate genus .
The Essex emerald ( Thetidia smaragdaria ) is a moth of the Geometridae family .
The Hysterangiales are an order of fungi in the class Agaricomycetes , subclass Phallomycetidae .
Japonactaeon is a genus of small predatory sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Acteonidae , the barrel bubble snails .
Anthriscus or Chervil is a common plant genus of the family Apiaceae , growing in Europe and temperate parts of Asia .
Eudonia is a large and widespread genus in the grass moth family ( Crambidae ) , subfamily Scopariinae .
Human coronavirus 229E is a single - stranded , positive - sense , RNA virus species in the Alphacoronavirus genus of the subfamily Coronavirinae , in the family Coronaviridae , of the order Nidovirales .
Guepinia is a genus of fungus in the Auriculariales order .
Heroceras descarpentriesi is a species of beetle in the family Dytiscidae , the only species in the genus Heroceras .
The Fly River trumpet - eared bat ( Kerivoula muscina ) is a species of vesper bat in the family Vespertilionidae .
Gobiops belongs to the family Brachyopidae .
Delalande 's coua ( Coua delalandei ) , also known as snail - eating coua and Delalande 's coucal , is an extinct species of non - parasitic cuckoo from Madagascar .
The Sulu hawk - owl ( Ninox reyi ) is a species of owl in the family Strigidae .
Simardoceras is a genus in the discosorid ( nautiloid cephalopod ) family Westonoceratidae from the Middle Ordovician of Quebec .
Shortridge 's horseshoe bat ( Rhinolophus shortridgei ) is a species of Horseshoe bat native to China , India and Burma .
Together with Sequoia sempervirens ( coast redwood ) and Sequoiadendron giganteum ( giant sequoia ) of California , Metasequoia is classified in the Cupressaceae subfamily Sequoioideae .
Notharctidae is an extinct family of adapiform primates found primarily in North America and Europe .
Retiskenea is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Neomphaloidea .
Naultinus tuberculatus , the West Coast green gecko or warty tree gecko , is a species of the family Gekkonidae ( gecko ) .
Epulorhiza is a genus of anamorphic fungi in the Tulasnellaceae family .
The Hylinae are the largest of three subfamilies of Hylidae , the `` tree frogs '' .
The Arctic shrew ( Sorex arcticus ) , also known as the blackback shrew or saddlebacked shrew , is a medium - sized shrew found in Canada and the northern United States .
Licinus is a genus of ground beetles in the Carabidae family native to the Palearctic ( including Europe ) , the Near East and North Africa .
Solenostomus is the only genus in the family Solenostomidae , and includes six currently recognized species .
Brachycrus is an extinct genus of terrestrial herbivore of the family Merycoidodontidae , subfamily Merycochoerinae , ( oreodont ) endemic to North America during the Middle Miocene to Late Miocene subepochs ( 20.6 - -13.6 mya ) existing for approximately 7 million years .
Hoogstraal 's gerbil , Gerbillus hoogstraali is distributed mainly in southwestern Morocco .
The Macinnes 's mouse - tailed bat ( Rhinopoma macinnesi ) is a species of bat in the Rhinopomatidae family .
Siparunaceae is a family of flowering plants in the magnoliid order Laurales .
Sphaerosporoceros is a genus in the hornwort family Anthocerotaceae .
The Ludwig 's bustard ( Neotis ludwigii ) is a species of bird in the bustard family , and named after Baron von Ludwig .
The Argus bare - eye ( Phlegopsis barringeri ) is a species of bird in the family Thamnophilidae .
The Djungarian hamster ( Phodopus sungorus ) , also known as the Siberian hamster , Siberian dwarf hamster or Russian winter white dwarf hamster , is one of three species of hamster in the genus Phodopus .
Bromelioideae is a subfamily of the bromeliads ( Bromeliaceae ) .
Protazteca is an extinct genus of ants in the subfamily Dolichoderinae , that were endemic to the United States , which was described by Carpenter in 1930 .
Howler monkeys ( genus Alouatta monotypic in subfamily Alouattinae ) are among the largest of the New World monkeys and one of only a few nest - building monkeys .
The Pátzcuaro chub ( Algansea lacustris ) is a species of freshwater fish in the family Cyprinidae .
Creolandreva is a genus of insect , belonging to the family of Gryllidae .
Phikzlikevirus ( synonym : PhiKZ - like viruses ) is a genus of viruses in the order Caudovirales , in the family Myoviridae .
Microsphinx is a genus of moths in the Sphingidae family , consisting of one species , Microsphinx pumilum , which is known from South Africa .
Parapercis is a genus of sandperches belonging to the fish family Pinguipedidae .
Heleniella is a genus of European non - biting midges in the subfamily Orthocladiinae of the bloodworm family ( Chironomidae ) .
Waterhouse 's leaf - nosed bat ( Macrotus waterhousii ) is a species of big - eared bat in the family Phyllostomidae .
Pomatosace filicula is a species of flowering plant in the family Primulaceae , endemic to the Qinghai--
Epidapus is a genus of fungus gnats in the family Sciaridae .
Ficopsis is an extinct genus of large sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Ficidae , the fig snails .
Krenopelopia is a Holarctic genus of the subfamily Tanypodinae of the non - biting midge family Chironomidae .
Syzygium is a genus of flowering plants that belongs to the myrtle family , Myrtaceae .
Gluta is a genus of plant in the subfamily Anacardioideae of the family Anacardiaceae .
Leptataspis is a genus of froghoppers belonging to the family Cercopidae .
The Asia Minor spiny mouse ( Acomys cilicicus ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Tripterotyphinae is a subfamily in the family Muricidae .
Agaricocrinus is a genus of extinct crinoid , belonging to the family Coelocrinidae .
Proiridomyrmex is an extinct genus of ants in the subfamily Dolichoderinae .
Macaldenia is a genus of moths of the Noctuidae family , it was considered a synonym of Dysgonia for some time .
Lithargyrus melzeri is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Lithargyrus .
Enneapterygius miyakensis , known commonly as the Izu Islands triplefin , is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Enneapterygius .
Azolla ( mosquito fern , duckweed fern , fairy moss , water fern ) is a genus of seven species of aquatic ferns in the family Salviniaceae .
Lander 's horseshoe bat ( Rhinolophus landeri ) is a species of bat in the family Rhinolophidae found in Africa .
The Maranhão slider ( Trachemys adiutrix ) , also commonly known as the Brazilian slider or Carvalho 's slider , is a species of turtle in the family Emydidae .
The Benguela long - billed lark ( Certhilauda benguelensis ) , also known as the Benguela lark is a species of lark in the Alaudidae family .
The Bannerman 's weaver ( Ploceus bannermani ) is a species of bird in the Ploceidae family .
Temnotropidae is an extinct family of fossil sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Haliotoidea , the abalones and their allies ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Peckoltia is a basal genus within the tribe Ancistrini of the subfamily Hypostominae .
The Shortridge 's free - tailed bat ( Chaerephon shortridgei ) is a species of bat in the family Molossidae .
Verschuren 's swamp rat ( Praomys verschureni ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Polystachya , abbreviated Pol in horticultural trade , and commonly known as yellowspike orchid , is a flowering plant genus in the orchid family ( Orchidaceae ) .
Wiliwili , with the scientific name Erythrina sandwicensis , is a species of flowering tree in the pea family , Fabaceae that is endemic to the Hawaiian Islands .
Livistona is a genus of palms ( family Arecaceae ) , native to southern and southeastern Asia , Australasia , and the Horn of Africa .
The Barbuda warbler ( Setophaga subita ) is a species of bird in the Parulidae family .
The Calamian treeshrew ( Tupaia möllendorffi ) is a treeshrew species found in the islands of Busuanga and Culion , which are part of the Calamian Islands group in the Philippines .
Procloeon is a genus of mayflies of the family Baetidae .
Saemundssonia is a genus of chewing lice belonging to the family Philopteridae .
The Palawan bulbul or grey - throated bulbul ( Alophoixus frater ) is a species of songbird in the Pycnonotidae family .
Black Creek Canal virus ( BCCV ) is a single - stranded , negative sense RNA virus species of New World Hantavirus .
Microhydrodytes elachistus is a species of beetle in the family Dytiscidae , the only species in the genus Microhydrodytes .
Lithodora is a genus of flowering plants in the family Boraginaceae , native to southwestern Europe , southern Greece , Turkey and Algeria .
Jovellania was named by Bayle ( 1879 ) and is type genus for the Jovellaniidae , a family assigned to the Oncocerida by Flower ( 1950 )
Margyricarpus pinnatus , commonly known as pearl - fruit , is an ornamental plant in the Rosaceae family , which is native to Southern America .
Pomatoschistus quagga , the Quagga goby , is a species of goby native to the western part of the Mediterranean Sea and the Adriatic Sea .
Macaca libyca is a prehistoric macaque from the Late Miocene of Wadi Natrun , Egypt .
The Australian sea lion ( Neophoca cinerea ) also known as the Australian sea - lion or Australian sealion , is a species of sea lion that is the only endemic pinniped in Australia .
Turpinia is a genus of trees and shrubs in family Staphyleaceae , native to Asia and North , Central , and South America .
Papuligobius is a genus of fish in the goby family , Gobiidae , native to Southeast Asia .
Betula kenaica , or Kenai birch , is a species of birch that can be found in Alaska and northwestern North America at 300 m ( 980 ft ) above sea level .
The Nicaraguan grackle ( Quiscalus nicaraguensis ) is a species of passerine bird belonging to the genus Quiscalus , a genus of grackles in the New World blackbird family , Icteridae .
Micraneflus imbellis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Micraneflus .
The genus Callophrys consists of butterflies in the family Lycaenidae .
Sp6likevirus ( synonym SP6-like viruses ) is a genus of viruses in the family Podoviridae , within the subfamily Autographivirinae .
The Blackbelly triplefin ( Enneapterygius fuscoventer ) is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Enneapterygius , described by German ichthyologist Ronald Fricke in 1997 and known from the western Pacific Ocean .
The African wedgefish , guitarra , Lubbert 's guitarfish , or spikenose wedgefish ( Rhynchobatus luebberti ) is a species of fish in the Rhynchobatidae family .
Gymnopilus is a genus of gilled mushrooms within the fungal family Strophariaceae containing about 200 rusty - orange spored mushroom species formerly divided among Pholiota and the defunct genus Flammula .
The Hova gallinule ( Hovacrex roberti ) is an extinct bird in a monotypic genus in the rail family .
The Andaman wood pigeon ( Columba palumboides ) is a species of bird in the family Columbidae .
Cardiocladius is a genus of non - biting midges in the subfamily Orthocladiinae of the bloodworm family ( Chironomidae ) .
Anomopoda is a suborder of the order Cladocera .
Callionymus filamentosus , the Blotchfin dragonet , is a species of dragonet native to the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
Kunaibidion panamensis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Kunaibidion .
Colpoda is a genus of ciliate in the class Colpodea Order Colpodida Family Colpodidae .
Knipowitschia goerneri , the Corfu dwarf goby , is a species of freshwater goby endemic to the island of Corfu in western Greece .
Platyspermation is a possible genus of plant in family Escalloniaceae .
Though small in absolute diversity of genera , the Hemitheini are nonetheless the largest tribes of geometer moths in the subfamily Geometrinae .
Troughton 's sheath - tailed bat ( Taphozous troughtoni ) is a species of sheathtail bat in the family Emballonuridae , found only in Australia .
Catesby 's snail - eater ( Dipsas catesbyi ) , also commonly known as Catesby 's snail sucker , is a nocturnal species of nonvenomous snake endemic to northern South America .
The Nicobar sparrowhawk ( Accipiter butleri ) is a species of bird of prey in the family Accipitridae .
Amphiuridae ( commonly called long - armed burrowing brittle stars or burrowing brittle stars ) are a large family of brittle stars of the suborder Gnathophiurina .
Echinophacops is a trilobite in the order Phacopida , that existed during the lower Devonian in what is now China .
Eutolype was a genus of moths of the Noctuidae family , it is now considered a subgenus of Psaphida .
Shelley 's sparrow ( Passer shelleyi ) , also known as Shelley 's rufous sparrow or the White Nile rufous sparrow , is a sparrow found in South Sudan , Ethiopia , Uganda , and Kenya .
Cromeria is a small genus of fish in the Kneriidae family found in fresh waters in the Sudan , Mali , and Guinea in the Nile and Niger Rivers of Africa .
Ledebouria is a genus of African bulbous perennial herbs in the Asparagus family , Asparagaceae , subfamily Scilloideae .
The Chimanimani stream frog ( Strongylopus rhodesianus ) is a species of frog in the Pyxicephalidae family found in Zimbabwe and Mozambique .
The Burma pipistrelle ( Hypsugo lophurus ) is a species of vesper bat in the family Vespertilionidae found in Myanmar and Thailand .
Cecidosidae is a little - known family of primitive monotrysian moths in the order Lepidoptera which have a piercing ovipositor used for laying eggs in plant tissue in which they induce galls , or they mine in bark ( Davis , 1999 ; Hoare and Dugdale , 2003 ) .
The South Australian cobbler , Gymnapistes marmoratus , often just called `` cobbler '' in Australia , is a brown coloured fish that lives in estuaries in southern Australia , both on the eastern ( New South Wales ) and western ( Western Australia - near Perth ) coasts .
Aporrhais is a genus of medium - sized sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Aporrhaidae and the superfamily Stromboidea .
The Anchitheriinae are an extinct subfamily of the Perissodactyla family Equidae , the same family which includes modern horses , zebras and donkeys .
Pentameroceras is a straight to slightly exogastric breviconic oncocerid from the middle Silurian of North America and Europe belonging to the Trimeroceratidae .
Summer savory ( Satureja hortensis ) is the better known of the savory species .
Pulitzer 's longbill ( Macrosphenus pulitzeri ) is a species of bird .
Romanophora verecunda is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Romanophora .
Rhodopsalta is a genus of cicada in the family Cicadidae .
The Ridged - eye flounder , Pleuronichthys cornutus , is a flatfish of the family Pleuronectidae .
Monochaetum is a genus of flowering plants in the family Melastomataceae , native to warm temperate to tropical regions of the Americas .
Physocrotaphus ceylonicus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Physocrotaphus .
Omiodes is a moth genus in the family Crambidae ( which is sometimes included in the Pyralidae ) .
Neoopisthopterus , the longfin herrings , is a small genus of fish in the herring family , Clupeidae .
Achiropsetta tricholepis , the Finless flounder or Prickly flounder , is a species of southern flounder with a southern circumpolar distribution .
The European storm petrel , British storm petrel or just storm petrel ( Hydrobates pelagicus ) is a seabird in the storm petrel family , Hydrobatidae .
Hydrocharis is a genus of aquatic plants in the family Hydrocharitaceae described as a genus by Carl Linnaeus in 1753 .
The Brazilian guitarfish ( Rhinobatos horkelii ) is a species of fish in the Rhinobatidae family .
The Dominican myotis ( Myotis dominicensis ) is a species of vesper bat .
The Greenland shark ( Somniosus microcephalus ) , also known as the gurry shark , or grey shark , or by the Inuit name eqalussuaq , is a large shark of the family Somniosidae ( `` sleeper sharks '' ) native to the waters of the North Atlantic Ocean around Canada , Greenland , Norway , and Iceland .
The Indian flying fox ( Pteropus giganteus ) , also known as the greater Indian fruit bat , is a species of flying fox in the family Pteropodidae .
Sansanosmilus ( pronounced - San - San - Oh - SMILE - Uss ) is an extinct genus of carnivorous mammal of the family Barbourofelidae ( false saber - tooth cats ) endemic to Europe and Asia , which lived during the Miocene , 13.6 - -11.1 mya , existing for approximately 2.5 million years .
The Mindanao flying squirrel ( Petinomys mindanensis ) is a common species of squirrel that is endemic to the Philippines .
Cope 's giant salamander ( Dicamptodon copei ) is a species of salamander in the Dicamptodontidae family .
Erythraeidae is a family of mites belonging to the Trombidiformes .
Kinkonychelys is classified as a member of the Kurmademydini group in the family Bothremydidae , together with the late Cretaceous turtles Sankuchemys and Kurmademys , from India .
Synophropsis lauri , sometimes called the bay leafhopper , is a species of leafhoppers of the subfamily Deltocephalinae , tribus Fieberiellini .
Calycorectes is a genus of plant in family Myrtaceae first described as a genus in 1856 .
Oxyloma haydeni haydeni , common name the Niobrara ambersnail , is a subspecies of small , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Succineidae , the amber snails .
Arabidopsis ( rockcress ) is a genus in the family Brassicaceae .
Cyphocerastis uluguruensis , also known as Uluguru Mountain Grasshopper is a rare species of Grasshopper in the family Acrididae .
The Angolan multimammate mouse ( Myomyscus angolensis ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
The Patagonian bonneted bat ( Eumops patagonicus ) is a species of bat found in Argentina , Bolivia and Paraguay .
Nigorella is a spider genus of the Salticidae family ( jumping spiders ) from Africa .
The Forbes ' snipe , Coenocorypha chathamica , was a species of New Zealand snipe endemic to the Chatham Islands .
The Indian tent turtle ( Pangshura tentoria ) is a species of the Geoemydidae family of turtles found in India and Bangladesh .
The Mexican narrow - mouthed toad ( Hypopachus variolosus ) is a species of sheep frog native to the Pacific and Caribbean lowlands from southern Texas to Costa Rica .
The genus Ebolavirus is a virological taxon included in the family Filoviridae , order Mononegavirales .
Skirroceras is a Stephanoceratacean ( ammonite ) genus belonging to the family Stephanoceratidae .
Colinus is a genus of birds in the New World quail family , Odontophoridae .
Shortraker rockfish ( Sebastes borealis ) is an offshore , demersal species distributed from the southeastern Kamchatka Peninsula , Russia , to Fort Bragg , California .
Olenellina is a suborder of the order Redlichiida of Trilobites that occurs about halfway during the Lower Cambrian , at the start of the stage called the Atdabanian .
The Philippine tailorbird ( Orthotomus castaneiceps ) is a species of bird formerly placed in the `` Old World warbler '' assemblage , but now placed in the family Cisticolidae .
The Atlas dwarf lizard ( Atlantolacerta andreanskyi ) is the only species of genus Atlantolacerta in the wall lizard family , Lacertidae .
Paraholopterini is a tribe of beetles in the subfamily Cerambycinae , containing the single genus Paraholopterus and the single species Paraholopterus nahuelbutensis .
Monjurosuchidae is a family of prehistoric reptiles belonging to the order Choristodera .
Cavia is a genus in the subfamily Caviinae that contains the rodents commonly known as guinea pigs .
The Rock - pool blenny ( Parablennius parvicornis ) is a species of combtooth blenny found in the eastern central Atlantic ocean .
Piper gurnard ( Trigla lyra ) is a fish species from the monotypic genus Trigla , family Triglidae .
The Mount Dulit caecilian , Ichthyophis dulitensis , is a species of amphibian in the Ichthyophiidae family endemic to Bornweo and only known from near its type locality , Mount Dulit in northern Sarawak , Malaysia .
Conant 's salamander ( Bolitoglossa conanti ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .
Nothoalsomitra suberosa is a species of subtropical vines in the family Cucurbitaceae , the only member of the monotypic genus Nothoalsomitra .
Jacquemontia ( clustervine ) is a plant genus in the morning glory family Convolvulaceae .
Cratosilis is a genus of soldier beetle belonging to the family Cantharidae .
Buxus sempervirens ( common box , European box , or boxwood ) , is a species of flowering plant in the genus Buxus , native to western and southern Europe , northwest Africa , and southwest Asia , from southern England south to northern Morocco , and east through the northern Mediterranean region to Turkey .
Entandrophragma is a genus of eleven species of deciduous trees in the mahogany family Meliaceae , restricted to tropical Africa .
Lettuce mosaic virus ( LMV ) is a typical potyvirus ( genus Potyvirus , family Potyviridae ) , which causes one of the major virus diseases of lettuce crops worldwide .
Chthonocephalus is a genus of annual herbs in the family Asteraceae .
Hutton 's tube - nosed bat ( Murina huttoni ) is a species of vesper bat in the family Vespertilionidae .
Steinbach 's canastero or chestnut canastero ( Pseudasthenes steinbachi ) is a species of bird in the canastero genus Asthenes in the ovenbird family Furnariidae .
Rudivirus is a genus of viruses in the order Ligamenvirales ; it is the only genus in the family Rudiviridae .
The genus Plesiotrygon is a small genus of freshwater stingrays in the family Potamotrygonidae endemic to the major river systems of South America , with two recognized species :
The Smooth pimpleback , scientific name of Quadrula houstonensis , is a species of freshwater mussel .
Ausktribosphenidae and monotremes have been assigned to the larger group Australosphenida .
Tradescantia mosaic virus ( TZV ) is a plant pathogenic virus in the genus Potyvirus and the virus family Potyviridae .
Notelaea is a genus of Australian plants of the family Oleaceae .
The Angolan hylomyscus or Angolan wood mouse ( Hylomyscus carillus ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Amomyrtus is a genus of flowering plants in the myrtle family , Myrtaceae described as a genus in 1948 .
The Silver Y ( Autographa gamma ) is a migratory moth of the family Noctuidae which is named for the silvery Y - shaped mark on each of its forewings .
The Andean swallow ( Haplochelidon andecola ) is a species of bird in the family Hirundinidae .
Hyoscyamus niger , commonly known as henbane , black henbane or stinking nightshade , is a poisonous plant in the family Solanaceae that originated in Eurasia , though it is now globally distributed .
The African red - eyed bulbul or black - fronted bulbul ( Pycnonotus nigricans ) is a species of songbird in the Pycnonotidae family .
In their review of putative euparkeriids from China , Richard Butler and colleagues concluded that Wangisuchus is a nomen dubium at Archosauriformes indeterminate because its holotype lacked diagnostic characters , even though the thecodont tooth implantation pointed to a closer relationship to Archosauria than to Proterosuchus .
The Yellownape tripplefin ( Enneapterygius flavoccipitis ) , also known as the Northern bicoloured triplefin in Australia is a species of threefin blenny in the genus Enneapterygius .
Brachidius crassicornis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Brachidius .
The Ammoxenidae are a small spider family with 18 species in four genera .
Yareta or llareta ( Azorella compacta , also known as `` Llareta '' in Spanish , and historically as Azorella yareta ) is a flowering plant in the family Apiaceae native to South America .
Tariccoia is a genus of small to average size ( between 2.5 centimetres ( 0.98 in ) and 6 centimetres ( 2.4 in ) long ) marine arthropods in the Liwiidae Family , that lived during the late Ordovician period .
Cyclolobaceae is one of seventeen superfamilies of the Goniatitina suborder .
Gessella is a fossil genus of liverworts in the family Haplomitriaceae .
The Lake Eacham rainbowfish ( Melanotaenia eachamensis ) is a species of fish in the Melanotaeniidae family endemic to Yidyam ( Lake Eacham ) , Queensland , Australia .
The Pangani barb ( Barbus oxyrhynchus ) is a ray - finned fish species in the family Cyprinidae .
Acremonium is a genus of fungi in the family Hypocreaceae ; it used to be known as `` Cephalosporium '' .
The Xingan salamander ( Hynobius maoershanensis ) is a species of salamander in the Hynobiidae family , endemic to China : it is only known from its type locality , Mao'ershan ( Mount Mao'er ) in the Xing'an County , Guangxi .
The Ozark cavefish , Amblyopsis rosae , is a small subterranean freshwater fish native to the United States .
The Nicaraguan woodrat ( Neotoma chrysomelas ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae found in Honduras and Nicaragua .
Caspia is a genus of marine snails , brackish water snails and freshwater snails with a gill and an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .
The Boletobiinae are a subfamily of moths in the Erebidae family .
Pagellus is a genus of porgies in the family Sparidae .
Colus ( lat . colus , distaff ) is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Buccinidae , the true whelks .
Lanephus njumanii is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Lanephus .
Tienmutrechus dispersipunctis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Tienmutrechus .
Galactia is a genus of flowering plants in the legume family ( Fabaceae ) .
Pearson 's horseshoe bat ( Rhinolophus pearsonii ) is a species of bat in the family Rhinolophidae .
The Wakatobi flowerpecker ( Dicaeum kuehni ) is a songbird that is endemic to the Wakatobi Islands of Indonesia .
Durianella is a fungal genus in the suborder Boletineae , family Boletaceae of the order Boletales .
Rissooidea , originally named Rissoacea by Gray , 1847 , is a taxonomic superfamily of small and minute marine snails , belonging to the clade Littorinimorpha .
The Chinamanfish , Symphorus nematophorus , is a species of snapper native to the western Pacific Ocean .
The Afroalpine vlei rat ( Otomys orestes ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Trimusculus is a genus of medium - sized air - breathing sea snails or false limpets , marine pulmonate gastropod molluscs in the family Trimusculidae .
Caulolatilus intermedius , the Gulf bareye tilefish , is a species of tilefish native to the Gulf of Mexico .
Pisaura is a genus of Eurasian spiders in the family Pisauridae .
Typhlodromus is a genus of predatory mites belonging to the family Phytoseiidae .
Unabiara collaris is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Unabiara .
The Vilcabamba brush finch ( Atlapetes terborghi ) is a species of bird in the Emberizidae family .
Spiroplasma phage 1-R8A2B is a filamentous bacteriophage in the genus Plectrovirus of the family Inoviridae , part of the group of single - stranded DNA viruses .
Cadulus is a large genus of small tusk shells in the family Gadilidae .
Cobboldia is a genus of parasitic flies in the family Oestridae .
The Kinabalu shrew ( Crocidura baluensis ) is a species in the family Soricidae .
The Allegheny mound ant ( Formica exsectoides ) is a species of ant native to the Atlantic area of North America .
Androzelma gigas is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Androzelma .
The Puerto Rican nesophontes ( Nesophontes edithae ) , or Puerto Rican shrew , is an extinct soricomorph endemic to Puerto Rico .
Obetia is a genus of plants in the Urticaceae family , containing the following species :
The Tasmanian thornbill ( Acanthiza ewingii ) is a small brown bird only found in Tasmania and the islands in the Bass Strait .
The Mithrodia is a genus of starfish in the family Mithrodiidae .
In 2004 , Baurusuchidae was even defined as the most recent common ancestor of Baurusuchus and Stratiotosuchus and all of its descendants ; thus , the definition of Baurusuchidae relies on the inclusion of Stratiotosuchus .
The Nyonga forest tree frog , Leptopelis lebeaui , is a species of frog in the Arthroleptidae family endemic to the Democratic Republic of the Congo .
Maoricicada is a genus of cicada in the family Cicadidae , endemic to New Zealand .
Palaeovespa is an extinct genus of wasp in the Vespidae subfamily Vespinae .
Orthomorpha coarctata ( alternately known as Asiomorpha coarctata ) is a widely - introduced species of Polydesmidan millipede of the family Paradoxosomatidae .
Fossombroniaceae ( sometimes Riccardiaceae ) is a family of liverworts in the order Metzgeriales .
The Muenster yellow - toothed cavy ( Galea monasteriensis ) is a species of rodent in the family Caviidae .
The Damar flycatcher ( Ficedula henrici ) is a species of bird in the family Muscicapidae .
The Mindanao shrew ( Crocidura beatus ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Parvioris is a genus of small ectoparasitic sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Eulimidae .
Megahertzia is a genus of tree in the family Proteaceae .
Pseudevernia is a genus of lichenized fungi in the family Parmeliaceae .
The Microniinae is a subfamily of the lepidopteran family Uraniidae .
Least puffer , Sphoeroides parvus , is a species in the family Tetraodontidae , or pufferfishes .
Diapheromeridae is a family of stick insects ( order Phasmatodea ) .
The Ruwenzori thicket rat ( Grammomys ibeanus ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Emilia 's marmoset ( Mico emiliae ) , also known as Snethlage 's marmoset , is a marmoset endemic to Brazil .
Siciliaria is a genus of small , air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod molluscs in the family Clausiliidae , all of which have a clausilium .
It was formerly classified within the now - obsolete order Lycoperdales , which , following a restructuring of fungal taxonomy brought about by molecular phylogeny , has been split ; the species of Bovista are now placed in the family Agaricaceae of the order Agaricales .
The American painted lady or American lady ( Vanessa virginiensis ) is a butterfly found throughout North America .
Parastylotermes is an extinct genus of termite in the Isoptera family Stylotermitidae known from North America , Europe , and India .
The Tasmanian ruffe , Tubbia tasmanica , is a medusafish of the family Centrolophidae , found in temperate waters in the Indian and southwest Pacific Oceans , at depths of between 700 and 850 m. Its length is up to 67 cm .
Tyrrheniella is a genus of land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod molluscs in the family Hygromiidae , the hairy snails and their allies .
Manniophyton is a genus of lianas of the spurge family ( Euphorbiaceae ) described as a genus in 1864 .
The Ctenocerinae are a subfamily of spider wasps , Pompilidae , which contains a small number of genera , two in the Neotropics , four in Australia and the remainder in Africa .
Nothoceratidae is a family of nautiloid cephalopods in the orthoceratoid order Oncocerida in which shells are exogastrically or endogastrically breviconic , planospiral , or torticonic ; often with a constricted or visored aperture ; and a siphuncle commonly composed of concave segments and occupied by actinosiphonate deposits .
The Barbary stag ( Cervus elaphus barbarus ) or Atlas deer is a subspecies of red deer that is native to North Africa .
Allocotocera is a genus of flies in the family of Mycetophilidae .
Rhyacophila is a genus of insects in the family Rhyacophilidae .
The Burmese short - tailed shrew ( Blarinella wardi ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Pilocarpus is a genus of about 13 species of plants belonging to the family Rutaceae , native to the neotropics of South America .
The Rhabdidae are scaphopod members of the same molluscan family , belonging to the order Dentaliida .
Valhalloceras is assigned to the Oncocerida , it and the related genus Phthanoncoceras are united in the family Phthanoncoceratidae .
Stempfferia kholifa , the Kholifa Epitola , is a butterfly in the Lycaenidae family .
Fagonia is a genus of wild , flowering plants in the caltrop family , Zygophyllaceae , having roughly 34 , distinct species .
The Gizo white - eye or yellow - billed white - eye ( Zosterops luteirostris ) is a species of bird in the Zosteropidae family .
Pachnoda is a genus from the subfamily Cetoniinae with nearly all the of species living in Africa .
Ancistrochilus is a genus of the orchid family ( Orchidaceae ) , comprising only 2 species .
Carmotetraviridae is a family of viruses ; there is currently only one genus in this family , Alphacarmotetravirus , and one species in this genus , the type species Providence virus .
Mexican redknee tarantula ( Brachypelma smithi ) is a terrestrial tarantula native to the western faces of the Sierra Madre Occidental and Sierra Madre del Sur mountain ranges in Mexico .
The New Grenada sea catfish , or Cazon sea catfish ( Notarius bonillai ) is a species of catfish in the Ariidae family .
Epilobium is a genus in the family Onagraceae , containing about 160 - 200 species of flowering plants with a worldwide distribution .
Fuelleborn 's stream frog ( Strongylopus fuelleborni ) is a species of frog in the Pyxicephalidae family .
The Mombasa woodpecker ( Campethera mombassica ) is a species of bird in the Picidae family .
Stenodus is a genus of large - sized whitefish in the Salmonidae family .
Amycterini is atribe in the subfamily Cyclominae .

Pinnaspis , first described by Cockerell 1892 , is a genus of scale insects belonging to the family Diaspididae , or armored scale insects .
The genus Passerina is a group of birds in the Cardinal family Cardinalidae .
Clito is a Neotropical genus of spread - winged skipper in the family Hesperiidae .
Palibacus praecursor is a fossil species of slipper lobster , the only species in the genus Palibacus .
The Karoo eremomela ( Eremomela gregalis ) , also known as the yellow - rumped eremomela , is a species of bird formerly placed in the `` Old World warbler '' assemblage , but now placed in the family Cisticolidae .
Philcoxia is a genus of four rare plant species in the Plantaginaceae that are endemic to Brazil and resemble terrestrial species of the genus Utricularia .
Antrolana lira is a species of crustacean in family Cirolanidae , the only species in the genus Antrolana .

The Bennett 's woodpecker ( Campethera bennettii ) is a species of bird in the Picidae family .
Catharus is a genus of birds in the thrush family Turdidae .

Gastropteron is a genus of small colorful sea slugs , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Gastropteridae .
Speozuphium poulteri is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Speozuphium .
The Monterrey Spanish mackerel ( Scomberomorus concolor ) is a species of fish in the Scombridae family .
The Western Borneo caecilian or black caecilian , Ichthyophis monochrous , is a species of amphibian in the family Ichthyophiidae .
The Galápagos sea lion ( Zalophus wollebaeki ) is a species of sea lion that exclusively breeds on the Galápagos Islands and -- in smaller numbers -- on Isla de la Plata ( Ecuador ) .
De Winton 's golden mole ( Cryptochloris wintoni ) is a species of mammal in the family Chrysochloridae .
Stempfferia cercene , the Cercene Epitola , is a butterfly in the Lycaenidae family .
Mnesarchaeoidea is a superfamily of `` New Zealand primitive moths '' containing one family , Mnesarchaeidae and a single genus , Mnesarchaea , endemic to New Zealand .
Cechides is a weevil genus in the tribe Aterpini .
Leptopodomorpha is an infraorder of the order Heteroptera that contains 300 species .
Sagaranella is a mushroom genus in the family Lyophyllaceae that has been segregated from both Lyophyllum and Tephrocybe using molecular analyses .
Lacandonia is a genus of mycoheterotrophic plants in the Triuridaceae , with very unusual inverted floral morphology .
Carlavirus , formerly known as the `` Carnation latent virus group '' , is a genus of viruses in the order Tymovirales , in the family Betaflexiviridae .
Exophthalmus is a genus of broad - nosed weevils in the family Curculionidae .
Tropaeolum minus , the dwarf nasturtium is a species of perennial plant in the Tropaeolaceae family .
The Diaphanometopidae are thought to have been an early transitional group between the Ptychopariida ancestors and all other Phacopina .
Metascopus camerunicus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Metascopus .
Rhagovelia is a genus of aquatic bug in the family Veliidae .
Philydor is a genus of foliage - gleaners , birds in the family Furnariidae .
The African finfoot ( Podica senegalensis ) is an aquatic bird inhabiting the rivers and lakes of western , central , and southern Africa .
Hudepohlellus semilunatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Hudepohlellus .
The Kemp 's longbill ( Macrosphenus kempi ) is a species of Old World warbler in the Macrosphenidae family .
Desmoxytes , whose species are commonly known as the dragon millipedes , is a genus of millipede of the family Paradoxosomatidae found in southeast Asia .
Croperoides is a genus of moths in the family Lymantriidae , with specimens documented in Negele Boran , Ethiopia in 1940 by the Società Entomologica Italiana .
Lucihormetica is a South American genus of giant cockroaches from the family Blaberidae , collectively referred to as glowspot cockroaches .
Genetic analysis using 18S ribosomal DNA reveal Facetotecta to be the sister group to the remaining Thecostraca ( Ascothoracida and Cirripedia ) .
Menetus is a North American genus of freshwater snails , aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Planorbidae , the ramshorn snails .
Carpolestidae is a family of primate - like Plesiadapiformes that were prevalent in North America and Asia from the mid Paleocene through the early Eocene .
Fraxinus gooddingii ( Goodding 's ash ) is a tree native to Sonora and southern Arizona .
Spondylus is a genus of bivalve molluscs , the only genus in the family Spondylidae .

Calocera is a fungal genus in the Dacrymycetes order .
Lotononis is a genus of legumes in the family Fabaceae and the tribe Crotalarieae .
Eastern Bonelli 's warbler ( sometimes known as Balkan warbler ) is a `` warbler '' in the leaf warbler genus Phylloscopus .
Rhombodus is a prehistoric genus of ray belonging to the family Rhombodontidae .
Celeriac ( Apium graveolens var . rapaceum ) , also called turnip - rooted celery or knob celery , is a variety of celery cultivated for its edible roots , hypocotyl , and shoots .
Pseudolaelia is a small genus belonging to the orchid family ( Orchidaceae ) , the entire genus endemic to Brazil .
Idiocerus is a large genus of homopteran bugs belonging to the family Cicadellidae ( the leafhoppers ) .
The African desert warbler ( Sylvia deserti ) is a typical warbler .
Phomopsis is a genus of ascomycete fungi in the Diaporthaceae family .
The Mérida tapaculo ( Scytalopus meridanus ) is a species of bird in the Rhinocryptidae family .
The Australian bustard ( Ardeotis australis ) is a large ground bird of grassland , woodland and open agricultural country across northern Australia and southern New Guinea .
Most recently , workers have placed Choristodera within Archosauromorpha .
Le Conte 's thrasher ( Toxostoma lecontei ) is a pale bird found in the southwestern United States and northwestern Mexico .
Mirbelia is a plant genus belonging to the Fabaceae family .
Narcissus mosaic virus ( NMV ) is a plant pathogenic virus in the genus Potexvirus and family Alphaflexiviridae , which infects Narcissus .
Bulbaeolidia is a genus of marine nudibranch in the family Aeolidiidae .
Trissexodontidae is a family of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Helicoidea ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
The Florida mouse ( Podomys floridanus ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
The Dhofar shrew ( Crocidura dhofarensis ) is a white - toothed shrew found only in the Dhofar region of Oman .
The Vaurie 's nightjar ( Caprimulgus centralasicus ) is a species of nightjar in the Caprimulgidae family .
The Lecanoromycetidae are a subclass of fungi in the class Lecanoromycetes .
Cnodalon is a genus of darkling beetles in the family Tenebrionidae .
The New Britain goshawk ( Accipiter princeps ) is a bird of prey species in the family Accipitridae .
Turritis ( commonly known as rockcress , towercress or tower mustard ) is a plant genus in the mustard family ( Brassicaceae ) .
The Gila monster ( Heloderma suspectum , /ˈhiːlə/ HEE - lə ) is a species of venomous lizard native to the southwestern United States and northwestern Mexican state of Sonora .
Troschelvindex is a genus of land snails with an operculum : these terrestrial gastropod mollusks are in the family Pomatiidae .
Echinolittorina is a genus of small sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Littorinidae , the winkles .
The Zambezi yellowfish , Labeobarbus codringtonii , is commonly found throughout the Zambezi and Okavango Rivers in Southern Africa .
The Santa Marta brush finch ( Atlapetes melanocephalus ) is a species of bird in the Emberizidae family .
The Seychelles warbler ( Acrocephalus sechellensis ) , also known as Seychelles brush warbler , is a small songbird found on five granitic and corraline islands in the Seychelles .
The Waigeo brushturkey or Bruijn 's brushturkey ( Aepypodius bruijnii ) is a large ( approximately 43 cm long ) brownish - black megapode with a bare red facial skin , red comb , maroon rump and chestnut brown below .
Ductilodon is an extinct genus of lepospondyl amphibian in the family Diplocaulidae .
The North Pacific hake , Pacific hake , Pacific whiting , or Jack Salmon , Merluccius productus , is a ray - finned fish in the genus Merluccius , found in the northeast Pacific Ocean from northern Vancouver Island to the northern part of the Gulf of California .
Within the subdivision Agaricomycotina , which already excludes the smut and rust fungi , the Agaricomycetes can be further defined by the exclusion of the classes Tremellomycetes and Dacrymycetes , which are generally considered to be jelly fungi .
The Sydney funnel - web spider ( Atrax robustus ) is a species of Australian funnel - web spider usually found within a 100 km ( 62 mi ) radius of Sydney , New South Wales , Australia .
Trypanoporida is an extinct order of encrusting animals from the Tentaculita class , which were common in the Devonian oceans ( Weedon , 1991 ) .
The Javan flameback ( Chrysocolaptes strictus ) is a species of bird in the Picidae family .
Termitaphididae , occasionally called termite bugs , is a small tropicopolitan family of true bugs placed in the superfamily Aradoidea .
Comstock 's silverspot butterfly ( Speyeria callippe comstocki ) is a silverspot butterfly ranging from Northern California to Baja Mexico .
The Katanga masked weaver ( Ploceus katangae ) is a species of bird in the Ploceidae family .
The South African pouched mouse or southern African pouched mouse ( Saccostomus campestris ) is a species of rodent in the family Nesomyidae , which is viewed as actually representing a complex of undescribed species .
The Robertinida are an order of Middle Triassic to recent , benthic Foraminifera in which tests are planispirally to trochospirally coiled , with chambers provided with an internal partition and hyaline perforated walls composed of optically radiated aragonite .
The Systellommatophora ( synonym Gymnomorpha ) is a clade of primitive , air - breathing slugs , according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda ( Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
In all species of Lamontichthys , there is one pectoral fin spine and seven pectoral fin rays on each fin , as opposed to the rest of Loricariinae species which have one pectoral fin spine and only six pectoral fin rays .
The Chinese warty newt ( Paramesotriton chinensis ) is a species of salamander in the Salamandridae family .
The Bermuda chub , Kyphosus sectatrix , a sea chub of the genus Kyphosus , is found in the Caribbean and off Florida , Bahamas , Bermuda , and in the Gulf of Mexico along coral reefs and walls .
Nemophila is a genus found in the flowering plant family Boraginaceae .
Caddidae is a family of harvestmen arachnids with 15 known species , the only family of the Eupnoi superfamily Caddoidea .
The Uganda mangabey ( Lophocebus ugandae ) is a species of Old World monkey found only in Uganda .
The Tropitidae is a family of Upper Triassic Ammonoidea belonging to the Tropitaceae , a superfamily of the Ceratitida Tropitidae have subspherical to discoidal , involute to evolute shells with long body chambers and a ventral keel bordered by furrows .
Dnieper barbel ( Barbus borysthenicus ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Barbus .
Leptalpheus is a genus of shrimp in the family Alpheidae , containing the following eight species :
The Purus jacamar ( Galbalcyrhynchus purusianus ) or chestnut jacamar is a species of bird in the Galbulidae family .
Cephalorhynchus is a genus in the dolphin family Delphinidae .
Hurter 's spadefoot toad or Hurter 's spadefoot ( Scaphiopus hurteri ) is a species of American spadefoot toad ( family Scaphiopodidae ) found in the south central United States ( Texas , Louisiana , Arkansas , Oklahoma ) ; its range might extend to the adjacent northern Mexico .
The Colombian four - eyed frog ( Pleurodema brachyops ; in Spanish : sapito lipon ) is a species of frog in the Leptodactylidae family .
Rüppell 's broad - nosed bat ( Scoteanax rueppellii ) is a species of vesper bat found in Australia .
Xylocopa caffra is a species of Afrotropical carpenter bee that ranges from west to central and southern Africa , besides Madagascar and some Indian Ocean archipelagos .
Cache Valley virus ( CVV ) is a member of the Bunyaviridae family , Orthobunyavirus genus , and Bunyamwera serogroup , which was first isolated in 1956 from Culiseta inornata mosquitos collected in Utah 's Cache Valley .

Platycelyphium voense is a species of flowering plants in the legume family , Fabaceae .

Gulfoceras was a genus of rhinoceros endemic to North America from the Miocene , living from 23.03 - -20.4 mya existing for approximately 2.63 million years .
The Bohol sunbird ( Aethopyga decorosa ) is a species of bird in the Nectariniidae family .
Partulina is a genus of tropical air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Achatinellidae .
The Mimosoideae comprise a subfamily of the flowering plant family Fabaceae ( Leguminosae ) characterized by flowers with small petals and numerous prominent stamens .
Hyatt and Smith ( 1905 , p. 114 - 115 ) included the Gymnitidae in the suborder Ceratitoidea , which later became the superfamily Ceratitaceae and included in it genera more primitive than Gymnites as well as the more advanced Gymnites .
The Gansu hamster ( Cansumys canus ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae , endemic to China .
Bleher 's rainbowfish ( Chilatherina bleheri ) is a species of fish in the Melanotaeniidae family .
The Chrysomelinae are a subfamily of leaf beetles ( Chrysomelidae ) .
The New Zealand smelt , New Zealand common smelt , or New Zealand cucumber fish , Retropinna retropinna , is a smelt of the family Retropinnidae , found only in New Zealand at shallow depths in estuaries and rivers .
Gigantocypris is a genus of ostracod crustacean in family Cypridinidae , and probably the most famous ostracod in the world .
Cercophaninae is a subfamily of the family Saturniidae , up until recently often treated as a separate family , Cercophanidae .
Marginellidae , or the margin shells , are a taxonomic family of small , often colorful , sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the clade Neogastropoda .
Protodiplatys gracilis is an extinct species of earwigs , in the genus Protodiplatys , the family Protodiplatyidae , the suborder Archidermaptera , and the order Dermaptera .
Rhammatophyllum is a genus of plants in the family Brassicaceae , found primarily in Central Asia .
The Cumberlandian combshell , scientific name Epioblasma brevidens , is a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae .
The Borneo broadfin shark ( Lamiopsis tephrodes ) is a species of requiem shark , and part of the family Carcharhinidae .
Tachigali is a flowering plant genus in the legume family ( Fabaceae ) that contains 54 species .
The New Mexico whiptail ( Cnemidophorus neomexicanus ) is a female species of lizard found in the southern United States in New Mexico and Arizona , and in northern Mexico in Chihuahua .
Pachystachys is a genus of 12 species of flowering plants in the family Acanthaceae , native to rainforest in the Caribbean and Central and South America .
Fedexia is an extinct genus of carnivorous temnospondyl within the family Trematopidae .
Daphoenus , like the rest of its family , was called a `` bear dog '' because it had characteristics of both bears and dogs .
Ciridops is an extinct genus of Hawaiian honeycreeper species that occurred in prehistoric and historic times on the Hawaiian islands of Hawaii , Molokai , Kauai and Oahu .
The Arundinoideae are a subfamily of the true grass family Poaceae with around 40 species , including giant reed and common reed .
The Vancouver Island marmot ( Marmota vancouverensis ) naturally occurs only in the high mountains of Vancouver Island , in British Columbia .
The Ascension night heron ( Nycticorax olsoni ) is an extinct night heron species from the genus Nycticorax endemic to the South Atlantic island of Ascension .
The Angiosperm Phylogeny Website considers them to be a family of their own ( as the Atherospermataceae ) , and together with the Gomortegaceae and Siparunaceae form a distinct branch of the Laurales .
The Michoacan pocket gopher ( Zygogeomys trichopus ) is a species of rodent in the family Geomyidae .
Heliosperma is a genus of around flowering plants in the tribe Sileneae of the family Caryophyllaceae .
Plectropus is a genus of poisonous fly in the family Dolichopodidae .
Tapinomini is a tribe of Dolichoderinae ants with 6 genera and one extinct genus .
The Kalkadoon grasswren ( Amytornis ballarae ) , also called the Ballara grasswren , is a species of passerine bird in the family Maluridae .
The Jullien 's golden carp ( Probarbus jullieni ) is a species of endangered freshwater ray - finned fish in the Cyprinidae family found in Southeast Asian river basins .
Fuscicupes parvus is a species of beetle in the family Ommatidae , the only species in the genus Fuscicupes .
The Barratt 's warbler or African scrub warbler ( Bradypterus barratti ) , is a species of Old World warbler in the Locustellidae family .
The Toltec cotton rat ( Sigmodon toltecus ) is a rodent species in the family Cricetidae .
