Wood 's slit - faced bat ( Nycteris woodi ) is a species of slit - faced bat that lives in the dry savanna regions of Southern Africa .
Augustoceras is a nautiloid cephalopod genus included in the order Oncocerida and family Valcouroceratidae .
Franklinoceras is an early discosorid from the family Reudemannoceratidae , similar to the ancestral Reudemannoceras .
The Hourglass triplefin ( Enneapterygius elegans ) ( also known as the Elegant triplefin in the United Kingdom ) is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Enneapterygius .
Anisotome is a genus of flowering plant in the Apiaceae , with 16 species .
Galiciotyphlotes weberi is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Galiciotyphlotes .
The Kerguelen petrel ( Lugensa brevirostris ) is a small ( 36 cm long ) slate - grey seabird in the family Procellariidae .
The Atlantic trumpetfish , Aulostomus strigosus ( or incorrectly Atlantic coronetfish ) is a species of trumpetfish in the family Aulostomidae .
The Chinese noctule ( Nyctalus plancyi ) is a common and widespread species of bat belonging to the family Vespertilionidae .
The Gomantong myotis ( Myotis gomantongensis ) is a species of bat in the family Vespertilionidae that is endemic to Sabah district of Malaysia .
Betula utilis ( Himalayan birch , bhojpatra , Sanskrit : भूर्ज bhūrja ) is a birch tree native to the Himalayas , growing at elevations up to 4,500 m ( 14,800 ft ) .
Ophiolamia is a genus of parasitic sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Eulimidae .
Chlamydophora is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the aster family , Asteraceae , containing the single species Chlamydophora tridentata .
The Gymnodiniales are an order of dinoflagellates , of the class Dinophyceae .
Gnatholepis is a genus of fish in the family Gobiidae , the gobies .
The Japanese accentor ( Prunella rubida ) is a species of bird in the Prunellidae family .
The Tyrian metaltail ( Metallura tyrianthina ) is a species of hummingbird in the Trochilidae family .
The Atlantic mudskipper ( Periophthalmus barbarus ) is a species of mudskipper native to fresh , marine and brackish waters of the tropical Atlantic coasts of Africa , including most offshore islands , through the Indian Ocean and into the western Pacific Ocean to Guam .
Haplochrois is a genus of moth in the family Elachistidae , though some classifications place it in the Agonoxenidae , Coleophoridae or Cosmopterigidae .
Harmandina sinensis is a species of harvestmen in a monotypic genus in the family Sclerosomatidae .
The Spilopsyllini form a flea tribe ( or depending on classifications a subfamily called the Spilopsyllinae ) in the family Pulicidae .
The Guianan bonneted bat , or Thomas ' mastiff bat , ( Eumops maurus ) is a species of free - tailed bat from South America .
The Jouanin 's petrel ( Bulweria fallax ) is a species of seabird in the Procellariidae family .
Carriker 's round - eared bat ( Lophostoma carrikeri ) is a bat species from South America .
Dicranidion is a genus comprising 13 species of fungi in the family Orbiliaceae .
The Indochinese bush lark ( Mirafra erythrocephala ) is a species of lark in the Alaudidae family .
The Napo spiny rat , Proechimys quadruplicatus , is a spiny rat species from South America .
Leptrichillus minutus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Leptrichillus .
The genus Vernicia , commonly referred to as tung or tung - oil tree , is a genus in the spurge family Euphorbiaceae , first described as a genus in 1790 .
Togniniaceae is family of fungi in the order Diaporthales .
Galeojanolus is a genus of sea slugs , specifically nudibranchs , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Proctonotidae .
The Santa Marta tapaculo ( Scytalopus sanctaemartae ) is a species of bird in the Rhinocryptidae family .
Campephaga is a genus of bird in the cuckoo - shrike family Campephagidae .
Phoronis is one of the two genera of the horseshoe worm family ( Phoronidae ) , in the phylum Phoronida .
The Magazine Mountain middle - toothed snail also known as the Magazine Mountain shagreen , scientific name Inflectarius magazinensis , is a species of small , air - breathing , land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod molluscs in the family Polygyridae .
Viverra species are distinguished externally from the other genera of the Viverrinae by the structure of the fore feet , of which the 3rd and 4th digits are provided with lobes of skin , which act as protective sheaths for the retractile claws .
Cassinoceras ( `` Cassin Horn '' ) is of the nautiloid genus belonging to the endocerid family Piloceratidae that comes from the late Early Ordovician of eastern North America and adjacent territories .
The desmids are sometimes placed in a separate order Desmidiales , which is closely related to Zygnematales , and the two are placed together in the class Zygnematophyceae .
The California thrasher ( Toxostoma redivivum ) is a large thrasher found primarily in chaparral habitat in California and Baja California .
Melamphaus is an Old World genus of true bugs in the family Pyrrhocoridae , the cotton stainers .
Acanthosicyos is a genus of thorny shrubs of the botanical family Cucurbitaceae , subfamily Cucurbitoideae .
Hoplopteropsis is a small genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Eulimidae .
The New Ireland yellow tiger ( Parantica clinias ) is a species of nymphalid butterfly in the Danainae subfamily .
Psephochelys is classified as a member of the family Placochelyidae , which is within the larger placodont superfamily Cyamodontoidea .
Cryptofusus cryptocarinatus is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fasciolariidae , the spindle snails , the tulip snails and their allies .
The Pitcairn reed warbler ( Acrocephalus vaughani ) is a songbird in the genus Acrocephalus .
Azadirachta is a genus of two species of trees in the mahogany ( Meliaceae ) family .
Triendoceras is a fairly large endocerid named by Flower ( 1958 ) , included in the Endoceratidae by Teichert ( 1964 ) , characterized by a holochoanitic ventral siphuncle in which the cross section through the endocones has an opening in the shape of an isosceles triangle with a sharp apex ( corner ) pointing down .
Listracanthus first appeared in late Carboniferous strata in North America , and eventually disappear from the fossil record some time during the Late Triassic , making it one of the longest - lived genera in the family Edestidae .
The Taiwan whistling thrush , also known as Formosan whistling thrush , ( Myophonus insularis ) is a species of bird in the family Muscicapidae .
Leipoxais is a genus of Moth in the family Lasiocampidae .
Apsaustodon segregatus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Apsaustodon .
Anderson 's white - bellied rat ( Niviventer andersoni ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .

Lasiococca is a plant genus of the family Euphorbiaceae first described in 1887 .
The Japanese quail , Coturnix japonica , is a species of Old World quail found in East Asia .
Amphiasma is a genus of 7 species of flowering plants in the Rubiaceae family .
Afrospilarctia is a genus of tiger moths in the Erebidae family and are found in the Afrotropics .
Shortridge 's langur ( Trachypithecus shortridgei ) is a lutung native to Burma and China .
Psilotaceae is a family of fern - like plants ( in order Psilotales ) consisting of two genera , Psilotum and Tmesipteris .
Fowlpox is the worldwide disease of poultry caused by viruses of the family Poxviridae and the genus Avipoxvirus .
Peters 's flat - headed bat ( Platymops setiger ) is a species of bat in the family Molossidae and the monotypic genus Platymops .
The Southern Palawan tree squirrel ( Sundasciurus steerii ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
Gonocaryum is a genus of plants in the family Cardiopteridaceae described as a genus in 1861 .
The subgenus Siphlodora belongs to genus Drosophila and consists of two species that share a sigmoid - shaped posterior crossvein .
The Calinaginae are a butterfly subfamily from the family Nymphalidae .
Anoplotettix is a genus of leafhoppers belonging to the family Cicadellidae subfamily Deltocephalinae .
Gonioceras is derived from Armenoceras and is the type genus of Gonioceratidae .
Spider beetles are the approximately 500 species of beetles in the subfamily Ptininae of the family Anobiidae .
Tumerepedes is a genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae , endemic to the Afrotropics .
The Congulu forest tree frog , Leptopelis jordani , is a species of frog in the Arthroleptidae family endemic to Angola .
Vulture bees are a small group of three closely related American stingless bee species in the genus Trigona which feed on rotting meat rather than pollen or nectar .

Psilotum ( whisk fern ) is a genus of fern - like vascular plants , one of two genera in the family Psilotaceae , order Psilotales , and class Psilotopsida ( the other being Tmesipteris ) .
The family Stylodactylidae is a group of shrimp and the only representative of its superfamily ( Stylodactyloidea ) .
Grant 's golden mole ( Eremitalpa granti ) is a golden mole species .
Pycnopygius is a genus of bird in the Meliphagidae , or honeyeater , family .
Stegolophodon was a Stegodontidae with two tusks and a trunk .
The Great Nicobar serpent eagle ( Spilornis klossi ) , also known as the South Nicobar serpent eagle , is a species of bird of prey in the Accipitridae family .
St. Aignan 's trumpet - eared bat ( Kerivoula agnella ) is a species of vesper bat in the family Vespertilionidae .
The Tondano rat ( Taeromys taerae ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Ptychadena is a genus of frogs in the Ptychadenidae family , the grassland frogs .
Cetotheriidae is a family of baleen whales ( suborder Mysticeti ) .
Cycloctenidae is a spider family with 36 described species in 5 genera .
Several recent phylogenetic analyses of notosuchians have placed Anatosuchus outside of Notosuchia altogether , and therefore outside Comahuesuchidae .
Aphanopetalum is a genus of twining shrubs or vines in the family Aphanopetalaceae which are endemic to Australia .
Amathuxidia , commonly known as the koh - i - noors , is a genus of butterflies in the Nymphalidae family .
Agnatha ( Greek , `` no jaws '' ) is a superclass of jawless fish in the phylum Chordata , subphylum Vertebrata , consisting of both present ( cyclostomes ) and extinct ( conodonts and ostracoderms ) species .
The Brazilian arboreal mouse , Rhagomys rufescens , is a South American rodent species of the family Cricetidae .
Runcinoidea is a taxonomic superfamily ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) or a clade Runcinaecea ( according to the Malaquias et al . ( 2009 ) ) of sea slugs , marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Euopisthobranchia .
Chrysocrata is a genus of moths belonging to the family Tineidae that is found in Madagascar .
The Granada hare ( Lepus granatensis ) , also known as the Iberian hare , is a hare species that can be found on the Iberian Peninsula and on the island of Majorca .
Rathouisia is a genus of carnivorous air - breathing land slugs , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Rathouisiidae .
Poroderma is a genus of catshark , and part of the family Scyliorhinidae .
The Nehring 's blind mole - rat ( Spalax nehringi ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Parakmeria is a genus of tree in the family Magnoliaceae , consisting of 5 species , native to eastern Asia in southern China and Indochina .
The La Palma giant lizard ( Gallotia auaritae ) is a giant lacertid historically living on the island of La Palma ( Canary Islands , Spain ) ; its habitat ranged from sea level up to altitudes of 800 m. It probably lives in xerophytic vegetation and is presumably an egg - laying species .
Notacanthus is a genus of spiny eels in the family Notacanthidae .
The Madagascar free - tailed bat or Malagasy giant mastiff bat ( Otomops madagascariensis ) is a species of free - tailed bat formerly included as a subspecies of the large - eared free - tailed bat , but was later considered to be a distinct , endemic Malagasy species .
The Palawan blue flycatcher ( Cyornis lemprieri ) is a species of bird in the family Muscicapidae .
Sopatas ' black - kneed katydid ( Aprosphylus sopatarum ) is a species of katydid that is endemic to the Klein karoo biome of Western Cape province in South Africa .
Pyramidulidae is a family of small air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Pupilloidea .
The sole species Campecarpus fulcitus is closely related to the Cyphophoenix and Veillonia palms with which it shares the island chain .
The Eastern Province rocky ( Sandelia bainsii ) , also known as rocky kurper , is a species of fish in the Anabantidae family .
Hoplobrotula is a genus of cusk - eels .

Lampona is a genus of spiders in the family Lamponidae and native to Australia and New Guinea .

Dalcera is a genus of moths of the family Dalceridae with four Neotropical species .
Trachelocyphoides setulosus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Trachelocyphoides .
The genus Artanema is a small group of flowering plant species formerly included in the plantain family , Plantaginaceae , but classified in Linderniaceae by recent authors .

Bourbon virus is an RNA virus in the genus Thogotovirus of the family Orthomyxoviridae , which is similar to Dhori virus and Batken virus .

Lithotelestidae is a family of coral in the order Coenothecalia originally described in 1977 by Frederick Bayer and Katherine Muzik .
Adrianitaceae is one of seventeen superfamilies currently included in the Goniatitina , but only one of six there included in the Treatise , 1957 .
Gregori 's labeo ( Labeo gregorii ) is fish in genus Labeo .
Zygopetalinae is an orchid subtribe in the tribe Cymbidieae .
The Antillean piculet ( Nesoctites micromegas ) is a species of bird in the woodpecker family Picidae .
The Tennessee clubshell ( Pleurobema oviforme ) is a species of freshwater mussel in the family Unionidae , the river mussels .
Leptus is a genus of large mites belonging to the family Erythraeidae ; they resemble members of the related genus Balaustium , but can be distinguished by the eyes , which in Leptus species are set much further forward on the body than in Balaustium species .
Panthera onca veraecrucis ( Nelson and Goldman , 1933 ) was proposed as a subspecies of jaguar , which ranged from the Tabasco in Mexico to Texas in the United States , before 1939 .
The Cuban pauraque ( Siphonorhis daiquiri ) , also known as the Cuban poorwill , is an extinct species of nightjar from the island of Cuba in the Caribbean .
The Cuban flower bat ( Phyllonycteris poeyi ) , also called Poey 's flower bat , is a species of bat in the family Phyllostomidae .
The Japanese silver - biddy ( Gerres equulus ) is a species of mojarra native to the coastal waters of the western Pacific Ocean from southern Korea to southern Japan , though it does not occur around the Ryukyu Islands .
The Ballyhoo halfbeak or Ballyhoo , ( Hemiramphus brasiliensis ) , is a baitfish of the halfbeak family ( Hemiramphidae ) .
The Berothidae are a family of winged insects of the order Neuroptera .
Ceratocumatidae is a family of crustaceans of the order Cumacea .
Mukdenia is a genus of plants in the saxifrage family , Saxifragaceae , consisting of 2 species .
The Atlantic bluefin tuna ( Thunnus thynnus ) is a species of tuna in the Scombridae family .
Tropicbirds are a family , Phaethontidae , of tropical pelagic seabirds now classified in their own order Phaethontiformes .
Ceroplesis is a genus of flat - faced longhorns beetle belonging to the Cerambycidae family , Lamiinae subfamily .
The Poecilopsettinae are a subfamily of fish in the Pleuronectidae family , comprising three genera and 21 species .
The Australian smelt ( Retropinna semoni ) is a small , pelagic silvery freshwater fish found in large numbers in waters of the south eastern Australian mainland .
Hose 's broadbill ( Calyptomena hosii ) is a species of bird in the Eurylaimidae family .
Acanthocyclops is a genus of copepod crustaceans in the family Cyclopidae .
Cerastium is a genus of annual , winter annual , or perennial plants belonging to the family Caryophyllaceae .
Acerodon is a genus of bats in the family Pteropodidae containing five species , all native to forests in Southeast Asia , and all except one threatened .
The Suspicious lizardfish ( Saurida suspicio ) is a species of lizardfish that lives mainly in the Caribbean .
Algericeras is included in the acathoceratacean family Brancoceratidae and subfamily Mortonoceratinae .
Dilatris is a genus of herbs in the family Haemodoraceae , first described as a genus in 1767 .
The African foam - nest tree frog or western foam - nest tree frog ( Chiromantis rufescens ) is a species of frog found in the tropical rainforests of Central Africa .
Sematurinae is a subfamily of moths in the family Sematuridae , represented by at least 29 species in the Neotropics .
The Mediterranean barbel or southern barbel ( Barbus meridionalis ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the Cyprinidae family .
Stonebergia is an extinct genus in the rose family Rosaceae which contains the single species Stonebergia columbiana .
The Russian desman ( Desmana moschata ) ( Russian : выхухоль vykhukhol‍ ' ​ ) is a small semiaquatic mammal that inhabits the Volga , Don and Ural River basins in Russia , Ukraine and Kazakhstan .
Serjania is a genus of flowering plants in the soapberry family , Sapindaceae .
Crassagena depressa is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Crassagena .
Argna is a genus of air - breathing land snails , pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Argnidae .
Dolichopus is a large cosmopolitan genus of fly in family Dolichopodidae .
Fraser 's dolphin ( Lagenodelphis hosei ) or the Sarawak dolphin is a cetacean in the family Delphinidae found in deep waters in the Pacific Ocean and to a lesser extent in the Indian and Atlantic Oceans .
The Lake Rudolf lampeye ( Aplocheilichthys rudolfianus ) is a species of fish in the Poeciliidae family .
Petalostigma is a genus of plants under the family Picrodendraceae and the monogeneric subtribe Petalostigmatinae , first defined by von Mueller in 1857 .
Melon necrotic spot virus ( MNSV ) is a virus that belongs to the Carmovirus genus of viruses in the Tombusviridae family .
Parker 's spinetail or white - breasted spinetail ( Cranioleuca vulpecula ) is a species of bird in the Furnariidae family .
Maoricrypta is a genus of small to medium - sized sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Calyptraeidae , the slipper snails , cup and saucer shells and Chinese hat shells .
Norealidys is a replacement name for preoccupied earthworm genus Reynoldsia - non Reynoldsia ( Diptera : Muscidae ) ( nec botanical genus Reynoldsia of flowering plant family Araiaceae ) - under ICZN ( 1999 ) as previously flagged .
Eutrephoceras is classified under the family Nautilidae , which includes the only extant nautiloids of the genera Allonautilus and Nautilus .
The Australian emerald ( Hemicordulia australiae ) , is a species of dragonfly in the family Corduliidae .
The Jamaican euphonia ( Euphonia jamaica ) is a species of bird in the Fringillidae family .
The Peruvian night monkey ( Aotus miconax ) , also known as the Andean night monkey , is a nocturnal New World monkey endemic to northern Peru .
Gobiinae also known as the True gobies , are a subfamily of the goby family Gobiidae .
The Antilles pinktoe tarantula ( Avicularia versicolor ) , also known as the Martinique red tree spider or the Martinique pinktoe , is native to Guadeloupe , Dominica and Martinique in the Caribbean Sea .
Sanborn 's big - eared bat ( Micronycteris sanborni ) is a bat species from South America .
The Philippine flat - headed frog ( Barbourula busuangensis ) is a species of frog in the Bombinatoridae family .
Melichthys is a small genus in the triggerfish family ( Balistidae ) .
The Mauke starling or mysterious starling ( Aplonis mavornata ) was a species of starling found on the island of Mauke , Cook Islands .
Atlantasellus is a genus of crustaceans , and the only member of the family Atlantasellidae .
Narcissus late season yellows virus ( NLSYV ) is a plant pathogenic Potyvirus of the family Potyviridae which infects plants of the genus Narcissus .
Apatosuchus is now thought to be a basal member of the clade Loricata .
The Bornean blue flycatcher ( Cyornis superbus ) is a species of bird in the family Muscicapidae .
Pteroplatidius octocostatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Pteroplatidius .
The Colombian gracile mouse opossum ( Gracilinanus perijae ) is a species of opossum in the family Didelphidae .
Victaphanta is a genus of carnivorous air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Rhytididae .
In a review published in 1950 , the American ornithologist Dean Amadon treated the Laysan honeycreeper as a subspecies of the ʻApapane and adopted the trinomial name Himatione sanguinea freethii .
The Utah prairie dog ( Cynomys parvidens ) is the smallest species of prairie dog , a member of the squirrel family of rodents native to the south central steppes of the US state of Utah .
The Rondonia warbling antbird ( Hypocnemis ochrogyna ) is a species of bird in the family Thamnophilidae .
Anise ( /ˈænɪs/ ; Pimpinella anisum ) , also called aniseed , is a flowering plant in the family Apiaceae native to the eastern Mediterranean region and Southwest Asia .
Anisolabis subarmata , commonly known as the Christmas Island earwig , is a species of earwig in the genus Anisolabis , the family Anisolabididae , the suborder Forficulina , and the order Dermaptera .
Pomatias is a genus of small operculate land snails , terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the family Pomatiidae .
Sesbania is a genus of flowering plants in the pea family , Fabaceae , and the only genus found in tribe Sesbanieae .
Following the revision , many species formerly in the genus Penaeus have been reassigned to new genera in the family Penaeidae :
Megalibgwilia is a genus of echidna known only from Australian fossils that incorporates the oldest known echidna species .
The Tete veld aethomys or Tete veld rat ( Aethomys ineptus ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Stolzmann 's crab - eating rat ( Ichthyomys stolzmanni ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Coelastrum is a genus of green algae in the Scenedesmaceae family .
The Indian golden gecko or Beddome 's golden gecko ( Calodactylodes aureus ) is a species of gecko known only from the Eastern Ghats of India .
Pagurus is a genus of hermit crabs in the family Paguridae .
The Eurasian oystercatcher ( Haematopus ostralegus ) also known as the common pied oystercatcher , or ( in Europe ) just oystercatcher , is a wader in the oystercatcher bird family Haematopodidae .
Acutocapillitium is a genus of fungi that is tentatively placed in the family Agaricaceae ; its phylogenetic relationships to other genera in the family are not well known .
Eberhardtia is a genus of plant in the Sapotaceae described as a genus in 1920 .
Chernov 's skink ( Ablepharus chernovi ) is a species of skink native to Armenia , eastern Turkey , northern Syria , and the valleys of the Arax River , Zanga River , and Razden Rivers in the Caucasus .
Eriaxis is a monotypic genus of orchids ( family Orchidaceae ) belonging to the subfamily Vanilloideae .
Eucera is a genus of bees in the family Apidae subfamily Apinae and the tribe Eucerini - or long - horned bees .
Crossopriza is a genus of cellar spiders ( family Pholcidae ) .
The Australian spotted catshark , Asymbolus analis , is a catshark of the family Scyliorhinidae , found only around Australia between 32 and 38 ° S , at depths between 10 and 180 m. It can grow up to 90 cm .
Poranthereae is a tribe in the flowering plant family Phyllanthaceae .
The Niobe ground squirrel ( Lariscus niobe ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
The Cuban black hawk ( Buteogallus gundlachii ) is a bird of prey in the family Accipitridae , which also includes the eagles , hawks and Old World vultures .
Miohippus ( meaning `` small horse '' ) was a genus of prehistoric horse existing longer than most Equidae .
Austrosynthemis cyanitincta , more commonly known as the turquoise tigertail , is a species of dragonfly from south - western Australia in the family Synthemistidae .
Neotheoridae , or Amazonian primitive ghost moths , is a primitive family of insects in the lepidopteran order containing a single genus and species , Neotheora chiloides .
Peters ' caecilian , Epicrionops petersi , is a species of caecilian in the Rhinatrematidae family found in Ecuador , Peru , possibly Brazil , and possibly Colombia .
The Sucre antpitta ( Grallaricula cumanensis ) is a species of bird placed in the family Grallariidae .
Halodule is a genus of plants in the family Cymodoceaceae described as a genus in 1841 .
Oliver Rauhut ( 2003 ) proposed that Coeluridae was composed of Coelurus plus the compsognathids , but he and others have not since found the compsognathids to group with Coelurus .
Xenocaligonellididae is a small family of acariform mites of the prostigmatan superfamily Raphignathoidea .
Morinda is a genus of flowering plants in the madder family , Rubiaceae .
Longetia is a genus of plants under the family Picrodendraceae first described as a genus in 1866 .
Agamodon is a small genus of worm lizards in the Trogonophidae family .
Belgrandia is a genus of very small aquatic snails , operculate gastropod mollusks in the family Hydrobiidae .
The Zululand dwarf chameleon ( Bradypodion nemorale ) is a species of lizard in the Chamaeleonidae family .
Kissing gouramis , also known as kissing fish or kissers ( Helostoma temminckii ) , are large tropical freshwater fish comprising the monotypic labyrinth fish family Helostomatidae ( from the Greek elos ( stud , nail ) , stoma ( mouth ) ) .
Pallas 's squirrel ( Callosciurus erythraeus ) , also known as the red - bellied tree squirrel , is a species of squirrel native to Greater China , India , and Southeast Asia .
Labeo is a genus of carps in the family Cyprinidae .
Barakula petersonorum is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Barakula .
Pseudosystenocentrus foveolatus is a species of harvestmen in a monotypic genus in the family Sclerosomatidae .
Gonipterini is a tribe of weevils in the subfamily Curculioninae .
The Papuan logrunner or New Guinea logrunner ( Orthonyx novaeguineae ) is a species of bird in the Orthonychidae family .
The Mauritanian shrew ( Crocidura lusitania ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
The Smith 's shrew ( Chodsigoa smithii ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Erythroecia was a genus of moths of the Noctuidae family , it is now considered a synonym of Psectrotarsia .
The Flores mud moray ( Gymnothorax davidsmithi ) is an eel in the family Muraenidae ( moray eels ) .
The New Zealand swan ( Cygnus atratus sumnerensis ) is an extinct swan from the Chatham Islands and the South Island of New Zealand .
The Mount Matafao different snail , scientific name Diastole matafaoi , was a species of air - breathing land snails or semi - slugs , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Helicarionidae .
The Baja California slider ( Trachemys nebulosa ) is turtle belonging to the Trachemys genus of the family Emydidae .
The Cuban nesophontes ( Nesophontes superstes ) is an extinct species of soricomorph of the genus Nesophontes .
Dalquest 's pocket mouse ( Chaetodipus dalquesti ) is a species of rodent in the family Heteromyidae .
Chris McNeill ( 20 November 1954 -- 5 February 2011 ) was an American ski jumper who competed in the 1980 Winter Olympics .
Eli Bremer ( born May 31 , 1978 ) is a modern pentathlete competed for the United States at the 2008 Summer Olympics in Beijing , China .
Uwe Dünkel ( born 3 November 1960 in Gera ) is a German former racewalker who competed in the 1980 Summer Olympics .
Michelle Smith de Bruin ( born 16 December 1969 in Rathcoole , County Dublin ) is a retired Irish swimmer who achieved notable success in the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta , becoming Ireland 's most successful Olympian to date , and whose career ended with a ban from the sporting authorities for tampering with a urine sample .
Thomas Lejdström ( born May 31 , 1962 ) is a former Swedish freestyle and medley swimmer , who competed in the 1980 and 1984 Summer Olympics .
Robert Pražák ( December 2 , 1892 -- May 16 , 1966 ) was a Czech gymnast who competed for Czechoslovakia in the 1920 Summer Olympics and in the 1924 Summer Olympics .
Wayne Erdman ( born February 3 , 1952 in Kitchener , Ontario ) is a retired Canadian judoka who represented Canada in Judo at the 1976 Summer Olympics in Montreal , Canada .
Antonio Caballero Bravo ( born June 24 , 1967 in Guipúzcoa ) is a retired boxer from Spain , who represented his native country at the 1988 Summer Olympics in Seoul , South Korea .
Frank Pfütze ( 15 January 1959 -- 20 January 1991 ) was a German freestyle swimmer who competed at the 1976 and 1980 Summer Olympics in five events .
Helen Jameson ( born 25 September 1963 ) is an English former competitive swimmer who represented Great Britain at the 1980 Summer Olympics in Moscow .
A Sultan 's Ransom , released in 1989 , is the third full - length studio album released by the British heavy metal band Cloven Hoof .
Wolfpack Party is the final and second studio album by the Bay Area rap group The Pack .
`` Lark on My Go - Kart '' is a song by American hip hop recording artist Asher Roth , released on March 24 , 2009 as the second single from his debut studio album Asleep In the Bread Aisle .
Taping the Radio is the third studio album by New Zealand punk band Steriogram .
Non è gratis is the first album by Italian recording duo Rapstar .
Dub Housing is the second album by American experimental rock group Pere Ubu .
`` Lies and Truth '' is the seventh single by L'Arc - en - Ciel , released on November 21 , 1996 it reached number 6 on the Oricon chart .
`` Älskade ängel '' is a song , written by Per Johan Widestrand and recorded by Lill - Babs .
Xerxes The God - King is the seventh studio album by Horrorcore rapper , King Gordy .
Vicissitudes is an album by pianist Barry Harris recorded in 1972 and released on the German MPS label .
Alyosha Andonov ( Bulgarian : Альошa Андонов ) ( born 31 January 1961 in Sofia ) is a Bulgarian football head coach who is a former coach of PFC Belasitsa Petrich .
Mario Fabbrocino ( Ottaviano , January 5 , 1943 ) , is a powerful Italian crime boss of the Camorra -- the Neapolitan mafia .
Alba Rohrwacher was born in Florence , the daughter of a German father and an Italian mother .
Isaac Sweers ( Nijmegen , 1 January 1622 -- 21 August 1673 ) was a 17th - century Dutch admiral .
After beginning his career in New Orleans he led Jimmie Noone 's Apex Club Orchestra , an influential Chicago band that recorded for Vocalion and Decca Records .
Kuh Ledesma was born in Bacolod City , Negros Occidental , Philippines with a Lebanese lineage .
Péter Hannich ( born 30 March 1957 in Győr ) is Hungarian footballer .
Albert Parsons was born June 20 , 1848 , in Montgomery , Alabama , one of the ten children of the proprietor of a shoe and leather factory who had originally hailed from Maine .
Gustav Gröber ( born in Leipzig , 4 May 1844 ; died in Ruprechtsau near Strasbourg , 6 November 1911 ) was a German Romance philologist .

José María Estrada ( 1802 Granada -- 13 August 1856 Ocotal ) was the President of Nicaragua under Fruto Chamorro command to direct the war , from 12 March to 22 October 1855 .
Antonín Engel ( May 4 , 1879 , Poděbrady - October 12 , 1958 , Prague ) was a Czech architect , urban planner and architectural theorist .
Max Bromme ( 18 August 1878 , Grünberg , Silesia -- 9 September 1974 in Frankfurt ) was a German architect and horticulturist .
Dyzma Gałaj ( 1915 , Mystkowice - 2000 , Warsaw ) was a Polish sociologist and a politician .
Ben Shlomo Lipman - Heilprin ( Hebrew : ליפמן היילפרין‎ ) ( 1902 - 26 September 1968 ) was an Israeli physician and director of the Neurology Department of Hadassah Hospital in Jerusalem .
Blas C. Silva Boucher was a twentieth - century Puerto Rican engineer from Ponce , Puerto Rico .
Simplício Rodrigues de Sá ( 1785 , São Nicolau Tolentino , Cape Verde , -- 9 March 1839 , Rio de Janeiro ) was a Portuguese - born painter and art professor who spent most of his career in Brazil .
Willy Merkl ( 6 October 1900 -- 9/17 July 1934 ) was a German mountain climber who is most notable for his attempt to lead a German - American team up Nanga Parbat ( the Naked Mountain ) in the Pakistani Himalayas in 1932 .
Louis - Marie Désiré - Lucas ( 15 October 1869 , Fort - de - France , Martinique - 29 September 1949 , Douarnenez ) was a French painter .
Thomas Little ( August 27 , 1886 in Ogden , Utah -- March 5 , 1985 in Santa Monica , California ) was a United States set decorator on more than 450 Hollywood movies between 1932 and 1953 .
José María Leandro Gómez Calvo , better known as Leandro Gómez ( Montevideo , 13 March 1811 -- Paysandú , 2 January 1865 ) was a Uruguayan military officer and politician .
Maximilian Leidesdorf ( June 27 , 1818 -- October 9 , 1889 ) was an Austrian psychiatrist born in Vienna .
Johannes Deegener was killed on 31 July 1943 near Lake Ladoga , Russia .
Jerzy Bulanow ( Russian : Юрий Буланов , Yury Bulanov , Polish : Jerzy Bułanow ; 29 April 1904 , Moscow - 1980 , Buenos Aires ) was a Russian - Polish footballer .
Alboino I della Scala ( c. 1284 -- 28 October 1311 ) was the Scaliger Lord of Verona from 1304 until his death .
Yem Sambaur , ( Khmer : យ៉ែម សម្បូរ , Khmer pronunciation : ( jaem sɑmbou ) ) ( February 2 , 1913 -- 1989 in Paris , France ) was a Cambodian politician , and twice prime minister of Cambodia between 1949 - 50 .
Karl Rechinger ( 1867 - -1952 ) was an Austrian botanist born in Vienna .
José María del Castillo y Rada ( December 20 , 1776 in Cartagena de Indias -- June 5 , 1833 in Bogotá ) was a neo - granadine politician , President of the United Provinces of the New Granada from October 5 , 1814 until January 21 , 1815 .
Grifo continued his rebellion , but was eventually killed in the battle of Saint - Jean de Maurienne in 753 , while Pepin became king of the Franks as Pepin III in 751 .

Giovanni Battista Ferrandini ( c. 1710 -- 25 October 1791 ) , an Italian composer of the Baroque and Classical eras , was born in Venice , Italy and died in Munich , at the age of 81 .
Piero Ginori Conti , Prince of Trevignano , ( Florence , June 3 , 1865 - Florence , December 3 , 1939 ) was a businessman and Italian politician .
Eugène Panon , Comte Desbassayns de Richemont was born on 29 March 1800 in Paris .
Henriette Johanne Marie Müller , called the Zitronenjette , ( 18 July 1841 -- 8 July 1916 ) was a popular figure now identified with the city of Hamburg .
Alphonse Louis Poitevin ( Conflans - sur - Anille , 1819 -- Conflans - sur - Anille , 1882 ) was a French chemist , photographer and civil engineer who discovered the light -- sensitive properties of bichromated gelatin and invented both the photolithography and collotype processes .
Margherita Sparapani Gentili Boccapadule ( Camerino , 29 October 1735 - Rome , 13 December 1820 ) , was a Roman noble salon holder and traveler .

Charles I , Duke of Mecklenburg(-Güstrow ) ( 28 December 1540 in Neustadt -- 22 July 1610 in Güstrow ) , was the reigning Duke of Mecklenburg in the Mecklenburg - Güstrow part of the country .
Ken Kersey ( April 3 , 1916 , Harrow , Ontario -- April 1 , 1983 , New York City ) was a Canadian jazz pianist who spent most of his life working in the United States .
Luís Caetano Pereira Guimarães Júnior ( Rio de Janeiro , 17 February 1845 - Lisbon , 20 May 1898 ) was a Brazilian diplomat , poet , novelist and dramaturgist .
Corrado Lojacono ( Palermo , 22 January 1924 -- Milan , 23 October 2012 ) was an Italian singer , actor and song composer .
Teffi ( Russian : Тэ́ффи ) ( 21 May ( O.S. 9 May ) 1872 , Saint Petersburg -- 6 October 1952 , Paris ) was a Russian humorist writer .
Sophia Bardina ( Tambov , Russia 1853 - Geneva , Switzerland ? ) was a Russian revolutionary .
Alfred Roth ( born 27 April 1879 in Stuttgart - died 9 October 1948 in Hamburg ) was a German politician and writer noted for his anti - Semitism .
Władysław Bakałowicz ( 1831 , Chrzanów - 1904 , Paris ) was a Polish - French painter ; primarily of genre scenes and portraits .
Pauwels Franck known in Italy as Paolo Fiammingo and Paolo dei Franceschi ( c. 1540 - 1596 ) , was a Flemish painter , mainly of landscapes with mythological and religious scenes , who was active in Venice for most of his life .
Emery Roth ( Hungarian : Róth Imre , 1871 -- August 20 , 1948 ) was an American architect of Jewish descent who designed many of the definitive New York City hotels and apartment buildings of the 1920s and 1930s , incorporating Beaux - Arts and Art Deco details .
Mekertich Portukalian ( October 21 , 1848 , Constantinople - 1921 , Marseille ) was an Armenian teacher , who founded the Armenakan party in Van , in 1885 .
Walther Poppelreuter ( also incorrectly written in the literature Walther Poppelreuther and Walter Poppelreuter ; born October 8 , 1886 in Saarbrücken ; died June 11 , 1939 in Bonn ) was a German psychologist and neurologist .
Andrea Camassei ( November 1602 -- 1649 ) was an Italian Baroque painter and engraver , who was mainly active in Rome under the patronage of the Barberini .
Generalleutnant Kurt Schmidt died on March 3 , 1945 in Aalsmeer whilst commander of the 526th Reserve Division .
Georg Haentzschel ( born in Berlin 23 December 1907 , died in Cologne 12 April 1992 ) was a German pianist , broadcaster , composer and arranger .
Edmund Blampied was born on a farm in the Parish of Saint Martin , Jersey in the Channel Islands on 30 March 1886 , five days after the death of his father , John Blampied .
Constant Vincent Houlbert ( 18 July 1857 in Voutré en Mayenne -- 22 December 1947 in Rennes ) was a French entomologist who specialised in Lepidoptera and Coleoptera .
Arthur von Weinberg ( 11 August 1860 in Frankfurt am Main - 20 March 1943 in the Theresienstadt Ghetto ) was a German chemist and industrialist .
Paul Ricca , also known as The Waiter ( 1897 -- October 11 , 1972 ) , was a Chicago mobster who served as the nominal or de facto leader of the Chicago Outfit for 40 years .
Count Franz Deym ( 23 August 1838 at Neuschloss , Hohenelbe ( now Dolní Olešnice , Vrchlabí ) -- 3 September 1903 at Eckersdorf , Glatz ( now Bożków , Kłodzko ) ) was an Austrian diplomat .

François de Camps ( 1643 - -1723 ) , who was made abbé of Signy after his nomination to the Bishopric of Pamiers had been vetoed in Rome , was an antiquarian of Amiens whose dissertations on medals were published in the Paris Mercuries of 1719 - -1723 .
Joseph Wolins ( born Atlantic City , New Jersey , 1915 , died 1999 , New York City ) was an American painter whose influences included Piero della Francesca , Mantegna and Giotto .
He had a daughter , Dr. Carolyn Walker Hopp , and a son , LeRoy T. Walker Jr. His home was in Durham , NC .
Corrado Cagli ( Ancona , 1910 - -Rome , 1976 ) was an Italian painter of Jewish heritage , who lived in the USA during World War II . Cagli was born in Ancona but he moved with his family to Rome in 1915 at the age of five .
Kálmán Giergl ( June 29 , 1863 in Pest -- September 10 , 1954 in Nógrád - Verőce ) , a significant figure in Hungarian eclectic architectural style .
Antonello Petrucci , also known as Antonello d'Aversa ( born in Teano -- died in Naples , 1487 ) was a Baron and secretary to King Ferdinand I of Naples ( Don Ferrante of Naples ) .
Eugène Ehrhart ( 29 April 1906 Guebwiller -- 17 January 2000 Strasbourg ) was a French mathematician who introduced Ehrhart polynomials in the 1960s .
Scarsellino or Ippolito Scarsella ( 1550 ( or 1551 ) - 28 October 1620 ) was an Italian Late - Renaissance - Mannerist painter of the School of Ferrara .
Halina Poświatowska ( née Halina Myga , entered into church records as Helena Myga ; May 9 , 1935 in Częstochowa , Poland -- October 11 , 1967 in Warsaw , Poland ) was a Polish poet and writer , one of the most important figures in modern / contemporary Polish literature .
Heinz Klingenberg ( 6 April 1905 , Bielefeld -- 12 September 1959 , Schweinfurt ) was a German film and television actor .
Else Frenkel - Brunswik ( August 18 , 1908 in Lemberg -- March 31 , 1958 in Berkeley , California , USA ) was a Polish - Austrian Jewish psychologist .
Adam Aston ( born Adolf Loewinsohn , 17 September 1902 , Warsaw , Poland : died 10 January 1993 in London , England ) was a Polish singer , actor , and pianist of Jewish origin .
Timofei Stukolkin was one of the most beloved actors of Saint - Petersburg .
August Neilreich ( 12 December 1803 , Vienna 1 June 1871 ) was an Austrian lawyer and botanist .
Hynek Boček of Poděbrady ( also known as : Hynek of Poděbrady or Hynek Boček of Kunštát and Poděbrady ; Czech : Hynek Boček z Poděbrad or Hynek Poděbradský ; died : 16 October 1426 in Nymburk ) was a Bohemian - Moravian nobleman and follower of the Hussites .
Bruno Ruffo ( 9 December 1920 - 10 February 2007 ) was an Italian Grand Prix motorcycle road racer born in Verona .
Ferdinand Cheval ( 1836 -- 19 August 1924 ) was a French postman who spent thirty - three years of his life building Le Palais idéal ( the `` Ideal Palace '' ) in Hauterives .
Kazimierz Fabisiak ( 11 February 1903 , Warsaw - 28 April 1971 , Kraków ) was a Polish actor , director , theatre , and theatre director .

Wilhelm Ralph Merton ( 14 May 1848 in Frankfurt--15 December 1916 in Berlin ) was a prominent and influential German entrepreneur , social democrat and philanthropist .
Adolf Lasson ( March 12 , 1832 , Alt - Strelitz , today Neustrelitz , Mecklenburg - Strelitz - December 20 , 1917 , Berlin ) was a German Jewish philosophical writer , strident Prussianist , and the father of Georg Lasson .
Charles Vacquerie ( 12 April 1817 , Nantes - 4 September 1843 , Villequier ) was a notable figure in the circle of Victor Hugo , his father - in - law .
Michel Rodange ( 3 January 1827 -- 27 August 1876 ) was a Luxembourgian writer and poet , best known for writing Luxembourg 's national epic , Renert ( full original title : Renert oder de Fuuß am Frack an a Ma’nsgrëßt ) .
Raffaello Matarazzo ( Rome , 17 August 1909 -- Rome , 17 May 1966 ) was an Italian filmmaker .
Reza Barati was a 23-year - old Iranian asylum seeker who was killed on Manus Island ( Papau New Guinea ) during rioting at the Manus Island Regional Processing Centre ( MIRPC ) .
Marie - Angélique Memmie Le Blanc ( born 1712 Wisconsin , French Louisiana ; died 1775 Paris , France ) was a famous feral child of the 18th century in France who was known as The Wild Girl of Champagne , The Maid of Châlons , or The Wild Child of Songy .
Alfred Merz ( 24 January 1880 in Perchtoldsdorf , Niederösterreich -- 16 August 1925 in Buenos Aires ) was an Austrian geographer , oceanographer and director of the Institute of Marine Science in Berlin .
Ignazio Busca ( August 31 , 1731 in Milan -- August 12 , 1803 in Rome ) was an Italian cardinal and Secretary of State of the Holy See .
Ewa Szelburg - Zarembina ( 10 April 1899 in Bronowice - 28 September 1986 in Warsaw ) was a Polish novelist , poet and screenplay writer .

George Washington Truett , also known as George W. Truett ( May 6 , 1867 -- July 7 , 1944 ) , was an American clergyman who was the pastor of the First Baptist Church of Dallas , Texas , from 1897 until 1944 , and the president of the Southern Baptist Convention from 1927 to 1929 .

Manuel Felipe Rugeles was a poet , journalist and Venezuelan politician who was born in San Cristóbal , Venezuela in 1903 and died in Caracas in 1959 .

Otto Weidt ( 2 May 1883 - 22 December 1947 ) was the owner of a workshop in Berlin for blind and deaf .

Arno Breker ( 19 July 1900 -- 13 February 1991 ) was a German sculptor , best known for his public works in Nazi Germany , which were endorsed by the authorities as the antithesis of degenerate art . He was born in Elberfeld , now a part of Wuppertal and died in Düsseldorf .
Osman Pazvantoğlu ( 1758 -- January 27 , 1807 , Vidin ) was an Ottoman soldier , a governor of the Vidin district after 1794 , and a rebel against Ottoman rule .
Nicolas Marie Alexandre Vattemare ( 1796 in Paris -- 1864 ) , also known under the stage name Monsieur Alexandre , was a French ventriloquist and philanthropist who created the first international system for the exchange of items among libraries and museums .

Eugen Wolf ( * 24 January 1850 in Kirchheimbolanden ; † 10 May 1912 in Munich ) was a German journanist and traveller .

Curucu , Beast of the Amazon is a 1956 American film directed and written by Curt Siodmak and starring John Bromfield , Beverly Garland and Tom Payne .
The Spirit of ' 45 is a 2013 documentary film by British director Ken Loach , focused on and celebrating the radical changes in postwar Britain under the Labour government of Clement Attlee , which came to power in 1945 .

Turkish Handball Super League ( Turkish : Türkiye Hentbol Süper Ligi ) is the highest league in the Turkish handball and comprises the top 12 elite men teams .
Goran Knežević ( Serbian Cyrillic : Горан Кнежевић , pronounced ( ɡǒran kněːʒeʋitɕ ) ) ( born 12 May 1957 in Banatski Karlovac ) is a former Serbian professional basketball player and a current politician , who served as Minister of Agriculture , Forestry and Water Management between 2012 and 2013 .

Oded Kattash ( Hebrew : עודד קטש‎ , born October 10 , 1974 ) is an Israeli basketball coach and former player .

Tony Salmelainen ( born August 8 , 1981 ) is a Finnish former professional ice hockey forward .
The 2007 Generali Ladies Linz is the 2007 Tier II WTA Tour tournament of the annually - held Generali Ladies Linz tennis tournament .
The 1983 Queens Grand Prix was a tennis tournament played on indoor carpet courts in Tokyo , Japan that was part of the 1983 Virginia Slims World Championship Series .

Spirorbis is a genus of very small ( 2 - 5 mm ) polychaete worms , usually with a white coiled shell .
Zopherus is a genus of beetles comprising 19 species .
Crocodiles ( subfamily Crocodylinae ) or true crocodiles are large aquatic reptiles that live throughout the tropics in Africa , Asia , the Americas and Australia .

Orcuttia viscida is a rare species of grass known by the common name Sacramento Orcutt grass .

Chaenactis is a genus of plants in the daisy family which are known generally as pincushions or dustymaidens .

Clanoptilus is a genus of beetles belonging to the family Melyridae .
Meiacanthus vicinus is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western central Pacific ocean where it is only known from Indonesia .
Owls are birds from the order Strigiformes , which includes about 200 species of mostly solitary and nocturnal birds of prey typified by an upright stance , a large , broad head , binocular vision , binaural hearing , sharp talons and feathers adapted for silent flight .
Sceptridium is a genus of seedless vascular plants , closely allied to ( and often included as a subgenus of ) the genus Botrychium ( the moonworts and grapeferns ) .
Erythronium quinaultense ( Quinault fawn - lily ) is a rare plant species endemic to a small region around Lake Quinault in Olympic National Park , Washington State , USA .
Banana slug is a common name for three North American species of terrestrial slug in the genus Ariolimax .
†Imoglobidae is an extinct family of fossil sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Caenogastropoda .
Lamellariinae is a subfamily of small slug - like sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs belonging to the family Velutinidae , in the clade Littorinimorpha .
Anochetus madaraszi is a species of ant of the subfamily Ponerinae , which can be found in India , Sri Lanka , and Bangladesh .
Purpuricenopsis humeralis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Purpuricenopsis .
Stomatella terminalis , common name the pointed false ear , is a species of very small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
The Umbrella Epidendrum ( Epidendrum umbelliferum ) is a species of orchid .
Pinarocorys is a genus of larks in the Alaudidae family .
Drosera anglica , commonly known as the English sundew or great sundew , is a carnivorous plant species belonging to the sundew genus .
Potentilla delphinensis is a herbaceous perennial species of cinquefoil belonging to the Rosaceae family .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Cryptascoma bisetula .
Eupholidoptera chabrieri is a species of ' katydids crickets ' belonging to the family Tettigoniidae subfamily Tettigoniinae .
Eigenmannia goajira is a species of glass knifefish found in the Lake Maracaibo basin in Colombia and Venezuela .
Cleopatra ferruginea is a species of freshwater snails with an operculum , aquatic gastropod molluscs in the family Paludomidae .
Piaractus is a genus of serrasalmid from South America .
Lastarriaea coriacea is a species of flowering plant in the buckwheat family known by the common name leather spineflower .
Abronia maritima is a species of sand verbena known by the common name red sand verbena .
Holconia insignis is a species of huntsman spider found in Queensland and New South Wales , Australia .
Melongena patula , common name Pacific Crown Conch , is a species of large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Melongenidae .
Zinnia anomala is a North American species of flowering plants in the sunflower family , with the common name shortray zinnia .
Morchella populiphila is a species of morel fungus ( family Morchellaceae ) native to northwestern North America .
Nerodia rhombifer , commonly known as the diamondback water snake , is a species of nonvenomous natricine colubrid endemic to the central United States and northern Mexico .
Homoeodera elateroides , the Click Beetle - like Fungus Weevil is a species of beetle belonging to the family Anthribidae .
Xenophora japonica is a species of large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Xenophoridae , the carrier shells .
Osbornia is a genus of plant in the myrtle family Myrtaceae described as a genus in 1862 .
The Caatinga parakeet ( Eupsittula cactorum ) or cactus parakeet is a species of parrot in the Psittacidae family .
Lethacotyle vera is a species of monogenean of the family Protomicrocotylidae Johston & Tiegs , 1922 .
The Daguinaspididae is family of early Cambrian trilobites found in Morocco , Ukraine , and Siberia .
Cerradomys is a genus of oryzomyine rodents from eastern Bolivia , Paraguay , and central Brazil found in cerrado , Caatinga and Gran Chaco habitats .
Utiaritichthys is a genus of serrasalmid found in the Amazon and Orinoco basins in tropical South America .
Incerticyclus is a genus of tropical land snails with gills and an operculum , terrestrial gastropod mollusks .
Chaca chaca is a species of angler catfish found in the Ganges - Brahmaputra River system of India and the Ayeyarwady River of Myanmar , where it is found in rivers , canals and ponds of grassland , scrubland , deciduous forest and rainforest habitats .
Thayeria is a genus of tetras from the Amazon Basin , and the Approuague and Maroni Rivers in tropical South America .
Calamagrostis canescens , known as purple small - reed , is a species of grass in the Poaceae family , native to Europe and western Siberia .
Valeriana pauciflora , commonly called the largeflower valerian , is a species of plant in the Caprifoliaceae family .
Eurotettix similraphael is a grasshopper species in the family Acrididae .
Crypturellus reai is a species of Miocene fossil bird in the Tinamou family .
Camposcia retusa , known commonly as the spider decorator crab , is a species of marine crustacea in the family Inachidae .
Leptobrachium mouhoti is a species of amphibian in the Megophryidae family .
The Madagascan flufftail ( Sarothrura insularis ) is a species of bird in the Sarothruridae family .
Liotomus is a genus of extinct mammal from the Paleocene epoch ( early Cenozoic era ) .
Cestrum diurnum ( Din Ka Raja ) is a species of Cestrum , native to the West Indies .
Elimia teres is a species of freshwater snail with an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Pleuroceridae .
Redondavenator ( meaning `` Redonda Formation hunter '' ) is a genus of sphenosuchian , a type of basal crocodylomorph , the clade that comprises the crocodilians and their closest kin .
Acacesia is a genus of orb weaver spiders with a mostly neotropical distribution .
Coluzea rotunda is a species of large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinellidae .
The Mount Data shrew rat ( Rhynchomys soricoides ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Nicotiana langsdorffii , Langsdorff 's tobacco , is a species of the Nicotiana genus ( tobacco ) .
Orthonyx kaldowinyeri is an extinct species of logrunner from the Late Oligocene to the Miocene of Australia .
Limnaecia cuprella is an extinct species of moth in the Cosmopterigidae family .
Raorchestes beddomii ( Beddome 's bubble - nest frog or Beddome 's bush frog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family .
Amphidiscosa is `` an order of hexactinellid sponges ... characterized by amphidisc spicules , that is , spicules having a stellate disk at each end '' .
Pogonomyrmex fossilis is an extinct ants species that lived during the Eocene 34 million years ago .
Poraspis is an extinct genus of heterostracan .
Parapristella is a genus of characins founnd in northern South America .
Woodsia neomexicana , the New Mexican cliff fern , is a fern species native to the Southwestern United States and northern Mexico .
Raouliopsis is a genus of South American plants in the pussy's - toes tribe within the daisy family .
Rubus coronarius is an Asian species of flowering plant in the rose family .
Spinopotemnemus kaszabi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Spinopotemnemus .
Neisosperma poweri is a species of tree in the Apocynaceae family .
Nerodia is a genus of nonvenomous colubrid snakes commonly referred to as water snakes due to their aquatic behavior .
Diporiphora is a genus of agamid lizards ; most species are endemic to Australia , but two ( D. australis and D. bilineata ) are also found in New Guinea .
It is unknown if these habits apply to the New Caledonian owlet - nightjar , but this species is larger and has longer legs than the others , so it may be more terrestrial .
Branchinecta brushi is a species of fairy shrimp found at an altitude of 5,930 m ( 19,460 ft ) in the Chilean Andes .
Reticulitermes banyulensis is a species of termite of the family Rhinotermitidae found in the Roussillon region in France .
Cepaea vindobonensis is a species of medium - sized air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod in the family Helicidae .
Sakhalin grasshopper warbler ( Locustella amnicola ) , is a species of grass warbler in the family Locustellidae ; it was formerly included in the `` Old World warbler '' assemblage .
Machairasaurus is a genus of oviraptorid dinosaur which was found in the Bayan Mandahu Formation , China dating to the late Cretaceous period .
Temognatha grandis is a species of beetles belonging to the family Buprestidae .
Mataichthys is an extinct genus of bony fishes which existed in what is now New Zealand in the early Miocene period .
Rubus superbus is an uncommon Guatemalan species of brambles in the rose family .
Amnicola walkeri , common name Canadian duskysnail , is a species of freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Amnicolidae .
Epipedobates espinosai is a species of frog in the Dendrobatidae family endemic to Ecuador .
Diaphus is a genus of lanternfishes , with 77 recognized species :
The genus Iberodon was named by Hahn G. and Hahn R. in 1999 based on a single species .
Conostephium is a genus of flowering plants in the heath or heather family Ericaceae .
The Caprifoliaceae or honeysuckle family are a clade of dicotyledonous flowering plants consisting of about 860 species in 42 genera , with a nearly cosmopolitan distribution .
The Tetramelaceae are a family of plant formerly classed in the Datiscaceae family .
Cliona patera , commonly called Neptune 's cup , is a species of demosponge in the family Clionaidae .
Kondoraphe kiyokoae is a species of tropical land snail with gills and an operculum , terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Neocyclotidae .
Allium scilloides , called the fragile onion , is a plant species endemic to the US State of Washington .
Acilius sulcatus is a species of water beetle in family Dytiscidae . It is fairly large ( 14.4 -- 18.2 mm ) , with color variation shown throughout its range .
The Brazilian slender - legged tree frog , Osteocephalus subtilis , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in Brazil and possibly Bolivia and Peru .
Cirrhilabrus claire is a species of wrasse native to the Cook Islands .
Tectus mauritianus , common name the Mauritius top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
Eulithidium adamsi is a species of minute colorful sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Phasianellidae , the pheasant shells .
Pleomele hawaiiensis , the Hawaiʻi hala pepe , is a rare species of flowering plant that is endemic to the island of Hawaiʻi .
Deconica aequatoriae is a species of mushroom in the family Strophariaceae found in Ecuador .
Zalembius rosaceus , the Pink seaperch or Pink surfperch , is a species of surfperch native to the eastern Pacific Ocean from Point Delgada , California , USA to southern Baja California and also in the Gulf of California .
Brodiaea jolonensis , known by the common name chaparral brodiaea , is a species of flowering plant in the cluster - lily family .
Magnolia amoena ( common name Tianmu magnolia , so called from Tianmu Mountain where it grows ) is a species of plant in the Magnoliaceae family .
The Eocrinidae are a family of early echinoderms that contain the genus Gogia .
Aphonopelma is a genus of tarantulas , members of which are native to the Americas .
The Sciaridae are a family of flies , commonly known as dark - winged fungus gnats .
Euchroma gigantea , the Metallic Wood Boring Beetle or Giant Metallic Ceiba Borer , is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Euchroma .
Phoenix caespitosa ( caespitosa - Latin , clumped or tufted ) is a species of flowering plant in the palm family native to the Arabian Peninsula and the deserts of Somalia .
Andamia reyi , the suckerlip blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the Pacific and Indian Oceans .
Haplorchis taichui is a species of intestinal fluke in the family Heterophyidae .
Lepisoreae is a tribe of ferns with clathrate ( lattice - like ) scales .
Epidendrum apaganoides ( resembles E. apaganum ) is a species of orchid in the genus Epidendrum .
Caseolus abjectus is a species of land snail in the family Hygromiidae , the hairy snails and their allies .
Knightia is an extinct genus of clupeid clupeiform bony fish that lived in the fresh water lakes and rivers of North America during the Eocene epoch .
Tricolia rosea , common name the rosy pheasant , is a species of small sea snail with calcareous opercula , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Phasianellidae , the pheasant snails .
Amphimallon majale is a species of beetle in the Melolonthinae subfamily that can be found in Belgium , France , Italy , Kosovo , Montenegro , Serbia , Spain , the Netherlands and Voivodina .
Geranium dalmaticum , commonly called Dalmatian cranesbill , is a species of hardy flowering herbaceous perennial plant in the genus Geranium in the Geraniaceae family .
Apocryptes bato is a species of mudskipper native to India , Bangladesh and Myanmar where it can be found in tropical rivers , estuaries and coastal waters of the Indian Ocean .
Stygobromus kenki is a rare species of amphipod , a crustacean .
Brunfelsia jamaicensis is a species of flowering plant in the family Solanaceae , the nightshades .
Anelosimus terraincognita is a species of spider discovered in the Rijksmuseum van Natuurlijke Historie , with no associated information as to its collector or location of discovery .
Lactarius fallax , commonly known as the velvety milk cap , is a species of fungus in the Russulaceae family .
Archips mortuanus , the dusky - back leaf roller , is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family .
Meridulia zerpana is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family that is endemic to Venezuela .
Oplurus cuvieri , commonly known as the collared iguanid lizard , collared iguana , or Madagascan collared iguana , is a species of arboreal Malagasy iguana , the largest of six species in the genus Oplurus .
Pteropurpura festiva , common name the festive murex , is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the rock snails .
Neolamprologus schreyeni is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it is only known from along the Burundi coast , inhabiting crevices .
Bombus wurflenii is a species of bumblebee found in several parts of central and northern Europe to Turkey and the Krim peninsula in the southeast .
The East Siberian brown bear ( Ursus arctos collaris ) is a subspecies of brown bear which ranges from eastern Siberia , beginning at the Yenisei river , as far as Trans - Baikaliya , the Stanovoy Range , the Lena River , Kolyma and generally throughout Yakutia and the Altai Mountains .
Rhamphocephalus ( `` beak head '' ) is an extinct genus of pterosaur from the Middle Jurassic of England .
Fritillaria meleagroides is a Eurasian species of bulb - forming plants in the lily family , native to Xinjiang , Russia ( Altay Krai , Western Siberia Krai , European Russia , North Caucasus ) , Kazakhstan , Ukraine , and Bulgaria .
The Thaliacea comprise a class of marine animals within the subphylum Tunicata .
Mackinlayoideae is a subfamily of plants containing about 67 species in six genera .
The Brachyceran infraorder Tabanomorpha is a small group that consists primarily of two large families , the Tabanidae ( horse and deer flies ) and Rhagionidae ( snipe flies ) , and an assortment of very small affiliated families , most of which have been ( or could be , or sometimes are ) included within the Rhagionidae .
Galeandra , abbreviated as Gal in horticultural trade , is a genus of 37 known species of orchids native to South America , Central America , the West Indies and Florida .
Carpodiptera ophiticola is a species of flowering plant in the Tiliaceae family .
Cnemaspis anaikattiensis is a species of gecko found in the Anaikatti Hills near the city of Coimbatore in Tamil Nadu , India .
Fundulopanchax avichang is a species of African killifish that mainly inhabits small temporary pools of the Ecucu River drainage systems .
Crepidodera pluta is a species of flea beetles from Chrysomelidae family that can be found everywhere in Europe , except Andorra , Finland , Ireland , Monaco , Moldova , Norway , San Marino , and Vatican City .
Colchicum variegatum , common name Κολχικό το ποικιλόμορφο or Güz Acıçiğdemi , Sürincan is a plant species native to Greece and Turkey but cultivated in many other places .
Scutiger nyingchiensis is a species of toad found in the Himalayas ( China , India , Nepal , Pakistan ) .
Labracoglossa is a genus of sea chubs native to the western Pacific Ocean .
Glyceria grandis is a species of mannagrass known by the common name American mannagrass .
Hydatellaceae are a family of small , aquatic flowering plants .
Lepetodrilus sp . East Scotia Ridge ( nomen nudum ) is an as yet undescribed species of small , deep - sea sea snail , a hydrothermal vent limpet , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Lepetodrilidae .
Pogonomyrmex occidentalis , or the western harvester ant , is a species of ant that inhabits the deserts and arid grasslands of the American West at or below 6,300 feet ( 1,900 m ) .
†Helenodiscus vernoni was a species of small air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Charopidae .

Rhacognathus punctatus , the Heather Bug , is a species of stink bugs ( family Pentatomidae ) .

Schistura is a genus of stone loaches from southern and eastern Asia .

The Oncopodidae are a family of harvestmen within the suborder Laniatores .
Arthroseps is the name given to a genus of spectacled lizards .
Mahajangasuchus is an extinct genus of crocodyliform which had blunt , conical teeth .

Acrantophis is a genus of terrestrial boid snakes endemic to the island of Madagascar .

Lemoniidae is a small family of moths .
Oedemera nobilis , also known as the False Oil Beetle , Thick - Legged Flower Beetle or Swollen - Thighed Beetle is a beetle in the family Oedemeridae , a common species in Western Europe , including the south of England .
Cyrtobagous salviniae is a species of weevil known as the salvinia weevil .
Clanculus undatus , common name the wavy Australian monodont , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Zilchogyra paulistana is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Helicodiscidae .

Peyrieras ' woolly lemur or Peyrieras ' avahi ( Avahi peyrierasi ) is a species of woolly lemur native to southeastern Madagascar .

Zaireichthys flavomaculatus is a species of loach catfish endemic to the Democratic Republic of the Congo where it is only found in the Lulua River .
Paracerceis sculpta is a species of marine isopod between 1.3 millimetres ( 0.05 in ) and 10.3 mm ( 0.41 in ) in length .
Biloclymenia is a genus in the ammonoid order Clymeniida which is characterized by a dorsal retrosiphonitic siphuncle with long adapically pointing septal necks .
Neodontobutis is a genus of freshwater sleepers native to eastern Asia .
Allelepidotus is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish that lived during the Middle Triassic epoch .
Heteroclinus whiteleggii , Whitelegg 's weedfish , is a species of clinid native to reefs around New South Wales , Australia .
Eusthenopteron is a genus of prehistoric sarcopterygian ( often called lobe - finned fishes ) which has attained an iconic status from its close relationships to tetrapods .
Crotoniidae are a family of mites of the Desmonomata group that may be the first animal lineage to have abandoned sexual reproduction and then reevolved it .
Sciotropis is a damselfly genus .
Squatina caillieti , also known as the Philippines angelshark is a species of angel shark , family Squatinidae , known only from a 33 cm ( 13 in ) long immature female caught in the Philippines , where it is the only known representative of its family .
Ehrlichia muris is a species of pathogenic bacteria first isolated from mice , with type strain AS145T.
Since the genus was first described in the early 20th century , several other specimens , mostly isolated vertebrae , have been attributed to Eocetus , but the taxonomic status of these widely distributed specimens remain disputed .
Placidina is a genus of clearwing ( ithomiine ) butterflies , named by d'Almeida in 1928 .
Erigeron poliospermus is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names gray - seeded fleabane and purple cushion fleabane .
Angolachelys is an extinct genus of African eucryptodiran turtle which existed in Angola during the Turonian stage of the Late Cretaceous .
The Lord Howe pigeon ( sometimes white - throated pigeon ) , Columba vitiensis godmanae , was a subspecies of the metallic pigeon which existed on Lord Howe Island .
Periodon is a genus of conodonts which existed in what is now Canada , Iran , Argentina , China , Russia , and the United States during the Ordovician Period .
Monolopia gracilens is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name woodland monolopia .

Chlorociboria argentinensis is a species of fungus in the family Helotiaceae .
Melonechinus is an extinct genus of echinoid that lived in the Carboniferous .
The Fringed Catasetum ( Catasetum fimbriatum ) is a species of orchid found in Bolivia .
Oecomys speciosus , also known as the savannah oecomys , arboreal rice rat , or Venezuelan arboreal rice rat , is a species of rodent in the genus Oecomys of family Cricetidae .
Cauca contestata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Cauca .
Cataulacus granulatus , is a species of ant of the subfamily Myrmicinae , which is a widespread species that can be found from Borneo , China , India , Indonesia , Malaysia , Myanmar , Nepal , Thailand , Singapore , and Sri Lanka ..
Phrynobatrachus sandersoni ( common name : Sanderson 's hook frog ) is a species of frog in the Phrynobatrachidae family .

Deanolis sublimbalis , the Red banded mango caterpillar , is a species of moth of the Crambidae family .

Crematogaster dohrni , is a species of ant of the subfamily Myrmicinae , which is a widespread species that can be found from Sri Lanka , India , Indonesia , Thailand , and China .
Viola sempervirens , known by the common names redwood violet and evergreen violet , is a species in the genus Viola .

Harrisia aboriginum ( prickly applecactus ) is a species of cactus .
