Yunnanaspis is an extinct genus of redlichiid trilobite of what is now China .
The Canadian toad ( also Dakota toad , Anaxyrus hemiophrys ) is a species of toad that ranges from the prairie regions of central Canada south to parts of United States upper midwest .
Nebria composita composita is a subspecies of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in Qinghai province and Tibet .
Zygnema is a genus of freshwater filamentous thalloid alga comprising about 100 species .
Ananas bracteatus ( common name , red pineapple ) is a species of the pineapple .
Osteobrama bakeri is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Osteobrama .
Jaxartosaurus is a genus of hadrosaurid dinosaur similar to Corythosaurus which lived during the Late Cretaceous .
Lithophragma campanulatum is a species of flowering plant in the saxifrage family known by the common name Siskiyou Mountain woodland star .
Tribolonotus is a genus of lizards , commonly known as crocodile skinks .
Acer duplicatoserratum is a species of maple , native to southern and eastern China ( Anhui , Fujian , Guizhou , Henan , Hubei , Hunan , Jiangsu , Jiangxi , Shandong , Taiwan , Zhejiang ) .
Shorea hypochra ( also called White Meranti ) is a species of plant in the Dipterocarpaceae family .
The Elegant sprite , or Three Striped Blue Dart , ( Pseudagrion decorum ) is a species of damselfly in the family Coenagrionidae .
Erronea caurica , common name the thick - edged cowry , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Ostracion meleagris , the White - spotted boxfish , is a species of boxfish found in the Indian and Pacific Oceans .
Harpalus laevipes is a species of black coloured phytophagous ground beetle in the Harpalinae subfamily that is absent in the following European and African countries and islands :
The Devaka 's fan - throated lizard ( Sitana devakai ) is an endemic species of agamid lizard recently found from Sri Lanka .
It was described by Rickards in 1964 , and the type species is Delops obtusicaudatus , which was originally described under the genus Phacops by Salter in 1849 .
Natterer 's bat is a medium - sized species and grows to a head and body length of 1.75 to 2 inches ( 44 to 51 mm ) with a forearm ( elbow to wrist ) length of 1.75 inches ( 44 mm ) .
Clithon retropictus is a species of freshwater and brackish water snail with an operculum , a nerite .
The Jobi manucode ( Manucodia jobiensis ) is a species of crow - like bird - of - paradise .
Platycerium coronarium is a species of staghorn fern in the genus Platycerium .
It contains only one known species , Ecua moluccensis , endemic to Maluku Province in eastern Indonesia .
Antennablennius hypenetes , the Arabian blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western Indian ocean , from the northern Red Sea to the Persian Gulf .
Allium atroviolaceum , the Broadleaf wild leek , is a plant species native to Iran , Iraq , Afghanistan , Syria , Lebanon , Saudi Arabia , Turkmenistan , Turkey , Georgia , Armenia , Azerbaijan , southern European Russia and the Caucasus , but widely cultivated in other regions as a food source and for its ornamental value .
Masdevallia wageneriana is a species of orchid found from Colombia into northern Venezuela .
Trachyglanis ineac is a species of loach catfish endemic to the Democratic Republic of the Congo where it is found in the Congo , Tshuapa , Lomela and Lomami Rivers .
Horkelia hispidula is a species of flowering plant in the rose family known by the common name White Mountains horkelia .
Streptomyces emeiensis is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil from the Emei Mountainin in the Sichuan Province in China .
The Bristoliinae is an extinct subfamily of trilobites , fossil marine arthropods , with species of small to average size .
Terthroptera is a genus of ermine moths ( family Yponomeutidae ) .
Streptomyces aburaviensis is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which was isolated from soil from Aburabi from the Shiga Prefecture in Japan .
Zephyranthes citrina , is a species of bulbous plant belong to the family Amaryllidaceae , native to Mexico .
Tauschia hartwegii is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common name Hartweg 's umbrellawort .
Bubalus is a genus of bovines that was first described by Charles Hamilton Smith in 1827 .
Nemacheilus olivaceus is a species of stone loach native to the benthopelagic freshwaters and tropical climates of such countries as :
Heliconia willisiana is a species of plant in the Heliconiaceae family It is endemic to Ecuador .
Huabeisaurus ( /ˌhwɑːbeɪˈsɔrəs/ , meaning `` North China lizard '' ) was a genus of dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous ( Cenomanian to Campanian stages , around 99.7 - -70.6 million years ago ) .
Diplomystes is a genus of velvet catfishes , a primitive family of catfishes ( order Siluriformes ) endemic to Chile .
Lepidopygopsis typus , the Peninsular hilltrout , is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to Kerala , India where it is only known from Periyar River and Periyar Lake .
Henriettea membranifolia ( thinleaf camasey ) is a species of plant in the Melastomataceae family .
Synaptolaemus is a genus of headstanders native to South America , where found in the Orinoco , Casiquiare and Amazon Basin .
Melica onoei is a species of grass in the Poaceae family that can be found in China , Japan , Korea , Pakistan and Taiwan .
Cyathea affinis is a variable species of tree fern native to Fiji , Samoa , the Cook Islands , Austral Islands , Tahiti , and the Marquesas Islands .
Ulva anandii is a species of seaweed in Ulvaceae family that can be found in Buleji and Karachi districts of Pakistan .
Vanikoridae is a family of minute to medium - sized sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the superfamily Vanikoridae .
Sphodromantis obscura is a species of praying mantis found in Tanzania .
Furcotanilla is a genus of ants in the subfamily Leptanillinae containing the single species Furcotanilla furcomandibula .
Sarahsaurus is a genus of basal sauropodomorph dinosaur which lived during the lower Jurassic period in what is now northeastern Arizona , USA .
Tribonema is a genus of filamentous , freshwater yellow - green alga .
Emblemariopsis ruetzleri is a species of chaenopsid blenny found around Belize , in the western central Atlantic ocean .
Jacobiasca formosana is an insect species belonging to the subfamily Typhlocybinae of the family Cicadellidae .
Chrysothamnus molestus is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names Arizona rabbitbrush , Tusayan rabbitbrush , disturbed rabbitbrush , and stickyfruit low rabbitbrush .
Allium lemmonii is a species of wild onion known by the common name Lemmon 's onion , named for botanist John Gill Lemmon ( 1831 - -1908 ) .
Bathystethus is a genus of sea chubs native to the Pacific Ocean .
Dicrodon is a genus of lizards in the family Teiidae .
Lucasium stenodactylum ( previously known as Diplodactylus stenodactylus ) , also known as the crowned gecko , is a species of gecko from Australia .
Trochia cingulata , common name : the girdled dogwhelk , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Acacia longissima , known colloquially as long - leaf wattle , is a species of Acacia native to eastern Australia .
Lithopoma tectum , common name the West Indian starsnail , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
Vitis chungii is a polygamo - dioecious species of wild grape native to China ( in Fujian , Guangdong , Guangxi , and Jiangxi provinces ) where it is known by the name min gan pu tao , or Fujian Jianxi grape .
Striga , commonly known as witchweed or witchers weed , is a genus of parasitic plants that occur naturally in parts of Africa , Asia , and Australia .
Haplostachys haplostachya is a rare species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name honohono .
Palpada megafemur is a species of flower fly .
Sporisorium sorghi is a species of fungus in the Ustilaginaceae family .
Euaspidoceras perarmatum is an extinct ammonoid cephalopod species that lived during the Jurassic .
Juncus capitatus is a species of rush known by the common names dwarf rush and leafybract dwarf rush .
Calycocarpum ( cupseed ) is a monotypic genus of plants in the family Menispermaceae .
Nemadoras elongatus is a species of thorny catfish native to the Amazon basin where it can be found in Brazil , Colombia and Peru .
Bathymodiolus tangaroa is a species of deep - sea mussel , a marine bivalve mollusk in the family Mytilidae , the mussels .
Cynoglossus carpenteri , commonly known as the Hooked tonguesole is a species of tonguefish .
Vanicela is a genus of moth in the family Stathmopodidae , although it is sometimes included in the Roeslerstammiidae family .
Siluosaurus ( meaning `` Silu ( Chinese for Silk Road , referring to the discovery location ) lizard '' ) is a genus of ornithopod dinosaur from the Barremian - Albian - age Lower Cretaceous Xinminbao Group of Gansu , China .
Dicoria calliptera is a Mexican species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
Choreutis nemorana , the fig - tree skeletonizer moth or fig leaf roller , is a species of moth of the Choreutidae family .
Hypselecara is a small genus of cichlids native to the Amazon and Orinoco basins in South America .
Protoadapis is a genus of adapiform primate that lived in Europe during the early middle Eocene .
Corynexochida is an order of trilobite that lived from the Lower Cambrian to the Middle Devonian .
Ochetellus is a genus of ants first described by Steve Shattuck in 1992 .
Exastilithoxus hoedemani is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil where it occurs in the Maurauiá River .
The Japanese Cypripedium ( Cypripedium japonicum ) is a species of orchid .
The Amazonian hocicudo , Oxymycterus amazonicus , is a rodent species from South America .
Callionymus mortenseni is a species of dragonet native to the waters around Indonesia where it occurs at depths of around 290 metres ( 950 ft ) .
Claire 's mouse lemur ( Microcebus mamiratra ) , or the Nosy Be mouse lemur , is a newly described species of lemur from the genus of the mouse lemurs ( Microcebus ) .
Gyraulus chinensis is a species of small freshwater snail , an aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Planorbidae , the ram 's horn snails .
Labidochromis zebroides is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is only known to occur in areas with rocky substrates around Likoma Island and Mazimbwe Island .
Dineutus is a genus of beetles in the family Gyrinidae , the whirligig beetles .
Ribes velutinum is a species of currant known by the common name desert gooseberry .
Chrozophora tinctoria ( commonly known as dyer 's croton , giradol , or turnsole ) is a plant species native to the Mediterranean , the Middle East , India , Pakistan , and Central Asia .
Cyrtothyrea is a small genus of Afrotropical chafer beetles .
Pristimantis helvolus ( in Spanish : rana pierniamarilla ) is a species of frog in the Craugastoridae family .
Larinioides is a genus of orb - weaving spiders that mostly occurs in temperate climates around the northern hemisphere .
Tuberozygocera albostictica is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Tuberozygocera .
Coniasaurus is an extinct genus of Late Cretaceous marine squamates that range in age from Cenomanian to Santonian .
Trachelipus aegaeus is a species of woodlouse in the genus Trachelipus belonging to the family Trachelipodidae that can be found in the Cyclades and in mainland Greece .
Platycheirus amplus is a species of hoverfly found in wetlands , fens , moorland streams and bogs .
Emigrantia is an extinct genus of trilobites , fossil marine arthropods , of small to average size .
Janulus pompylius was a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Gastrodontidae .
Fonchiiichthys uracanthus is a species of armored catfish native to Costa Rica and Panama .
Platymantis vitianus ( common names : Fiji ground frog , Viti wrinkled ground Frog ) is a species of frog in the Ceratobatrachidae family .
Ocypode gaudichaudii , also known as the painted ghost crab or cart driver crab , is a species of crab found on Pacific beaches from El Salvador to Chile as well as on the Galápagos Islands .
Allium commutatum is a species of Mediterranean onions in the amaryllis family .
Tagetes patula , the French marigold , is a species in the daisy family ( Asteraceae ) .
Caloria elegans is a species of colorful sea slug , an aeolid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Facelinidae .
Carmona retusa , also known as the Fukien tea tree or Philippine tea tree , is a species of flowering plant in the borage family , Boraginaceae .
Cordylanthus is a genus of plants in the broomrape family native to western North America .
Quercus grisea , commonly known as the gray oak , shin oak or scrub oak , is a North American species deciduous or evergreen shrub or medium sized tree in the white oak group .
Monomorium fieldi is a small species of ant , originally described from Australia by Forel ( 1910 ) , where it is widespread in all states ( Heterick , 2001 ) .
The rough - snouted giant gecko or tough - snouted gecko ( Rhacodactylus trachyrhynchus ) is a species of gecko found in central and southern New Caledonia and on the outlying New Caledonian island of Ile de Pines .
Salix bebbiana is a species of willow indigenous to Canada and the northern United States , from Alaska and Yukon south to California and Arizona and northeast to Newfoundland and New England .
Species The only known species is Chimaerochloa archboldii .
Cortinarius flexipes is a fungus , specifically a mushroom , a small brown species in the genus Cortinarius .
Arbutus pavarii is a species of plant in the heath family .
Halimolobos is a genus of flowering plants in the mustard family known generally as fissureworts .
Dictyonosteus is a genus of prehistoric coelacanth fish which lived during the Late Devonian period .
Alnashetri is an extinct genus of alvarezsauroid coelurosaurian theropod dinosaur known from the early Late Cretaceous ( Cenomanian stage ) of La Buitrera , Río Negro Province , Argentina .
Zonites algirus is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropodmollusk in the family Zonitidae .
Luganoia is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish that lived during the early Ladinian stage of the Middle Triassic epoch .
Desmodema is a small genus of ribbonfishes .
Sepia elongata is a species of cuttlefish native to the northwestern Indian Ocean , specifically from the Red Sea to Somalia .
Myoxocephalus tuberculatus is a North Pacific species of sculpin in the scorpeaniform fish family Cottidae .
Rhantus papuanus was a species of beetle in family Dytiscidae .
Triopha maculata , common name `` speckled triopha '' , is a species of colorful sea slug , a nudibranch , a shell - less marine gastropod mollusk in the family Polyceridae .
Exoneura robusta is a species of the primitively eusocial allodapine bee , belonging to the genus commonly referred to as `` reed bees '' .
The Kamchatkan rainbow trout ( Oncorhynchus mykiss mykiss ) is a subspecies of the rainbow trout , which is a fish in the Salmonidae family .
Adventor elongatus , the Visitor , is a species of velvetfish native to the Pacific Ocean waters along the coasts of Papua New Guinea and Australia .
Photinia anlungensis is a flower species in the family Rosaceae .
Anemosella viridalis is a species of snout moth in the genus Anemosella .
The Cyperaceae are a family of monocotyledonous graminoid flowering plants known as sedges , which superficially resemble grasses or rushes .
Dakotadon is a genus of iguanodont dinosaur from the Barremian - age Lower Cretaceous Lakota Formation of South Dakota , USA , known from a partial skull .
Nochelaspis is an extinct genus of Galeaspida .
Saurolophus ( /sɔːˈrɒləfəs/ ; meaning `` lizard crest '' ) is a genus of large saurolophine hadrosaurid dinosaurs that lived about 70.0 - -68.5 million years ago , in the Late Cretaceous of North America and Asia ; it is one of the few genera of dinosaurs known from multiple continents .
Plagiopholis styani , also known by the common name Chinese mountain snake , is a species of colubrid snake .
Agapetes is a semi - climbing shrub genus native to the Himalayas , grown as an ornamental for its attractive pendulous benches of red tubular flowers blooming over a long period .
Conus auricomus , common name the gold - leaf cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Amphiachyris dracunculoides is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Busseola fusca is a species of moth that is also known as the maize stalk borer .
Hedysarum sulphurescens , the yellow sweetvetch or white sweetvetch , is a perennial herb species .
Juniperus squamata ( flaky juniper or Himalayan juniper ; Chinese : 高山柏 gao shan bai ) is a species of juniper native to the Himalayas and China , from northeastern Afghanistan east to western Yunnan in southwestern China , and with disjunct populations north to western Gansu and east to Fujian .
Aechmea tomentosa is a species in the genus Aechmea .
Paramorariopsis anae is a species of copepod in the family Canthocamptidae .
Cladrastis kentukea , the Kentucky yellowwood or American yellowwood ( syn . C. lutea , C. tinctoria ) , is a species of Cladrastis native to the Southeastern United States , with a restricted range from western North Carolina west to eastern Oklahoma , and from southern Missouri and Indiana south to central Alabama .
There is only one known species , Japonolirion osense , endemic to Japan .
Nectomys squamipes , also known as the Atlantic Forest nectomys , South American water rat , or scaly - footed water rat , is a semiaquatic insectivorous rodent species .
Allium elegantulum is a species of onions endemic to the province of Liaoning northeastern China .
Callicarpa longifolia is a species of beautyberry .
The Blue - banded Eggfly ( Hypolimnas alimena ) is a species of butterfly in the Nymphalidae family .
Acarospora flavisparsa is a species of lichen in the family Acarosporaceae .
Zophos baudoni is a species of air - breathing land snail , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Haplotrematidae .
Livoniana is a genus of prehistoric lobe - finned fish which lived during the Devonian period ( Givetian - Frasnian stages , about 374 - 391 million years ago ) .
Sphaerocoris annulus , common names Picasso Bug or Zulu Hud Bug , is a species of shield - backed bugs belonging to the family Scutelleridae .
Epigridae is a family of very small sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the superfamily Rissooidea , and clade Littorinimorpha .
Portulaca samhaensis is a species of flowering plant in the purslane family , Portulacaceae .
Delphacidae is a family of planthoppers containing about 2000 species , distributed worldwide .
Eurydema oleracea is a species of shield bug in the Pentatomidae family and is commonly known as the rape bug , the crucifer shield bug , the cabbage bug or the brassica bug .
Anemone thomsonii is a species of Anemone from East Africa .
Janthina umbilicata , also known as the elongate janthina , is a species of holoplanktonic sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Janthinidae , the violet snails or purple storm snails .
Chiloglanis sardinhai is a species of upside - down catfish endemic to Angola where it is found only in Cuanza Sul Province .
Erigeron gracilis is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name quill fleabane .
Lygisma is a plant genus in the family Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1883 .
Carabus italicus italicus is a black coloured subspecies of beetle from Carabidae family , that can be found in Italy and Switzerland .
Zospeum tholussum is a cave - dwelling species of air - breathing land snails in the family Ellobiidae .
Peringia ulvae , also known as Peringia ulvae , common name the Laver spire shell or mudsnail , is an European species of very small aquatic snail with gills and an operculum , a gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .
Atractaspis leucomelas , or the Ogaden burrowing asp , is a species of venomous snake in the Atractaspididae family .
Porcellio expansus is a species of woodlouse in the genus Porcellio belonging to the family Porcellionidae that can be found in Spain .
Salvinia auriculata is a species of plant in the Salviniaceae known by the common names eared watermoss , African payal , and butterfly fern .
Physokentia is a genus of flowering plant in the palm family , native to certain islands of the western Pacific .
Dorochoviella is a monotypic genus of beetles in the family Buprestidae , the jewel beetles .
Phisalixella is a genus of lamprophiid snakes endemic to the island of Madagascar .
Conus litoglyphus , common name the lithograph cone , is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk , more popularly known as a cone snail , cone shell or cone .
Austropotamobius torrentium , also called the stone crayfish , is a European species of freshwater crayfish in the family Astacidae .
Iris fosteriana is a species in the genus Iris , subgenus Scorpiris .
Tillandsia bartramii , commonly known as Bartram 's airplant , is a species of flowering plant in the bromeliad family .
The rare spider species Tegenaria silvestris is mostly found in caves , or on dumps ; sometimes it occurs on forest edges , or in dry forests .
Plesiorycteropus , also known as the bibymalagasy or Malagasy aardvark , is a recently extinct eutherian mammalian genus from Madagascar .

Tanacetum camphoratum is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names camphor tansy and dune tansy .
Eriastrum sapphirinum is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name sapphire woollystar .
Buchanosteus is an extinct genus of arthrodire placoderm .
Acanista alphoides is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Acanista .
Genycharax tarpon is a species of characin endemic to Colombia , where it is found in the upper Rio Cauca .
Apiospora montagnei is a plant pathogen that causes kernel blight on barley but is more often seen a saprophyte or secondary invader of many other plant species .
Apterichtus flavicaudus , variously known as the Orange snake eel , the Sharpnose sand eel or the Sharpnose snake eel , is a species of snake eel native to the Indian Ocean from the Seychelles to Hawaii in the Pacific Ocean .
Cirrisalarias bunares is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western central Pacific and Indian Oceans .
Eurymylidae is a family of extinct simplicidentates .
Parapterois is a genus of venomous fish in the scorpionfish family .
Blaculla is an extinct genus of shrimp .
Curassanthura bermudensis is a species of isopod crustacean in the family Leptanthuridae , endemic to Bermuda .
Euprenolepis is a Southeast Asian genus of ants in the subfamily Formicinae with eights recognized species .
Leiostyla vincta is a species of minuscule , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Lauriidae .
Athous subfuscus is a species of beetle from a family of elateridae in a genus of Athous .
Hookeria lucens , the shining hookeria , is a species of moss in the family Hookeriaceae .
Nymphon leptocheles is a species of sea spider first described by Georg Ossian Sars in 1888 .
Pavona cactus , the cactus coral , potato chip coral or leaf coral , is a species of colonial stony coral in the family Agariciidae .
Malpighia coccigera is a species of flowering plant in the nance family , Malpighiaceae , that is native to the Caribbean .
The Coniocybaceae are a lichenized family of fungi in the Ascomycota phylum .
Phidippus tyrannus is a species of jumping spider found in the United States and Mexico .
Porricondyla media is a species of dipteran fly in the Cecidomyiidae family .
Biscutella rotgesii ( Lunetière de Rotgès ) is a species of flowering plant in the Brassicaceae family .
Diospyros virginiana is a persimmon species commonly called the American persimmon , common persimmon , eastern persimmon , `` ' simmon '' , `` possumwood '' , or `` sugar - plum '' .
Scincella gemmingeri , commonly known as the forest ground skink , is a species of lizard endemic to Mexico .
Placenticeras whitfieldi is an ammonite species from the Late Cretaceous .
Petroica is a genus of Australasian robins , named due to their red and pink markings .
Nepenthes lavicola ( /nɨˈpɛnθiːz ˌlævɪˈkoʊlə/ ; from Latin : lavicola growing upon lava ) is a tropical pitcher plant species endemic to the Geureudong Massif of Aceh , northern Sumatra , where it grows at 2000 - -2600 m above sea level .
Garuleum is a genus of flowering plants in the sunflower family , native to southern Africa .
Psilocybe uxpanapensis is a species of entheogenic mushroom in the Strophariaceae family .
Kulceratops is a genus of ceratopsian dinosaur from the Early Cretaceous .
Achyranthes aspera ( common names : chaff - flower , prickly chaff flower , devil 's horsewhip , Sanskrit : अपामार्ग apamarga ) is a species of plant in the Amaranthaceae family .
Hapalidiaceae is a family of red alga belonging to the order Corallinales .
Girardia tigrina is a species of dugesiid native from America .
Conus obscurus , common name the obscure cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Veigaiidae is a family of mites belonging to the superorder Parasitiformes .
Streptomyces calvus is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil in Dinepur in India .
Euphorbia lurida is a species of spurge known by the common name woodland spurge .
Nymphicula bombayensis is a Crambidae species in the genus Nymphicula .
Roridula ( /rɒˈrɪdjʊlə/ ; from Latin roridus `` dewy '' ) is a South African genus of plants restricted to the Cape Provinces .
Voluta ebraea , common name the Hebrew volute , is a species of medium - sized sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Volutidae , the volutes .
Chuanjiesaurus is a genus of sauropod dinosaurs from the middle Jurassic Period .
Uloboridae is a family of non - venomous spiders , known as cribellate orb weavers or hackled orb weavers .
Perityle saxicola is a rare species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names Roosevelt Dam rockdaisy and Fish Creek rockdaisy .
Scolia hirta is a species belonging to the family Scoliidae subfamily Scoliinae .
Intercapperia is a genus of moth in the Pterophoridae family containing only one species , Intercapperia scindia , which is only known from the Scinde Valley in Kashmir .
Dicroidium is an extinct genus of fork - leaved seed ferns that were distributed over Gondwana during the Triassic ( 252 to 201 million years ago ) .
Cymodocea nodosa is a species of seagrass in the family Cymodoceaceae and is sometimes known as little Neptune grass .
Tornoceratidae is a family of goniatitid ammonoids from the middle and upper Devonian .
Trachypollia didyma is a species of small big predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Quasipaa yei , or Ye 's spiny - vented frog , is a species of frog in the Dicroglossidae family .
The genus is monotypic , containing the single species Melanomphalia nigrescens , found in Europe .
Isograptus is an extinct genus of graptolite from the Ordovician .

Estrilda is a genus of finch in the Estrildidae family .
Hoplocorypha vittata is a species of praying mantis found in Malawi and Tanzania .
Gobiderma is an extinct genus of Late Cretaceous lizard whose fossils are known from the Gobi Desert in southern Mongolia .
Colletes compactus a species of ground - nesting bee in the genus Colletes .
Gnaphosa prosperi is a ground spider species found in Spain .
Flores giant rat , which is the only extant species in the genus Papagomys , was given its latin name after Dutch Jesuit missionary Kornelis J. F. le Cocq d'Armandville who was stationed in the Dutch East Indies and later in New Guinea .
Bulbostylis is a genus of plants in the sedge family .
Chapmannia is a genus of legume in the Fabaceae family , and was recently assigned to the informal monophyletic Pterocarpus clade of the Dalbergieae .
Alectrosaurus ( /əˌlɛktroʊˈsɔːrəs/ ; meaning `` alone lizard '' ) is an extinct genus of tyrannosaurid theropod dinosaur that lived approximately 83 to 74 million years ago during the latter part of the Cretaceous Period in what is now Inner Mongolia .
Occidozyga vittata ( common name : striped oriental frog ) is a species of frog in the Dicroglossidae family .
Spermacoce keyensis , the Florida false buttonweed , is a species of plants in the Rubiaceae , first discovered in the Florida Keys .
Heterotilapia buttikoferi , also known as the zebra tilapia , is a species of cichlid .
Oxyropsis acutirostra is a species of armored catfish native to Brazil , Colombia and Venezuela , where it occurs in the Orinoco and Negro River basins .
Matonia is a genus of fern native to Malesia , named for English botanist William George Maton .
Dzihunia is a genus of stone loaches native to Central Asia .
The Agathina Emperor ( Doxocopa agathina ) is a species of butterfly of the Nymphalidae family .
Micractaeon koptawelilensis is a species of land snail , terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Achatinoidea ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
It contains only one species , Tia enervana , which has been recorded from Russia ( Siberia ) and Canada ( Alberta ) .
Liobagrus styani is a species of catfish in the Amblycipitidae family ( the torrent catfishes ) endemic to the province of Hubei in China .
Astragalus molybdenus is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common names Leadville milkvetch and molybdenum milkvetch .
Antennaria pulchella is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family known by the common names showy pussytoes and handsome pussytoes .
Metteniusa is a genus of flowering plants in the monogeneric family Metteniusaceae .
Chalinochromis is a small and disputed cichlid genus from the subfamily Pseudocrenilabrinae .
Uroteuthis duvaucelii , also known as the Indian Ocean Squid or Indian Squid , is an Indo - West Pacific species of squid with a wide range throughout the Indian Ocean to Malaysia and the South China Sea , and is also present in the Red Sea and the Arabian Sea .
Niceforonia is a small genus of frogs in the Craugastoridae family .
Its only described species , Fritzia muelleri is found in Brazil and Argentina .
The Guildayichthyiformes is a prehistoric order or marine fish from the Mississippian of Montana .
Dimelaena is a genus of rimose to areolate placoidioid crustose lichens .
Teredora princesae is a species of marine bivalve mollusc in the family Teredinidae , the shipworms .
Thesprotia caribea , common name Caribbean grass mantis , is a species of praying mantis found in Antigua and Jamaica .
Macrodontia batesi is a species in the Macrodontia genus of long - horned beetles .
Viola kauaensis is a rare species of flowering plant in the violet family known by the common names Kauai violet and pohe hiwa .
Kleskunsaurus is an extinct genus of scincomorph lizard from the Late Cretaceous of Alberta , Canada .
Cycas brachycantha is a species of cycad in the genus Cycas , native to northern Vietnam where it is endemic to Bắc Kạn Province .
Acanthaeschna victoria , the thylacine darner , is a species of dragonfly in the family Aeshnidae .
Caucalis platycarpos is a species of flowering plants in the carrot family , the only member of the genus Caucalis .
Bonnetiaceae is a family of flowering plants , consisting of 3 genera and 35 species .
Cayaponia is the largest genus in the gourd family Cucurbitaceae , with about 60 species .
Ranunculus abortivus is a species of flowering plant in the buttercup family , Ranunculaceae .
Phenacobrycon henni is a species of characin endemic to Ecuador , where it is found in the Vinces River basin .
Clanculus euchelioides , common name the small top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Memecylon hullettii is a species of plant in the family Melastomataceae .
Agave schottii , also known by the common name Schott 's Century Plant , is a shrub species within the Agave genus .
Parambassis wolffii , commonly known as the duskyfin glassy perchlet , is a species of freshwater fish in the Asiatic glassfish family Ambassidae of order Perciformes .
Pseudomugil furcatus , commonly known as the forktail blue - eye , is a species of fish in the family Pseudomugilidae .
Aesculus chinensis , the Chinese horse chestnut ( Chinese:七叶树 qi ye shu ) , is a tree species in the genus Aesculus found in eastern Asia .
Cyperus elegans , the royal flatsedge , is a sedge species in the genus Cyperus from Central and South America .
Borrelia afzelii is a species of Borrelia that can infect various species of vertebrate and invertebrates .
Sclerorhynchidae is an extinct family of cartilaginous fish from the Cretaceous and Paleogene belonging to the primitive Batoidea suborder Pristiformes .
Bogolubovia is a genus of pterosaur from the Upper Cretaceous ( early Campanian ) Rybushka Formation of Petrovsk , Saratov Oblast , Russia .
Trachys minutus is a species of jewel beetles belonging to the family Buprestidae .
Exallias brevis , the leopard blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the Pacific and Indian oceans .
Undorosaurus is an extinct genus of ophthalmosaurid ichthyosaur known from western Russia .
Bathyraja mariposa , sometimes referred to as the butterfly skate is a species of skate found in the Aleutian islands .
Camponotus cinctellus , commonly known as the shiny sugar ant , is a species of sugar ant with an extensive range in the eastern Afrotropics .
Kuntinaru is an extinct genus of tolypeutine dasypodid armadillo which existed in Bolivia , during the late Oligocene ( Deseadan age ) .
Brickellia desertorum is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names desert brickellbush and desert brickellia .
Wrightia is a genus of flowering plants in the Apocynaceae ( dogbane ) family , first described as a genus in 1810 .
Mautodontha parvidens is an extinct species of small air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Charopidae .
Nebria tatrica is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in Poland Czech Republic and Slovakia .
Hugueninia tanacetifolia , the tansy - leaved rocket , is a species of flowering plant in the monotypic genus Hugueninia belonging to the mustard family .
Diodora galeata , common name the cup - shaped keyhole limpet , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets and slit limpets .
Stigmatomma testaceum , is a species of ants in the subfamily Amblyoponinae .
Leymus ambiguus is a species of grass known by the common names Colorado wildrye and Rocky Mountain wildrye .
Austrocarina recta is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Horaiclavidae .
Abachausia is a genus of moths belonging to the family Pyralidae .
It was described as the only species of the subgenus `` Ekbletomys '' of genus Oryzomys in a 1962 Ph.D. thesis , but that name is not available under the International Code of Zoological Nomenclature and the species remains formally unnamed .
Liocarcinus navigator is a species of crab in the family Portunidae .
Crassula arborescens , the silver dollar plant , is a species of succulent plant in the Crassulaceae family .
Hyperolius pusillus ( common names : waterlily reed frog and various variants thereof , dwarf reed frog ) is a species of frog in the Hyperoliidae family .
Musca albina is a widespread Old World species , known from dry areas of the Afrotropical Region , North Africa and the Middle East , Central Asia , India and Sri Lanka .
Neopseustidae is a small family of day and night - flying `` archaic bell moths '' in the Lepidoptera order .
Aloe perryi ( syn . Aloe forbesii Balf.f . ; Aloe socotrina ) is a species of plant in the genus Aloe .
Bertholdia trigona ( commonly called Grote 's Bertholdia ) is a species of moth in the family Arctiidae .
Acacia imbricata , commonly known as imbricate wattle , is a shrub species that is endemic to South Australia .
Tsaraphycis safedella is a species of snout moth in the genus Tsaraphycis .
Etia nguti is a species of cichlid fish endemic to Cameroon in Central Africa where it is only known from the Nguti River ( Ehumbve river ) , a tributary of the Cross - Manyu River .
Adetomyrma bressleri is a species of ant belonging to the Adetomyrma genus .
Lepista flaccida is a species of mushroom found across the Northern Hemisphere .
Planoprotostelium aurantium is a mycetozoan species .
Acinonyx is a genus within the cat family .
Leptanillinae is a subfamily of ants .
The Eurasian beaver or European beaver ( Castor fiber ) is a species of beaver which was once widespread in Eurasia .
Calymperastrum latifolium is the sole species in the monotypic moss genus Calymperastrum .
Urbananthus is a genus of Caribbean plants in the boneset tribe within the sunflower family .
Nassarius consensus , common name the striate nassa , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Nassariidae , the Nassa mud snails or dog whelks .
Platycnemis sikassoensis is a species of damselfly in the family Platycnemididae .
Hemithrinax is a genus of palms which is endemic to eastern Cuba .
Dioscorea alata , known as purple yam and many other names , is a species of yam , a tuberous root vegetable .
Anchylobela dyseimata is a species of snout moth in the genus Anchylobela .
Hemidonax pictus is a species of bivalve from family Hemidonacidae .
Conus cardinalis , common name the cardinal cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Saccharum munja is a choice species for vegetation and stabilization of erosion - prone rugged slopes and their conversion into biologically productive sites of high socio - economic values .
Ropalidia is a large genus of eusocial paper wasps in the tribe distributed throughout the Afrotropical , Indomalayan and Australasian biogeographical regions .
Cautethia exuma is a species of moth in the family Sphingidae , which is known from the Bahamas .
Acineta superba is a species of orchid and the type species of the genus Acineta found in Venezuela , Colombia , Ecuador and Peru .
The Neblina uakari ( Cacajao hosomi ) or black - headed uakari , is a newly described species of monkey from the far northwest Brazilian Amazon and adjacent southern Venezuela .
Acrochordonichthys septentrionalis , the Maeklong chameleon catfish , is a species of catfish of the family Akysidae .
Farlowella hahni is a species of armored catfish of the family native to Argentina and Paraguay where it occurs in the middle Paraná River basin .
Rhodiola integrifolia is a species of flowering plant in the stonecrop family known by the common names ledge stonecrop , western roseroot , and king 's crown .
Metellina merianae is a spider species found in Europe up to Georgia .
Oroxylum indicum is a species of flowering plant belonging to the family Bignoniaceae , commonly called midnight horror , oroxylum , kampong , or Indian trumpet flower .
The Arfak pygmy bandicoot ( Microperoryctes aplini ) is a species of marsupial in the family Peramelidae .
Helianthus simulans is a North American species of sunflower known by the common name muck sunflower .
Lyonia truncata is a species of flowering plant in the heath family known as Dominican staggerbush .
Leptofoenus pittfieldae is an extinct species of wasp in the family Pteromalidae known from early Miocene Burdigalian stage Dominican amber deposits on the island of Hispaniola .
Intejocerida is the name given to a group of generally straight shelled nautiloid cephalopods originally found in Lower and Middle Ordovician sediments in the Angara River basin in Russia ; defined in the Treatise as an order , and combined there with the Endocerida in the Endoceratoidea .
Anomomorpha lecanorina is a species of lichen in the family Graphidaceae .
Galathea intermedia is a species of squat lobster found in the north - eastern Atlantic Ocean , as far north as Troms , Norway , south to Dakar and the Mediterranean Sea .
Psidium is a group of trees and shrubs in the myrtle family , described as a genus by Linnaeus in 1753 .
Myrmica laurae is a species of ant .
This species used to be classified as Mimosa biuncifera but it was found that phenotypic variations occurred across its range and a new taxonomy was proposed by Rupert C. Barneby in 1986 , splitting the species into Mimosa aculeaticarpa var . biuncifera and Mimosa texana .
It contains the single species Dohertya cymatophoroides , which is found in Burma .
Arthuria africana is a sponge species of the genus Arthuria from South Africa from which the species is named .
Carabus hummeli hummeli is a subspecies of ground beetle from Carabidae family , that can be found in Mongolia and Russia .
Bumastus is an extinct genus of corynexochid trilobites which existed from the Early Ordovician period to the Late Silurian period .
Equus occidentalis or the Western horse , was a Pleistocene species of horse , now extinct , that inhabited North America .
Omobranchus aurosplendidus is a species of combtooth blenny found in the Northwest Pacific ocean , around China and Macau .
Gogo arcuatus is a species of catfish of the family Anchariidae endemic to Madagascar where it is found in the Sandrananta River basin .
Allophyllum is a small genus of flowering plants in the phlox family known as false gilyflowers .
Parabuthus is a genus of large and highly venomous Afrotropical scorpions , that show a preference for areas of low rainfall .
Tanganikallabes is a genus of airbreathing catfishes .
Tessema sensilis is a little - known moth species , the only member of genus Tessema .
Narcissus cyclamineus ( cyclamen - flowered daffodil ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Amaryllidaceae , native to North West Portugal and North West Spain .
Dravidogecko is a monotypic genus of Indian gecko , commonly known as forest gecko .
Xenocerus deletus is a species of beetles from the family Anthribidae , also known as fungus weevils .
Liopsetta is a genus of righteye flounders native to the northern oceans .
Chrysochampsa is an extinct genus of alligatorine .
Nannosalarias nativitatis , the Pygmy blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the western Pacific and Indian oceans .
Kolihapeltis is a genus of trilobite that lived from the Early Devonian to the Middle Devonian .
Croton aromaticus is a species of plant of the genus Croton and the family of Euphorbiaceae , native to in the Indian subcontinent .
Paphiopedilum superbiens is a species of orchid endemic to northern and western Sumatra .
Pseudoceros is a genus of flatworms .
Paruroctonus boreus , sometimes called the `` Northern Scorpion '' , is a species of scorpion of the family Vaejovidae that can be as far north as 50 ° N. It is the only scorpion found in Canada , with specimens collected in the Okanagan valley of British Columbia and more widely in Alberta .
Robia legula is a species of fanfin found in the western central Pacific Ocean where it is found at depths of 1,000 to 1,500 metres ( 3,300 to 4,900 ft ) .
Eburia bahamicae is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family , that can be found on the Bahamas .
The Itatiaia spinetail ( Asthenes moreirae ) , also known as the Itatiaia thistletail , is a species of bird in the Furnariidae family .
Pomaderris ferruginea is a species of shrubs and small trees from eastern and southern Australia .
Mastacembelus ellipsifer , the Tanganyikan spiny eel , is a species of spiny eel .
Chaetomium cupreum is a fungus species in the Chaetomium genus .
Gasparinisuchus is an extinct genus of peirosaurid notosuchian known from the Late Cretaceous ( Santonian to early Campanian stage ) of Neuquén and Mendoza Provinces , western central Argentina .
Mactra stultorum , previously sometimes known as Mactra corallina , is a species of edible saltwater clam , a marine bivalve mollusc in the family Mactridae , the trough shells .
Orthetrum migratum is an Australian freshwater dragonfly species .
Arachnospila is a predominantly Holarctic genus of spider wasps , with limited representation in montane habitats in Neotropical and Afrotropical regions .
Brookesia griveaudi , commonly known as the Marojejy leaf chameleon , is a species of chameleon endemic to northeastern Madagascar .
Cotesia glomerata , the white butterfly parasite , is a small parasitic wasp species belonging to family Braconidae .
Glyptothorax alaknandi is a species of catfish that was first described by Tilak , 1969 .
Pleurodiscus is a genus of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Pupilloidea .
Dendrobium bilobum , the Two Lobed Dendrobium , is a species of orchid of the genus Dendrobium native to Oceania .
Orobanche corymbosa is a species of broomrape known by the common name flat - top broomrape .
Papilio cacicus is an indicator species of primary mountain forest for instance in the Cordillera de la Costa montane forests in Venezuela and more generally in the Tropical Andes .
The species was first described by Ferdinand von Mueller as Cylicodaphne bindoniana in 1865 , before he reclassified and renamed it as Litsea bindoniana in 1882 .
Pedobacter rhizosphaerae is a species of Gram - negative bacteria , first isolated from rhizosphere soil of Brassica campestris , hence its name .
Juncus tiehmii is a species of rush known by the common name Nevada rush .
Agapetes serpens is a semi - climbing shrub species native to the Himalayas , 40 - -60 cm tall , grown as an ornamental for its attractive pendulous benches of red tubular flowers blooming over a long period .
Helcogramma nesion is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Helcogramma .
Paraxenisthmus springeri is a species of fish in the monotypic genus Paraxenisthmus of the Xenisthmidae ( wriggler ) family from the West Pacific .
Psaeropterella punctifrons is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Psaeropterella of the family Ulidiidae .

Atriplex rosea is a species of saltbush known by the common names tumbling saltbush , red orach , redscale and tumbling orach .

Dromicoida elegantia is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Dromicoida .

Phyllodon ( meaning `` leaf tooth '' ) was a genus of small ornithopod dinosaur from the Kimmeridgian - age Upper Jurassic Guimarota Formation of Leiria , Portugal .

Geisonoceratidae is an extinct family of orthoceroid cephalopods endemic to what would be Asia , Europe , and North America from the Middle Ordovician to the Middle Devonian living from about 470 - -380 mya , existing for approximately 90 million years .
Megadontosuchus is a genus of tomistomine crocodylian from the middle Eocene of Italy .
Ceratodiscus is a genus of tropical and subtropical land snails with an operculum , terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the family Helicinidae .
Valenciennea wardii , Ward 's sleeper , is a species of goby native to the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean in bays , reefs and lagoons at depths of from 12 to 35 metres ( 39 to 115 ft ) .

Dicrateria is a genus of haptophytes , comprising the three species Dicrateria gilva , Dicrateria inornata , and Dicrateria vlkianum .
Leotia lubrica , commonly referred to as a jelly baby , is a species of fungus in the family Leotiaceae .

Rhabdodon ( meaning `` fluted tooth '' ) is a genus of ornithopod dinosaur that lived in Europe approximately 70 - -66 million years ago in the Late Cretaceous .

Caligus musaicus is a sea louse species that parasitises the European flounder ( Platichthys flesus ) ; it was discovered off Portugal .
Anomoses hylecoetes is a species of primitive hepialoid moth endemic to Queensland and New South Wales , Australia .

The Actiniidae is the largest family of sea anemones , to which most common , temperate , shore species belong .

Selaginella sibirica , the Siberian spikemoss , is a species of spikemoss that can be found in dry or exposed rocks and ridges from Alaska to the northwestern region of the district of Mackenzie as well as in northern Russia .

The superfamily Siricoidea is an archaic group of the order Hymenoptera , consisting of three families ( one extinct ) of xylophagous sawflies .
Exallodontus aguanai is a catfish species ( order Siluriformes ) of the monotypic genus Exallodontus of the family Pimelodidae .

Agrostis idahoensis is a species of grass known by the common name Idaho bent grass .
Nebria altisierrae is a species of black coloured ground beetle from Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in the US state of California .
Dioscorea villosa is a species of a twining tuberous vine that is native to eastern North America .
Dasysyrphus venustus is a Europen species of hoverfly .
Lachnia subcincta is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Lachnia .
Schaefferia is a genus of flowering shrubs and small trees in the staff vine family , Celastraceae .
Cotaena phlegyropa is a species of sedge moths in the genus Cotaena .
Opsilia transcaspica is a species of beetle from a Cerambycidae family , that are distributed in Central Asia .
Ecklonia stolonifera ( Japanese : ツルアラメ , turuarame ) is a brown alga species in the genus Ecklonia found in the Sea of Japan .
Arctostaphylos edmundsii , with the common name Little Sur manzanita , is a species of manzanita .
Streptomyces graminilatus is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from the plant Sasa borealis in Damyang in Korea .
Helvella macropus is a species of fungus in the Helvellaceae family , Pezizales order .
Rudgea parquioides is a shrub species that occurs in Brazil , in the Atlantic Forest Biome in the regions Sudeste ( in São Paulo state ) and Sul ( in Paraná , Santa Catarina and Rio Grande do Sul states ) .
Sebastes semicinctus is a species of fish in the rockfish family found in Eastern Central Pacific
Ammocharis nerinoides is a plant species endemic to Namibia , known from the Gobabis and Etoshapan Districts .
Stellaria porsildii is a rare species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common name Porsild 's starwort .
Xenotilapia ornatipinnis is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it can be found in schools in areas with sandy substrates .
Divandu albimarginatus is a species of cichlid native to the Republic of Congo and Gabon in Africa .
Hypsoblennius sordidus is a species of combtooth blenny found in the southeast Pacific ocean , around Chile .
Hystricella turricula is a species of small , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Hygromiidae .
Parosphromenus is a genus of gouramies native to freshwater in Southeast Asia .
Lambis lambis , common name the spider conch , is a species of large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Strombidae , the true conchs .
Lepturoschema penardi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Lepturoschema .
Prionus lecontei is a species of longhorn beetle in the genus Prionus .
The Peruvian meadowlark ( Sturnella bellicosa ) is a species of bird in the family Icteridae .
Schizoeupsalis promissa is a species of weavil in the Brentidae family .
Alatina alata is a Pacific and Atlantic Ocean species of box jellyfish , often referred to as a sea wasp .
Allium parciflorum is a plant species known only from the islands of Corsica and Sardinia in the Mediterranean .
Sporobolus heterolepis , commonly known as prairie dropseed , is a species of prairie grass native to the tallgrass and mixed grass prairies of central North America from Texas to southern Canada .
The Sinuate Clubtail , ( Burmagomphus pyramidalis ) is a species of dragonfly in the family Gomphidae .
Duttaphrynus beddomii ( common name : Beddome 's toad ) is a species of toad endemic to the Western Ghats of India .
Dubautia pauciflorula is a rare species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Wahiawa Bog dubautia .
Arthrocereus is a genus of cactus , originating from southern Minas Gerais , Brazil .
Collemopsidium elegans is a lichenized fungus species in the genus Collemopsidium .
Pseudomyrmex spinicola is a species of red myrmecophyte - inhabiting neotropical ants which are found only in Nicaragua and Costa Rica .
Trochus maculatus , common name the maculated top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Gobius koseirensis is a species of goby native to the western Indian Ocean where it is only known to occur off the coast of Egypt .
The Southern red - sided opossum ( Monodelphis sorex ) is an opossum species from South America .
Vellozia andina is a species of plant in the order Pandanales .
Canna liliiflora is a species of the Canna genus , a member of the family Cannaceae , and a native of Peru and Bolivia .
Unachlorus viridis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Unachlorus .
Vicia nana is a flowering plant species in the genus Vicia found in South America .
Eutrochium maculatum ( spotted Joe - Pye weed ) is a North American species of flowering plants in the sunflower family .
Borkhausenia minutella is a species of moth .
Pseudanamera fulvomaculata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudanamera .
The Empidoidea are a large monophyletic superfamily of true flies , the sister taxon to the Muscomorpha (= `` Cyclorrhapha '' ) .
Actinidia oregonensis is an extinct species of flowering plant in the kiwi family , Actinidiaceae , solely known from the middle Eocene sediments exposed in north central Oregon .
Neophrynichthys is a genus of fatheads native to the southwestern Pacific Ocean waters around New Zealand .
Peripsocus consobrinus is a species of Psocoptera from Peripsocidae family .
Archaeocidaris is an extinct genus of echinoid that lived from the Late Devonian to the Late Permian .
Nototriton richardi ( common name : Richard 's salamander ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .
Megalotriton is an extinct genus of prehistoric salamanders which lived in Europe during the Late Eocene .
Ulex europaeus ( gorse , common gorse , furze or whin ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Fabaceae , native to portions of Europe from the northern United Kingdom south to Galicia in Spain and Portugal , and from the western Republic of Ireland east to Galicja in Poland and Ukraine .
Pardosa lugubris is a wolf spider species with Palearctic distribution .
Balsamorhiza serrata ( serrate balsamroot ) is a North American species of plants in the sunflower tribe within the aster family .
Amblyoponinae is a subfamily of ants in the poneromorph subfamilies group containing 13 extant genera and one extinct genus .
Melilotus officinalis , known as yellow sweet clover , yellow melilot , ribbed melilot and common melilot is a species of legume native to Eurasia and introduced in North America , Africa and Australia .
Meiacanthus kamoharai is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the western Pacific ocean , around southern Japan .
Maresaurus is an extinct genus of pliosaur from the Middle Jurassic ( Bajocian ) of what is now Argentina .
Chaetura is a genus of needletail swifts found in the Americas in modern times .
Nothocestrum longifolium , the longleaf ʻaiea , is a species of tree in the nightshade family , Solanaceae , that is endemic to Hawaiʻi .
Kupea martinetugei is a species of plant in the Triuridaceae family .
Lactarius fuliginosus , commonly known as the sooty milkcap , is a species of fungus in the family Russulaceae .
Xenophidia ( Caenophidia ) is a superfamily of the suborder Serpentes ( snakes ) that contains cobras , vipers , sea snakes and the majority of snake species .
Perithemis is a genus of dragonflies commonly known as Amberwings .
Tricholoma is a genus of fungus that contains a large number of fairly fleshy white - spored gilled mushrooms which are found worldwide generally growing in woodlands .
The Tupaiidae are one of two families of treeshrews , the other family being Ptilocercidae .
Gymnopilus maritimus is a fungus species of the family Cortinariaceae first collected in northern Sardinia , Italy , in 2006 .
Stictogryllacris quadripunctata is a species of Orthoptera in the family of Gryllacrididae .
Neolamprologus is a genus of cichlids endemic to eastern Africa with all but one species , Neolamprologus devosi from the Malagarasi River , occurring in Lake Tanganyika .
Drupa morum , common name the purple drupe , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Asplenium australasicum is a species of epiphytic fern in the Aspleniaceae family found in eastern Australia .
Microryzomys altissimus , also known as the Páramo colilargo or highland small rice rat , is a species of rodent in the genus Microryzomys of family Cricetidae .
Gallienica is a genus of moths in the family Erebidae from Madagascar .
Myosotis azorica , common name Azorean mouse - ear or Azorean forget - me - not , is a plant species endemic to the Azores Islands in the North Atlantic Ocean .
Anaplagiomus garnieri is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Anaplagiomus .
Krachia cossmanni is a species of sea snail , a gastropod in the family Cerithiopsidae , which is known from European waters , including the United Kingdom Exclusive Economic Zone .
Eriogonum nortonii is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name Pinnacles buckwheat .
Sepia irvingi is a species of cuttlefish native to the southeastern Indian Ocean , specifically western Australia , from Cockburn Sound to North West Shelf ( 18 ° 49′S 118 ° 29′E ) .
Russula silvicola is a species of agaric fungus in the family Russulaceae .
Specklinia is a genus of orchids native to South America , Central America , Mexico and the West Indies .
The Pleosporales is the largest order in the fungal class Dothideomycetes .
Microceratus ( meaning `` small - horned '' ) is a genus of small ceratopsian dinosaur that lived in the Cretaceous period in Asia .
Xerula megalospora is a species of gilled mushroom in the Physalacriaceae family .
Trachichthys australis , the southern roughy , is a species of slimehead native to the waters off Australia , where it is found around reefs down to around 1,557 m ( 5,108 ft ) .
Proablepharus is a genus of skinks endemic to Australia .
Milnesiidae is a family of tardigrades of the class Eutardigrada .
Afroneta blesti is a species of sheet weaver found in Ethiopia .
Julidochromis dickfeldi is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika in Africa where it is only known from the southwestern portion .
Nephrotheca is a genus of plants in the calendula tribe within the sunflower family .
Beurlenia araripensis is an extinct species of shrimp in its own genus , Beurlenia .
Leptogyra inflata is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Melanodrymiidae .
Doto amyra , or the hammerhead doto , is a species of very small or minute sea slug , a dendronotacean nudibranch , a shell - less marine gastropod mollusk in the family Dotidae .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Irydyonia filicis .
Aethionema saxatile , the burnt candytuft , is a species of flowering plant in the Brassicaceae family .
Wegea is a genus of fungi within the Arthoniales order .
Leptophis diplotropis , commonly known as the Pacific Coast parrot snake , is a species of snake in the family Colubridae .
Jurahylobittacus is an extinct genus of hangingfly in the family Bittacidae and containing a single species Jurahylobittacus astictus .
Boiga forsteni , commonly known as Forsten 's cat snake , is a species of mildly venomous rear - fanged colubrid endemic to South Asia .
Anolis conspersus , also known as the Cayman blue - throated anole , Grand Cayman blue - fanned anole anole or Grand Cayman anole , is a species of anole found on the Cayman Islands .
The African penguin ( Spheniscus demersus ) , also known as the jackass penguin and black - footed penguin is a species of penguin , confined to southern African waters .
The Thripidae are the most speciose family of thrips , with over 290 genera representing just over two thousand species .
Cyathea hunsteiniana is a species of tree fern endemic to eastern New Guinea , where it grows in rain forest at an altitude of 1300 - -2000 m. This species has a slender , erect trunk up to 1 m tall and about 3 cm in diameter .
Upeneus is a genus of goatfishes native to the Atlantic , Indian and Pacific oceans .
Leptoperla cacuminis is a species of insect in family Gripopterygidae .
Pseudonigrita is a genus of bird classified in the family Passeridae , or sometimes the family Ploceidae .
Thelymitra rubra , commonly called the Salmon Sun Orchid , is a species of orchid endemic to southeastern Australia .
Ptiliogonys is a genus of bird in the Ptiliogonatidae family .
Podachaenium is a genus of Mesoamerican plants in the sunflower tribe within the daisy family .
Tresus capax is a species of saltwater clam , marine bivalve mollusk , common name the fat gaper , in the family Mactridae .
Streptocephalus gracilis is a species of crustacean in family Streptocephalidae .
Crucibulum is a genus in the Nidulariaceae , a family of fungi whose fruiting bodies resemble tiny egg - filled bird 's nests .
Ipomoea polymorpha is a morning glory species that was first described by Swiss botanist Johann Jacob Roemer and Austrian botanist Josef August Schultes .
Adenocarpus ombriosus is a species of flowering plant in the Faboideae subfamily that is endemic to El Hierro of the Canary Islands , where it can be found on the elevation of 500 metres ( 1,600 ft ) and 1.400 metres ( 4 ft 7.1 in ) .
Amata bicincta is a species of moth in the genus Amata ( or Syntomis ) of the family Arctiidae ( `` wooly bears '' or `` tiger moths '' ) .
Padillasaurus is an extinct genus of brachiosaurid sauropod known from the Early Cretaceous ( Barremian stage ) Paja Formation in Colombia .
Cacozelia basiochrealis , the yellow - based cacozelia , is a species of snout moth in the genus Cacozelia .
Spelaeodiscus triarius is a species of very small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Spelaeodiscidae .
Amblyrhynchichthys is a small genus of cyprinid fish containing only two Southeast Asian species .
The marsupial family Potoroidae includes the bettongs , potoroos , and two of the rat - kangaroos .
Pleurodiscus balmei is a Mediterranean European species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Pleurodiscidae .
Pseudoxanthomonas koreensis is a species of Gram - negative , non - spore - forming , rod - shaped bacteria , first isolated from ginseng fields .
Schilbe moebiusii is a species of schilbid catfish endemic to Tanzania where it occurs in the Ruaha , Kingani and Kilombero Rivers .
Turris babylonia , common name : the Babylon turrid or Tower Turrid , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turridae , the turrids .
Hipposauridae is an extinct family of biarmosuchian therapsids from the Late Permian of South Africa .
The Neblina Frog ( Adelastes hylonomos ) is a species of frog in the Microhylidae family .
Scolopendra heros is a species of centipede found in North America .
Phacelia corymbosa is a species of flowering plant known by the common name serpentine phacelia .
Polystichum is a genus of about 260 species of ferns with a cosmopolitan distribution .
Toeless Snake Skink , Nessia monodactyla , also known as One - toed nessia , is a species of skink endemic to island of Sri Lanka .
Mascagnia haenkeana is a species of plant in the Malpighiaceae family .
Fuligo is a widespread genus of plasmodial slime mold .
Camissonia lacustris is a species of evening primrose known by the common name grassland suncup .
Aparallactus moeruensis , or the Zaire centipede - eater , is a species of venomous rear - fanged snake in the Atractaspididae family .
Habenaria quinqueseta ( longhorn bog orchid ) is a species of orchid closely related to H. macroceratitis and often mistaken for it .
The Kerala caecilian , Uraeotyphlus interruptus , is a species of caecilian found in India .
Nelumbo aureavallis is an extinct species of flowering plant in the lotus family known from Ypresian age Eocene fossils found in western North Dakota , USA .
Sergestoidea is a superfamily of prawns , divided into two families -- the Luciferidae and the Sergestidae .
Microleropsis rufimembris is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Microleropsis .
Ixodes ricinus , the castor bean tick , is a chiefly European species of hard - bodied tick .
Calathus giganteus is a species of ground beetle from the Platyninae subfamily that can be found in Albania and Greece .
Harpactor angulosus is a species of true bug ( Harpactorinae ) .
Coeranoscincus is a genus of skinks found in Wet Tropics of Queensland , Australia .
Mosses are in the phylum ( division ) Bryophyta , which formerly also included hornworts and liverworts .
Lethocerus deyrollei is a species of giant water bug ( family Belostomatidae ) that traditionally is included in the genus Lethocerus , although recent authorities places it in the Kirkaldyia .
The infraorder Anomura is divided into nine superfamilies :
Cycas pruinosa is a small to medium species of cycad , a seed plant .
It contains the single species Eutomis minceus , which is found in South Africa .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Fabrella tsugae .

Moerbes dryopella is a species of snout moth , and the only species in the genus Moerbes .
Haliotis gigantea , common name the giant abalone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Haliotidae , the abalones .
Orthogeomys is a genus of rodent in the family Geomyidae , found in Mexico , Central America and Colombia .
Nebria elbursiaca is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Iran .
Nemophila heterophylla is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common name small baby blue eyes .
Crataerina acutipennis , is a species of biting fly in the family of louse flies Hippoboscidae .
