The Cryptocoryneae are a small Aroid tribe consisting of the closely related genera Cryptocoryne Fisch .
The Italian wolf ( Canis lupus italicus ) is a subspecies of grey wolf native to the Italian Peninsula .
Nostima duoseta is a species of shore fly .
Milda cincta , common name the banded pyram , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
Nototodarus sloanii is a species of squid commonly known as the New Zealand arrow squid or Wellington flying squid .
Georgeantha is a monotypic genus of herbaceous , rhizomatous plant endemic to Western Australia .
Georissa rufula is a species of minute cave snails , gastropod mollusks in the family Hydrocenidae .
Candida insectamens is a yeast species in the genus Candida
Syringa vulgaris ( lilac or common lilac ) is a species of flowering plant in the olive family Oleaceae , native to the Balkan Peninsula , where it grows on rocky hills .
Gnaphosa bithynica is a ground spider species found in Crete and Turkey .
Bosmina longirostris is a species of water flea found in the Great Lakes and Central Europe .
Craterellus lutescens , or Cantharellus lutescens or Cantharellus xanthopus or Cantharellus aurora , commonly known as Yellow Foot , is a species of mushroom .
Ginkgo huttonii is an extinct ginkgo species in the family Ginkgoaceae from the Jurassic of England .
Percursaria percursa is a species of seaweed from a family of Ulvaceae .
Salvia hispanica , commonly known as chia ( /ˈtʃiːə/ ) , is a species of flowering plant in the mint family , Lamiaceae , native to central and southern Mexico and Guatemala .
Margarites simbla , common name the beehive margarite , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Margaritidae .
Lysimachia lydgatei is a rare species of flowering plant in the family Primulaceae known by the common name Maui yellow loosestrife .
Orthonectida ( /ˌɔːrθəˈnɛktɪdə , -θoʊ-/ ) is a small phylum of poorly known parasites of marine invertebrates that are among the simplest of multi - cellular organisms .
Leurospondylus is a genus of plesiosaur whose family is not known for certain , but is thought to be Plesiosauridae .
Frankenia palmeri is a species of flowering plant in the frankenia family , Frankeniaceae , known by the common name Palmer 's seaheath , Palmer 's frankenia , or yerba reuma .
Diocirea violacea has a restricted distribution in a small area between Salmon Gums and Spargoville in the Coolgardie and Mallee biogeographic regions where it often grows as the dominant species on sandy , gravelly or clay soils .
Diasporus diastema is a species of frog in the family Eleutherodactylidae .
Percopsis transmontana , the Sand roller , is a species of percopsiform fish endemic to the Columbia River drainage in the northwestern United States .
Sandgrouse is the common name for Pteroclididae , a family of sixteen species of bird , members of the order Pteroclidiformes .
Apophlaea is a genus of thalloid algae comprising two species , both from the high intertidal zone on New Zealand 's coasts .
Rhynchactis is a genus of deep - sea anglerfish in the family Gigantactinidae , containing three species found worldwide at depths greater than 400 m ( 1,300 ft ) .
Astarte elliptica , or the elliptical astarte , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Astartidae .
Mimulus breweri is a species of monkeyflower known by the common name Brewer 's monkeyflower .
Typhlops annae is a species of blind snake endemic to the Caribbean island of Saint Barthélemy , an overseas collectivity of France .
Leucopsarion petersii is a species of fish in the goby family , Gobiidae , and the only member of the monotypic genus Leucopsarion .
Schizothorax yunnanensis weiningensis is a subspecies of Schizothorax yunnanensis .
Zamia roezlii is a species of cycad , a plant in the Zamiaceae family .
Bossiaea aquifolium , commonly known as Water Bush , is a species of flowering plant in the pea family Fabaceae .
Eriogonum soredium is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name Frisco buckwheat .
Koninckioceratidae is a family of nautilid genera , typically with more or less evolute shells with depressed whorl sections , that are combined as a family within the Tainocerataceae .
Hampea thespesioides is a species of flowering plant in the Malvaceae family .
Spirembolus oreinoides is a species of sheet weaver found in the United States and Canada .
Stylochidae is a family of Turbellarian Flatworms .
Scorpions are predatory arachnids of the order Scorpiones .
Atractaspis reticulata , or the reticulate burrowing asp , is a species of snake in the Atractaspididae family .
Promicromonosporaceae is an Actinomycete family .
Ceriops tagal ( spurred mangrove , Indian mangrove , Afrikaans : Indiese wortelboom , Zulu : Isinkaha ) is a mangrove tree species in the family Rhizophoraceae .
Scorpaena guttata is a species of fish in the scorpionfish family known by the common name California scorpionfish .
Lactuca hirsuta , the hairy lettuce , is a North American species of wild lettuce .
Ivesia paniculata is a species of flowering plant in the rose family known by the common name Ash Creek mousetail , or Ash Creek ivesia .
Hypsosinga albovittata is an orb - weaving spider species found in Europe , North Africa , Russia and Ukraine .
Urosalpinx cinerea , common name the eastern or Atlantic oyster drill , is a species of small predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murexes or rock snails .
The family Thaumastochelidae contains five known species of deep - sea lobsters , three in the genus Thaumastocheles , and two in the genus Thaumastochelopsis .
Tropidophorus berdmorei , commonly known as Berdmore 's water skink , is a species of skink endemic to Asia .
Echinochloa muricata is a species of grass known by the common names rough barnyard grass and American barnyard grass .
Xylosma pachyphyllum , commonly known as Spiny Logwood , is a species of flowering plant in the willow family , Salicaceae , that is endemic to Puerto Rico .
Conus coffeae , common name the coffee cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Canna discolor also known as Achira in Colombia is a species of the Canna genus , belonging to the family Cannaceae , found naturally in the range from South Mexico to Colombia , widely introduced elsewhere .
Paphiopedilum gratrixianum is a species of plant in the Orchidaceae family found from Laos to Vietnam .
Pilumnoidea is a superfamily of crabs , whose members were previously included in the Xanthoidea .
The rough mabuya or brown mabuya ( Eutropis rudis ) is a species of skink .
Mirachelus is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Chilodontidae .
Haworthia viscosa is a species of flowering succulent plant from the Western and Eastern Cape Provinces , South Africa .
Tricyrtis chinensis is a Chinese species of herbaceous plant in the lily family .
Navarretia fossalis is a rare species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name spreading navarretia .
Cobitis hellenica is a species of ray - finned fish in the true loach family ( Cobitidae ) .
Cheirodon pisciculus is a species of fish in the Characidae family endemic to Chile in freshwater environments within a benthopelagic depth range .
Recilia lactipennis is a species of bug from the Cicadellidae family that can be found in Liberia .
Vespula rufa , commonly known as the red wasp , is a social wasp species belonging to the Vespula genus .
Etroplinae is a subfamily in the cichlid family of fishes .
Hillebrandia sandwicensis is a species of a herbaceous perennial flowering plant native to some of the Hawaiian Islands .
Chrysomyxa pyrolae , is a species of rust fungi in the Coleosporiaceae family that can be found in such US states such as Alabama , Colorado , Maine and Vermont .
Calathea hagbergii is a species of flowering plant in the family Marantaceae .
Distorsio smithi , common name Smith 's distorsio , is a species of medium - sized sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Personidae , the Distortio snails .
Betta chloropharynx is a species of gourami endemic to Bangka Island , Indonesia .
Lyogyrus granum , common name the squat duskysnail , is a species of very small or minute freshwater snail with a gill and an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .
Uvularia sessilifolia , sessile bellwort , sessileleaf bellwort or wild oats , is a species of bellwort native to eastern and central North America .
Habronattus ophrys is a species of spider from a Salticidae family , that can be found in the United States .
Praeanthropus is a genus used by some researchers to include certain hominid species generally included in other genera by most researchers .
Plectranthus barbatus , also known by the synonym Coleus forskohlii and vernacular names forskohlii and Indian coleus , is a tropical perennial plant related to the typical coleus species .
Anasimus latus is a species of crab in the family Inachoididae .
Streptomyces griseoflavus is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from garden soil .
Charaxes solon , the black rajah , is a butterfly species found in tropical Asia .
Lycopodiella lateralis , commonly known as slender club moss , is a species of club moss native to eastern Australia and New Zealand .
Caragana sinica ( Chinese 金鵲根 : Jīn què - gēn ) is a species belonging to the genus Caragana .
Clitocybe agrestis is a species of agaric fungus in the family Tricholomataceae .
Guaiacum angustifolium is a species of flowering plant in the caltrop family , Zygophyllaceae .
Goggia lineata , the striped dwarf leaf - toed gecko , is a minute and delicate species of dwarf leaf - toed gecko , that is indigenous to the western part of the Cape of South Africa .
Neostethus is a genus of priapum fish native to freshwater and brackish habitats in southeast Asia , with the majority of the species restricted to the Philippines .
The crustacean order Tanaidacea ( known as tanaids ) make up a minor group within the class Malacostraca .
Lachnoderma asperum is a species of ground beetles from the genus of Lachnoderma .
Zophodia ebeniella is a species of snout moth in the genus Zophodia .
Scolodonta is a genus of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Scolodontidae .
Bolinia euryptera is a species of deep - water sculpin known only from the northern Pacific Ocean around the Aleutian Islands of Amukta , Carlisle and Semisopochnoi .
Conasprella mazei , common name Maze 's cone , is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails , cone shells or cones .
Orthochromis is a genus of haplochromine cichlids native to the rivers of West , Central , Southern , and Eastern Africa .
Marchantia is a genus in the family Marchantiaceae of the order Marchantiales , a group of liverworts .
Pallaseidae ( from the genus name Pallasea ) is a family of amphipod crustaceans endemic to Lake Baikal .
Liotia cancellata is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Liotiidae .
Kunzea parvifolia , commonly known as Violet Kunzea , is a shrub species in the family Myrtaceae .
Neolamprologus obscurus is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it is only known from southern end of the lake where it inhabits crevices .
Mystus atrifasciatus ( known locally as trey kanchos chhnoht ) is a species of catfish endemic to Cambodia , Laos , Thailand and Vietnam , known from Mekong River , Chao Phraya River and Mae Klong River and was described from Phitsanulok , Thailand .
Collomia larsenii is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name talus collomia .
Dicyphus hesperus is a species of true bug in the family Miridae .
Disteira is a genus of sea snakes .
Occirhenea georgiana is a species of medium - sized predatory air - breathing land snails , carnivorous terrestrial pulmonate gastropod molluscs in the family Rhytididae .
Colistium is a genus of righteye flounders native to the southwest Pacific Ocean where they occur around New Zealand .
Eucalyptus alba , or white gum , is a species of Eucalyptus which is native to Australia , Timor , and New Guinea .
Scartichthys viridis is a species of combtooth blenny found in the southeast Pacific ocean , from Peru to Chile .
Dyslocosaurus ( meaning `` hard - to - place lizard '' ) is the name given in 1992 to a genus of sauropod dinosaur from the Late Jurassic Period of Wyoming , North America .
It contains only one species , Phosphaticola gemmatella , which is found in Tunisia .
Zabrus boldorii is a species of ground beetle in the Pterostichinae subfamily that is endemic to Albania .
Cybaeus montanus is a spider species found in Switzerland and Italy .
Fritillaria gibbosa is an Asian species of herbaceous perennials in the lily family , native to Pakistan , Iran , Afghanistan , Turkmenistan , and South Caucasus .
Didymograptus is an extinct genus of graptolite with four rows of cups .
The species is named in honor of Ms. Jessie Barron , great - greatgrandmother of Jessie Hill of Philadelphia and Hawaii , in recognition of Jessie Hill 's contribution to saving and inventorying the conserved ACG rain forest in which Dunama jessiebarronae breeds .
The exact taxonomic placement of the Andean condor and the remaining six species of New World vultures remains unclear .
The Tawitawi forest rat or Tawitawi Island rat ( Rattus tawitawiensis ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
The sole species is Pachymitus cardaminoides , commonly known as Sand Cress , which is native to Australia .
Awaous guamensis is a species of goby native to the Pacific islands from Mariana to Vanuatu , New Caledonia and Fiji where it can be found in fresh , brackish and marine waters .
Hednotodes callichroa is a species of snout moth in the genus Hednotodes .
Iriartella is a genus of two species of palms found in northern and northwestern South America ( Guyana , Venezuela , Colombia , Peru , and western Brazil ( Acre , Amazonas , Roraima , Pará States ) ) .
Broscus cephalotes is a species of nocturnal , coastal ground beetle found throughout most of Europe .
Dahlia pinnata ( D. x pinnata ) is a species in the genus Dahlia , family Asteraceae , with the common name garden dahlia .
Didymogonyx is a genus of South American bamboo in the grass family .
Chacomylus is an extinct genus of odd - toed ungulate condylarth which existed in the Nacimiento Formation , USA during the early Paleocene period ( Puercan age ) .
Corona pfeifferi is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Orthalicidae .
Cleome hassleriana , commonly known as spider flower , spider plant , or pink queen , is a species of flowering plant in the genus Cleome of the family Cleomaceae , native to southern South America in Argentina , Paraguay , Uruguay , and southeast Brazil .
Melica transsilvanica , Red Spire , is a species of grass in the Poaceae family that can be found in Europe and temperate Asia which includes Caucasus and China .
Polacanthoides ( meaning Polacanthus like ) is an extinct genus of nodosaurid dinosaur from Europe .
The Phymosomatoida are an order of sea urchins , found in Europe , North America , North Africa and the Middle East .
Vinciguerria attenuata , commonly known as the slender lightfish , is a small species of ray - finned fish in the Phosichthyidae family , found in deep water in warmer parts of the Atlantic , the Indian and Pacific Oceans .
The Talamancan small - eared shrew ( Cryptotis gracilis ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Nebria reichii is a species of ground beetle in the Carabinae subfamily that is endemic to Romania .
Tripogandra is a genus of flowering plants in the spiderwort family , Commelinaceae .
Chiton tuberculatus , the West Indian Green Chiton , is a species of chiton , a marine polyplacophoran mollusk in the family Chitonidae , the typical chitons .
Gnaphosa lucifuga is a ground spider species with Palearctic distribution .
Cabassous is a genus of South and Central American armadillos .
Pellegrinisaurus ( meaning `` Lizard from Pelligrini '' ) is the name given to a genus of dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous .
Trichoniscidae are a family of isopods ( woodlice ) , including the most abundant British woodlouse , Trichoniscus pusillus .
The Guasiniidae are a family of harvestman with three described species from South America .
Dromiidae is a family of crabs , often referred to as sponge crabs .
Pleurobrachia pileus is a species of comb jelly , commonly known as a sea gooseberry .
Calyptrocalyx is a monoecious genus of flowering plant in the palm family found in Papua New Guinea and the nearby Maluku Islands .
Acanthostomatops is an extinct genus of temnospondyl from the Lower Permian Döhlen Basin of Saxony .
Sibinia subelliptica is a species of acorn and nut weevils belonging to the family Curculionidae , subfamily Curculioninae .
Caloplaca mereschkowskiana is a species of lichen in the family Teloschistaceae .
Tindariidae is a family of clams of the order Nuculanoida .
Protesilaus macrosilaus is a species of butterfly of the genus Protesilaus .
Phoebe nanmu is a species of evergreen tree in the Lauraceae family .
The Yungas pygmy owl ( Glaucidium bolivianum ) , is a species of owl in the family Strigidae .
Corynidae is a family of athecate hydroids .
Scaevola socotraensis is a species of flowering plant in the family Goodeniaceae .
The Ouachita madtom ( Noturus lachneri ) is a catfish of the family Ictaluridae . The first specimens of the species were collected in 1952 it was not until 1969 that they were recognised as a species .
Fowlerichthys radiosus , the Singlespot frogfish , is a species of frogfish found in the Atlantic Ocean .
Calocalanus pavo is a species of copepod in the family Calocalanidae .
Polytrichum commune ( also known as common haircap , great golden maidenhair , great goldilocks , common haircap moss , or common hair moss ) is a species of moss found in many regions with high humidity and rainfall .
The genus Loxaulax was named by Simpson G.G. in 1928 based on one species .
There have been a few species ascribed to it , but currently several varieties with various fruit colours all are recognised as Syzygium jambos .
Thermoplasma acidophilum is an archaeon , the type species of its genus .
Hypericum rumeliacum is a species of flowering plant in the Hypericaceae family , native to southeastern Europe .
Cattleya violacea ( literally , The `` Violet Cattley 's '' ) common name Superba of the Orinoco , is a bifoliate Cattleya species of orchid .
Andropogon capillipes is a species of grass known by the common name chalky bluestem .
Cagosima sanguinolenta is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Cagosima .
Periconodon is a genus of adapiform primate that lived in western Europe during the early middle Eocene .
Alphacrinus is an extinct genus of crinoid which existed during the early Ibexian period .
Clinuropsis is a genus of extinct sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks unassigned in the superfamily Conoidea .
Schilbeidae is a family of catfishes native to Africa and Asia .
Sticteulima richteri is a species of ectoparasitic sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Eulimidae .
Rhytida greenwoodi is a species of medium - sized , air - breathing predatory land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Rhytididae .
Cryptocaryon irritans is a species of ciliate protozoa that parasitizes marine fish , causing marine white spot disease or marine ich ( pronounced ik ) .
Sepiolinae is a subfamily of bobtail squid encompassing 5 genera and more than 30 species .
Nebria louisae is a species of ground beetle in the Carabinae subfamily that is endemic to Canada .
Orthochromis kasuluensis is a species of cichlid endemic to Tanzania where it is only known from the upper Ruchugi River drainage .
Synodontis grandiops is a species of upside - down catfish endemic to Lake Tanganyika .
Paragorgopis oreas is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Paragorgopis of the family Tephritidae .
Meottomyces is a small genus of relatively nondescript , fleshy , brown mushrooms related to Tubaria .
Steriphopus lacertosus is a species of spider in the family Palpimanidae .
Mirabilis expansa ( mauka or chago ) is a species of flowering plant cultivated as a root vegetable in the Andes , at cold , windy altitudes between 2,200 m ( 7,200 ft ) and 3,500 m ( 11,500 ft ) .
Cassia aldabrensis is a species of legume in the subfamily Caesalpinioideae endemic to Assumption and Aldabra near the Seychelles .
It consists of only one species , Genustes lutata , which is only known from India .
The bird genus Minla ( from minla , Nepali for M. ignotincta ) of the family Leiothrichidae is commonly used for three , most likely unrelated species .
Cylichnidia ovuliformis is a species of land snail in the family Ferussaciidae .
Macvaughiella is a genus of Mesoamerican flowering plants in the bonset tribe within the sunflower family .
Allium macropetalum , the desert onion , is a species of wild onion native to the desert regions of southwestern United States and northwestern Mexico .
Crenella faba , or the little bean mussel , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Mytilidae .
Cassida denticollis is a species of beetle in the leaf beetle family , that can be found in Mongolia , West China ( Xinjiang province ) , and the Western Palaearctic region .
The Mauritius blue pigeon ( Alectroenas nitidissima ) is an extinct species of blue pigeon formerly endemic to the Mascarene island of Mauritius in the Indian Ocean east of Madagascar .
Cleroidea is a small superfamily of beetles .
Stachys pycnantha is a species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name shortspike hedgenettle .
Ferrissia gentilis is a species of small freshwater snail or limpet , an aquatic gastropod mollusc in the family Planorbidae , the ram 's horn snails and their allies .
Neohouzeaua is a genus of Asian bamboo within the grass family ) .
Liometopum bogdassarovi is an extinct species of ant in the genus Liometopum , found in Belarus .
Triceratella is a genus of annual monocotyledonous flowering plants in the dayflower family .
It contains only one species , Diplolopha cycloptera , which is found in Central and South America , including Argentina , Colombia , Ecuador and Costa Rica .
Senecio serra is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names tall ragwort and sawtooth groundsel .
Lathyrus belinensis is an annual species of Lathyrus discovered in Turkey in 1987 .
Gillellus semicinctus , the Half - banded stargazer , is a species of sand stargazer native to the Pacific coast of the Americas from the Gulf of California to Colombia , as well as occurring in the Galapagos Islands .
Scutellaria floridana is a rare species of flowering plant known by the common name Florida skullcap .
Ostreococcus is a genus of unicellular coccoid or spherically shaped green alga belonging to the class Mamiellophyceae .
The Sonoran woodrat ( Neotoma phenax ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae found only in Mexico .
Hypochaeris oligocephala is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family native to the Canary Islands .
Ruscarius is a genus of sculpins native to the eastern Pacific Ocean .
Percilia gillissi is a species of perch - like fish in the Percichthyidae family found only in Chile .
Acanthemblemaria chaplini , the Papillose blenny , is a species of chaenopsid blenny found in the western Atlantic ocean .
Bathyuriscus is an extinct genus of Cambrian trilobite .
Alchemilla erythropoda ( dwarf lady 's mantle ) is a species of flowering herbaceous perennial plant in the family Rosaceae , native to Eastern Europe .
Ploiaria is a cosmopolitan genus of thread - legged bugs ( Emesinae ) .
Saxifraga aspera is a species of saxifrage known by the common name of rough saxifrage .
Carlana eigenmanni is a species of characin found in Costa Rica , Nicaragua and Panama .
Ancylopsetta ommata , the Gulf of Mexico ocellated flounder , is a species of large - tooth flounder native to the Atlantic coast of North America and the Gulf of Mexico .
Eigenmannia vicentespelaea is a species of weakly electric knifefish in the family Sternopygidae .
Pupisoma is a genus of minute , air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod molluscs or micromollusks in the family Valloniidae .
Araeosoma tessellatum is a species of sea urchin of the family Echinothuriidae .
Leptodactylus rhodomystax ( common name : Loreto white - lipped frog , rose - lipped thin - toed frog ) is a species of frog in the Leptodactylidae family .
Pleurojulidae is an extinct family of millipedes known from the Westphalian stage of the upper Carboniferous that are distinct enough to be placed in their own order , Pleurojulida .
Andrographis is a genus of flowering plants in the acanthus family .
Toulgarctia is a genus of moth in the family Arctiidae from Madagascar .
Oncidium auriferum is a species of orchid ranging from western South America to northern Venezuela .
Trapeziidae is a family of crabs , commonly known as coral crabs .
Trifolium aureum , known by the various common names large hop trefoil , large trefoil , large hop clover , golden clover or Hop clover , is a species of clover native to much of Eurasia .
Arundo is a genus of stout , perennial plants in the grass family .
Schizosaccharomycetales is an order in the kingdom of fungi that contains the family Schizosaccharomycetaceae .
Turbo canaliculatus , common name the channeled turban , is a species of large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
Fukuia integra , also known as Blanfordia integra , is a species of land snail which has an operculum , a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Pomatiopsidae .
Trilepisium gymnandrum is a species of urnfig that is endemic to the Seychelles , where it is threatened by habitat loss .
Tucanoichthys tucano is a species of characin endemic to Brazil , where it is found in the Uaupés River .
Dipsastraea speciosa is a species of colonial stony coral in the family Merulinidae .
The Hymenopteran superfamily Proctotrupoidea is a somewhat confusing assemblage of taxa , with new families being added ( or removed ) with surprising frequency , and very little to unify them all into a single natural group .
Chelativorans is a genus of Gram - negative , strictly aerobic , non - motile bacteria .
Prunus domestica ( sometimes referred to as Prunus × domestica ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Rosaceae .
Spelaeornis , the typical wren - babblers , is a bird genus in the family Timaliidae .
Xenotilapia is a genus of cichlids species endemic to Lake Tanganyika in east Africa .
The Malabar goby , Stenogobius gymnopomus is a species of goby endemic to the Indo - Pacific regional countries such as India , Somalia , Indonesia , Andaman Islands .
Diphlebia euphoeoides , sometimes spelled Diphlebia euphaeoides , known as the tropical rockmaster is an Australian species of broad winged damselfly .
Acromantis insularis , common name Luzon mantis , is a species of praying mantis found in India , Sumatra , and Java .
The Gnathophiurina are a group of Ophiuroidea mostly treated as suborder ( but at first as an order Gnathophiurida , and sometimes as infraorder of Ophiurina or not used at all ) .
The Aciculidae are a family of minute land snails which have opercula .
Vicinopone conciliatrix , the only species in the genus , was first described as Simopone conciliatrix by Brown in 1975 and was transferred to its own genus by Bolton & Fisher in 2012 .
Cetopsorhamdia is a genus of three - barbeled catfishes native to South America .
It contains the species Stereodmeta xylodeta , which is found in Brazil .
Oxymonas is a genus of Excavata .
Elias Magnus Fries described this species in his 1838 book Epicrisis Systematis Mycologici seu Synopsis Hymenomycetum as Cortinarius cyanites .
Eriogonum pelinophilum is a rare species of wild buckwheat known by the common name clay - loving wild buckwheat .
Fossil remains of the only known species , Sloanbaatar mirabillis , have been found in the Coniacian - Santonian ( Upper Cretaceous)-age strata of the Djadokhta Formation in Mongolia .
Lithospermum californicum is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common name California stoneseed .
Steinernema scapterisci , the mole cricket nematode , is a species of nematode in the order Rhabditida .
Leptotyphlops gracilior , or the Slender thread snake , is a species of snake in the Leptotyphlopidae family .
Endelomorphus biakensis is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Endelomorphus .
Beccariophoenix madagascariensis , commonly known as the Giant Windowpane Palm or Windowpane Coconut , is a species of flowering plant in the Arecaceae family .
Idiomarina is a genus of bacteria in the Gammaproteobacteria class , including the sequenced species Idiomarina loihiensis .
Galaxiella is a genus of Australian fish of the family Galaxiidae .
Rhinotyphlops graueri is a species of snake in the family Typhlopidae .
Anomoeotes leucolena is a species of moth of the Anomoeotidae family .
Emilia sonchifolia , also known as lilac tasselflower or cupid 's shaving brush is tropical flowering species of tasselflower and in the sunflower family .
Reseda alba is a species of flowering plant in the reseda family known by the common names white mignonette or white upright mignonette .
Campanula barbata , common name Bearded Bellflower , is a species of perennial bellflower in the family Campanulaceae .
Ctenanthe oppenheimiana , the Giant Bamburanta or Never Never Plant , is a species of plant of family Marantaceae and is a native of Brazil .
Arrhinoceratops ( meaning `` no nose - horn face '' , derived from the Ancient Greek `` a-/α- '' `` no '' , rhis/ῥίς `` nose '' `` keras/κέρας '' `` horn '' , `` -ops/ὤψ '' `` face '' ) is a genus of herbivorous ceratopsian dinosaur .
The genus Crocidura is one of nine genera of the shrew subfamily Crocidurinae .
Parablennius verryckeni is a species of combtooth blenny found in the eastern Atlantic ocean from Congo to Sierra Leone .
Octomeria rohrii is a species of orchid endemic to Brazil ( Santa Catarina ) .
Doleorthis is an extinct genus of brachiopod .
Eccopsis deprinsi is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family that is endemic to Kenya .
Ambastaia is a genus of botiid loaches native to Mainland Southeast Asia .
The Epipyropidae comprise a small family of moths .
Cortusa is a genus that consists of 19 species of delicate , hardy , alpine perennials , relative to Primula both in general appearance and habit of growth .
Phobaeticus serratipes ( formerly known as Pharnacia serratipes ) is a species of stick insect that at one time was the longest known insect , with one female specimen recorded as being 555 mm long .
Lanzhousaurus is a genus of dinosaur .
Parksosaurus ( meaning `` William Parks 's lizard '' ) is a genus of hypsilophodont ornithopod dinosaur from the early Maastrichtian - age Upper Cretaceous Horseshoe Canyon Formation of Alberta , Canada .
Sigmoilina ia a miliolid genus , referring to the foraminiferal order Miliolida , characterized by an assymmetricall biconvex test formed by strongly overlapping chambers , one - half coil in length , that form a sigmoid ( S - shaped ) curve in cross section .
Duellmanohyla is a genus of frogs ( mountain brook frogs ) in the Hylidae family found in Oaxaca , Mexico , as well as Central America .
Geranium thunbergii ( Thunberg 's geranium ) is a cranesbill species .
Drosera zonaria , the painted sundew , is a perennial tuberous species in the carnivorous plant genus Drosera and is endemic to south - west Western Australia from near Perth southeast to near Esperance .
Gonyostomus goniostomus is a species of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Strophocheilidae .
Entolasia is a genus of African , Australian , and Papuasian plants in the grass family .
Amanita smithiana , also known as Smith 's amanita , is a species of agaric found on soil in coniferous ( Abies , Tsuga , Pseudotsuga ) and broadleaved ( Alnus , Quercus ) woodland in the Pacific Northwest of North America .
Chiroteuthis imperator is a species of chiroteuthid squid .
Phacelia saxicola is a species of phacelia known by the common name stonecrop phacelia .
Cyclamen pseudibericum ( incorrectly spelled pseudoibericum ) , the false Iberian cyclamen , is a species of flowering plant in the genus Cyclamen of the family Primulaceae , native to the Amanus or Nur and Anti - Taurus Mountains in southern Turkey .
Tampichthys is a genus of cyprinid fish endemic to Mexico .
Erpetosuchus is an extinct genus of pseudosuchian from the Late Triassic .
Chrysactinium is a genus of South American flowering plants in the daisy family .
Carabus rossii is a species of beetle from Carabidae family , that can be found in Italy and on the island of Sicily .
Thrixspermum calceolus , commonly called the Small Shoe - carrying Thrixspermum , is a species of orchid native to Thailand , Vietnam , Borneo , Malaysia and Sumatra .
Hemiphractus proboscideus , or the Sumaco horned treefrog , is a species of frog in the Hemiphractidae family .
Phragmipedium fischeri is a species of orchid endemic to Ecuador .
Balnearium lithotrophicum is a species of bacteria described in 2003 and classified as belonging to the Aquificae .
Longiculter siahi is a species of cyprinid fish found in Southeast Asia where it is found in Cambodia , Laos and Thailand .
Crotalaria novae - hollandiae , known commonly as the New Holland Rattlepod , is a species of flowering plant that is native to Australia .
Senecio bahioides is a species of the genus Senecio and family Asteraceae and is a native of Chile .
Icanosaurus is an extinct genus of trematosaurian temnospondyl within the family Trematosauridae .
Porichthys notatus is a species of fish in the toadfish family .
Caligus is a genus of sea lice in the family Caligidae .
Arthropleuridea is an extinct subclass of myriapod arthropods that flourished during the Carboniferous period , having first arose during the Silurian , and perishing due to climate change during the Early Permian .
Anastrangalia laetifica is a species of beetle from Cerambycidae family , that could be found in Canada , United States , and Mexico .
Gunungia capitirecava is a species of snout moth in the genus Gunungia .
The Chaetopteridae are a family of marine filter feeding polychaete worms that live in vertical or U - shaped tubes in tunnels buried in the sedimentary or hard substrate of marine environments .
Euglossa imperialis is a bee species in the family Apidae .
Tricholoma saponaceum is yet another fungus which may represent a species complex of two or more species .
Lupinus arbustus is a species of lupine known by the common name longspur lupine .
Chelodes is a genus of Palaeozoic mollusc made up of serially repeated monoplacophoran - like valves .
Daihinibaenetes arizonensis is a species of insect in the family Rhaphidophoridae known commonly as the Arizona giant sand treader cricket .
Nokona coracodes was placed as a synonym of Nokona carulifera , but was reinstated as a valid species in 2001 .
Pseudomusonia rapax is a species of praying mantis native to Costa Rica and Venezuela .
Gastroplakaeis forficulatus is a moth species in the family of Lasiocampidae found in Ghana and Gabon .
Campsomeriella is a genus of the family Scoliidae , also known as the scoliid wasps .
Calopappus is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the aster family , Asteraceae , containing the single species Calopappus acerosus .
Agrocybe putaminum , commonly known as the mulch fieldcap , is a species of agaric fungus in the family Strophariaceae .
Plectrogenium , is a genus of scorpaeniform fishes , the stinger flatheads , the only genus in the family Plectrogenidae .
Erigeron jamaicensis is a Caribbean and Mesoamerican species of flowering plant in the daisy family commonly callde Jamaican fleabane .
Malacoctenus delalandii is a species of labrisomid blenny native to the Atlantic Ocean and the Caribbean Sea from Guatemala to Brazil .
Myrmica gallienii is an ant species distributed from Central Europe to West Siberia .
Agathis philippinensis ( in Tagalog : Almasiga or Dayungon ) is a species of large Agathis tree native to the Philippines , Sulawesi and Halmahera , where it occurs in upland tropical rainforest at 450 - 2,200 m altitude , rarely as low as 250 m in northern Luzon .
Acacia rostriformis , commonly known as Bacchus Marsh wattle , is a plant species that is endemic to Australia .
Cordylanthus palmatus , now reclassified as Chloropyron palmatum ' , is a rare species of flowering plant in the broomrape family .
Luma apiculata ( Chilean myrtle ) is a species of flowering plant in the myrtle family , native to the central Andes between Chile and Argentina , at 33 to 45 ° south latitude .
Austroliotia saxa , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Liotiidae .
Centaurea paniculata , the Jersey knapweed , is a species of Centaurea found in France and Northern Italy .
Ancistrus is a genus of freshwater fish in the family Loricariidae of order Siluriformes , native to South America and Panama .
Cryptotaenia japonica ( Japanese : mitsuba ) is a plant species native to Japan , Korea , and China .
Cyathea grevilleana is a species of tree fern endemic to Jamaica , where it grows in moist gullies and on wooded hills in both calcareous and noncalcareous soils at an altitude of 200 - -1200 m. The trunk of this plant is erect , about 7 m tall , and 10 - -15 cm in diameter .
Epimesosa taliana is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Epimesosa .
The Port Jackson shark is a migratory species , traveling south in the summer and returning north to breed in the winter months .
Bersama abyssinica is a species of medium - sized evergreen tree in the Melianthaceae family .
Xiaotingia is a genus of bird - like theropod dinosaur from early Late Jurassic deposits of western Liaoning , China , containing a single species , Xiaotingia zhengi .
Rhinopias cea , Cea 's Scorpionfish , is a species of scorpionfish known only from Easter Island .
Ctenophryne carpish is a rare and little - known species of microhylid frog endemic to Peru .
Tamijia flagellaris is the only species within the Tamijia genus .
Ameles assoi is a species of praying mantis native to Morocco , Tunisia , and Spain .
Chydenanthus is a genus of woody plant in the Lecythidaceae family first described as a genus in 1875 .
Cnemaspis otai is a species of geckos found in southeast India .
Trichocereeae is a tribe of cactus that are particular to South America .
Elachistocleis surinamensis ( Spanish : Sapito Apuntado De Surinam ) is a species of frog in the Microhylidae family .
Platygyra daedalea , sometimes known as the lesser valley coral , is a colonial species of stony coral in the family Merulinidae .
Stachyophyton is a genus of extinct vascular plants known from fossils found in the Posongchong Formation , Wenshan district , Yunnan , China , in deposits of Early Devonian age ( Pragian , around 410 million years ago ) .
Goya ovaliger is a species of snout moth in the genus Goya .
The McCloud River redband trout ( Oncorhynchus mykiss stonei ) is one of three redband trout subspecies of the rainbow trout in the Salmonidae family .
Agyneta allosubtilis is a species of sheet weaver found in the Holarctic .
Schenkia spicata is a species of annual herb in the Gentianaceae family .
Oryza glaberrima , commonly known as African rice , is a domesticated rice species .
The Tarry hogfish , Bodianus bilunulatus , is a species of wrasse native to the Indian Ocean from the African coast to the western Pacific Ocean to Japan , New Caledonia , and the Philippines .
Angiostoma is a genus of parasitic nematodes in the family Angiostomatidae .
Candidia is a genus of cyprinid fish endemic to Taiwan .
Thrissops is an extinct genus of teleost fish from the Jurassic and Cretaceous periods .
Hymenoxys cabrerae is a South American species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
Lygodium ( climbing fern ) is a genus of about 40 species of ferns , native to tropical regions across the world , with a few temperate species in eastern Asia and eastern North America .
Benitoa is a monotypic genus containing the single species Benitoa occidentalis , which is known simply as benitoa .
Linyphiidae is a family of very small spiders , including more than 4,300 described species in 578 genera worldwide .
Ceratopteris richardii is a fern species belonging to the genus Ceratopteris , one of only two genera of the Ceratopteridoideae subfamily of the Pteridaceae .
Thermonectus zimmermani is a species of diving beetle native to western Mexican states of Jalisco , Colima , and Morelos .
Lydomorphus dusaulti is a species of beetle in family Meloidae .
Argulus foliaceus is a species of crustacean in the family Argulidae , the fish lice .
The Ichetucknee siltsnail , also known as the sand grain snail , scientific name Floridobia mica , is a species of small freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod in the family Hydrobiidae .
Ditropis whitei is a species of land snails with opercula , terrestrial gastropods in the family Cyclophoridae .
Submargarita notalis is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the top snails .
Aulacomya atra ( often misspelled Aulacomya ater ) , called also the Magellan mussel or the ribbed mussel , is a southern species of edible saltwater mussel , a marine bivalve mollusk in the family Mytilidae , the true mussels .
Artemisia bigelovii is a North American species of sagebrush known by the common name Bigelow sagebrush or flat sagebrush .
Astroblepus grixalvii is a species of catfish of the Astroblepidae family .
Eurhamphaeidae is a family of ctenophores , it contains the following species :
Megacephala inca is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae that was described by Naviaux and Ugarte - Pena in 2006 , and is endemic to Peru .
Corticovirus is a genus of viruses , in the family Corticoviridae .
Jurua monachina is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Jurua .
Schiacallia tristis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Schiacallia .
Proboscidea althaeifolia is a species of flowering plant in the family Martyniaceae known by the common names desert unicorn - plant and yellow - flowered devil 's claw .
Epiprineae is a tribe of plants of the family Euphorbiaceae .
Hoita strobilina is a rare species of legume known by the common name Loma Prieta leatherroot , or Loma Prieta hoita .
The genus is monotypic , containing the single species Hydnocristella himantia , found in North America .
Euphorbia revoluta is a species of euphorb known by the common name threadstem sandmat .
The Golden Orchid ( Cephalanthera falcata ) is a species of orchid .
Arion simrothi is a species of air - breathing land slug , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Arionidae , the round - back slugs .
Kummerowia stipulacea is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name Korean clover .
Eriocaulon scariosum , commonly named common , rough or pale pipewort , is a species of tufted grass - like herbaceous plants , constituting part of the plant family Eriocaulaceae .
Dorymyrmex bicolor is a species of ant in the Dolichoderinae subfamily .
Callionymus bentuviai Ben - Tuvia 's deepwater dragonet , is a species of dragonet endemic to the Red Sea .
Morchella septimelata is a species of fungus in the Morchellaceae family described as new to science in 2012 .
Cheilodactylus is a genus of morwongs .
Acheilognathus tabira tabira is a subspecies of Acheilognathus tabira .
Athyrium asplenioides , or Southern lady fern , is a species of the family Woodsiaceae .
Pseudosasa japonica , common names Arrow bamboo and Japanese arrow bamboo , is a species of bamboo .
The Peruvian small - eared shrew ( Cryptotis peruviensis ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Dracontioides desciscens is a plant species in the Araceae .
Plagiobothrys distantiflorus is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common name California popcornflower .
Dipodium elegans is an orchid species that is native to Sumatra in Indonesia .
Pyropia rakiura , formerly known as Porphyra rakiura , is a red alga species in the genus Pyropia , known from New Zealand .
Hackelia cusickii is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common name Cusick 's stickseed .
Tectitethya crypta ( formerly known as Cryptotethya crypta and Tethya crypta ) is a species of demosponge belonging to the family Tethyidae .
Rubus chloocladus is a European species of plants in the rose family , found in central and western Europe ( Germany , Netherlands , Italy , etc . ) .
Scaled sculpins ( genus Icelus ) are a group of small benthic fishes ( up to 25 cm ) living in cold waters .
Leiopotherapon plumbeus , known commonly as the silver perch , is a species of fish in the family Terapontidae , the grunters .
Oliveridia is a genus of midges and consists of two species : hugginsi and tricornis .
Rochonia is a genus of Madagascarian plants in the aster tribe within the daisy family .
Apopterygion alta , known commonly as the Tasseled triplefin , is a species of triplefin blenny .
Ymeria is an extinct genus of early tetrapod from the Devonian of Greenland .
Thermopsis macrophylla is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common names Santa Inez goldenbanner and Santa Ynez false - lupine .
Carabus kantaikensis is a species of ground beetle in Carabinae subfamily that are endemic to Russia .
Vangueria madagascariensis , commonly known by the names Spanish - tamarind , tamarind - of - the - Indies , or voa vanga , is a species of flowering plant in the Rubiaceae family native to the African continent having edible fruit .
Asthenosoma is a genus of sea urchins in the family Echinothuriidae .
Quercus macranthera , commonly called the Caucasian oak , or the Persian oak , is a species of deciduous tree native to Western Asia ( northern Iran , Turkey ; and in the Caucasus in Georgia , Armenia , and Azerbaijan ) that is occasionally grown as an ornamental tree in Europe growing to 30 meters tall .
Zingiber spectabile is a species of true ginger , native to Maritime Southeast Asia .
Cordylanthus eremicus is a species of flowering plant in the broomrape family known by the common name desert bird 's beak .
Melaleuca fissurata was first formally described in 1986 by Bryan Barlow in Nuytsia as a new species .
Melica violacea , is a species of grass in the Poaceae family that is endemic to Chile .
Haemoproteus plataleae is a species of parasitic protozoa that infects ibises and spoonbills .
It is monotypic , with the only species being Zintha hintza , the Blue - eyed Pierrot , Blue Pied Pierrot or Hintza Blue .
Diarrhena ( beakgrain ) is a genus of Asian and North American plants in the grass family .
Garrya buxifolia is a species of flowering shrub , known by the common names dwarf silktassel and boxleaf silktassel , in the Garrya genus .
Picrasma crenata , the pau - amargo , pau - tenente or tenente - josé , is a tree species that belongs to the family Simaroubaceae .
Boletellus obscurecoccineus , known as the rhubarb bolete , is a species of fungus in the family Boletaceae , found in Australia , New Guinea , Java , Borneo , Japan , Korea , and Taiwan .
Haworthia maxima ( `` Vratjiesaalwee '' ) is a species of Haworthia succulent plant , from the Western Cape , South Africa .
Penicillium atramentosum is a fungus species of the genus of Penicillium which produces tannase .
Streptomyces aomiensis is a Gram - positive , aerobic bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which was isolated from soil from Aomi in Tokyo in Japan
Sigapatella tenuis is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Calyptraeidae , the slipper snails , Chinese hat snails and cup - and - saucer snails .
Soliclymenia is a genus of ammonite from the Late Devonian .
Brodiaea coronaria is the type species of Brodiaea and also known by the common name crown brodiaea .
Capsella rubella , the pink shepherd's - purse , is a plant species in the genus Capsella , a very close relative of Arabidopsis thaliana and a member of the mustard family , Brassicaceae .
Procambarus nigrocinctus , the blackbelted crayfish , is a species of crayfish in the family Cambaridae .
Apalus is a genus of blister beetle .
It was described by Delo in 1935 , and the type species is Eomonarachus intermedius , which was originally described under the genus Dalmanites by Walcott in 1877 .
Rucervus is a genus of deer from India , Nepal , Indochina , and the Chinese island of Hainan .
Capsaspora is a monotypic genus containing the single species Capsaspora owczarzaki , a single - celled eukaryote which is a symbiont in the haemolymph of the tropical freshwater snail Biomphalaria glabrata .
Arca mailleana is an extinct species of saltwater clam , a fossil marine bivalve mollusk in the family Arcidae , the ark shells .
Eumecosomyia lacteivittata is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Eumecosomyia of the family Tephritidae .
Pseudocalotes kakhienensis , the Kakhyen Hills spiny lizard , is a species of agamid lizard found in southern China ( western Yunnan ) , Myanmar (= Burma ) ( east of Irrawadi River ) , India , and northern Thailand .
Aborichthys elongatus is a species of freshwater fish in the stone loach family .
Kabatiella lini is a species of fungus in the family Dothioraceae .
The Arctornithini are a tribe of tussock moths of the Erebidae family .
Penicillium janczewskii is an anamorph and filamentous species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from the rhizosphere of Vernonia herbacea .
Songlingornithidae is a family of early ornithuromorph birds from the early Cretaceous Period of China .
Hypericum forrestii is a species of flowering plant in the family Hypericaceae native to Yunnan and Sichuan Provinces in China , and northeastern Burma .
Hedera azorica is a species of Ivy ( genus Hedera ) which is native to the Atlantic coast in Azores Islands .
Rhabdias bufonis is a species of parasitic nematode in the family Rhabdiasidae .
Illaenus crassicauda is a species of trilobites belonging to the family Illaenidae .
Lepidochitona is a genus of chitons .
Allium azutavicum is a rare plant species endemic to Kazakhstan .
Phalaenopsis speciosa is a species of orchid endemic to the Andaman and the Nicobar Islands .
Eulimellini is a tribe of minute sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
Genipa americana is a species of Genipa , native to northern South America ( south to Peru ) , the Caribbean and southern Mexico , growing in rainforests .
Thermochrous neurophaea is a species of moth of the Anomoeotidae family , discovered by Erich Hering in 1928 .
Epilachna borealis is a species of beetle that can commonly be found in the eastern United States .
Metarhinus is a genus of brontothere endemic to North America during the Eocene living from 46.2 - -42 mya , existing for approximately 4.2 million years .
Phygelius capensis ( cape figwort , cape fuchsia ) is a species of flowering plant in the Scrophulariaceae family , native to South Africa .
Pavoclinus pavo , the Peacock klipfish , is a species of clinid found from Lüderitzbucht , Namibia to the Kei River , South Africa where it can be found in weedy areas at the low tide line .
Parasaccogaster melanomycter is a species of viviparous brotula endemic to Colombia .
Sphagnum macrophyllum , the largeleaf sphagnum , is a species of peat moss native to southern and eastern North America .
Zamenis is a genus of nonvenomous Old World snakes in the Colubridae family .
Globampyx is an extinct genus raphiophorid trilobites .
Corallimorpharia is an order of marine cnidarians closely related to stony or reef building corals ( Scleractinia ) .
Heliomeris hispida is a North American species of flowering plants in the sunflower family called the hairy goldeneye or rough false goldeneye .
Opisthacanthus capensis ( Thorell , 1876 ) is a Cape Province and Zimbabwean species of scorpion with robust chelae , dark brown to black in colour , turning green when under cover for some time .
Rhynchodoras is a small genus of thorny catfishes native to South America .
The Andean tit - spinetail ( Leptasthenura andicola ) is a species of bird in the Furnariidae family .
Luzula pallescens is a species of perennial plant in Juncaceae family .
Tychicus longipes is a spider species found in Amboina ( Indonesia ) and was introduced in the Netherlands .
The Thyrididae comprise the family of picture - winged leaf moths .
Carissa carandas is a species of flowering shrub in the dogbane family , Apocynaceae .
Anyperodon leucogrammicus , the slender grouper , is the only species in the genus .
Haplochromis goldschmidti is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Victoria , where it is only known to occur with certainty in the southern part of the Emin Pasha Gulf .
Hexachaeta valida is a species of tephritid or fruit flies in the genus Hexachaeta of the family Tephritidae .
Afrotyphlops anomalus , commonly known as the Angolan giant blind snake or the anomalous beaked snake , is a species of snake in the Typhlopidae family .
Oncotylus viridiflavus is a species of plant bugs belonging to the family Miridae , subfamily Phylinae .
Penstemon barnebyi is a species of penstemon known by the common names White River Valley beardtongue and Barneby 's beardtongue .
Turbo magnificus , common name the magnificent turban , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
Antirrhinum cornutum ( syn . Sairocarpus cornutus ) is an uncommon species of New World snapdragon known by the common name spurred snapdragon .
Agrostis curtisii ( Bristle Bent ) is a species of grass in the Poaceae family native to Eurasia .
Nastus is a genus of slender , erect , scrambling or climbing bamboos in the grass family .
Pavoclinus is a genus of clinids found in the southeastern Atlantic and western Indian Ocean coastal waters of southern Africa .
Pinus luzmariae is a species of conifer in the family Pinaceae .
Nebria zioni is a species of brownish - black coloured ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Utah , United States .
Chorizanthe blakleyi is a rare species of flowering plant in the buckwheat family known by the common name Blakley 's spineflower .
Brassaiopsis hainla is a species of shrub in the family Araliaceae . It is used as fodder by the farmers in Nepal .
Salix viminalis , the basket willow , common osier or osier , is a species of willow native to Europe , Western Asia , and the Himalayas .
Myxodagnus walkeri is a species of sand stargazer native to the Pacific coast of Central America from Nayarit , Mexico to Golfo de Nicoya , Costa Rica where it can be found at depths of from 0 to 6 metres ( 0 to 20 ft ) .
Cyathea latipinnula is a species of tree fern native to the Philippines , where it grows in ridge forest at an altitude of about 1400 m. The trunk of this plant is erect and grows to 1 - 2 m in height and 10 cm in diameter .
Parvigrus is an extinct bird genus , with the single species Parvigrus pohli .
Okenia elegans is a species of a sea slug , specifically a dorid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Goniodorididae .
The Caddo madtom ( Noturus taylori ) is a species of fish in the Ictaluridae family .
Steyerbromelia ramosa is a species in the genus Steyerbromelia .
Alluaudina is a genus of harmless lamprophiid snakes endemic to the island of Madagascar .
Dendropsophus sartori ( common name : Taylor 's yellow treefrog ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .
Hypoestes is a flowering plant genus with many dozens of species .
Melipona quadrifasciata is a species of eusocial , stingless bee of the order Hymenoptera .
Menegazzia asahinae is a species of lichen from Japan .
The single described species Sarindoides violaceus is only found in Brazil .
Echinopsis atacamensis ( cardón ) is a species of cactus from Chile , Argentina and Bolivia .
Canthigaster margaritata ( commonly called a pearl toby in English ) is a species of `` toby '' or `` sharpnose puffer '' ( Canthigaster ) , which is part of the pufferfish ( Tetraodontidae ) family .
Oeceoclades lonchophylla is a terrestrial orchid species in the genus Oeceoclades that is native to Tanzania , Mozambique , KwaZulu - Natal in South Africa , and Comoros .
Synsepalum subverticillatum is a species of flowering plant in the family Sapotaceae .
Cyrtopodium , often abbreviated Cyrt in horticulture , is a genus of more than 40 species of epiphytic and terrestrial orchids found from Florida and Mexico through Argentina .
The Cape York rat ( Rattus leucopus ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Mimoblennius rusi , the Rusi blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western Indian ocean .
Hyalobagrus leiacanthus is a species of bagrid catfish endemic to Indonesia where it is known only from the Kapuas River and the Barito River basins in central Borneo .
Isoetes taiwanensis is a species of plant in the Isoetaceae family .
Valencia letourneuxi , the Corfu toothcarp , is a species of fish in the Valenciidae family .
Ancylomenes venustus , also known as the graceful anemone shrimp , is a species of shrimp which belongs to the family of the Palaemonidae .
The Johnston 's river frog or Tshiromo frog ( Amietia johnstoni ) is a species of frog in the Pyxicephalidae family .
Schistura sijuensis is a troglobitic species of stone loach endemic to India .
Titanosaurus ( meaning ' titanic lizard ' - named after the mythological ' Titans ' , deities of Ancient Greece ) is a dubious genus of sauropod dinosaurs , first described by Lydekker in 1877 .
Raphionacme is a plant genus in the family Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1842 .
Allosmaitia is a genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae . The members ( species ) are found in the Neotropic ecozone .
Drosera pedicellaris is a pygmy species of the sundew genus ( Drosera ) .
Poa litorosa is a species of tussock grass that is native to the subantarctic islands of New Zealand and Australia .
Jameson 's mamba ( Dendroaspis jamesoni ) is species of a quick , highly arboreal and highly venomous snake of the family Elapidae .
The South American gray fox ( Lycalopex griseus ) , also known as the Patagonian fox , the chilla or the gray zorro , is a species of Lycalopex , the `` false '' foxes .
Marsupites is an extinct genus of crinoid from the Cretaceous .
Pseudathyma is an Afrotropical genus of brush - footed butterflies called false sergeants .
Chaetosphaeria is a genus of fungi in the family Chaetosphaeriaceae .
Astiericeras is generally considered to be a douvillieceratid , however according to W. J. Kennedy , the genus may instead be a scaphitoid .
Trachelochismus is a genus of clingfishes endemic to the shores of New Zealand , with currently two recognized species in this genus :
Amolops marmoratus is a species of ranid frog found in Asia .
Brookesia lineata , also commonly known as the lined leaf chameleon , is a species of chameleon that is endemic to Madagascar .
Oxyropsis wrightiana is a species of armored catfish ( Loricariidae ) native to Brazil , Colombia and Peru where it occurs in the Amazon basin .
Thymops birsteini , the Patagonian lobsterette , is a species of lobster found around the coasts of South America , particularly the South Atlantic .
Metacyrba taeniola is a species of spider in the family Salticidae , the jumping spiders .
Lissocampus is a genus of pipefishes mostly native to the Indian Ocean .
Paraisobuthus is an extinct genus of scorpion from the Upper Carboniferous of Europe and North America .
Bromheadia brevifolia is a small epiphytic orchid species in the genus Bromheadia .
Laguncula pulchella is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Viviparidae .
Dictyochloropsis reticulata is a species of green algae in the Microthamniales .
Dendrochilum javieriense is a species of orchid , commonly known as Javier 's Dendrochilum .
Hohenbergia utriculosa is a species in the genus Hohenbergia .
Herminiimonas aquatilis is a bacterial species isolated from drinking water .
Borealosaurus is a genus of titanosaurian sauropod dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous of northern China .
Liopteridae is a family of wood - boring parasitoid wasps .
The Raphignathoidea is a superfamily of the Acari ( mite ) Order Trombidiformes .
Corizus hyoscyami is a species of scentless plant bug belonging to the family Rhopalidae , subfamily Rhopalinae .
Spiniphryne duhameli is a species of dreamer known from the central Pacific Ocean .
Aylacostoma chloroticum is a species of freshwater snail , aquatic gastropod mollusc in the family Thiaridae .
Oxychilus navarricus , before 2002 known as Oxychilus helveticus ( Blum , 1881 ) , is a species of small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Oxychilidae , the glass snails .
Hipposcarus harid ( also known as Longnose parrotfish or Candelamoa parrotfish ) is a species of fish from Scaridae family found on coral reefs of Indian Ocean and the Red Sea .
Citharidium ansorgii is a species of lutefish found in the Niger River basin in Nigeria and also reported from Cameroon .
Adelospondyli is an order of elongate , presumably aquatic , Carboniferous amphibians .
Lampranthus sociorum is a species of plants in the family Aizoaceae .
Hoplitoidea , formerly Hoplitaceae , is a superfamily of mostly Upper Cretaceous ammonites comprising families united by a similar suture pattern with multiple similar elements that tend to decrease in size going toward the umbilicus , at the inner edge of any whorl , and which are typically in a straight line .
Hyosciurus is a genus of rodent in the family Sciuridae endemic to Sulawesi , Indonesia .
Iris albicans , also known as the Cemetery Iris , White Cemetery Iris , or the White Flag Iris , is a species of iris which was planted on graves in Muslim regions and grows in many countries throughout the Middle East and northern Africa .
The violet black - legged robber fly , Dioctria atricapilla , is a species of robber fly in the subfamily Dasypogoninae .
Lutzomyia shannoni is a species of fly in the subfamily Phlebotominae , the phlebotomine sand flies .
Astacus pachypus , the Caspian crayfish is a species of crayfish found in the Caspian Sea , the Don river , and parts of the Black Sea and Sea of Azov , where it lives in salinities of up to 14‰.
Holarrhena is a genus of plant in the Apocynaceae family first described as a genus in 1810 .
Muscari latifolium ( broad - leaved grape hyacinth ) is a species of flowering plant of the genus of the grape hyacinths ( Muscari ) in the family ( Asparagaceae ) .
Laosepilysta flavolineata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Laosepilysta .
Gautama Thryssa ( Thryssa malabarica ) , also known as Malbar anchovy , is a species of amphidromous ray - finned fish in the family Engraulidae .
Stemmatophora honestalis is a species of snout moth in the genus Stemmatophora .
Kedestes is a genus of skippers in the family Hesperiidae . The genus is restricted to the Afrotropical ecozone .
Apateopholis ( meaning `` confusing scale '' ) is a genus of prehistoric fish .
Badister collaris is a species of ground beetle of the subfamily Licininae that can be found everywhere in Europe except for Estonia , Finland , Moldova , Romania , and various European islands .
Acanthocardia tuberculata , common name the rough cockle , is a species of saltwater clam , a cockle , a marine bivalve mollusc in the family Cardiidae .
Galium munzii ( Munz 's bedstraw ) is a species of plant in the Rubiaceae family .
Cyathea hookeri is a species of tree fern endemic to Sri Lanka , where it grows in lowland forest .
Sticholotidini is a beetle tribe in the subfamily Sticholotidinae of the family Coccinellidae ( ladybirds ) .
Austromuellera trinervia , commonly known as Mueller 's silky oak , is a species of rainforest tree of the family Proteaceae from north - eastern Queensland .
Olea hochstetteri ( East African olive , black ironwood ) is a species of tree of the Oleaceae family , often considered a subspecies of Olea capensis .
Plectroctena is a Afrotropical genus of ants , with most species occurring in the rainforest zones of West and Central Africa .
Mercuria similis is a species of small freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .
Setaria dielsii , commonly known as Diels ' Pigeon Grass , is a species of grass native to Australia .
Calliostoma leanum , common name the pretty mouth , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliostomatidae .
Pectocarya pusilla is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common names little combseed and little pectocarya .
Aseroe floriformis is a species of fungus in the stinkhorn family Phallaceae .
Edithcolea is a monotypic genus with a single species Edithcolea grandis ( Persian carpet flower ) .
Salarias ceramensis , the Seram blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western central Pacific ocean .
The Green - flowered Cymbidium ( Cymbidium chloranthum ) is a species of orchid .
Achalinus jinggangensis , commonly known as Zong 's odd - scaled snake , is a species of colubrid snake .
Gastropila fumosa is a species of puffball in the family Agaricaceae .
Phragmipedium reticulatum is a species of orchid ranging from southern Ecuador to Peru .
Achatinella apexfulva is a species of colorful , tropical , tree - living , air - breathing , land snail , an arboreal pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Achatinellidae .
Astragalus bernardinus , known by the common name San Bernardino milkvetch , is a species of milkvetch .
Saltugilia latimeri is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name Latimer 's woodland gilia .
Epischidia caesariella is a species of snout moth in the genus Epischidia .
Cyrtalastor is a monotypic Afrotropical genus of potter wasps .
Geraea viscida is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name sticky geraea , or sticky desertsunflower .
Antrocarcinus petrosus is a species of crab in the family Xanthidae , the only species in the genus Antrocarcinus .
Sarcophaga peregrina ( synonym Boettcherisca peregrina ) is a species of flesh fly belonging to the family Sarcophagidae .
Penicillium westlingii is a species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from soil near Poznan in Poland .
Marmyan is an extinct genus of scale insect , containing a single species , Marmyan barbarae and unplaced in any coccid family .
Parischnogaster mellyi is a medium - sized species of a hover wasp in the family Vespidae .
Orthotylus salicorniae is a species of bug from the Miridae family that is endemic to Canary Islands .
The Simuliini are a tribe of black flies , and contains huge species numbers , mostly in the genus Simulium .
Oberthür 's grizzled skipper ( Pyrgus armoricanus ) is a species of skipper ( family Hesperiidae ) .
Coleia is an extinct genus of decapods in the group Polychelida that lived from the Late Triassic to the Late Jurassic .
Nanorana ercepeae ( common names : torrent paa frog , R.C.P. 's paa frog ) is a species of frog in the Dicroglossidae family .
Palisota is a genus of plant in family Commelinaceae , first described in 1828 .
Macronyssidae is a family of parasitic mites in the order Mesostigmata .
Burkholderia gladioli is a species of aerobic gram - negative rod - shaped bacteria that causes disease in both humans and plants .
The Rio Suno robber frog , Strabomantis cornutus , is a species of frog in the Craugastoridae family .
Californiulus yosemitensis is species of cylindrical millipede in the family Paeromopodidae that is found in the Western United States : predominantly in the Sierra Nevada of California but also extending into southeastern Oregon and parts of Nevada .
Oligolepis acutipennis , the Sharptail goby , is a species of goby native to marine , freshwater and brackish waters along the coasts of Indo - West Pacific region .
Carabus torosus spinolae is a subspecies of black - coloured beetle from Carabidae family , that is endemic to Turkey .
Haemulon is a genus of fish in the grunt family known as the scaled - fin grunts .
The Malagasy paradise flycatcher ( Terpsiphone mutata ) is a species of bird in the Monarchidae family .
Carabus gigas is a species of beetles belonging to the Carabidae family .
Excidobates is a genus of poison dart frogs endemic to the Marañón River drainage in Peru and Ecuador , South America .
Amorpha fruticosa is a species of flowering plant in the legume family ( Fabaceae ) known by several common names , including desert false indigo , false indigo - bush , and bastard indigobush .
Albertonectes is an extinct genus of elasmosaurid plesiosaur known from the Late Cretaceous ( middle upper Campanian stage ) Bearpaw Formation of Alberta , Canada .
Amphiprion barberi , is a species of anemonefish that is found in the is found in the western Pacific Ocean ..
Weismanniola is a genus of moths in the Sesiidae family , containing only one species Weismanniola agdistiformis , which is found in southern Russia and western Kazakhstan .
The Analgoidea are a superfamily of the Acarina ( mite ) order Sarcoptiformes .
Thriambeutis coryphaea is a species of moths of the Heliodinidae family .
Monadenia fidelis , common name the Pacific sideband , is a medium - sized species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Monadeniidae .
Castilleja schizotricha is a species of Indian paintbrush known by the common name splithair Indian paintbrush .
Veluticeps is a small genus of wood - rot fungi characterized by the production of resupinate to bracket shaped , perennial , tough , brown fruitbodies , that blacken when KOH solution is applied , and with a smooth to warted or cracked fertile undersurface .
Frontilabrus caeruleus is a species of wrasse native to the Indian Ocean waters around the Maldives .
Orlaya is a genus of flowering plant in the Apiaceae family , with between 1 and 11 species .
Carex backii , commonly known as back 's sedge , is a species of sedge ( Carex ) in the section Phyllostachyae .
Urophycis is a genus of phycid hakes .
Perittopus breddini is a species of Riffle bug from Indonesia .
Laetesia mollita is a species of sheet weaver found in Western Australia .
Coreopsis nuecensis ( crown tickseed ) is a North American plant species of the tickseeds in sunflower family .
Lophonectes is a genus of small lefteye flounders found in the southwestern Pacific Ocean off Australia and New Zealand .
Pila ampullacea , is a species of freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Ampullariidae , the apple snails .
The Malagasy coucal or Madagascar coucal ( Centropus toulou ) is a species of cuckoo in the family Cuculidae .
Sphaerocarpos drewei is a species of liverwort in the family Sphaerocarpaceae .
Dermomurex goldsteini , common name Goldstein 's trophon , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Lankascincus taprobanensis , also known as the smooth Lanka skink or Ceylon tree skink , is a species of skink endemic to the island of Sri Lanka .
Epinephelus flavocaeruleus , commonly called blue - and - yellow grouper , is a species of marine fish in the family Serranidae .
Sticharium is a genus of clinids native to the coastal waters of southern Australia .
Florestina tripteris , the sticky florestina , is a North American species of flowering plants in the sunflower family .
The Coqui francolin ( Peliperdix coqui ) is a species of bird in the Phasianidae family .
Amblydoras gonzalezi is a species of thorny catfish found in Colombia and Venezuela .
Lichenostigma is a genus fungi .
Aspredinichthys tibicen , the Tenbarbed banjo , is a species of banjo catfish found in coastal brackish waters and coastal rivers in South America from Venezuela to Brazil including the island nation of Trinidad and Tobago .
Semibalanus balanoides is a common and widespread boreo - arctic species of acorn barnacle .
Astragalus rattanii is a species of milkvetch known by the common name Rattan 's milkvetch .
Thyreus ceylonicus is a species of bee belonging to the family Apidae in subfamily Apinae .
Nemestrinidae , or tangle - veined flies is a family of flies in the superfamily Nemestrinoidea , closely related to Acroceridae .
Mesoplasma is a genus of bacteria belonging to the class Mollicutes .
Tulerpeton is a fossil of an extinct genus of Devonian labyrinthodont that was found in the Tula Region of Russia at a site named Andreyevka .
Aeshna crenata , the Siberian hawker , is a species of dragonfly in the family Aeshnidae .
Battus lycidas is a species of butterfly in the family Papilionidae native to the Neotropic ecozone .
Neuwiedia zollingeri is a species of orchid that native to Hainan , Hong Kong , Yunnan , Borneo , Sumatra , Java , Bali , Malaysia , Singapore , Thailand , Vietnam .
Heliopsis annua is a species of flowering plant in the family sunflower family .
Chenopodiastrum is a genus of herbaceous flowering plants in the family Amaranthaceae .
Ixora coccinea ( also known as jungle geranium , flame of the woods or jungle flame ) is a species of flowering plant in the Rubiaceae family .
Rhomaleodus is an extinct genus of basal selachimorph elasmobranchii cartilaginous fish known from the Middle Triassic ( Anisian stage ) of Bulgaria .
Monodilepas diemenensis is species of small sea snail , a keyhole limpet , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets and slit limpets .
Kalotermes flavicollis , the ' Yellownecked dry - wood termite ' , is a species of ' Dampwood termites ' belonging to the family Kalotermitidae , one of the most primitive families of termites .
Astragalus chrysostachys is a species of milkvetch in the family Fabaceae .
Megalomycter teevani is a species of flabby whalefish found in the waters of the Atlantic Ocean near Bermuda at depths of around 1,647 metres ( 5,404 ft ) .
Bacillus rossius ( Rossi , 1788 ) is a species of stick insect , common in Europe .
Zygodontomys brunneus , also known as the brown zygodont , brown cane mouse , or Colombian cane mouse , is a rodent species in the genus Zygodontomys of tribe Oryzomyini .
Allium rupicola is a species of onion found in Israel , Turkey , Lebanon and Syria .
Ohmyia omya is a species of South American hoverfly .
Calliscelio is a parasitoid wasp genus in the family Platygastridae .
Phrynoponera bequaerti is an Afrotropical species of ant in the subfamily Ponerinae .
Penicillium araracuarense is a fungus species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from soil from the Colombian Amazon forest
Remya montgomeryi is a rare species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Kalalau Valley remya .
Grant 's bluebill ( Spermophaga poliogenys ) is a species of estrildid finch found in forests in central Africa .
Papilio longimacula , is a species of butterfly in the family Papilionidae .
Agyneta trifurcata is a species of sheet weaver found in Finland and Russia .
Vaccinium cespitosum , ( also , caespitosum ) , the dwarf bilberry , is a species of flowering shrub in the genus Vaccinium , which includes blueberries , huckleberries , and cranberries .
Danio erythromicron , often known as emerald dwarf rasbora , is a species of cyprinid fish which is endemic to Inle Lake in Myanmar .
Elates ransonnettii , the Dwarf flathead , is a species of flathead native to the western Pacific Ocean where it is found over sandy bottoms at depths of from 5 to 53 metres ( 16 to 174 ft ) .
Hericium erinaceus can be mistaken for other species of Hericium , all popular edibles , which grow across the same range .
Metrius contractus is a species of bombardier beetle .
Gnathophausia zoea is a species of lophogastrid crustacean .
Cycloclasticus pugetii is a species of bacteria , named in honor of Peter Puget .
Trifolium andinum is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name Intermountain clover .
Neopycnodonte cochlear is a species of marine bivalve mollusks belonging to the family Gryphaeidae .
Savignia superstes is a species of sheet weaver found in France .
Oncaea venusta is a species of copepod with a cosmopolitan distribution , but lacking from the Arctic Ocean .
Propupa hoffeinsorum is the only species in the genus Propupa , and was described from a fossil found in Baltic amber in 2006 .
Prunum cineraceum is a species of gastropod from the Marginellidae family .
Minous monodactylus ( Grey stingfish ) ( Bloch & J. G. Schneider , 1801 ) is a species of stingfish found in the Indo - Pacific particularly Red Sea , East Africa , Indonesia and Japan .
Craesus septentrionalis , the flat - legged tenthred or birch sawfly , is a species of insect in the order Hymenoptera , the suborder Symphyta and the family Tenthredinidae .
Megaloptera is an order of insects .
Iranecio is a genus of flowering plants in the sunflower family , native to the eastern Mediterranean east to the Caucasus .
Taphrina is a fungal genus within the Ascomycota that causes leaf and catkin curl diseases and witch 's brooms of certain flowering plants .
Cotula australis is a species of plant in the daisy family known by the common names Bachelor 's Buttons , annual buttonweed , southern waterbuttons and Australian waterbuttons .
Jatropha dioica is a species of flowering plant in the spurge family , Euphorbiaceae , that is native to Texas in the United States as well as Mexico as far south as Oaxaca .
Protolepis is an extinct genus of butterfly from the Upper Jurassic of Karatau , Kazakhstan .
Lupinus odoratus is a species of lupine known by the common name Mojave lupine .
