Musa tuberculata is a tropical Asian species of plant in the banana family native to the Malesian region ( Brunei ) .
Conus malacanus , common name the Malacca cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Idiopidonia pedalis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Idiopidonia .
Dugesia sicula is a species of dugesiid triclad that lives in freshwater bodies of the Mediterranean Basin , where it is widely distributed .
Microgadus , the Tomcods , is a genus of cods .

Raphiglossoides is a small genus of afrotropical potter wasps known from South Africa .
Astacoides is a genus of freshwater crayfish endemic to Madagascar .
Spirembolus is a genus of sheet weaver spiders that was described by Ralph V. Chamberlin in 1920 .
Clinus taurus , the Bull klipfish , is a species of clinid that occurs in subtropical waters of the Atlantic Ocean from Namibia to South Africa where it occurs in the tidal and subtidal zones .
Orconectes sloanii is a species of crayfish in the family Cambaridae , endemic to Indiana and Ohio .

Poraniopsis inflata , the spiny sea star , is a species of starfish in the family Poraniidae .
Sphaerocoryphe is a genus of trilobite that lived from the middle Ordovician to the Silurian .
Allium longistylum is a species of wild onion native to Korea and northern China ( Hebei , Inner Mongolia , Shanxi ) .
Rhododendron lutescens ( Chinese : 黄花杜鹃 ) is a rhododendron species native to Guizhou , Sichuan , and Yunnan , China , where it grows at altitudes of 1700 - -2000 meters .
Nicotiana benthamiana is a close relative of tobacco and species of Nicotiana indigenous to Australia .
Cheng 's jird , Meriones chengi , is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Hamaticolax unisagittatus is a species of parasitic copepod belonging to the family Bomolochidae .
Scissurella ornata , common name the ornate slit shell , is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Scissurellidae , the little slit snails .
Gekko canaensis is a species in Gekko genus , Gekkonidae family , first found from Southern Vietnam in 2011 .
Pseudolechriops is a genus of Central American weevils alternatively placed in the subfamily Conoderinae or Baridinae .
Lipaesthesius leeanus is a species of crab in the family Xanthidae , the only species in the genus Lipaesthesius .
Rhododendron phaeochrysum ( 栎叶杜鹃 ) is a rhododendron species native to western Sichuan , southeastern Xizang , and northwestern Yunnan in China , where it grows at altitudes of 3000 - -4800 meters .

Eleutherococcus is a genus of 38 species of thorny shrubs and trees in the family Araliaceae .

Chaetocladus is a non - calcifying genus of unicellular green algae known from the Upper Silurian .
Dioscorea elephantipes ( elephant 's foot or Hottentot bread ; syn . Testudinaria elephantipes ) , is a species of flowering plant in the genus Dioscorea of the family Dioscoreaceae , native to south west South Africa , but also rediscovered in Northern Cape Province by an expedition collecting seeds for the Millennium Seed Bank Project .
Costasiellidae is a taxonomic family of small to minute sacoglossan sea slugs .
Kassina senegalensis , the Senegal Running Frog , is a species of frog in the Hyperoliidae family .
The Seram mountain pigeon ( Gymnophaps stalkeri ) is a species of bird in the family Columbidae .

Newcombia philippiana was a species of land snail , a gastropod in the Achatinellidae family .
Formica sanguinea , or blood - red ant , is a species of slave - maker ant in the genus Formica characterized by the ability to secrete formic acid .
Hunnemannia is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the poppy family Papaveraceae , containing the single species Hunnemannia fumariifolia ( tulip poppy or Mexican tulip poppy ) native to the highlands of Mexico .

Hemicentetes is a genus of tenrec with two species , present on the island of Madagascar .
Hieracium piloselloides is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name tall hawkweed .

Cucurbita palmata is a species of flowering plant in the squash family known by the common names coyote melon and coyote gourd .
Paguristes cadenati , the red reef hermit crab or scarlet hermit crab , is a small ( about 3 centimetres or 1.2 inches across ) species of hermit crab with a bright red body and yellow eyestalks that lives in the Caribbean Sea .
Farlowella jauruensis is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil where it occurs in the upper Paraguay River basin .
Zanthoxylum dipetalum is a rare species of tree in the citrus family and in the same genus as Szechuan pepper .
Sardinella atricauda ( Bleeker 's blacktip sardinella ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Sardinella from the western Pacific .
Hackelia californica is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common name California stickseed .
Rhytidiadelphus triquetrus , the big shaggy - moss or rough goose neck moss , is species of moss in the family Hylocomiaceae .
Globitermes is a genus of termite .
Telescopus , the Old World catsnakes , is a genus of 12 species of mildly venomous opisthoglyphous snakes in the Colubridae family .
The genus Pygoscelis ( `` rump - legged '' ) contains three living species of penguins collectively known as `` the brush - tailed penguins '' .
Berberis standleyi is a shrub in the Berberidaceae described as a species in 1952 .
Ammotheidae is a family of picnogonids .
Amoebophyra ( or Amoebophrya ) is a genus of dinoflagellate .
Trochulus villosus is a species of small , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Hygromiidae , the hairy snails and their allies .
Apodocreedia vanderhorsti , the Longfin burrower , is a species of sandburrower native to the Indian Ocean coast of southern Africa where it can be found from Delagoa Bay , Mozambique to Durban , South Africa .
Selenophanes is a genus of Neotropical butterfly .
Gnaphalium norvegicum , the highland cudweed or Norwegian arctic cudweed , is a European species of plants in the sunflower family .
Streptomyces aureofaciens is a species of Streptomyces , and the source of many tetracycline antibiotics .
Gratiola amphiantha is a rare species of flowering plant known by the common names little amphianthus , pool sprite and snorkelwort .
Pavoclinus myae , Mya 's klipfish , is a species of clinid found from East London to Algoa Bay along the coast of South Africa where it can be found in the subtidal zone from near the surface to 3 metres ( 9.8 ft ) .
Stenostelma is a genus of plants in the Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1894 .
Planchonia careya is a tree species in the family Lecythidaceae .
Acourtia runcinata , common name Featherleaf desertpeony , or desert paeonia , is a North American species of plants in the sunflower family .
Hazhenia is an extinct genus of therocephalian therapsid from the Early Triassic of China , of which Hazhenia concava is the only species .
Nephelomys albigularis , also known as the white - throated oryzomys or Tomes 's rice rat , is a species of rodent in the genus Nephelomys of family Cricetidae .
Ancistrus leucostictus is a species of armored catfish native to Guyana where it is found in the Essequibo River basin .
Hypna clytemnestra , common name jazzy leafwing , marbled leafwing or silver - studded leafwing , is a species of Neotropical butterflies belonging to the Nymphalidae family , Charaxinae subfamily .
Dendropoma corallinaceus , common name the colonial worm shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Vermetidae , the worm snails or worm shells .
The only known species is Columbiadoria hallii , native to the northwestern United States ( States of Washington and Oregon ) .
Tachina ursina is a species of fly in the genus Tachina of the family Tachinidae that can be found in such European countries as Austria , Benelux , Czech Republic , France , Germany , Hungary , Italy , Poland , Romania , Scandinavia ( except Norway ) , Spain , Switzerland , and Ukraine .
Banksia violacea , commonly known as violet banksia , is a species of shrub or tree in the plant genus Banksia ( family Proteaceae ) .
Blennosperma bakeri is a rare species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names Baker 's stickyseed and Sonoma sunshine .
Gymnobela homaeotata is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Raphitomidae .
Jasus frontalis , known as the Juan Fernández rock lobster , is a species of spiny lobster in the genus Jasus , found around the Juan Fernández and Desventuradas Islands in the south - eastern Pacific Ocean .
Madieae is a tribe of flowering plants in the sunflower family , Asteraceae .
Theiophytalia is a genus of herbivorous iguanodontian dinosaur from the lower Cretaceous period ( Aptian - Albian stage , about 112 million years ago ) of Colorado , USA .
Francoa appendiculata is a species of the Melianthaceae family which consists of herbs endemic to Chile .
Aegialomys is a genus of oryzomyine rodents from the lowlands and mountains of western Peru and Ecuador , including the Galápagos Islands .
Acacia sakalava is a species of Acacia that is endemic to Madagascar .
Lophostemon suaveolens is a tree species , also known as swamp mahogany , swamp box or swamp turpentine , of the botanical family Myrtaceae It grows to a medium - sized tree , native in Australia and New Guinea .
Arabis lemmonii is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name Lemmon 's rockcress .
Gomphodontosuchus is a genus created to have described the species Gomphodontosuchus brasiliensis .
Clinostomus funduloides ( commonly known as the rosyside dace ) is a species of cyprinid fish .
Rhodocollybia fodiens is a species of fungus in the Marasmiaceae family of mushrooms .
Penstemon pahutensis is a species of penstemon known by the common name Pahute Mesa beardtongue , or simply Pahute beardtongue .
Oryzias is a genus of ricefishes .
Mimomyagrus pfanneri is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimomyagrus .
Renanthera matutina , common name Early Blooming Renanthera , is a species of terrestrial orchid in the genus Renanthera , belonghing to the Orchidaceae family .
Genyatremus luteus , the Torroto grunt , is a species of grunt native to the Atlantic coast of South America from Colombia to Brazil .
Paraclinus tanygnathus , the Longjaw blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny native to the Pacific coast of Mexico including the Gulf of California where it can be found at depths of from very shallow waters to about 14 metres ( 46 ft ) .
Crocus aleppicus is a species of flowering plant in the genus Crocus of the family Iridaceae , that is found from West Syria to Jordan .
Aenigmastropheus is an extinct genus of protorosaurid archosauromorph reptile known from the middle Late Permian Usili Formation of Songea District , southern Tanzania .
Benthobia tryonii is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pseudolividae .
Papilio weymeri is a species of swallowtail butterfly in the Papilioninae subfamily that is endemic to Papua New Guinea where it is found on Los Negros and Manus Islands .
Vitis menghaiensis is a species of climbing vine in the grape family native to China .
Cytora pannosa is a species of very small land snails with an operculum , terrestrial gastropod molluscs in the family Pupinidae .
The Xerinae comprise a subfamily of squirrels , many of which are highly terrestrial .
Sphagesaurus is an extinct genus of sphagesaurid notosuchian crocodylomorph from the Late Cretaceous of southwest São Paulo , southern Brazil .
Orthotylus creticus is a species of bug from a family of Miridae that is endemic to Crete .
Chalarodon is a genus of Malagasy terrestrial iguanian lizard .
Echinops spinosissimus is a European species of plants in the thistle tribe within the sunflower family .
Isatis tinctoria is classified as an invasive species in parts of the United States .
Codium tomentosum is a species of green seaweed in the family Codiaceae .
Vibrio mimicus is a Vibrio species that mimics V. cholerae .
Puerphorus is a genus of moth in the Pterophoridae family containing only one species , Puerphorus olbiadactylus , which is known from Yemen , Afghanistan , Algeria , Iran , Israel , Jordan , Lebanon , Morocco , Syria , Tunisia , southern Europe and Turkey .
Hemipristis serra is an extinct species of weasel shark which existed during the Miocene epoch .
Acaua exotica is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Acaua .
Radopholus similis is a species of nematode known commonly as the burrowing nematode .
Coahuilix is a genus of small freshwater snails that have an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Cochliopidae .
Cyphochlaena is a genus of plants in the grass family native to certain islands in the Indian Ocean .
Pelargonium peltatum is a species of pelargonium known by the common names ivy - leaf geranium and cascading geranium .
Marmots are large squirrels in the genus Marmota , of which there are 15 species .
Paphiopedilum vietnamense is a species of orchid found from Thái Nguyên Province in Vietnam .
Pristimantis unistrigatus ( common name : striped robber frog , in Spanish cutín de Quito ) is a species of frog in the Craugastoridae family .
Hypsibarbus suvattii is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Hypsibarbus .
Carduus is a genus of flowering plants in the aster family , Asteraceae , and the tribe Cynareae , the thistles .
Tulipa humilis is a species of flowering plant in the lily family , found in Syria , Lebanon , Israel , Turkey , Iran , and the North Caucasus region of Russia .
Cupiennius is a genus of wandering spiders , known by the common name banana spiders , found from Mexico to northwestern South America , and on some Caribbean islands .
Middendorf 's vole ( Microtus middendorffi ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Omobranchus hikkaduwensis is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western central Pacific and eastern Indian ocean .
Stemonitis is a distinctive genus of slime moulds found throughout the world ( except Antarctica ) .
Sargochromis is a genus of haplochromine cichlids native to East Africa .
The Calamariinae are a subfamily of colubrid snakes which are found throughout Asia .
Cantharidella beachportensis , common name the Beachport top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Anthurium subcoerulescens is a species of plant in the Araceae family endemic to Ecuador but threatened by habitat loss .
Zabrus humeralis is a species of ground beetle in the Epomidozabrus subgenus that is endemic to Portugal .
Lepturobosca virens is a species of beetle in the longhorn beetle family , that can be found in Europe and Russia .
Rasbora rubrodorsalis is a species of cyprinid fish native to southeast Asia where it occurs in the basins of the Mekong , Chao Phraya and Mae Klong rivers .
Phyllomedusa oreades is a species of frog in the Hylidae family , endemic to the Brazilian savanna .
Hyloxalus delatorreae is a species of frog in the Dendrobatidae family .
Planetetherium is an extinct genus of herbivorous gliding mammal ( like Colugo ) endemic to North America during the Paleogene living from 56.8 - -55.4 mya , existing for approximately 1.4 million years .
Pouteria altissima is a species of plant in the Sapotaceae family , and a source of anigre hardwood .
Latiscopidae is a family of Mesozoic Era amphibian Temnospondyli .
Antennaria marginata is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name whitemargin pussytoes .
Pistacia is a genus of flowering plants in the cashew family , Anacardiaceae .
Amorphoscelis singaporana is a species of praying mantis found in Singapore , India , Sumatra , and Thailand .
Homalopoma draperi , common name Draper 's dwarf turban , is a species of small sea snail with calcareous opercula , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Colloniidae .
Gorzula 's Amazon tree frog , Tepuihyla rimarum , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to Venezuela .
Sinhalestes orientalis , the emerald Sri Lanka spreadwing , is a monotypic species of damselfly in the family Lestidae .
Chamaebatiaria is a monotypic genus of aromatic shrub in the rose family containing the single species Chamaebatiaria millefolium , which is known by the common names fern bush and desert sweet .
Paraclinus naeorhegmis , the Surf blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny endemic to the Bahamas where it occurs in eroded limestone shorelines .
Eumorphus alboguttatus is a species of beetles belonging to the family Endomychidae .
Aristida purpurea is a species of grass native to North America which is known by the common name purple three - awn .
Siphonalia pfefferi , common name Pfeffer 's Whelk , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Buccinidae , the true whelks .
Paraclinus cingulatus , the Coral blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny native to the Atlantic Ocean and the Caribbean Sea from southern Florida to Honduras and through the Greater Antilles .
Pogogyne floribunda is a species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common names profuseflower mesamint and profuse - flowered pogogyne .
Argyroxiphium grayanum , commonly known as the greensword , is a species of flowering plant in the sunflower family , Asteraceae , and a member of the silversword alliance , a group of over 50 species which are diverse in morphology and habitat but are genetically closely related .
Batophora oerstedii is a species of algae in the family Dasycladaceae .
Mycena luxaeterna , common name eternal light mushroom , is a species of fungus in the Mycenaceae family .
Xotodon is an extinct genus of toxodontid mammal that lived during the late Pliocene in South America .
Dioryctria okanaganella is a species of snout moth in the genus Dioryctria .
Lonicera japonica , the Japanese honeysuckle or suikazura ( スイカズラ／吸い葛 in Japanese ; jinyinhua in Chinese ; 忍冬 in Chinese and Japanese ) is a species of honeysuckle native to eastern Asia including China , Japan and Korea .
Scinax altae is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to Panama .
Suaeda californica is a rare species of flowering plant in the amaranth family known by the common name California seablite .
Vitex parviflora is a species of plant in the Verbenaceae family , known as smallflower chastetree , or molave tree .
Dendropsophus sarayacuensis ( common name : Shreve 's Sarayacu treefrog or Clown tree frog ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .
Calyptrocalyx elegans is a palm species in the genus Calyptrocalyx found in Papua New Guinea and the nearby Maluku Islands .
Potentilla johnstonii is a rare species of flowering plant in the rose family known by the common name sagebrush cinquefoil .
Tmarus is a genus of crab spiders , comprising the following species :
Salix purpurea ( purple willow purpleosier willow or purple osier ) is a species of willow native to most of Europe and western Asia north to the British Isles , Poland , and the Baltic States .
Fritillaria cirrhosa , common name Yellow Himalayan Fritillary , is an Asian species of herbaceous plant in the lily family , native to China ( Gansu , Qinghai , Sichuan , Tibet , Yunnan ) , the Indian Subcontinent ( Nepal , Pakistan , India , Bhutan ) , and Myanmar .
Bauria is an extinct genus of the suborder therocephalia .
Oryctocephalus is a genus of trilobite known from the Middle Cambrian Burgess Shale .
Sisymbrium altissimum is a species of Sisymbrium .
Acentria ephemerella ( formerly A. nivea ) is a species of grass moth known as the watermilfoil moth or water veneer .
Stegenodes ruber is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Stegenodes .
Sickius is a genus of tarantulas .
Cryptothecia is a genus of white to greenish crustose lichens that grow on bark , wood , or leaves .
Arenga is a genus of palms , native to Southeast Asia , southern China , New Guinea , and northern Australia .
Philobdella floridana is a species of leech that lives in the most southern parts of the United States .
Sphodromantis centralis , common name African mantis or Central African mantis , is a species of praying mantis from Africa .
It was described by Edward Meyrick in 1929 , and contains the single species Hebdomactis crystallodes .
Dolloidraco longedorsalis is a species of barbeled plunderfish native to the marine waters around Antarctica where it is found at depths of from 203 to 1,145 metres ( 666 to 3,757 ft ) .
Dicranota is a genus of flies in the family Pediciidae .
Hoplostethus fedorovi , is a small deep - sea fish species belonging to the slimehead family ( Trachichthyidae ) .
Sturisoma panamense is a species of armored catfish native to Colombia , Ecuador and Panama .
Cyclamen purpurascens ( Alpine , European or purple cyclamen ) is a species of flowering plant in the genus Cyclamen of the family Primulaceae , native to central Europe , northern Italy , and Slovenia .
Bayerotrochus westralis , commonly known as `` Australia 's split shell '' , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pleurotomariidae .
Orthetrum julia , the Julia skimmer is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae .
Veitchia lepidota is a plant species endemic to the Solomon Islands in the Pacific Ocean .
Acropora millepora is a species of branching stony coral native to the western Indo - Pacific where it is found in shallow water from the east coast of Africa to the coasts of Japan and Australia .
Stephanodoria is a genus of Mexican plants in the aster tribe within the sunflower family .
Hypleurochilus caudovittatus , the Zebratail blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western central Atlantic ocean , around the United States .
Isolepis cernua ( syn . Scirpus cernuus ) is a species of flowering plant in the sedge family known by the common names low bulrush , slender club - rush , tufted clubrush , and fiberoptic grass .
Grevillea ilicifolia , commonly known as holly grevillea , is a species of the plant genus Grevillea .
Neotamandua is an extinct genus of anteaters that lived in the Miocene to Pliocene in South America .
Mochokus brevis is a species of upside - down catfish native to the Nile and Chad Basins .
Tentaoculus granulatus is a species of sea snail , deep - sea limpet , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cocculinidae .
Physokentia dennisii is a species of palm tree in the family Arecaceae .
Adiantum tenerum , common name Brittle Maidenhair Fern , is a species of maidenhair fern belonging to the family Pteridaceae .
Agapanthia persicola is a species of beetle in the Lamiinae subfamily , that is endemic to Iran .
Calosoma investigator is a species of ground beetle belonging to the genus Calosoma and the subgenus Charmosta .
Lithops dorotheae is a species of Lithops found in South Africa .
Lampropeltis webbi is a species of king snake endemic to Mexico .
Ctenopristis is a prehistoric genus of saw fish whose fossils are found in rocks dating from the Maastrichtian stage .
Ichthyocladius is a genus of chironomid midges that belongs to the subfamily Orthocladiinae described by Fittkau based on one species , Ichthyocladius neotropicus , from Peru , though some other species were recognised , the lack of knowledge did not allow their description .
It contains a single species Pseudobornia ursina , and is the earliest fossil assigned with certainty to the Sphenopsida .
The Little Blue , ( Amphiallagma parvum ) is a species of damselfly in the family Coenagrionidae .
Trematocranus microstoma , known in the aquarium trade as the `` Haplochromis placodon pointed head '' is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is found in shallow waters close to shore , apparently showing a preference for areas with plentiful vegetation .
Liodon is a genus of mosasaur from the Late Cretaceous .
Pristidactylus alvaroi is a species of lizard in the family Iguanidae , with the common name Alvaro 's Lizard .
Guichenotia is a genus of about 16 species of flowering plant which are endemic to the south west of Western Australia .
Pundt 's tuco - tuco ( Ctenomys pundti ) is a species of rodent in the family Ctenomyidae .
Pheropsophus jessoensis , colloquially known as the Asian bombardier beetle ( miidera beetle in Japan ) is a species of ground beetle from Japan , North and South Korea , and the province of Yunnan , China .
Reflectopallium papillatum , is a species of air - breathing land slug , specifically a leaf - veined slug , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Athoracophoridae .
Dizoniopsis aspicienda is a species of sea snail , a gastropod in the family Cerithiopsidae , which is known from the Strait of Gibraltar .
Pistosaurus is an extinct genus of aquatic sauropterygian reptile closely related to plesiosaurs .
Apha arisana is allied to Apha horishana and both species were described as subspecies of Apha tychoona by Matsumura in 1927 .
Protosphagnum nervatum is the only known species of order Protosphagnales .
Oncidium hastilabium is a species of orchid found from northwestern Venezuela to western South America .
Rosenblattia robusta is a species of deepwater cardinalfish found around the world in southern temperate waters , where it occurs at depths from 700 to 2,000 m ( 2,300 to 6,600 ft ) .
The blacklip abalone , Haliotis rubra , is an Australian species of large , edible sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Haliotidae , the abalones .
Trachischium fuscum , commonly known as the blackbelly worm - eating snake or the Darjeeling slender snake , is a species of colubrid snake , which is endemic to Asia .
Zalipais benthicola is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Skeneidae .
Indorana is an extinct genus of lissamphibians which existed in what is now India during the Early Eocene .
Islamia trichoniana is a species of small freshwater snail with a gill and an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusc or micromollusc in the family Hydrobiidae .
Candida keroseneae is a species of yeast in the genus Candida , family Saccharomycetaceae .
Akodon boliviensis , also known as the Bolivian grass mouse or Bolivian akodont , is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Phyllophorella queenslandica is a species of katydid described in 2009 .
Buddleja subcapitata is a small shrub discovered in 2003 by Liu and Peng in Sichuan , China , growing alongside a road bordering forest in Yanbian County at an elevation of 2,200 m. First described in 2004 , this putative species was not included in Leeuwenberg 's study of Asiatic and African buddleja published in 1979 .
Crematogaster tanakai species of ant in the subfamily Myrmicinae .
Longitarsus angorensis is a species of beetle in the subfamily Galerucinae that is endemic to Ankara , Turkey .
Ascobulla fragilis is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod sacoglossan mollusk in the family Volvatellidae .
Lobelia chinensis , commonly known as the Chinese Lobelia , Herba Lobellae Chinensis , aze mushiro , and mizo kakushi , is a species of flowering plant in the family Campanulaceae .
Aulacopleura is a genus of proetid trilobite that lived from the Middle Ordovician to the Middle Devonian .
Salmo ohridanus , also known by the local name as the belvica , is a species of freshwater salmonid fish , endemic to Lake Ohrid in Albania and Macedonia .
Dipterocarpus sarawakensis , locally called the Sarawak keruing , is a species of tree in the family Dipterocarpaceae , found in peninsular Malaysia and Borneo .
Sinadoxa corydalifolia is the only species in the monotypic plant genus Sinadoxa , in the family Adoxaceae .
Crescentia cujete , commonly known as the Calabash Tree , is species of flowering plant that is native to Central and South America .
Hoplolatilus marcosi , the redback sand tilefish , is a species of tilefish native to the western central Pacific Ocean .
Myotis midastactus is a golden - coloured species of vesper bat from South America , where it occurs in Bolivia and Paraguay .
Pelargonium graveolens is an uncommon Pelargonium species native to the Cape Provinces and the Northern Provinces of South Africa , Zimbabwe and Mozambique .
Alburnus atropatenae is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Alburnus .
Menodora spinescens is a species of flowering plant in the olive family known by the common name spiny menodora .
Aethalida is a genus of tiger moths in the Erebidae family that occur in the Sundaland and Philippines .
Monardella viridis is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the mint family which is endemic to California .
Cirsium neomexicanum is a North American species of thistle known by the common names New Mexico thistle , powderpuff thistle , lavender thistle , foss thistle and desert thistle .
Dendrochirus brachypterus , known commonly as the shortfin turkeyfish or dwarf lionfish among other vernacular names , is a species of marine fish in the family Scorpaenidae .
Heliconiophaga cranei is a species of tachinid flies in the genus Heliconiophaga of the family Tachinidae .
Pinus mugo , known as creeping pine , dwarf mountainpine , mugo pine , mountain pine , scrub mountain pine or Swiss mountain pine , or is a species of conifer , native to high elevation habitats from southwestern to Central Europe .
Caudinidae is a family of sea cucumbers , marine animals with elongated bodies , leathery skins and tentacles that are found on the sea floor .
Strumigenys inopinata , is a species in the genus Strumigenys .
Austropeucedanum oreopansil is a species of flowering plant in the Apiaceae , the only member of the genus Austropeucedanum .
Tritemnodon was a genus of hyaeanodontid which lived 54 - 38 million years ago .
Anaea aidea , commonly known as the Tropical Leafwing , is a species of brush - footed butterfly ( family Nymphalidae ) in the subfamily Charaxinae .
Pseudosquilla ciliata , the common mantis shrimp , is a species of mantis shrimp , known by common names including rainbow mantis shrimp and false mantis shrimp .
Diogenes pugilator is a species of hermit crab , sometimes called the small hermit crab or south - claw hermit crab , with a maximum carapace length of 5.45 mm ( 0.215 in ) .
Jaltomata weberbaueri is a plant species native to Peru .
Mimulus viscidus is a species of monkeyflower known by the common name sticky monkeyflower .
Asiadodis is a genus of praying mantises native to Asia and possessing common names such as shield mantis , hood mantis ( or hooded mantis ) , and leaf mantis ( or leafy mantis ) because of their extended , leaf - like thoraxes .
The Sumba hornbill is a monogamous species .
Listriolobus pelodes is a species of marine spoon worm .
Hypochaeris glabra is a species of flowering plant in the dandelion tribe within the daisy family known by the common name smooth cat 's ear .
Sinotaia quadrata is a species of a freshwater snail with a gill and an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Viviparidae .
Arsinoitherium is an extinct genus of paenungulate mammal belonging to the extinct order Embrithopoda .
Chaetostomella cylindrica is a species of fruit flies in the genus Chaetostomella of the family Tephritidae .
Garypus titanius is a species of pseudoscorpion of the family Garypidae .
Sabia conica , common name : the bonnet limpet , is a species of small limpet - like sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Hipponicidae , the hoof snails .
Acteonellidae is an extinct family of gastropods in the informal group Lower Heterobranchia ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Gerarda prevostiana , commonly known as Gerard 's water snake or the cat - eyed water snake , is a species of water snake endemic to Asia .
The insect family Nabidae contains the damsel bugs .
Neocrepidodera cyanenscens is a species of black coloured flea beetle from Chrysomelidae family that can be found in Austria , Czech Republic , France , Italy , Poland , Romania , Slovakia , Slovenia , Switzerland , and Ukraine .
Lear 's macaw was first described by French ornithologist Charles Lucien Bonaparte in 1856 , but in 1978 , the rarely seen bird was considered a distinct species when ornithologist Helmut Sick finally located the wild population .
Protolophotus is an extinct genus of crestfishes , family Lophotidae .
Carassius auratus argenteaphthalmus is a subspecies of ray - finned fish in the genus Carassius .
Bletiinae is a small - sized subtribe of orchids in the Arethuseae tribe of the subfamily Epidendroideae .
Xenocalamus sabiensis , or the Sabi quill - snouted snake , is a species of venomous rear - fanged snake in the family Atractaspididae .
Planomicrobium ( formerly Planococcus ) is a genus of Gram - positive staining bacteria .
Orycteropus abundulafus is an extinct species of aardvark .
Idiosepius biserialis is a species of bobtail squid native to the southwestern Indian Ocean off southern Africa .
Pseudognaphalium saxicola , common name Cliff cudweed or Rabbit - tobacco , is a rare plant species endemic to Wisconsin .
Pleuropogon oregonus is a species of grass known by the common name Oregon semaphoregrass .
Petroravenia friesii is a species in the family Brassicaceae native to Chile .
Adriacentrus is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish that lived from the Turonian .
Termitidae is a family of termites , containing the following subfamilies :
Kuhlhasseltia is a genus of orchids ( family Orchidaceae ) belonging to the subfamily Orchidoideae .
Plumbaginaceae is a family of flowering plants , with a cosmopolitan distribution .
Gunnellichthys is a genus of wormfishes native to the Indian Ocean to the central Pacific Ocean .
Insulivitrina mascaensis is a species of gastropod in the Vitrinidae family .
Elseya nadibajagu is a Pliocene species of extinct Australian snapping turtle , described from the Bluff Downs region of Queensland , Australia .
The Percopsiformes are a small order of ray - finned fishes , comprising the trout - perch and its allies .
Its only species is Aphandra natalia , sometimes called mastodon palm or fiber palm , and is used by indigenous peoples in the construction of brooms and other products .
Parachrysina is a genus of beetle in the Scarabaeidae family .
Carex angustata is a species of sedge known by the common name widefruit sedge .
Pholiota nubigena , commonly known as the gastroid pholiota or the bubble gum fungus , is a species of secotioid fungus in the family Strophariaceae .
Lutrogale is a genus of otters , with only one extant species -- the smooth - coated otter .
Malva moschata ( musk - mallow ) is a species of Malva native to Europe and southwestern Asia , from Spain north to the British Isles and Poland , and east to southern Russia and Turkey .
Isolepis prolifera is a species of flowering plant in the family Cyperaceae that grows in temperate regions of the Southern Hemisphere .
Euphorbia schizoloba ( syn . Euphorbia incisa ) is a species of euphorb known by the common name Mojave spurge .
The Himalayan goral ( Naemorhedus goral ) is a bovid species found across the Himalayas .
Caconemobius howarthi is a species of cricket known by the common name Howarth 's cave cricket .
Casearia engleri is a species of plant in the Salicaceae family .
Dinocephalosaurus is a genus of long necked , aquatic protorosaur that inhabited the Triassic seas .
Napeogenes is a genus of clearwing ( ithomiine ) butterflies , named by Bates in 1862 .
Binneya is a genus of air - breathing land slugs , shell - less terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the family Binneyidae .
Corumbataia tocantinensis is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil , where it is found in the Araguaia and Tocantins River basins .
Parietaria floridana , common name Florida pellitory , is a plant species native to the southeastern United States , the West Indies , and much of Latin America .
The Cuban oriole ( Icterus melanopsis ) is a species of bird in the family Icteridae .
Parablennius cyclops is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western Indian ocean , in the Red Sea .
Paronychia franciscana is a species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common names San Francisco nailwort , California Whitlow - wort , Franciscan paronychia , and Chilean nailwort .
Huitzilac virus ( HUIV ) is a single - stranded , enveloped , negative - sense RNA hantavirus species of the Bunyaviridae family .
Agave mitis is a plant species native to the Mexican states of Hidalgo , Tamaulipas and San Luis Potosí , referred to as Agave celsii in many publications .
Clubiona saxatilis is a sac spider species found in Europe .
Yakirra is a genus of Burmese and Australian plants in the grass family .
Suillellus atlanticus is a species of bolete fungus found in coastal sand dunes in Galicia .
Caseolus sphaerulus is a species of small land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk .
Leptotyphlops occidentalis , or the Western thread snake , is a species of snake in the Leptotyphlopidae family .
Masdevallia davisii ( Davis ' masdevallia ) is a species of the Masdevallia genus of orchids .
Parasikukia maculata is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to Thailand .
Conasprella lenhilli , common name the brown - flamed cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Cicatrisestoloides costaricensis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Cicatrisestoloides .
Garcinia kola ( bitter kola , a name sometimes also used for G. afzelii ) is a species of flowering plant in the Clusiaceae or Guttiferae family .
Nicotiana persica is a species of tobacco which is cultivated in Iran .
Homaloptera bilineata is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Homaloptera found in Myanmar and Thailand .
Petroscirtes ancylodon , the Arabian fangblenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in the western Indian ocean as well as Iskenderun Bay in the Mediterranean Sea .
Kallyntrosternidius bucarensis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Kallyntrosternidius .
Cortinarius mucosus , commonly known as the orange webcap or the slimy cortinarius , is a species of mushroom in the family Cortinariaceae .
The Himalayan field rat ( Rattus nitidus ) , sometimes known as the white - footed Indo - Chinese rat , is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Zabrus mateui is a species of ground beetle in the Epomidozabrus subgenus that is endemic to Spain .
Columellia is a group of plant species in the Columelliaceae described as a genus in 1794 .
Lomatium cookii is a rare species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common names Cook 's lomatium and agate desertparsley .
Aerides orthocentra is a species of epiphytic orchid endemic to the Yunnan region of China .
Parajulis poecilepterus is a species of wrasse native to the northwestern Pacific Ocean along the coast of Asia .
Anthocoris is a genus of Hemiptera .
Clarke 's vole ( Microtus clarkei ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Platypterocarpus is a genus of plant in family Celastraceae .
Borrelia coriaceae is a species of spirochete bacteria and member of the genus Borrelia .
Elseya is a genus of large side - necked turtles , commonly known as Australian snapping turtles , in the family Chelidae .
Lyncina vitellus , common name : the Calf Cowry or the Pacific Deer Cowry , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Philodendron melanochrysum is a species of flowering plant in the Araceae family , endemic to Colombia but widely cultivated elsewhere as an ornamental .
Sarcosaurus ( meaning `` flesh lizard '' ) is a genus of theropod dinosaur , either a coelophysoid or a basal ceratosaur , roughly 3.5 meters long .
Linguliformea is a subphylum of inarticulate brachiopods .
Eriogonum cinereum is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common names coastal buckwheat and ashyleaf buckwheat .
Sedum debile , commonly called orpine stonecrop or weakstem stonecrop , is a low growing carpet forming flowering plant species of the genus Sedum in the family Crassulaceae .
Rhynchospora californica is a species of sedge known by the common names California beaked - rush and California beaksedge .
Enallagma recurvatum , the pale barrens bluet , is a species of damselfly in the family Coenagrionidae .
Pennatulidae is a family of sea pens , a member of the subclass Octocorallia in the phylum Cnidaria .
Pharomachrus is a genus of birds in the Trogonidae family .
Mitrephora caudata is a species of flowering plant in the Annonaceae family .
Clupeiformes is the order of ray - finned fish that includes the herring family , Clupeidae , and the anchovy family , Engraulidae .
Plagiobothrys humistratus is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common names dwarf popcornflower or low popcornflower .
Grimmia is a genus of mosses ( Bryophyta ) , originally named by Jakob Friedrich Ehrhart in honour of Johann Friedrich Carl Grimm , a physician and botanist from Gotha , Germany .
Melnea is a gelechioid moth genus usually placed in the cosmet moth family ( Cosmopterigidae ) ; its exact relationships are not yet resolved however .
In the subfamily Acanthopinae there is one tribe , Acanthopini , which contains 7 genera and 37 species .
Monoblastia is a genus of lichens in the Monoblastiaceae family of fungi .
Nuphar japonica is an aquatic plant species in the genus Nuphar found in Japan and the Korean Peninsula .
Discordia evulsa is a species of snout moth in the genus Discordia .
Lyriocephalus scutatus is a species of lizard within the agamid family , the only species in the genus Lyriocephalus .
Catocala coniuncta is a circum - Mediterranean species of moth whose range extends across southern Europe , North Africa and extending to the Middle East .
Cosmopepla is an insect genus of stink bugs in the Pentatomidae family .
Plagiobothrys austiniae is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common name Austin 's popcornflower .
Rosa persica is an anomalous species of rose that at one time was placed in a separate genus Hulthemia .
Erigeron klamathensis is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Klamath fleabane .
Anisolabidinae , alternatively known as Carcinophorinae , Gonolabiinae , Placolabidinae , or Titanolabiinae , is a subfamily of earwigs that contains approximately twenty - five genera .
Gambierdiscus toxicus is a species of dinoflagellate that can cause ciguatera .
Geitonoplesium is a genus of a sole species Geitonoplesium cymosum , the scrambling lily , constituting part of a lily plant family Hemerocallidaceae .
Eurycheilichthys limulus is a species of armored catfish endemic to Brazil , where it is found in the upper Jacuí River basin .
Tambja sagamiana is a species of colourful sea slug , a dorid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Polyceridae .
Copidosoma is a genus of chalcid wasps , parasitoidal mainly of moths in the subfamily Plusiinae .
Martensia australis is a species of red algae .
Rosa multiflora , commonly known by its synonym Rosa polyantha and as multiflora rose , baby rose , Japanese rose , many - flowered rose , seven - sisters rose , Eijitsu rose , is a species of rose native to eastern Asia , in China , Japan and Korea .
Isoetes engelmannii , commonly known as Engelmann 's quillwort or Appalachian quillwort ( not to be confused with the newly described Isoetes appalachiana ) , is an aquatic pteridophyte and is the most widely distributed species of its genus in eastern North America .
The Drakensberg Copper or Drakensberg Daisy Copper ( Chrysoritis oreas ) is a species of butterfly in the Lycaenidae family .
Marstoniopsis insubrica is a species of minute freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Amnicolidae .
Neacomys dubosti , also known as Dubost 's neacomys or Dubost 's bristly mouse , is a species of South American rodent in the genus Neacomys of family Cricetidae .
Rhizoclosmatium is a genus of fungi classified in the family Chytriomycetaceae .
Athysanus is a monotypic genus whose only species is Athysanus pusillus , the common sandweed .
It was first named by David Elliott and David Dineley in 1985 , and is placed in the monotypic genus Alainaspis , closely related to Boothiaspis .
Conraua alleni is a species of frog in the Conrauidae family found in the Ivory Coast , Guinea , Liberia , and Sierra Leone .
Pleione limprichtii ( hardy Chinese orchid ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Orchidaceae , endemic to China ( central Sichuan ) , and also possibly grows in northern Burma .
Acanthostichus is a predatory and predominantly subterranean genus of ant in the subfamily Dorylinae .
Allium sinaiticum is a Middle Eastern species of wild onion found in sandy areas in Israel , Sinai , Palestine , Jordan and Saudi Arabia .
The tribe contains only one genus , Leiopodus .
Trichomycterus laucaensis is a species of pencil catfish endemic to Chile where it is found in the Lauca River basin .
New World orioles are a group of birds in the genus Icterus of the blackbird family .
Stephanostema is a genus of flowering plants in the family Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1904 .
Engystomops pustulatus ( common name : Guayaquil dwarf frog ) is a species of frog in the Leptodactylidae family .
Bankera is a genus of four species of tooth fungi in the family Bankeraceae .
Sepia confusa is a species of cuttlefish native to the southwestern Indian Ocean , specifically southeastern Africa from Port Elizabeth to southern Mozambique , Zanzibar and Pemba ( 5 ° to 30ºS ) , and Madagascar .
Aldabrinus is a genus of pseudoscorpion , which contains the following species :
Cecropis is a genus of large swallows found in Africa and tropical Asia .
The Eastern Aegean bleak ( Alburnus demiri ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Alburnus .
Zeltornis ( `` Zelten bird '' ) is an extinct genus of heron .
Chiton squamosus is a species of chiton , a marine polyplacophoran mollusk in the family Chitonidae , the typical chitons .
Pseudorhodopis inermis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudorhodopis .
Dinoponera gigantea is a species of ants belonging to the family Formicidae .
Cypraecassis rufa is a species of large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cassidae .
Paolaura maldivensis is a species of very small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Marginellidae .
Barreleyes , also known as spook fish ( a name also applied to several species of chimaera ) , are small deep - sea argentiniform fish comprising the family Opisthoproctidae found in tropical - to - temperate waters of the Atlantic , Pacific , and Indian Oceans .
Coryanthes gerlachiana is a species of orchid endemic to Bolivia .
Tanyemblemaria alleni , the Slender blenny , is a species of chaenopsid blenny found around Panama , in the eastern central Pacific ocean .
Neosomatidia bipustulata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Neosomatidia .
Haracca parnassiina is a species of tachinid flies in the genus Haracca of the family Tachinidae .
Ambrosia eriocentra is a North American species of ragweed known by the common names woolly bursage and woollyfruit burr ragweed .
Rusingaceros or Dicerorhinus leakeyi is an extinct genus of rhinocerotine rhinoceros known from the Miocene of Rusinga Island , Kenya .
Rissoa auriscalpium , common name the golden - capped risso , is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Rissoidae .
Hylomyscus endorobae is a species of rodent of the genus Hylomyscus that is found only in select portions of the wet East African montane forests of the Kenyan Rift mountains of southwestern Kenya and Tanzania , and only at elevations above 2,000 metres ( 6,600 ft ) .
Helichrysum petiolare , known as silver - bush everlastingflower , licorice - plant , liquorice plant , trailing dusty miller and kooigoed , is a species of flowering plant in the family Asteraceae , native to South Africa and introduced to Portugal and the United States of America .
Lindernia montana is a plant species in the Linderniaceae family .
Ladislavia taczanowskii , the Taczanowski 's gudgeon , is a species of cyprinid fish found in the Yalu and Amur drainages in Eastern Asia .
Labidochromis is a genus of cichlid fishes that are endemic to Lake Malawi in East Africa .
Eriogonum nervulosum is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name Snow Mountain buckwheat .
The Glacidorbidae is a taxonomic family of freshwater snails , gastropod mollusks in the clade Panpulmonata .
Matudina is a genus of flowering plants in the boneset tribe within sunflower family .
Ambrosia dumosa , the burro - weed or white bursage , a North American species of plants in the sunflower family .
Korinch 's rat ( Rattus korinchi ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Bedotia alveyi , the Makira rainbowfish , is a species of Madagascar rainbowfish from rivers and streams in the Makira region of Madagascar .
Chama sinuosa , common name the smooth - edged jewel box , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Chamidae , the jewel boxes .
Monstera standleyana , five holes plant is a species of flowering plant from Araceae family which can be found in Costa Rica , Honduras , Nicaragua , and Panama .
Chaetomorpha antennina is a species of green algae of the family Cladophoraceae .
Campanula pyramidalis ( chimney bellflower ) is a species of Campanula , native to southeastern Europe in Italy and the western Balkans .
Narthecium asiaticum is a species of plants traditionally placed in the Liliaceae , but now considered a member of the Nartheciaceae .
Tagetes tenuifolia , the signet marigold or golden marigold , is a species of the wild marigold in the daisy family ( Asteraceae ) .
Panthera crassidens is a possible species of leopard , that is now extinct .
Haplomitriopsida is a newly recognized class of liverworts comprising fifteen species in three genera .
Cephalanthus occidentalis is a species of flowering plant in the coffee family , Rubiaceae , that is native to eastern and southern North America .
Penicillium cairnsense is a fungus species of the genus of Penicillium which produces benzomalvins , citreoviridin , phoenicin , terrain , quinolactacin and decaturin . Penicillium cairnsense is named after Cairns a city in Australia where nearby this species was first isolated .
Callionymus martinae is a species of dragonet endemic to the Pacific waters around Taiwan where it occurs at depths of from 73 to 92 metres ( 240 to 302 ft ) .
Argopatagus vitreus is a species of sea urchin of the family Macropneustidae .
Zhou 's box turtle ( Cuora zhoui ) is a species of turtle in the family Geoemydidae ( formerly Bataguridae ) .
The Svalbard reindeer ( Rangifer tarandus platyrhynchus ) is a reindeer subspecies found on the Svalbard archipelago of Norway .
The Syntrophobacterales are an order of Proteobacteria , with two families .
Palaemon adspersus , commonly called Baltic prawn , is a species of shrimp that is frequent in the Baltic Sea , and is the subject of fisheries in Denmark .
Only a single species , Tympanonesiotes wetmorei , is known to date .
It contains only one species , Heracula discivitta , which is found in India ( Sikkim ) and Nepal .
Spinozorilispe fusca is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Spinozorilispe .
Minuartia pusilla is a species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common names annual sandwort and dwarf stitchwort .
Hadogenes gracilis is a species of scorpion in the family Hemiscorpiidae .
Ammobates dusmeti is a species of bee in the family Apidae .
Hunstein 's mannikin or mottled munia ( Lonchura hunsteini ) is a species of estrildid finch breeding in Papua New Guinea .
Favites abdita , the larger star coral , is a species of stony coral in the Merulinidae family .

Haplocarpha ( onefruit ) is a genus of African flowering plants in the daisy family .
Pinus luchuensis , commonly called Luchu pine or Okinawa pine , is a species of conifer in the Pinaceae family endemic to , and locally abundant in the Ryukyu Islands of Japan .
Buckleria brasilia is a species of moth in the genus Buckleria , known from Brazil .
Lupinus apertus , summit lupine , is a species of flowering plant from the order of Lamiales which is native to Nevada and California .
Cymatosaurus is an extinct genus of pistosauroid or nothosauriform sauropterygian .
Sarcoscypha dudleyi , commonly known as the crimson cup or the scarlet cup , is a species of fungus in the Sarcoscyphaceae family of the Pezizales order .
Rotala ramosior is a species of flowering plant in the loosestrife family known by the common name lowland rotala .
Draba malpighiacea is a plant species endemic to southwestern Colorado .
Crassisporium is a burn - inhabiting agaric fungal genus that colonizes forest fire and campfire sites on ground and charred woody debris in Europe , north Africa and western North America .
Vauquelinia californica , commonly known as Arizona rosewood , is an evergreen species of shrub or tree , in the rose family Rosaceae .
Odax is a genus of weed whitings native to the Pacific waters of New Zealand .
The genus Simias is distinct and remains valid , containing a single species , the pig - tailed langur ( Simias concolor ) .
Sesamum radiatum is a species of flowering plant in the Pedaliaceae .
Beloglottis costaricensis is a terrestrial species of orchid .
Agnorhiza ovata ( syn . Wyethia ovata ) is a species of flowering plant known by the common name southern mule 's ears .
Venturia pyrina is a species of fungus in the Venturiaceae family .
Graphistemma is a species of plants in the Apocynaceae first described as a genus in 1876 .
Scutellaria sarmentosa is a species of flowering plant in the Lamiaceae family .
Silene parryi is a species of plant in the Caryophyllaceae family known by the common name Parry 's silene .
Puccinia asparagi also attacks a number of nonedible species of asparagus , including A. brouseopetii , A. caspius , A. maritimus , A. medeoloides , asparagus fern ( A. plumosus ) , and A. verticillatus .
Cistus monspeliensis is a species of rockrose known by the common name Montpellier cistus .
Rhoicissus is an Afrotropical plant genus in the grape family and Vitoideae subfamily .
Tungtingichthys is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish that lived during the middle division of the Eocene epoch .
Fomitopsis palustris is a species of fungus in the family Fomitopsidaceae .
Kadua cordata ( formerly Hedyotis schlechtendahliana ) is a species of flowering plant in the coffee family known by the common name kopa .
Sebastes rastrelliger is a species of fish in the rockfish family found in tide pools and on rocky bottoms in Eastern Pacific It commonly known as a Grass Rockfish , Grass Rockcod and a Grassy .
Lahontan cutthroat trout ( Oncorhynchus clarkii henshawi ) is the largest subspecies of cutthroat trout , and the state fish of Nevada .

Syringa josikaea , the Hungarian lilac , is a species of lilac , native to central and eastern Europe , in the Carpathian Mountains in Hungary , Romania , and western Ukraine .
Pellonula is a small genus of fish in the herring family , Clupeidae .
Arthroleptis aureoli ( common name : Freetown long - fingered frog ) is a species of frog in the Arthroleptidae family .
Vallonia tenuilabris is a species of very small , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Valloniidae .
Carabus lefebvrei lefebvrei is a bluish - black - coloured subspecies of ground beetle in the Carabinae subfamily , that can be found in Italy and Sicily .
Chorizopes is a genus of araneid spiders , with more than twenty described species .
Isthmohyla rivularis is a rare species of frog in the Hylidae family .
Stenaster is an extinct genus of brittle star that lived from the Ordovician to the Silurian .
Megabalanus tintinnabulum is a species of large barnacle in the family Balanidae .
Bolosauridae is an extinct family of ankyramorph parareptiles known from the latest Carboniferous ( Gzhelian ) or earliest Permian ( Asselian ) to the early Guadalupian epoch ( latest Roadian stage ) of North America , China , Germany , Russia and France .
Cleistosphinctes is an extinct cephalopod genus from the ammonite order that lived during the Middle Jurassic .
The genus Hyla is a member of the family of tree frogs ( Hylidae ) .
Hoplomelas albolineelus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Hoplomelas .
Poropanchax is a genus of poeciliid fishes native to Africa .

Uropeltis phillipsi , commonly known as Phillips ' earth snake , is a species of nonvenomous snake in the family Uropeltidae .
Nebria saeviens is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Japan .
Gadimyxa arctica is a species of parasitic myxozoan .
Asterechinus elegans is a species of sea urchin of the family Trigonocidaridae .
Stanulus is a genus of combtooth blennies found in the Pacific and Indian Oceans .
Mandschurosaurus is a genus of hadrosaurs based on material from the Upper Cretaceous of Belye Kruchi , Manchuria .
Labidostomma is a genus of mites belonging to the family Labidostommatidae .
Jameson 's antpecker ( Parmoptila jamesoni ) is a songbird species found in central Africa .
Kosmoclymeniidae is a family in the ammonoid order Clymeniida .
Tropidophis hendersoni , commonly known as the Cuban khaki dwarf boa , is a species of dwarf boa endemic to the West Indies .
Pseudogynoxys cummingii is a species of the genus Pseudogynoxys and family Asteraceae .
Tefflus is a genus of large , black and flightless Afrotropical ground beetles in the tribe Panagaeini .
Apocynum , commonly known as Indian hemp , is a genus of the plant family of the Apocynaceae with seven species .
Chagunius is a genus of cyprinid fish containing three species which occur in South and Southeast Asia .
The Misise , Misizé , or Mississé ( Calpocalyx klainei ) is a species of legume in the Fabaceae family .
Orsonwelles malus is a species of spider endemic to Kauai in the Hawaiian Islands .
Moinidae is a crustacean family within the order Cladocera .
Dioclea grandiflora is a species of legume native to the Americas .
Carex pachystachya is a species of sedge known by the common name Chamisso sedge .
It contains only one species , Sparganocosma docsturnerorum , which is found in north - western Costa Rica .
Lampsilis fasciola , common name the Wavy - rayed Lampmussel , is a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae , the river mussels .
Pulveroboletus bembae is a species of fungus in the Boletaceae family that was first described in 2009 .
Shorea leprosula ( also called Light Red Meranti or Meranti ) is a species of plant in the Dipterocarpaceae family .
Euselenops luniceps is a species of sea slug , a pleurobranchomorph gastropod mollusc in the family Pleurobranchaeidae .
Adenophyllum is a small genus of plants in the marigold tribe within the sunflower family .
Heteroclinus nasutus , the Large - nose weedfish , is a species of clinid that is found in the waters of the Pacific Ocean coast of Australia where it prefers algae covered rocky outcrops along the coast down to a depth of about 10 metres ( 33 ft ) .
The Amazonian umbrellabird ( Cephalopterus ornatus ) is a species of bird in the family Cotingidae native to the Amazon basin with a separate population on the eastern slopes of the Andes .
Narthecium americanum is a species of flowering plant in the Nartheciaceae known by the common names yellow asphodel and bog asphodel .
Laminacauda dysphorica is a species of sheet weaver found in Bolivia and Peru .
Palaeotheriidae is an extinct family of herbivorous perissodactyl mammals related to tapirs and rhinoceros , and probably ancestral to horses .
Vallisneria ( named in honor of Antonio Vallisneri ) is a genus of freshwater aquatic plant , commonly called eelgrass , tape grass or vallis .
Rhacophorus arvalis is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family endemic to Taiwan .
The Green - yellow Catasetum ( Catasetum viridiflavum ) is a species of orchid .
Funariales is an order of mosses .
Emmelichthys nitidus is a species of rover native to the Indian and Pacific oceans at depths of between 86 to 500 metres ( 282 to 1,640 ft ) .
Terinos is a genus of Nymphalid butterflies .
Claytonia nevadensis is a species of wildflower in the purslane family known by the common names Sierra springbeauty and Sierra Nevada claytonia .
Silene regia is a species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common name royal catchfly .
Coreobagrus is a genus of bagrid catfishes found in Eastern Asia .
Lamyropsis is a genus of Asia and European flowering plants in the thistle family .
Sidalcea neomexicana is a species of flowering plant in the mallow family known by the common names salt spring checkerbloom , Rocky Mountain checker - mallow , and New Mexico checker .

Leiopyrga lineolaris , common name the lined kelp shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Odostomellini is a taxonomic tribe of minute sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs within the family Pyramidellidae the pyrams and their allies .
Loreleia is a genus of brightly colored agarics in the Hymenochaetales that have an omphalinoid morphology .
Cyathus helenae is a species of fungus in the genus Cyathus , family Nidulariaceae .
Carabus montivagus montivagus is a subspecies of beetle from Carabidae family , that can be found in Bulgaria , Greece , Hungary , Italy , Romania , Macedonia , Slovakia , Yugoslavia , and European part of Turkey .
Cystiscinae are a taxonomic subfamily of minute sea snails .
Fritillaria crassicaulis is an Asian species of herbaceous plant in the lily family , native to Sichuan and Yunnan Provinces in China .
Eremanthus Less is a genus of plants belonging to the sunflower family .
The Umbridae ( mudminnows ) are a family of Actinopterygii , ray - finned fish that inhabit freshwater environments in temperate regions across the Northern Hemisphere .
Cliona viridis , commonly called the green boring sponge , is a species of demosponge in the family Clionaidae .
The desman , a snouted and naked - tailed diving insectivore of the tribe Desmanini , belongs to one of two Eurasian species of the mole family , Talpidae .
Coelogyne miniata is a species of orchid .
Argentinosaurus ( meaning `` Argentine lizard '' ) is a genus of titanosaur sauropod dinosaur first discovered by Guillermo Heredia in Argentina .
Crataegus azarolus is a species of hawthorn known by the common names azarole , azerole , and Mediterranean medlar .
Aerides inflexa is a species of orchid in the genus Aerides that was first described in 1862 .
Parambassis siamensis is a species of freshwater fish in the Asiatic glassfish family Ambassidae of order Perciformes .
Lophobela sinuosa is a moth in the Xyloryctidae family , and the only species in the genus Lophobela .
